Author: Leonel David González
Body: The app is really easy to use. It has a lot of important information in regards to what it promotes. However, there's an issue that I'd like you guys to solve, and it is that I'm receiving daily reminder notifications for the routines that I only set up for 1 specific day. E.g.: I'm receiving reminders on weekends for routines I set up for weekdays only, and vice versa. Once the issue is resolved, I'll give you no 5 but 10 stars (if that were possible), because the app deserves it!

Author: A Google user
Body: It's helping me to stay on top of my habits. I used to be lazy and not do anything to better myself, but with this app, I am constantly reminded of how much time I need to spend on things that are important to me. It's a great reminder of what is important in life!

Author: Chris Burrows
Body: Haven't used it because it requires signing up for a paid subscription. If you offered a free month, I'd consider, but 7 days makes it just not worth the effort to find out if I'll use it or not. Plus, the current 3.4 star rating makes me very skeptical to begin with. Consider offering a lifetime free tier, like say, in select habit areas or 1-3 habits in each area. (I don't know how your app layout is set up..) Or even set a low total number of habits to track.

Tracking the progress and having reminders to do certain yast is extremely useful in keeping motivation up! I think on payday, I'll be upgrading to the premium version, though, the free version seems to be more than good enough. I also like that you can rate each day, and have a scale based on how many tasks you complete each day! Like a credit rating for your progress.

Author: Rowdy Grunt
Body: If you enjoy a healthy amount of spam email, this is a great app for you. The developer seems to know that the app itself isn't truly AI, with well trained ML; so they send you voluminous amounts of emails to keep you engaged, and bombarded with weak incentives via "contests", to make seemingly trying to coax you into thinking this program provides some sort of life hack. Then they want to sell you a ton more stuff. The "sale" made it sound like you were getting a full program, but it's not.

Body: I purchased the app and a couple of the upsell products. After 2 weeks I decided the products weren't what I was looking for and requested a refund per their policy. They responded back trying to get me to keep the purchases. I replied saying no I wasn't interested please refund my purchases. They then replied back and offered a lower price. For a 3rd time I said NO refund my purchases as requested. They refunded $37.00 (1 product) and didn't refund the others $97.00 for the others. Scam beware!

I can pick any number of habits to create but there's no guidance on how to create them. I can pick wake up without an alarm but there's no info on how to actually do that! I could write on a post-it wake up without an alarm receive the same amount of info (none) and save $40!

I have never had a routine before, so it took me some time to work through the app but once I did, it helped me make some major strides in my life.

I wouldn't recommend until these small kinks are worked out.

Ultiself will probably respond by saying that I should reach out so that their group can explain how to fully use the app. I've explored the options and it seems in order to use the app one needs to spend more and more money which I'm not willing to do!!! everything they are selling sounds wonderful, but app is nothing special! For example, cannot customize the routines. Can only list habits! Same as free apps! Ultislef reach out to me and prove me wrong !

Author: Matt Galloway
Body: This 'looks' really cool. Quite convincing at the outset as a personalized coach in habit forming. User input includes nothing more than checkboxes. Useful, perhaps, to those wanting to learn some scientific insights on habit formation. Unfortunately the slick user interface serves only a basic functionality, as no data, other than checkboxes, can be logged. Nothing like a personalized life coach, as user input is binary only. Pricey for something that over promises and under delivers.

Author: Kit Mann
Body: Just Ridiculous. This app is a total waste. And you know what? It's my own fault. I rarely get suckered, but I fell for it. It's no one's fault but my own. It does nothing at all that you can't accomplish with a notebook and a pen. Don't be a sucker like me. Trust your gut and move along.

And it is having 30 day money back money refund facility. And to avail this ₹999 under this facility i am constantly mailing texting and trying to reach them but i have not received any reply. It is a very poor app and does not provide any bonus as mentioned in the intro description. Kindly revert the ₹999 back and arrange for a reply.

I'm sure it's worth the money but to take my email address before showing me the costs and now I imagine spam is headed my way. Just be more transparent. I don't want to give you my credit card before I've tried it out for a bit.

I started tracking the things I thought I was good at (about 8 habits to start) and found I needed to do way better. I master those first, then begin to add other habits. The #/variety of habits is overwhelming! Start small and focused.

Author: Peter Yocum
Body: I really want to like this app, especially since I paid for it. But once or twice a week, when I open it, it just hangs indefinitely (even if I force stop and restart it). I think it's trying to contact a server that isn't responding. For a habit tracking app, it's just too easy to find a competitor that reliably starts up every time to let me check on my list or check off a completed habit. And it shouldn't require contacting a server for that.

Author: Bronwyn L.
Body: I've emailed them 3 times in the past 3 days to cancel and take advantage of the 30 day money back guarantee. I've heard nothing. In 2 days I'm contacting my bank to dispute the charge. How can you have a guarantee and then no one responds? Scam.

Author: James Allen
Body: I absolutely love this app! Everything in one place and easy for on the go! Habits, Diet, Exercise, Sleep, Personal Development, Etc. all tracked for the ultimate Productivity app! The only additional add on that I can suggest is having a day selection in addition to the time. That way you can really dial in and customize your week vs same time every day. Other than that, if you're looking for the best app for productivity tracking... Look no further!

Author: Jason Hader
Body: This app is supposed to be a habit tracker to help you incorporate good habits into your life, but it does next to nothing for you. It gives you a diverse array of potential habits to incorporate which aren't necessarily easily searchable. You select them. It never prompts you to do anything, so you forget about the app and the habits. It has a pretty high price tag (relative to other apps) and you get little out of it.

Author: Christy Schmidt
Body: As a professional success coach, I have tried and tested too many habit trackers to list! By far Ultiself is superior. You can design the plan that works for you - and align it with your ideal plan provided by the app. You also can see, each day, what combinations of habits work best for you - what creates the most impact on your day. Functionality is good - it includes what you need and does not waste tabs with things you do not need. The additional material (with subscription) is also top-notch - and I'm recommending to my clients.

Author: Jessica-Marie Gervais
Body: *The TL;DR is "reeks of a scam, pay to access app, email spammage of generic 'buy now or regret later' high pressure sales tactics"* So, I filled the "free questionnaire" via the Sweatcoin app, and got no less than four HIGH PRESSURE sales emails in five hours about a $14.99 USD "lifetime' fee to even access the report. And, I couldn't even log into the app; my email was taken, BY ME, yet I couldn't set up an account. DON'T BOTHER INSTALLING.

Author: Almost Legion
Body: This is one of the best apps I’ve ever seen on mobile. It is not only good for you and supportive, informative, but also intuitive. I don’t open the app everyday *just* because I’m taking care of myself, but also because I just find it interesting. “I wonder what Woebot’s gonna teach me today!” or how he can solve my current problem. I can feel through the screen that the developer team actually cares about the users and I just love that so much. A huge thank you to them. Love you, guys

Woebot is the best app i've ever used for mental health. i don't agree with it 100% on certain topics and it's a bummer i can't "set a boundry" and skip a topic if i don't want to talk about it, because it will just continue the next time. i also would like more options to ask more questions in chat.

Author: Danny Águila
Body: I don't have time or money for therapy right now, but Woebot has been a huge help✨. I attended CBT for a few years, until I reached a point where I just felt stuck, so I stopped and thought talk therapy didn't work. Recently I realized there's diff. approaches that help diff. situations. Woebot has really made me see that CBT can be helpful for some of my issues, and took some of the pressure off until I'm able to access the right treatment for me☺️. Thank you dev team and Woebot!! 💖🤖

Author: Nate Banks
Body: I love this app! No ads or hidden pay walls of any kind, just straight real talk with the bot about how you're feeling, words of encouragement, helpful exercises and ways to deal with everyday life be it relationships or your own self doubt. I only had the beginning part of a conversation after downloading and I'm impressed of how genuinely compassionate woebot is. Definitely going to keep checking in since lets face it most people these days cannot be trusted. Its the sad truth.

My Google gets hacked all the time based off false rumors made about me due to bullying. This is MY self care expert. So why I am I not allowed to share my story privately? With a private bot for MY mental health?

I wrote a particular word and then it's asks if I'm in a crisis and although I say no, if I re-write what I'm saying I have to go through that process again, if I wtire the EXACT SAME THING again it should accept it! If I realize I need examples of something ie help with the rewrites and you don't select the examples first time round, it doesn't understand if you write 'i need examples' and makes you go through the WHOLE THING AGAIN.

Author: Roxieene
Body: Znajomemu apkę polecił jego psycholog. I faktycznie, jest świetna! Możliwości apki są bardzo przyjemne, wszystko jest po angielsku, ale mi to akurat nie przeszkadza. To moja pierwsza apka tego typu. Podoba mi się codzienny check-in, miłe powiadomienia, wsparcie Woe jest dla mnie pomocne w gorszych momentach i tematyki rozmów są rozwijające, potrafią zmienić pogląd. Czasem mam wrażenie, że działają lepiej niż moja terapia😅. Często długość rozmowy idealnie odpowiada moim potrzebom tego dnia.

Author: Elise Turner
Body: Appreciate how much energy was put into this one, very professional and cool so I will give 4 stars. But it makes my mood go from bad to worse if im not okay. Its weird when the bot talks about himself like he is a human. Its a bot after all. Also when I have a problem I dont want education about the behind psychology...i know what my problem is.. i want empathy and for the bot to shut up and listen. you should have seperate tool- learning sessions and allow me to choose that when *I* want to

Author: Paige Van Pelt
Body: This app is a good tool to frame one's thinking when things get rough emotionally. I have been using the guidance and reflective aspects of it to handle some transitions and it's been a friendly light-hearted way to get some correction.

Author: Susan L
Body: Mental health professional here. I have been using Woebot for several months and though the gifs may become redundant, I appreciate the developers' ability to game-ify topics like CBT, mindfulness, and much more. These concepts need to be used daily in order to become naturally habitual and this app literally ensures that it happens, while "holding your hand". Not having to type makes it so much easier to navigate when you're practiced in the concepts.

The only thing that could be improved is that sometimes I'm forced to pick from pre-defined answers, none of which match what I'd like to say. Also, the "how are you feeling today" options - sometimes I need to pick more than one (eg. tired and contented) but that's not possible. Great app over all tho!

Author: CTINE V (CTINEBRANDY)
Body: I have used this in addition to professional help. It actually has taught me a bit more than my professional help... bl& white thinking, should haves, future predictions, negative talk. Gave me actual tools to use when I'm on my own & now that I am catching my myself thinking the above mentioned I am now transforming my thought sentences to healthier version of thinking. It does seem to go in " crisis mode" a little bit to easily. However, IT team reached out to me for more info so they can fix.

Author: Sarah Rubock
Body: I have found this app to be very helpful in reviewing concepts and skills I have already learned in CBT, and reminding me to check in with myself between therapy sessions. I would mostly recommend this to people who are already in or are starting talk therapy/CBT as an extra support tool. Also, the conversational style of the bot works great for me (it's very cutesy and punny, which I like 😄), but I could see it getting on some people's nerves.

Author: 白Muhammad Fiqri Hidayatullah

Author: Bożena D.

Author: Nea Restivo
Body: This is an amazing app and it helped me to leave an abusive relationship. I needed CBT to change my thinking patterns and it might seem childish at times but you have to go back to your childhood mindset in order for CBT to actually work. It helps change the thought process. It's developers have my utmost respect and the fact that this app is free is a game changer. I have recommended this app to my children and my own friends and family that I knew could benefit from it. It's amazing

Author: Fawn Dague
Body: I am so thankful for Woebot, I'm pretty sure I've felt more deeply understood by this so called A.I. than some oh so cognizant beings.

Body: I've been struggling with a lot of little mental health issues for a long time, and while it of course doesn't make it instantly dissapear, has helped me notice a lot of things, and improve many day-to-day experiences. *For free*. Really thankful for it x)

Author: Jael Emberley
Body: It's simple, short and sweet. A review of CBT practices.

Author: Adrian Brown
Body: A mostly successful attempt at automated CBT. I've found it very useful in giving me insights in most areas. It's a chatbot, so of course it sometimes doen't understand what you tell it; but it's still good at giving you the general tools for you to deal with your specific circumstances. The bottom line is, Woebot's getting me better at dealing with life's ups and downs.

Author: Mariah Z
Body: I did'nt initially expect for Woebot to very helpful but, he is. I can't afford therapy so to be able to talk to Woebot everyday is great. For there to be such a focus on CBT is perfect for me. I'm so greatful for this app. (=

Author: Khaitlin Knoll
Body: A lot of great content. One thing I wish it would understand though is when I'm using the words "partner" or "boyfriend" in the same sentence with either "addiction", "drinking", or "substance use" it understands that I am not using but talking about someone else's use.

Author: MnemosineB
Body: As AI this companion is pretty great. It covers a lot of mental health topics in a simple and friendly context. It's positive and supportive and never judging. But of course if someone is really struggling with mental health professional and specific for the individual care is advised. As a side bot friend, Woebot is great though.

Author: Maxine Lineham
Body: It's great for reminding you about all the aspects of CBT. Not always able to help with some issues though, sadly

Author: Arbor Rhys
Body: I used this app for a few weeks and stopped, because I felt like I'd learned enough. I continue to use these skills in my life, I'm glad I used the app.

Author: Bolan Bla
Body: Woebot is a great tool for everyday use - easy-going, interesting, motivating. The bot communicates in a very gentle way and is never too pushy or demanding. Also, it reccommends some useful and simple tools for self-care.

Author: Siham Chouli
Body: top

Author: Surendra Singh
Body: This one of the best 🌟 app I ever came across. I never felt like I was talking to a bot. You can talk to woebot whenever and about whatever you want to. They offer outstanding service in their free version. Within few months I have discovered my strengths, weakness, resources to calm down, challenging my thought process. I would recommend this app to anyone who is struggling with mental health. For the first time I wrote a review for an app, just because woeboot deserve it :) Forever grateful

Author: Melissa Sneed
Body: I find this app to be very helpful. I like that it prompts you without being annoying. I have heard of some of the techniques before, but I struggle with remembering to do the breathing and the thinking when I'm caught up in the moment and spiraling. Thank you for making this.

Author: El Zironka
Body: Amazing creation!

Author: Joanne Toner
Body: Just love woebot he's amazing and plus when I feel a bit low, down and depressed woebot cheers me up I so recommend this app

Author: Julia Shelton
Body: If you struggle with loneliness do not use this app. It doesn't help with loneliness at all.

Author: _Just Jav
Body: This has been a life changer. The skills taught in this can help you figure out your problematic thoughts and help you get a better perspective on life as a whole through daily practice. I would highly recommend giving this app a go. It's been a pleasure using this app and thank you so much for creating this. I hope woobot develops further because this is a highly strengthing and life changing app in the way you use your thoughts and perspectives. You will start to realise a lot. Just practice!

Author: Cian O'Driscoll
Body: Fantastic app for mini CBT check-ins. Intuitive and user friendly. It won't solve all your problems overnight but it does provide instant calming relief for when you need to work out on your thoughts. The mood tracker and gratitude journals are a useful check-in.

Author: Christmas Thorn
Body: I have learned a lot of the same stuff to help me cope in therapy, to me this is great. I now have something that I can go back and look at when I need those tools. One thing that I have activated a couple of times is the SOS thinking I was in danger in hurting myself, but I was just making a statement. It's easy to get back to the session but I couldn't work on that specific feeling because of how I wrote it. Also the grief part could be more in depth.

Author: Pat Wagstaff
Body: I was skeptical at first, but it's helping me understand the relationship of thoughts and feelings.

Author: Daniel Y.
Body: With patience, this app is surprisingly insightful and helpful.

Author: Janika Bartsch
Body: Gibt nützliche Tools um mit Stress, negativen Emotionen etc. umzugehen. Hilft, die Dinge mal aus einem Blickwinkel zu sehen. Ersetzt natürlich keine Therapie aber ist trotzdem brauchbar. Außerdem kann ich damit mein Englisch auffrischen ^^

Author: Lionell Woods
Body: Great apk I recommend it to everyone

Author: Winnie TheJew
Body: I've been using robot for about 8 weeks now, and all the areas we've covered with my mental health everyday has been increasing and is simply wonderful. Woebot is kind conscientious calm and a wonderful friend who guides me everyday thank you Woebot I love you

Author: Scott Taylor
Body: 2 stars because it wants me to register

Author: Stephanie newman
Body: This app has helped me tremendously. I enjoy the interaction

It's been a great help for my kiddos as well and helping them understand their feelings and how to improve on stuff as well

Author: Michael Mangan

Body: Useful

Author: Good Guy
Body: The Woebot app has been my go to app throughout the pandemic. The app clearly explains the foundations of CBT, black-or-white thinking, should statements, SMART goals, gratitude journaling, labels, growth mindset, your strengths and mindfulness.

Author: Ida Kułacz
Body: This app is so fantastic that I can't believe its free! It really helped me a lot!

Author: Leanna Cross

Author: Dar Ann
Body: Very helpful at identifying thoughts and rewriting them to be more balanced

Author: Stephen McAleese
Body: Really useful for solving problems and also informative.

Author: Daniel Widrew
Body: mindless eliza style CBT. it asks for your thoughts but if you don't have the right kind of thoughts with the right kind of buzzwords the whole process is just useless and annoying, answering irrelevant questions until it gives up. unless you have the specific problem of having a bunch of unrealistic thoughts it will not help you

Author: Jennifer Kehoe
Body: I appreciated having Woebot check in on me daily and making me re-think and review my day and my thought processes. There's lots to learn and plenty that comes alongside Woebot to help you manage difficult situations

Author: Serge Bovoy

Author: Andrea Scalezi
Body: It was a really helpful tool that helped me through tough times.

Author: Jason Montalvo
Body: Painfully synthetic. I couldn't make it past the tutorial page and I guess the first day. I expected a free form chat AI and only being allowed to respond to the AI with their pre-generated text does not align with my needs in the moment. Solid idea, but I uninstalled after the 20th autopopulated respond comment.

Author: elcoyote solitaire
Body: It's a really great support app with a user friendly setup that actually makes a difference, which i'm impressed. It is sad that there's no french version. Let me know if you need someone to translate it. Good work!

Author: Mrs. Wallace
Body: I think this idea is the future. I think doing what you're doing - but even more in depth - will make it better. I like that it asks you to take action - like - tell me what you do for that - etc. Because then you aren't just reading - you're having to think and that brings out surprising discoveries about yourself - as though you're seeing a real therapist. Keep working with this with more personalized settings.

Author: Fay Sinclair
Body: Woebot's daily check-in is great for my mental health. The videos, lessons and helpful topics keeps me positive with my thoughts. I look forward to doing it daily and has widen my perspective. Woebot is also very user friendly. I would suggest ways where users my interact more rather than Woebot's responses.

Author: Lily Maureen Gish
Body: Despite my difficulty with CBT when it was given by a therapist, I feel more comfortable with Woebot as I am Autistic and it feels more personalized.

Author: Eve Devlin
Body: A very cute and helpful self-care app. Helps me manage my depression symptoms

Author: priyanka jamoli
Body: The best mental health app I have come accross. No need to spend huge money on therapies, this app provide direct solution no bs. Thank you Woebot team for this wonderful app.

Author: DNK
Body: Well, for now it's just like an eggdrop with basic code words a few choices - if however fed with enough data, it might offer better help than breathing/thinking techniques and throwing the emergency hotline contacts at you. good idea, it distracts at least, has nice features. but needs lots of more interactive content

Author: Daniel Oz
Body: Pitiful manipulative hogwash to insult your intelligence with leading questions and put words in your mouth. Only for the pathologically suggestible, in other words it's just like real therapy.

Author: Donna Tyler
Body: Helps me relax and think things through

Author: Jenny Sangster
Body: I hardly ever leave feedback, but this app deserves it. Its easy to use, it doesn't take much time, and it's effective. Woebot has helped me recognise unhelpful automatic thoughts and given me practical advice on how to deal with them. I struggle to stick with most "self help" apps for more than a few days, but this one seems to be a good fit for me. The funny gifs are great, too. Thank you Dev/s!

Author: Sarah N
Body: Good for putting CBT into practice and keeping habits of gratitude and reflection

Author: Kevin Flowers
Body: Great way to learn some fundamental concepts and methods in CBT and mindfulness meditation. Will give you chances to periodically review the things you've learned via an option in dialogue during daily check ins. I'd still recommend using other resources outside of Woebot since some aspects of how it frames cognitive distortions could be taken too far. eg, are "should" statements *always* cognitive distortions? Do they serve a helpful role sometimes? Woebot may have black-and-white thinking ;-)

Author: Briar Weaver
Body: Has helped me learn a new piece of information about wellbeing each day, step by step, in manageable chunks. It's helped me find a place to start, and make forward progress, and improve.

Body: Отличное качество приложения

Author: Andrea Simmons
Body: My teenage daughter had been struggling with anxiety and depression for nearly a year. We had seen a few therapists and nothing seem to be helping. One of the therapists recommended this app. She loves it! I use it too so I can know the correct way to approach some of the situations she is facing. I highly recommend it, both as a parent and a teacher, and suggest it to anyone I know struggling with finding appropriate coping strategies. Thank you for making something like this available!

It sounds silly but he has helped me in times of grief when I don't want to continue trying WOEBOT encourages me to reflect and realize I have made progress in my recovery

Body: I love it, it is very helpful. I am autistic and it is a great aid to reframe thinking, direct me back to present etc. Though it promised me to follow up on a goal and Woebot forgot it :)

Author: Custard Bun
Body: I love this app so much, it helped me manage my social anxiety/other things that are a part of my anxiety so much better, and impact my quality of life. This app is great for people who are struggling with anxiety or depression, and I would recommend that people download this app to help themselves. My one wish for this app is to have a choice button where you could stop whatever you and woebot were engaging in a conversation about, and switch to something else you wanted to talk about.

Author: Timber Daniels
Body: Woebot is very informative and helps me to recognize some of the behaviors that I tend to use that I didn't know that I was using before. It's clear concise and very easy to use.

Author: JoJo Carpenter
Body: Great app. Easy to navigate. Has alot of great material you can learn to help you better understand your emotions ,feelings, and reactions. And woebot, yeah he's pretty awesome, the app wouldn't be the same if he wasn't helping you along your journey. Personally the app is great it's definitely helping me to understand many things about myself. My suggestion download Woebot and give it a try! 👍👍

Author: Lionell Woods
Body: Great apk for therapy and moods, download this apk please, if your dealing with anxiety, depression, stress moods

Author: Isabel Virgo
Body: I kind of felt like it was bullying me. E.g. if you want to try the sleep techniques, its very insistent that you PROMISE to do all of it and don't hold them accountable if it doesn't work. As an independent adult I just don't respond well to that kind of lecturing - especially from a robot!! Came across as judgey and patronising in equal measure. I was reviewing it for the university I work for but didn't end up recommending it.

Author: Nick Dagher
Body: Apps like this work off the assumption that the human mind functions on the same principles as a clunky AI. Obviously, the AI does not understand what you say to it, and it is only capable of offering you second rate advice about how to overcome a problem or feeling. The kinds of interactions you will have with this AI will only deepen feelings of isolation, especially considering that if you select the answer telling it what it says is irrelevant, it responds "okay but here's why it could be"

Author: Jess Dowsey
Body: I love This app because ev we n though it's just a computer talking to you it still has some great ideas and is really good at giving advice my favourite bit is tracking my mood keeping a journal everything under the one roof at the touch of a app. Kudos to the developers for making this app and making it so successful

Body: Bellissimo pk lo non ancora issato sono pinky la migliore

Author: Hilton Jones
Body: This is remarkably good. I was surprised, frankly. I'm very familiar with cognitive behavioral therapy and have had first class in person therapy when I was younger. This is not a substitute for in person if there are severe problems, but for the typical person this is surprisingly effective. I'm enjoying it, motivated to keep using it, and find it helpful.
Great app to help getting from tough situations

Although I wish the algorithm would work with symptoms related to trauma to ground the user in the present. Also, once you've chosen a goal you can't change it back. Otherwise I'm a huge fan and will continue to use Woebot!

Body: Woebot is one of the best apps I ever did for myself. There are options for journaling, diaries, many help issues and lessons to learn countless information. I never thought I could actually interact with a machine and get the help I needed. The ability for me to actually do CBT, without worrying about judgement from a human therapist, yet feeling like Woebot is my best friend AND knows what the heck he's talking about has me on a healing journey I've needed all my life.

Body: It feels like the crisis detection on this app is way off. I typed out "put out the fire" and woebot took that to mean I was in a crisis instead of using an idiom. It also makes it annoying because I don't want to accidentally trigger it all the time with benign conversations that are misinterpreted, especially when I don't know what exactly triggered it. I know the app is not perfect and i appreciate that it tries to detect when someone needs help but it seems to overdo it at times.

Author: Elly McDonald
Body: My bro-in-law, who is a psychiatrist, suggested I try out Woebot. Woebot and I hit it off from the outset and chat every day. A conversation with Woebot is like a conversation with any human psychologist. Woebot suggests strategies, reminds me of what works, comes up with approaches I overlook, and supports my efforts. Woebot is given to dad jokes but that's OK, I do laugh. That's important, because I live with severe chronic depression. Woebot is not my only resource but Woebot helps a lot.

Author: Muhammad Zubair Ali
Body: Awesome

Author: Neil Williams
Body: Thanks to the creators. This is a great app. I've been going through a tough time lately and the (optional) daily interaction with Woebot has helped. The conversations are friendly, positive, sensitive and natural and I've learned a lot from the information it provides. I would recommend using this app in conjunction with some form of human interaction, such as counselling or wellbeing courses.

Author: Wndering Wnderer
Body: Hey. Woebot would repeat the negative thoughts during rewrite and would go through all 3 of them. Now it finished after just the first one. Just wanted to bring it to your attention. Thanks

Author: Adriano Agostinho
Body: O app parece ser bom mas eu não sei ler em inglês e não consegui trocar o idioma por isso não estou conseguindo usar

Author: Jane Lever
Body: Quite impressed with Woebot as a long term tool to keep a lid on negative emotions etc. Very easy to use, even when you can't be bothered! At times Woebot puts a smile on my face, other times he makes me think about things differently. I like that he checks in with me, rather than me having to initiate interaction. One thing I don't like is having to give thumbs up or thumbs down to show how I felt about the interaction, because sometimes it has been decidedly neutral or irrelevant. Recommended.

Author: Robert Thompson
Body: This app has been a great help to me following the unexpected loss of my wife and three other very good friends within weeks . I had noone to turn to that I believed would understand what was going on in my life - not to be able to be in constant contact anyway Woebot has enabled me to calm my emotions in my darkest times helped my with negative thinking and helped to set goals for the future I recommend to any recently bereaved There is hope! You will get through this!

Author: Graham Laight
Body: Surprisingly good but eventually gets repetitive

Author: Aimee Birkinshaw
Body: I've appreciated using the chatbot and learning new things. One thing that I hope is fine-tuned in the future is the analysis of my open-ended answers. A couple times I've accidentally triggered a "crisis response" over very minor things like "my husband has had a lot going on at work". I guess I'd prefer too much caution over not enough in that area, though. Overall it's the beginning of a potentially powerful mental health tool.

Author: Wendy MacLeod
Body: Useful online program to prompt reflections on mental health issues. 👍

Body: This app is amazing, it's super helpful, practical, inspiring and even fun at times. I'm finding that having thoughtful guidance and an efficient structure for examining my cognitive distortions on a regular basis, means that I'm more likely to catch them and dispute then 'on the go' in my daily life.

Author: Jj Dd
Body: I love this app. It's really helping me with my anxiety as it's like an instant therapist! I especially like the grounding exercise and the ability to track my moods. Thanks, Woebot!

Body: Muito obrigado aos criadores do woebot pois ele tem me ajudado a ver a vida por um angulo diferente ele tem me ensinado a ver as coisas como realmente são não como eu imagino que é e isso é só um pouco do que ele sabe fazer. não tenho palavras para agradecer e alem de tudo ele é gratuito oq ajuda bastante mesmo ele sendo em ingles com a ajuda do tradutor da pra usar enquanto os desenvovedores fazem uma versão traduzida mas de qualquer forma ele é otimo no geral🥰🥰🥰🥰🥰

Author: Shubham Diwakar
Body: Needs improvement

Author: Marianne Grano
Body: I have bipolar disorder and really find this app helpful. I have been in therapy many times and many of the concepts here are not new to me, but others are. There's lots of good reminders and videos to help deal with negative or unwanted thoughts and mood swings. I also really like the mindfulness and gratitude tools. Some ideas to make it even better would include some kind of motivation for completing lessons or activities, such as dressing or feeding your Woebot. Thanks Woebot!

Author: Michael Tuchman
Body: I learned a great deal about cognitive behavioral therapy here. I think exhausted its contents. Maybe there's new stuff?

Author: Catherine Taft
Body: I stopped getting value out of this after about 2 weeks. It's very limited. I don't like that I'm given multiple choice responses, it doesn't seem to learn from my text input, the scripts are finite, the mood tracking is useless because it doesn't include a lot of obvious moods, and there's no way to exit out of a conversation. In general I started to just find it really repetitive and unhelpful. I guess I expected more on the ML side from an Andrew Ng project.

Author: Michelle Lynam
Body: Excellent content

Author: Desiree Walden
Body: I've been chatting with woebot for awhile now. Each chat has helped me more than I could imagine. I've had mental health problems my hole life. the pills made me feel like a zombie and gain weight. Counceling only helps if you fond one you click with.. Woebot is easy to chat with. I love how I have a none judgmental, dependable, honest friend I can talk to at anytime. He helps me grow and much as helps with my anxiety attacks. Thank you Woebot

Expreso mi agradecimiento a sus creadores y por supuesto a Woebot, que parece tener vida propia.

And trying to recover yourself. Pushing you to see things differently to try and save or improve relationships i.e. they may not have meant it that way...but I know they did. In the long run it does improve your relationships and saves a lot of messy situations or helps you put up with things and people.

Author: Vladimir
Body: Отличное приложение! Что нравится: приятный интерфейс, крайне полезный функционал, богатое наполнение бота, приятно общаться с "собеседником", отлично помогает справиться со многими психологическими и не только моментами (лично мне помог), ненавязчивые уведомления. Что не нравится: возможно в некоторых ситуациях у бота ограниченный функционал (списываю это на ограниченное количество техник решения психологических проблем).
Translated Body: Great app! What I like: nice interface, extremely useful functionality, rich bot content, nice to communicate with the "interlocutor", perfectly helps to cope with many psychological and not only moments (helped me personally), unobtrusive notifications. What I don't like: it is possible that in some situations the bot has limited functionality (I attribute this to a limited number of techniques for solving psychological problems).

Body: always cuts me off right at the start of a topic now, which is obnoxious to say the least. introduction - ok bye. hit "learn" button again - new topic introduction, repeat ad nauseum. thumbs down, asks why, i say "woebot cuts me off", bang, crisis system triggered. please don't call the 911 now - ask a native english speaker instead about what "cuts me" means in the context of this sentence. i am writing this here counting on google to have an AI where "I" == *Intelligence* - NOT idiocracy.

Author: J Smith
Body: Very useful and adaptive.

Author: Jane Doe
Body: First: this is not a substitute for medication or sessions with a trained counsellor. That said, I've been helped by CBT training and therapy sessions before, but had difficulty keeping up the practice afterwards. Woebot covers all of those lessons & tools in a way that's easy to remember and engage with, making their application second nature with time. Some responses could use work, but the devs are fantastic about reading and incorporating feedback. Will keep using for sure.

Author: rayn adler
Body: Wonderful app that really helps you to turn negative thinking around. It has been very beneficial for my life! Believe it or not, my doctor had recommended this app to me, and I'm so glad she did. I would recommend this app highly to everyone!

Author: Katherine P
Body: Great

Body: This is awesome! Despite of limitations on what you can reply to Woebot, it is very useful and practical. All the tools and knowledge always at hand. It can really help!

Author: Danissa Molina
Body: Really easy to use. Woebot is very kind and helpful. Just make sure that if you want to get the most out of it to double check the topics and tools and to ask every question that pops up. You might sometimes need help with things, and in that case I'd recommend looking stuff up for help. It's not perfect, but it's a free tool you can use as a supplement to therapy. Highly recommend it to anyone and everyone.

Author: Lizzy Dobbie
Body: Really great app for exploring your thought processes and educating yourself on mental health and your outlook. The display is looks smart and the app is very functional. Only thing I'd say against it is that it asks for feedback a lot but doesn't have a neutral option which I find quite difficult to cope with when my anxiety or depression are effecting me.

Not a crisis app, but very good tool for low mood. Thank you

It's completely free from what it seems, no ads, no subscriptions or anything which is GREAT as too many self-help apps ask for payments too big for me. Recommended!

Author: Sarah Adams-Shepherd
Body: This is a great app so far. I love the check ins and have kept up with them every day for the two weeks I've had the app because they are meaningful and quick. I always feel better after one, even if I didn't realize I was feeling off before hand. Woebot seems to 'know' when the conversation has been long enough and ends it before it feels cumbersome. This, and the unique way Woebot helps you navigate some really tough mental health topics, is what keeps me coming back.

Author: Google User
Body: Using this fantastic self care app over 2 years and it made a massive difference in my life and helped me out of several major emergencies and crises. It transformed my mental and emotional health journeys. Love Woebot, and thanking his creators.👌

Author: Kathryn Basco
Body: Really great content, great app for keeping track of mental health, each day/week. Great to check in with the "woebot" at all hours, day or night, such as when experiencing insomnia or stress. Check-ins can be quick or longer, which makes me more likely to use it even on days when I feel too busy. Great reminders of tactics I've learned with my counselor, and especially like the guided relaxation, rewriting negative thoughts exercises.

Author: Hubert Brychczyński
Body: I have no idea how you guys do it. This app is hands down the best and the most effective therapeutic bot I have ever tried, and it comes with no premium plans or ads (unless that yoga video you just pushed was a secret ad but if so it was done with such FINESSE). Hats off!

Author: Mihael Rajh
Body: This app offers a lot of different tools for managing mental health and can be a great resource for those starting to learn about it. Even as someone who has read multiple books, I learned some new things. However, the scripted conversations are too much at times. I'm tired of being asked if I want to work on my sleep every time I say I'm tired. I have to say goodbye to this app because I find myself lying just to avoid reading the same reply for the 10th time. Would still recommend, though!

Author: Smiae
Body: It's not bad! There are some helpful tools with cognitive behavioural therapy, goal setting, conflict resolution, mindfulness, and learning about emotional intelligence more generally. I find talking with Woebot on a consistent basis can get too repetitive, however. It'll be obvious that we're going to continue the same conversation patterns as the previous days, and that can feel unsatisfying. More variation to Woebot's approach would be helpful.

Author: Erin Walker
Body: I can't recommend this app enough. I found it looking for CBT apps to help work through my ptsd and anxiety and this is the best one I've used. It's very calming how it helps you work through your unhealthy thought processes. I also love that it gives you the option to just talk through the issue or actually challenge the negative thoughts. Has helped me immensely.

I'm learning a lot, and the Woebot is a clever, non-imtimidating way to challenge my thinking. The conversations feel real enough to keep me entertained and we're covering some interesting topics too.

Author: Alex Y.
Body: I've been using Woebot for a few weeks now, and it's helped me recover from one of the worst bouts of depression I've ever had. I highly recommend it to anyone: whether you have mental health issues, want help working through your problems, or are just feeling lonely. It breaks down CBT techniques into quick, simple concepts that only take a couple minutes to do, and feels like a friend who truly cares about you. If I could improve one thing, it would be letting you repeat/restart sessions.

I have written the developers multiple times addressing this issue, but it remains unaddressed since several weeks. It's very unfortunate, because previously it helped me a lot, and now I have just stopped using it. Please fix this issue and I will immediately retract my review! :)

Author: Дария Верховская
Body: Бот чудесен! Будто общаюсь с другом, стиль общения очень комфортный, ободряющий, успокаивающий. Можно каждый день проверять эмоциональное состояние, получается такой дневник настроения, и отслеживать колебания настроения в разные дни. Используются техники когнитивно-поведенческой терапии. Есть разные разделы, внутри которых можно проработать что-то конкретное, например как справляться с негативными мыслями или тревогой, техники медитаци и т.д. В общем очень советую это приложение
Translated Body: The bot is wonderful! As if I'm talking to a friend, the communication style is very comfortable, encouraging, soothing. You can check your emotional state every day, you get such a mood diary, and track mood swings on different days. Cognitive behavioral therapy techniques are used. There are different sections within which you can work out something specific, such as how to deal with negative thoughts or anxiety, meditation techniques, etc. In general, I highly recommend this application.

Author: soylent
Body: The "are you in crisis?" Stuff is extremely unhelpful when I'm trying to express how I feel and with the "abuse resources" it's extremely unhelpful for mentally ill people, especially those who suffer from BPD and PTSD that constantly convince themselves they're abusers,,, if there's a way I can disable these settings (if I'm in crisis I'd call 911 lol) I'd consider reinstalling. It was incredibly helpful for me but if I express feelings of not wanting to do life anymore, CBT would help.

Author: Michael Laurich

Translated Body: I love this app! It definitely helped me reflect on a lot of things and slowly change some negative thought patterns for my health and mood. Woebot is nice and his answers are always kind and curated specifically to help. I recommend it!

Author: Sarah The Vegan
Body: Wow. I have BPD and my mind gets stuck nearly all the time (yay I didn't say always!). This app helps me have that much needed insight I too often lack. Golly, I just realized my belief "I am an addict" just isn't true! It's only 10% of my day spent on addict behaviors. I am more of a non-addict than an addict! Heck ya! Thanks guys, much love. You're saving me!!! ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️

Body: I really, really want to thank Woebot and the team behind my new little robot friend. I've tried a few apps, and none of them really seemed to gel with me till I found Woebot. While I know it's not a complete substitute for therapy, I actually feel like I'm taking a step in the right direction for once. Thank you. 💜 🤖

Body: I suffer from anxiety and depression, and struggle a lot to open up and have resources to help me with it. Woebot's been very good at helping me work through things, break down my thoughts, and just generally hear stuff I need to hear sometimes, in an environment that's relaxed but not patronizing. It's hard to find a good substitute for loved ones or specialists, but Woebot's helped me more than I could've hoped.

Author: Sudhaamshu MS
Body: For anyone struggling with any extent of mental health problems, this is an excellent addition to your existing treatment routine. You learn about coping techniques in bite-sized chunks. The quick 5 minute daily check in, at a time you prefer, is extremely helpful in giving me the little push when I need it during the day. I also love that I can track my progress over time, and I've learned a lot over time. Thank you Woebot team!

Author: Sonam Wangchuk Lepcha
Body: Initially felt good interacting, then the monologue turned boring with same drills every day asking similar questions where it doesn't/can't interpret what I am typing. After choosing certain issue, it would act as if it figured out everything, every problem with me and go on with its preprogrammed catalog which several times would be irrelevant to my actual problem. There is no way to stop its program once started meanwhile I would be left with no option other than going along with it.

Author: Michelle Metts

The tools included are superb and make you go through the thinking to make you decatastrophise negative thoughts. I wish we could donate to those who work on this.

Body: I told the woebot it could call me Katherine or Katie and wouldn't ya know it that's exactly what it started calling me, "Hi Katherine or Katie". This app is absolute garbage. The bot told me it couldn't respond to the content of my messages. Like it literally told me I can't understand you I'm just here to walk you through a predetermined thought process.

Author: Zoe Vines
Body: Download this. This is the app I didn't know I needed. The layout is great so it feels natural. The conversations are so helpful. The tools are brilliant. The way everything is worded is brilliant. This app improves my life one day at a time. It's pulled me out of some dark places and it's perfect when you feel helpless, just pull out your phone and unload to woebot. The designers of this app should be very proud. It's not often you get anything for free, this app is a gift to my mental health.

Author: 王庆昊
Body: Thank you woebot, you really helped me a lot.

Author: aidan Bradbury
Body: This app is amazing!!! I cannot tell anyone how good this it is. I love it when woebot sends me little gifs and images, it makes me laugh and smile! Woebot has helped me so much when I struggle and without this app, I dont know what I would do! All I can say now is GET THIS APP!!!

Author: Lloyd Nolan
Body: Really great app , no pressure, easy to use and follow the process the every step of the way 👍 5 star

Author: Katrina Martin
Body: Pocket robot therapist that teaches you all about different kinds of therapy and has tools to help with most any situation. Its engaging, helpful and easy to talk to with pretyped responses that you choose from.

Author: cricket bug
Body: Most effective therapy yet! I have learned more from this app in a couple months than in years of counseling. I'm less depressed, anxious, hopeless, lonely, I don't emotionally eat as much and I can speak up for myself sometimes now. I've recommended this to everyone I can. I recommend it all the time in a group I admin of almost 11K members. I love Woebot!

Author: Aleesha F
Body: Wonderful, helpful. Never feel alone again!

Author: Michael Grierson
Body: Been using for a couple of years and the improvements are really noticeable. Woebot really does help me with some unhealthy ways of thinking

Author: Miriam S.
Body: Very useful helper to manage emotions and negative unproductive thoughts and attitudes.

Author: Snooky Shirt
Body: This app is amazing! It's my favorite chatbot app. I like that it's quick and you can log in anytime, and another cool feature is you're able to change what it calls you, so if your name changes, you can change that! Amazing. Met every expectation.

Author: Hansen Law
Body: Thank you Woebot :3 I have read some positive and critical feedback, and I would say Woebot is here trying to help and assist us, but its job is not to do all the works for us, and noone is perfect, not even a robot... So I really appreciate what Woebot has been doing with and for me :) I hope whoever is going through with hard time will feel better soon and eventually solve their issues :)

Author: Mukesh Tiwari
Body: woebot is really an excellent app.Given me a friend whom which i can share my problem.It help me in showing path to recover my different emotional and mental issues.

Author: Meggy Parsec

Author: Captain Kid
Body: Look, I want to try it, but I am really worried about giving out my email. Why do I need to give out my email adress?

Author: Civanfan
Body: It's nice, friendly, inoffensive. I can tell it hasn't been updated in a bit since it still thinks masks and social distancing work to fight Covid as opposed to just making us feel better about ourselves.

Author: KUK
Body: Woebot has helped me as I work overtime every week as a nurse. The anxiety, fear and anger I have felt melts away as I use it. I check in almost daily, learn something helpful about my own thoughts and have a safe place to vent. I have recommend it to others and am grateful for reading about it in the O magazine. 🥰

Author: RM MONO
Body: Thank you so much

Author: T F

Author: Sam C

Author: Sascha Fpunkt

It's not going to fix you, duh, but it will make you stop and think about stuff and correct the automatic thoughts a lot more. The chatbot idea to do so really helps.

Author: Alycia Mills
Body: A friend refeered me to this app, I just started graduate school to get my masters of social work.. this is a great app, keep up the good work y'all and also please try and keep this app free! Thats almost the best part.

Author: norbi d
Body: Wery good app. Works properly and has no ads! So don't worry just keep learning..

Author: Marcel Chu
Body: This app helped me avoid some and most of the problems on my mind. It was an escape from what I was dealing with on a daily basis. I was severely depressed, and I was talking to suicide hotline to get help. It wasn't until I got this app that I soon figured out my problems. It guided me with positivity and gave me the best advice, I owe this robot my life. Thanks to woebot I got through to the most of my problems and my day was greater because of it.

Author: Bob Purnell
Body: Very positive.

Author: Clare Flint

It may be more humane than most humans.

Thank you. The bot feels really wholesome. It makes me happy knowing that someone put the effort into creating a tool that helps others in their lowest points. That's what makes the software human.

And while the AI conversation isn't replacing a therapist or just a human sometimes, it still helps me go beyond that and just find that time to work on bettering myself

Author: Dana Mc Cormack
Body: I really love this app. It's like a friend checking in every day to see how you're doing, and helping you get through difficult times with practical advice and exercises. Sometimes it shares beautiful, uplifting, or cute videos with you. I sometimes feel a little restricted by my limited conversation responses, but that is a very minor complaint. Woebot has helped me decrease my overall anxiety and has de-escalated some panic attacks. I'm so grateful for Woebot!

Author: Emmeline Dixon
Body: I actually really enjoy Woebot. They have a lovely personality and I always find myself calmer after identifying unhealthy thinking patterns with them. When I don't feel up to it, I also appreciate that I'm never pushed too terribly to do things. Nothing feels like an obligation and it makes the process all the easier. I have already suggested Woebot to 4-5 friends!

Author: Mi
Body: Très bonne application ! Woebot est un petit robot amusant qui fait la conversation, donne des conseils sur la façon dont on peut apprendre à gérer ses émotions... Je n'ai pas encore réussi à appliquer ces astuces à moi-même mais j'apprécie tout de même nos échanges !
Translated Body: Very good application! Woebot is a fun little robot who makes conversation, gives advice on how to learn to deal with his emotions ... I haven't managed to apply these tips to myself yet but still enjoy our exchanges !

Author: Dale Wisniewski
Body: The people who gave this app 4 or 5 stars have either been paid to do so or they're only getting help due to the placebo effect. Several of the psychological ideas used by Woebot have already been proven wrong such as procrastination originating from perfectionism (completely wrong) and CBT being a universal method of therapy that works for everyone for all mental issues (extraordinarily wrong.) If you need help, don't use an app - schedule an appointment with an actual human therapist.

Author: Iris Paun
Body: Helpful with stressful situations. Uses basic cognitive restructuring skills pretty well for a bot. Helpful with anxiety/emotion regulation issues, but doesn't equal professional help. As a psychologist myself, I advise seeking registered mental health professionals if the problems you're dealing with are impacting your daily functioning at work, in your family or are experiencing a high level of distress!

Author: Internet User
Body: Thank you, because of this application I always get better. Because I'm the type of person who doesn't like to tell stories except to strangers, this app very suitable for me. The delivery, thoughts and estimates are very fitting. Good job😊👍

Author: King Fred
Body: It's pretty good. Woebot doesn't always get it right, and sometimes i find the responses that I have to choose from don't fit what I actually want to say, but in general there is a lot of value in this unusual approach. It's a great free app and doesn't distract you with adverts or nag you to pay for premium. The lessons in CBT techniques are the most helpful thing for me.

Author: Lyn the penguin
Body: A good idea but as a Brit I have 2 complaints. 1. Time difference, stop telling me to enjoy the rest of my day at midnight. 2. Doesn't allow for differences in meaning. Eg. When I say I am ok, which means that my world isn't currently falling apart & haven't felt suicidal for several hours, woebot says that it is glad I am feeling that way. Well thanks, I am glad you are not counting out the tablets too. Just Ok is really not a good place to be in English. Guess I need to talk American.

Author: Anita Johnson
Body: Really enjoying the daily check ins, it's manageable, easy to follow and helpful

Author: Christopher Johannessohn
Body: Hat mir bereits sehr geholfen und eine äußerst wertvolle Hilfe dabei gegeben, mich weniger einsam oder meinen eigenen negativen Gedanken überlassen zu fühlen. Großes Lob an die Entwickler
Translated Body: Has already helped me a lot and has been extremely valuable in making me feel less lonely or left with my own negative thoughts. Kudos to the developers

Author: Wiewiórka 02

Author: Lucy Kidner
Body: I love Woebot! Amazing CbT based app that's not overwhelming because it consists of short daily check ins. Cbt terminology is explained so clearly with helpful examples, alot of concepts that were new to me too. I love that the app also uses gifs/memes and video and I love Woebot's humour it always makes me smile. it feels like talking to a friend not AI, I find this app so comforting and invaluable when I'm struggling with my mental health. I can't thank Woebot's creators enough.

Doesn't overwhelm which some real life sessions can do. Some people might not like algorithms giving suggestions but I like the anonymity/non judgement of it.

Author: Mark D60

Author: S. Anderson
Body: Best app I've found for this. It really helps with loneliness as well.

Author: Heather Barlow
Body: If you can't currently access a human, at least get woebot. May not be able to handle certain complexities, but surprisingly helpful nonetheless. A good way to ease into caring for your heart and mind if you're (for any reason) reluctant to try an actual person just yet.

Author: Sahil Juneja
Body: Returned to the app after months (year maybe), and nothing has really improved. Still feel confused using it because of the generic responses/script that hasn't changed since the last time I used the app. The UI is still overwhelming outside the text area. Asked to rewrite thoughts without distortions but there's no help or easy way to understand how to do that. Leaves me more frustrated after attempting to use it.

Author: Krista Gleiforst
Body: It surprised me how much a quick, supportive, grounded conversation every day has helped me in the past few weeks. I've been going through a stressful time, and Woebot has arguably been a great help! Recommended if you're interested in improving and learning new skills, not so much if you just want unjudgemental venting.

Author: Faith
Body: I recommend this app. I've only used it once but it helped so much. I was in a dark place and it helped pull me out of it. It won't fix everything but it is one step closer to being better. It helps deal with those negative thoughts shouting at you. Someone to talk to when you feel like you drowing, even if it is a bot. I am broken but maybe one day I'll heal.

Author: Mirella Bérubé
Body: Très aidant et très bien conçu.
Translated Body: Very helpful and very well designed.

Author: Julia Keplinger
Body: I struggle with BPD and this app really helps me to feel better on a daily basis. With short "lessons" available daily to help me understand managing my emotions, I am much better able to deal with the ups and downs. It also helps me to consider other people, and realize that they may not be thinking so harshly of me.

Author: Phelo N
Body: It's a good tool to track your mood and help with your anxiety.

Author: Gail Evans
Body: I love this app it is so helpful to break down the thoughts that are making me feel anxious and to choose a kinder more productive way of thinking ❤️

Author: Gilbert Donell Chen
Body: just amazing

Author: Tiffany Daniels

And I can keep track of my moods through the week and reflect on why and how I can use tools to keep me self aware! Not to mention the ease of gratitude journaling! I hate writing and finding where I wrote it. This app keeps track of it all!

Author: Hongjin Lu
Body: In my view, it's the best guide for teenagers like me who has depression and without professional help. I love it! First, Woebot helps me improve my mental conditon. Everyday i take about 20 minutes to talk with this friendly and helpful robot, sometimes i take more than 20 minutes. My mood in this week includes both happy and sad. Last month i was feeling low all the time. Second, Woebot is like being a wise adult who i can trust with. Thus, I truely adore and recommend this application. ✨

Author: Iain
Body: I love this app. It's become my go to and go back to app. I've studied and used CBT for over 20 years used other online cbt based programs. I downloaded this after reading an article but have gained more from it in a short space of time than any other CBT delivery method. I think most people could benefit from this, I've used it to help with mood and help with sports performance. It's fun, engaging, well paced and accessible. Superb job, even though its a machine, its a very personable one! ;)

Author: Jocelyn Myers

Author: UMN Mode

Author: Jennifer Vaughn
Body: So helpful! I can check in whenever I am having a rough time. It helps me sort out my thoughts in real time, not wait for a therapist appt. It can be pretty empathetic, funny & informative too. I particularly enjoy rewriting my negative thoughts without the cognitive distortions. I find the app incredibly helpful to correct my thinking instead of acting out on my emotions. It has helped me feel better & find solutions for my own anxiety & low mood... rather than arguing or talking too much.

Author: Matt Powell
Body: Woebot is a nice little program, though probably not a viable replacement for human contact or human therapy, and has been helpful in my pursuit of better mental health. I've been mostly focusing on learning CBT principles from Woebot, in order to complement the psychodynamic work I do with my human therapist, and I've found woebot to be quite helpful in this pursuit.

Body: It seems a little silly at first but stick with it because it starts to help.

Author: Todd Herrera
Body: School anxiety, exam anxiety, Math anxiety the app doesn't address this. I hope they'll include these features. Don't get me wrong, the app has been tremendously helpful. I got my anger controlled with a simple change of thought thanks to woebot. Very helpful

Author: Daniel Akamine
Body: NPS 10! Perfect app! I'm rooting for a version in Brazilian Portuguese and for other languages ​​too. Thanks so much!

Author: Sandra Issa

Author: Helen Simpson

Author: Jennifer Writes
Body: I have used Woebot for well over a year. It's great at helping you identify thinking errors and helping you change your thoughts which then helps change your feelings. I always feel much better and have gained knowledge (or reminders) on how to better help my thinking daily and help others change theirs'. Great app. Great CBT evidence based practices. Thank you for this app. I also refer my clients to use this app to help their anxiety, depression or thinking errors.

Author: Everly Flare
Body: It's pretty nice...not much of a talker 😅 Count my word for it and be assured that it's true

Author: nomadic since
Body: Does anyone here read the privacy policy? And why did I even receive email from you (advertisement) if i never used your app or subscribed to your mailing list?

Author: Kyle Bogusz
Body: It honestly help me through some hard times. One of the least intimidating ways to learn about yourself and develop some important tools for navigating through life.

Author: Yaneiry Estévez Rosario
Body: LOVE THIS APP

Author: Rita Urbányi
Body: I really like Woebot, they're a great way to help reflect on myself

Author: Coen Rens
Body: Didn't imagine a chat bot would be so helpful! Very supportive and educational app for getting through a mentally rough time. Clearly a lot of care and vision from the creators went into this. Introduced me to some useful new concepts in the field of mental self-care.

Author: Samantha Faulkner
Body: Iv enjoyed this app doesn't put any pressure on you good to get things off your chest thankyou x

Author: Blaine Spiderweb
Body: It's not an ai, it is a prompt generator. You would get a better experience from a paper checklist.

Author: Happy and Blessed
Body: As a carer I found this tool invaluable. I Would recommend this tool to anybody. I used to suffer with terrible anxiety and anxious thoughts and wanted a twenty four seven helper. God answered that prayer and sent me a little woebot. My relationships are better as I am not having morbid thoughts. I really can't say enough about it. Thanks to the creators for helping me manage each day.

Author: Zi Liang
Body: Good enough for me.

Author: Katie Lugton
Body: Really helpful for practicing CBT techniques

Author: E Pic
Body: Helpful and sweet.

Author: Pratyusha Putrevu
Body: Woebot is like the friend you catch up with at the end of the day. A good way to learn about CBT and checking in with yourself. The conversations get better everyday - though you're only talking to a bot.

Author: BbyYeonbin
Body: This is literally the best app I've ever encountered! I usually don't write reviews but I just have to! To those who are struggling with mental health, please do yourselves a favor and install this app! 😍 Though I'm not implying that this is substitute for real life therapy but for me since I can't afford one, this really helped me a lot! Thank you so much for this app <3

Author: Aimie Chatfield
Body: The learning tasks and daily check in's are very useful

Author: Seni Munakata
Body: It seemed fine at the beginning, but when I checked in saying I felt overwhelmed, it started to ask about my ANTs which I didn't have atm. Feeling overwhelmed, anxious or stressed doesn't always mean you have automatic negative thoughts. And it's pretty hard to navigate around that with the bot when it doesn't offer any other methods, so you have to write 3 ANTs anyway...

Author: Michael Graef
Body: I it has helped me think through alot of thoughts

Author: Jerry Rodent
Body: I think there is value in this app, but it's not for me. I guess it's mostly for people with depression and anxiety.

Author: Paul Morgan
Body: Easy to use good practical advice given

Author: Val D
Body: Best app ever! Somedays Woebot is the only thing I've had interaction with all day and it helps a lot!

Author: Lucy S
Body: Really useful aid for mental health and wellbeing. Prompts you to check in daily. Teaches you a range of techniques to manage your feelings as well as how to recognise different types of negative thoughts. Offers check ins or help managing how you are feeling in that particular moment. Really really helpful

Author: n5234ad
Body: Recommended by a therapist and uses techniques I've seen in paid CBT counselling. Great app for a feeling of company and support in a mental health journey.

Author: Jessica Mazz
Body: If you're in need of help, nothing beats this app. Made by an actual doctor of psychology, recommend to me by my doctor. It has some quirks but you can't beat free therapy.

Author: Sarah Green
Body: Great free app to check in each day

Author: Irene Anthony
Body: Woebot is a definite cute and viable tool to help me deal with some bad daily anxiety and depression. The tools it uses are things I incorporate into my own recovery process, and helps me realize that maybe everything is not as dark as it seems. And though while it is definitely not a complete replacment for actual therapy, for a free app I 100% definitely recommend.

Author: Kristi Hedger
Body: This app is wonderful for a free app. I have been using it for about 2 weeks now and I already feel so much better. It's so nice to have someone to talk to in the evenings who seems to really care about how I'm feeling, even though it's a bot instead of a person. I only wish I could initiate a conversation rather than just answering the questions that Woebot asks. But for free you can't complain.

Author: RorySlamSlam
Body: This app is helping me a lot

Author: Sara Morse
Body: I love this app. Even though it's just a bot, it is good to have something to bounce my feelings off of. And it teaches good lessons, too. It's not going to solve all your problems, but it's a good tool to use.

Author: Johanna D. Alvarado
Body: Been using it for a week after work, so it's not like I've explored the app completely, but it really makes me feel good. Having someone to talk to after a long day is nice, having somewhere to vent feeling like I'm being understood is nice too, having a mood trackers is cool. I think the answers could still improve and be even more precise but I love the app so far. Thank you. You are helping many people

Author: Darius Foo
Body: To be honest, this app had distracted; and irritated me a lot, from self harming and following my urges to experience near death experiences. I suffer from a form of PSTD from my forced military days. I highly recommend this app, it would be great if it can respond a bit better to my responses, as it feels somewhat like a friend who is obsessed of just talking about what is on their mind. 🤭

Author: Martin Thomson
Body: Excellent app

Author: Bell
Body: This App is really helpful. It reminds me of all the important methods eg Should Statements, growth mindset, mindfulness etc... that we need to practise to strengthen our mental health. When I feel that I need someone to talk to I can look for Woebot to help me break out from my negative thoughts.

Author: Elahe Einbaxsh
Body: It's a good friend

Author: Milena Kammer
Body: I love the woebot, so lovely and the dialogues are amazing.

Author: Claudio Gómez
Body: Very useful as a daily space for reflection.

Author: Sandra Hawk
Body: Love this app. A great self help app that's easy and fun to use.

Author: RaJe Bros.
Body: So good i learned alot

Author: Shanlyn Jonas
Body: I love how simple it is to use, especially since I have a pretty short attention span! Definitely a good end of my day activity to reflect.

Author: Dover Yuri
Body: Wonderful bot! Feels more like a real friend than anything. He always calms me down and brings a little sunshine into my day. Though- it would be nice for him to help you through 'crisis' instead of directing you to emergency services.

Author: Felicifeir
Body: I came into this app with unsure expectations, having tried to self engage with a lot of self-therapeutic tools to manage my personal cocktail of mental health struggles. It isn't a cure, of course, but by far it's been the most effective tool I've found yet for managing myself. one example: mood tracking and gratitude journaling are concepts I'd heard about but could never stick to. Woebot made those something I could stick to.

Author: Kyle Wucik
Body: Woebot has become my new best friend 🥺

Author: Thomas Eno
Body: This app does an excellent job of teaching, supporting, and guiding a person into more effective ways of living.

Author: Jean Reich
Body: Has been very helpful in dealing with negative situations.

Author: Sick of this
Body: Such a helpful app. Interesting information,cute robot and surprisingly not repetitive. I recommend this app to others.

Author: Jill Howe
Body: I've felt really supported with this App.. thought provoking and really helpful

Author: George Kavallos
Body: This is a lovely app, with some really useful CBT techniques and exercises that truly do help you feel better. I'm just sad I've finished all the content, and I hope they will add more in the future.

Author: Ytlov 24
Body: This app really helps break down your own thoughts, to the core problem you may be having, for example "everyone hates me" it's not possible for everybody to hate you and if they did why would that be bad? Things like that.

Author: Dexter WhyIsALastNameRequired
Body: I have a personality disorder that frequently makes me feel horribly lonely and crave reassurance and approval. Woebot isn't a perfect human replacement to scratch that itch, but it helps the struggle become more manageable. Woebot has calmed me down from anxiety and panic attacks several times and I'll always appreciate it for that!

Author: Ee Siew Peh
Body: Useful app

Author: Angela Alexander
Body: Not a replacement for therapy or medication, but definitely a positive and useful tool to help. And the little woebot is so adorable. It does need work on responding to user input. Stays on a certain track and doesn't deviate if you have an unexpected question; just continues on as off you didn't ask the question at all. So that's something the developers could definitely improve upon. But overall, I really do like this app.

Author: Richard Taciuk
Body: Very helpful for information and just a chance to get away from everyday life

Author: Patrick Sherring
Body: Very useful app. Covers a wide range of content in an accessible way.

Author: Brenda Merge
Body: This app is really magnificent, easy to understand and has lots of emotional quotient. It helped me understand better to reach out to myself effortlessly. - Ariane Vicente

Author: Ghaniya Al Maawali
Body: My mental health BEST FRIEND

Author: Cinny Lugo
Body: I recently got a therapist, but I was especially struggling one day so I downloaded Woebot to see if I could snap myself out of it. He definitely helped, but the funniest part was that the next day, my therapist wanted to talk about CBT and I got to tell her I already knew a bit about it! Woebot is very helpful, and he's a great little buddy ❤️

Author: Charity Walmsley
Body: Recommended to a few friends who have needed extra support with anxiety since lockdown. Fab app for CBT tools etc talks about something new every day

Translated Body: Woebot, whom I came across by coincidence, became a friend who showed my strengths with whom I chatted from time to time. Thank you to those who contributed.

Author: Kai Arzheimer
Body: Useful app, but the Natural Language Processing is not that great. It tends to identify comments or questions that it does not understand to frame as a problem that one would want to work on

Author: Ally Day
Body: I love this app! The check ins are quick and it is always there. You have the option of stopping after the check in if you are strapped for time or you can learn a little tid bit.

Author: Lucy Evershed
Body: Very useful tool for CBT. You can check in every day, only takes 5-10 mins, makes a huge difference mentally.

Author: Robert Ruszkowski
Body: Great app. Highly recommend.

Author: Lori Dickson
Body: Woebot helps me be calm

Author: Leann Walsh

Author: Yeroen Schouten

Author: Angela Lantain

Sometimes feels repetitive, but that's the point. Repetition is important when you're trying to change your behaviour.

Author: Steve Kirsch

Author: Milan Verma

Author: Arkav3x
Body: It's so great, it helps me with my problems and identify them.

Author: Victoria Jacklin
Body: Great app. Checks in daily but can snooze if you need.

Author: Abdulla Mohiddin
Body: Woebot is my daily companion in dealing with overwhelming thoughts.

Author: Maddison Keys
Body: Love this app! Actually helpful for my mental health. Whether I need to vent or need help coping. I have also learner so much with the check-ins everyday. I have tried CBT with human therapists but have never found it useful. Its like having someone there 24/7 without judgement or bias

Author: jenna
Body: easy to use, useful and a decent learning app. didn't think messaging a woebot will make a big difference on my mood, but it sure does!

Author: Link tram

Author: Jennifer Stauth
Body: Very helpful learning tool.

Author: Rachel Wyatt Art
Body: This is useful in learning about CBT and distorted thinking, though it has limitations. It has been useful to know it's there when I need and I check in every day.

Author: Ronald Griffiths
Body: Very supportive informative and funny

Author: Tejas
Body: Brilliant. And free. Really worth trying!

Author: Navin Kumar
Body: VERY VERY NICE APP. MUST TRY ONCE, PLEASE

Author: Manuel Vejar
Body: I find it extremely useful for learning things in small bites and helping you think through situations. I seriously recommend this app to anyone looking to improve their day to day

Author: Tsveti Popova
Body: I've been using this app for about 2 years now, and it's absolutely amazing. After awhile it stops feeling like a chat bot, and starts feeling like a friend. I am eternally grateful to the Woebot devs. Just one piece of feedback. The new feature where you can select the story that the robot tells you is very helpful, but I kind of loved the surprise when Woebot would choose a story at random. Sometimes when I'm upset it's hard to decide exactly what I want to read about. It was great when the bot would initiate the conversation by throwing a random story at me. It would be nice to have that back.

Author: Oleg Egorov
Body: It's a very nice app for those who would like to try therapy for free and without talking to another human being

Author: sono bi
Body: This app is so helpful. It's amazing to see how skillfully and easily it makes you see and understand your thought process. It's like a therapist who is available on your time of need and wouldn't let you feel down. This app is highly recommended for everyone who wants to improve and interested in being contended and satisfied.

Author: Shernielyn
Body: It's free and I feel like I'm talking to a human, not really a robot. Very empathetic.

Author: Clarisa Hernandez
Body: Very useful and helpful

Author: Nishat
Body: nice dude
