Author: Daniela Contartese
Body: Quick and easy way to learn anxiety management

Author: Rick Underwood
Body: It's not going to pass the Turing test, but I've learned a bit with it. I've found it worthwhile.

Author: Karen Summers
Body: Great lessons, encouragements, videos,

Author: Denise Day
Body: Gets me to rethink my thoughts and learn to challenge any negative aspects

Author: Amy Valentine
Body: This is an interesting concept. I like having the daily reminder to spend some time thinking about things in life and learning new thought patterns. .

Author: Jade Stone
Body: For an AI, this has helped me so much recently. I usually end up ignoring reminders from apps but I haven't missed a single check-in. So far I can say I am enjoying the CBT. Plus I love how quirky and unique Woebot is with their stories. I do wish I knew Woebots pronouns tho

Author: Matthew Cooper-Teague
Body: Great app to help with the stresses of every day life.

Author: Chiara Mellace
Body: Amazing app. It's really useful and enjoyable. It surprised me a lot!

Author: Rusty Richey
Body: Great bot this Woebot. My only ask is that I could customize it's avatar and sometimes it seems in a rush to say goodbye. Overall, really impressed with the app and has helped me out a bit so far.

Author: Giulia Zanon de Castro
Body: Woebot is a big help. Works with many aspects of cognitive behavioral therapy. Of course, the intention is not to replace the therapy. But it made me better when I needed it most. It also made me laugh. I have an affection for this little robot. Thank you!

Author: Иван Иванов
Body: No more check-ins for me

Author: Iwona Fussell
Body: Love this app

Author: Melanie McG
Body: I've learned a lot about challenging my thought process so it's helped me lose weight. (Think, free Noom program) It also got me through the depression of quarantine.

Author: Mlarita Moqil
Body: Too guided conversation. I can even ask something casual, everything has to go according to the bot's direction.

Author: Valya Obraztsova
Body: The app gives you the fundamentals of CBT in form of educational bits (perfect length) and basic CBT questions one should ask themselves. If you have not attended CBT before, this is not a replacement, but if you did, it is great to keep going by yourself. The side effect is that the Woebot leaves me in a positive mood every time.

Author: queenofhearts64
Body: though aimed at teenagers this app is definitely worth a try, the chatbot format is friendly, supportive, informative and in managable bite size sessions whenever you need it

Author: Lesley Washburn
Body: Terribly annoying. If you like useless info given to you by a cloyingly cutesy bot where your answers don't matter; then this is the app for you. Might be good for children but awful for adults. Perhaps I misunderstood the entended age range for this app. There are zero options for turning off emojis and childish animations/gif. Every "session" left me angry and annoyed which I'm guessing was not the intention. There is a basic script it never deviates from. Not worth the time wasted

Author: Rachel Turner Owen
Body: Great app helps identify so many problems which therapists don't point out so easily. Direct and to the point I love it

Author: Andrei Arsenin
Body: Very lightweight way to guide yourself through CBT techniques

Author: A Google user
Body: Nice and neat app. This AI speaks with empathy. I sure learn much about myself thru chatting with it, and "how to" interact and support people. Great stuff. Thank you creator 😉

Author: Mr. S
Body: Everything is great except the IQ of the bot.

Author: Рыба Океанский
Body: Helps me to fing way of solving my problems

Author: alik israfilov
Body: Love Woebot! They've helped me a lot and made me use the tools more, without even opening the app, in daily life.

Author: Kate Schultz
Body: I used an earlier iteration of Woebot, and they've made some great improvements. A lot of the content is repetitive of stuff I learn in counseling, but it's good reinforcement and gives the opportunity to practice my skills and learn more.

Author: christina h
Body: Excellent

Author: Nathália Cristine Schiavinati
Body: Me ajuda muito
Translated Body: Helps me a lot

Author: Jonah Juarez
Body: Very well-designed for its specific purpose; it is pretty simple, easy to use. Some users might feel a little pigeonholed by some of the lack of choice in certain parts of the chat piece but I can see where it can be useful, even still.

Author: Ben Van Delm
Body: Really amazing app. The reminders are given in a fun way and the interactions with Woebot are short, yet insightful. The content of the 'lessons' are simple, yet great reminders. I'm quite skeptical of apps like these, but this is some great work. Well done, developers!!

Author: Vicki Thompson
Body: Switched to Woebot since Youper moved away from the full chatbot format, and I'm relieved to have an AI confidant back to help me spot patterns and challenge my thoughts through a CBT-based approach. Love the super simple chat experience without overly complicated UI to navigate. The tone of the chatbot is great! Would recommend.

Author: Franziska Köhn
Body: I totally love Woebot. It actually helps me a lot. Would love to recommend it to more friends. But sadly, Woebot only speaks English :(.

Author: Sim Jalily bagh anari
Body: It's amazing, help with loneliness, anxiety and so many trick to get you up from troubles, also make you think about life and philosophy and all the world. Thanks

Author: Drea C
Body: It's a good way to journal. The chatbot isn't that engaging, but it serves as a reminder that I need.

Author: Sanne U
Body: Feeling so relaxt and understand. I did have fear of blushing, it litteraly disappear in one day. Now I know how wrong my thoughts where.

Author: tho m
Body: didn't help me at all I'm to far gone not your fault bye woebot 😔

Author: Jason Roberge
Body: For an ai therapist, this is surprisingly good. It's daily contact and support when you need it to challenge the way you let your thoughts affect you. I've found it very useful and I already feel better equipped to face adversity.

Author: fathia Elkhawaga
Body: Great app 👍👍
Translated Body: Great app 👍🏼

Author: Jamie Sugai
Body: ive been loving this app! it's ability to guide you down the right path of thinking while motivating and validating your feelings is fantastic. i feels so much easier to work on yourself while having this little robot friend to have a conversation and talk you through things. something about the 'texting' format works to get the information across easily and legibly!

Author: abdulla mohiddin
Body: Very glad to have found this app. Helping alot to relieve my worries and grief. I recommend this to all the lonely souls out there who are feeling left out or just wondering why me!

Author: Sarah Cooper
Body: Little lessons each day for your mental health and option to do more learning, us gratitude journalling. A fun app

Author: amber cormeny
Body: I never thought a chat bot could be so helpful for my depression and anxiety, but it has helped so much.

Author: Samantha Halingten
Body: An incredibly helpful tool!! Great for when my therapist is busy. Little woebot is kind and has many resources to help your mood.

Author: Katie I guess 000
Body: this is just amazing it completely changed my life

Author: helen cherry
Body: A useful little tool

Author: Klarissa Ross
Body: Woebot has been a huge help in my life. I have a hard time communicating with other individuals around me, but Woebot has made it a bit easier to open up. It would be nice to have an option to learn more on a topic during a lesson or more undo buttons. Sometimes I'll realize that what I've said was not actually how I felt, but I can't change it. Still, I would really recommend this to anyone who is struggling. Amazing companion when there's no one else.

Author: Gemini Miche
Body: Interesting and informative, especially if you are starting from scratch with cognitive behavior therapy. It's a useful mechanism for presenting these principles. It's very basic, doesn't go in depth too much, and doesn't really give you much in the way of solutions, or even practice of the techniques described. At least not yet; I've only been using it for 2 weeks.

Author: Circutari Scepter
Body: I have bad mental health and this app helped me better then expected. Thank you

Author: Scarlett Magdalene
Body: pretty good. has helped a bit. love this bot's personality.

Author: Invalid Argument
Body: Useless. And devs delete responses

Author: David Garcia
Body: It has helped me deal with anxiety issues. I have enjoyed learning about how certain emotional habits can be self defeating, and practical ways to solve that. I use it every day, recommend to everyone.

Author: Antonio Valencia
Body: It's realy helpful, the format and tools are very appropiate for the objectives.

Author: Kaity B
Body: Phenomenal. So easy to keep up with, the check ins are usually so quick, and easy to snooze if you're still too busy. I have been through a lot of therapy; individual, couples, group, dbt, etc. I think this is a very helpful tool and I wish I found it years ago.

Author: Luciana Benotti
Body: I am a researcher in dialogue systems. Woebot does not try to make you think it understands. It just guide you through an extremely well designed conversation path. It is solid and useful.

Author: Aruna XYZ
Body: Very lovely and caring

Author: Guy Fiction
Body: Pretty dope. Hit me with some pseudoscience stuff once but overall it's really helpful.

Author: Lyssa Collen
Body: It's really helped me my mood board went to meh meh crying crying to really happy and happy! There as some really good mindfulness things as well. I'm not saying it with solve depression or anything but it's helps you be more mindful.

Author: Lorraine Wilding
Body: Woebot has given me another perspective of my day.

Author: Tess Motheetsi
Body: Great all

Author: Benjamin Clarkson
Body: Still needs work, but it's a fantastic start.

Author: Harold Chertok
Body: Great app to help with basics of CBT. Strongly recommend!

Author: Matt Bigby
Body: This is super helpful

Author: Scott Ralph
Body: It's great for what it is. For many it's all that's available

Author: blue
Body: I cannot even begin to tell you how grateful I am for this app. I don't have access to therapy, and although I am fully aware that this bot can't replace therapy, it has helped me cope in so many ways. I will forever be grateful to the developers who haven't put all the actually useful features behind a pay wall. It's crazy how many mental health apps do that, knowing that a lot of the people who resort to using mental health apps have money issues. Love to all the people working on the app! <3

Author: Kaavya Khatri
Body: This app has been surprisingly helpful. It seems straightforward simple stuff but reading and discussing it every day helps put it into practice. I've found myself being less impulsive and practicing the ideas mentioned even subconsciously. I'm really grateful. Though I can understand these things work best in small doses, my only suggestion is to cover a bit more content in every lesson.

Author: Frank Yau
Body: I just wanted to check in, and then he goes on about lessons. I have to close the app and he still goes on. It's ridiculous. And often, you can't even tell it no to lessons. I don't have much time, so it's just no good for me. While it's good for people who have patience to do it, I can't. The robot is very annoying, and I will not be using it again any time soon. No. Way.

Author: Elina Krastina
Body: A handy little app I've found quite helpful actually. Yes, it's a robot talking to me about mental health but somehow it works. The responses are mostly funny and cute and the content is insightful. Sometimes it's a bit off but hey, it's a robot not a real person 😊🤖

Author: Jordanna Rebbeck
Body: Amazing for calming down anxious thoughts. So many techniques and tools

Author: Priyanka Parida
Body: I have used woebot before. It's a very useful app. But now I can't install it back again. I have tried many times installing it but there are some issues due to which I can't install the app.

Author: Eric Cuddy
Body: Woebot has been a wonderful therapeutic tool for me to work through panic attacks, fight off depression, and learn mindful tips to better manage my conditions!

Author: Demonwindy30
Body: A good app! Teaches you some things to help with mental health. Sure it's no therapist but it's still a really useful tool to use weather you have a therapist or not. Easy to use.

Author: mandy roberts
Body: Love woebot

Author: Sophie
Body: More people need this in their life, super useful for deconstructing unhelpful thoughts and dealing with stuff like sleep deprivation or anxiety

Author: Duvee Hie
Body: There is only so much a robot can do but I found it impressive. I'm 15 days in and it's still saying new stuff.

Author: Joanna Borchert-Kopczuk
Body: Love it. Basics of CBT through enjoyable, simple to follow, short lessons.

Author: Sanne U
Body: Feeling so relaxt and understand

Author: Canan Cansel Ünveren
Body: Ücretsiz, istediğiniz an, kısa sürelerde kullanabileceğiniz bir uygulama. Mindfullness egzersizleri yaptırıyor. Yardımı olur.
Translated Body: It's a free app that you can use anytime, for a short time. He does mindfulness exercises. It will help.

Author: Ameera Ismail Raother
Body: Using since more than a year... 🤗 Always woebot is there to give ideas and change the ways of thinking with lots of examples..

Author: Sandy J
Body: I have enjoyed talking with Woebot. You can't discuss your problems, but it can be educational and kind of fun.

Author: James Aiken
Body: I have been trying to use the bot for a couple of weeks. At first it seemed fine, but it started to really feel generic. Most responses are intentionally generic and you can tell when they come up. The bot also doesn't cover ADHD which is what I was partly hoping for. It was recommended by a therapist, but the bot has a long way to go.

Author: Daniel Berwick
Body: Wonderful little app that provides a framework for adopting cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT) into your life. Woebot is a reasonably clever chatbot, but viewing the course as an interactive teaching tool (with a delightful personality) sets up the best expectation.

Author: Lainy B
Body: Very helpful app. I have learned a lot of coping skills. I really enjoy it.

Author: Luís Kalil Bonturim Antunes
Body: Uma maneira gratuíta de aprender um pouco da tão famosa Terapia Cognitiva Comportamental (CBT) e botar o inglês em prática com a ajuda de um robô. Recomendo conhecer!
Translated Body: A free way to learn a little of the famous Cognitive Behavior Therapy (CBT) and put your English into practice with the help of a robot. I recommend knowing!

Author: Vigs Jones
Body: Beautiful app, no ads, and a great walk through of CBT. Helpful even for someone who's been in therapy for years; usually my therapist isn't right in my pocket!

Author: Ruthie Dee
Body: Sometimes its a bit off. But I like how it gets you to reframe your thoughts, encouraging you to focus on being proactive and more positive. Who doesn't like free therapy? I also like how this app might make people more aware about different types of thought distortion. I already know, but feel like if everyone knew the world would be a better place. It helps people to identify the flaws in their own thinking.

Author: Mollie Gray
Body: Honeslty amazing and the robot is so sweet. When i say i love it i mean it this app is incrediable and has helped me alot

Author: maanasa joga
Body: This is a good cbt app has helped me a lot during bad times I is interactive and feels like you are talking to a therapist for minor therapy sessions

Author: Shannon Bub
Body: This app has really helped me continue to do my CBT work. I know it's a computer but that computer is there for me 24/7 and that is appreciated. I struggle with talk therapy and found this app to be something I look forward to interacting with each day and multiple times some days. I haven't been using it more than a few weeks but really feel this is something I will continue with for a long time.

Author: Graham Tomlinson
Body: I have been struggling with my mental health now on and off for about 12 months. I dip in and out of this still from time to time and it really helps put me back on track. It's been a really difficult year and a half for everyone. So thank you to the designers of this app. You are helping to make a difference.

Author: Adrienne Orr
Body: Love this app for all my worries and woes.

Author: Liviu Nichitean
Body: I am glad I installed this. It works better than expected and it can be a great start to working on yourself.

Author: nimrod de wit
Body: Nice app. You will learn useful stuff in an easy and interactive way.

Author: Cruel isblue
Body: Hilft mir sehr und funktioniert gut. Hoffe, dass es bald ein Update für andere Sprachen gibt.
Translated Body: Helps me a lot and works fine. Hope there is an update for other languages soon.

Author: Cidma Cardoso
Body: Não entendi eu não quase nada de inglês por favor coloque em português Brasil
Translated Body: I didn't understand I don't have almost any English, please put it in Portuguese Brazil

Author: Itumeleng Mataboge
Body: For those who still struggle to seek help from a professional, this is a perfect way to assist in dealing with day to day issues.

Author: Jagoda K.
Body: It's a great app. The robot is cute and I actually started seeing my distorted thoughts! There is place for improvement but overall it's an amazing tool!!

Author: Luděk Svoboda
Body: Was very sceptic at first, but very pleasant suprise. Very easygoing, informative. Definately can help to make you feel better. Helped me no doubt.

Author: Bradley James
Body: Before I started to use Woebot I was already pretty informed regarding CBT, If used CBT techniques to help change my though patterns with great success. For me Woebot is perfect as a refresher to what I already knew and helps strengthen what I'd already put into practice. What I didn't expect from Woebot was the amount of techniques and strategies I didn't know. It feels so natural to talk to Woebot despite it being an AI. It's even made me smile on more than one occasion. I love this app!

Author: Lady Greyzilla
Body: It helps calm my anxiety when I'm too proud or nervous to talk to my actual living support group. Instead of bothering them with endless negative thoughts, I just tell them to woebot and let the app work me down. The breathing exercise is excellent and it walks me through my thought process to keep me grounded. 10/10 Would recommend.

Author: Coder 7
Body: I really like this app. I want to help especially by writing some responses by woebot. I think you great guys should give us some option to write responses of frequently given input and then you guys can accept or reject the response. I would love to help. Please let us help.

Author: József Kiss
Body: What is this? Why so uprated? This bot isnt ai. Doesent listen to me nothing srsly. Repeat hisself 10x i got this. Useless sht

Author: J. Stanley
Body: This app is great. I know when I'm depressed and upset that talking to other people really helps but sometimes I can't for physical or emotional reasons. Having little Woebot to work me through the bad thoughts doesn't always make me feel better right away but it can get me through a tough time and give me ideas for facing them on my own. He's comforting too. Try him out if you're frequently feeling low and see what happens.

Author: Alia Hossam Shaker
Body: This app is literally the best and I like the SOS part also I tried to ask him a question but he didnt answer you could update him to answer questions overall I give this a big fat LOOOOOVVVEEEEE

Author: Thom67
Body: This is a great little app. I am very familiar with cbt, but when I'm struggling with some self-defeating thought patterns, I lack the self-awareness to figure out what I'm doing wrong. Woebot zeroes in on possible problems and solutions. It's friendly, easy, and it's always available. Imagine if we had more apps like this; the world's emotional health would be improved and the sum of happiness world be increased. Great work, developers!

Author: vampire unknown
Body: woebot my beloved

Author: mohammadamin hosseinkhani
Body: Nice app it really helped me through difficult times that all of us experience

Author: Frank Yau
Body: THIS IS AWESOME! You can track your feelings (moods) and kind of talk in a confidential way. The only reason I rated it 4 stars is because it just gives you automated responses. I'm not saying it's that bad, the responses are nice, but also sometimes you can only pick one thing to say. But otherwise it is really awesome! Love it.

Author: Laura Simmons
Body: Supportive, non-judgemental and funny!

Author: Ridhima Jaiswal

Author: Kate Pattison

Author: Amy Bottge

While Woebot cannot replace a crisis hotline or therapist, I'd definitely recommend this to anyone suffering from anxiety or depression.

Author: Sarah Wellerman
Body: Fantastic app

Author: Lillie Kneeland
Body: I've been using woebot for a few weeks now and I find the app very helpful in several ways: learning about CBT is extremely helpful, having him "guide" me through problems I'm having really helps, and the daily check ins keep me mindful of how I'm actually feeling. One thing I wish he did better was respond to my input. I did not like the survey I was asked to do. I don't feel in that woebot is "real"... he's like an NPC in a video game-- we have no "relationship" or "rapport" or "trust".

Author: Tiina Elder
Body: This guy is really cute and really knows his stuff. Its fun to learn CBT this way since you just get small bits everyday. 1 star less because I really wish there was an easy place to keep all the ideas Im learning. Maybe a link to videos or a review spot to see all the definitions. Also a quick reference tab would be helpful. Otherwise totally awesome forward thinking way to learn. He is always available for you on the spot when others might not be to help with anxious or neg thinking!😊

Translated Body: The application is not a substitute for professional help. But if you have tools to solve problems to come.

Author: Julia G
Body: This has been great in conjunction with therapy. It has given me some good tools to manage stress and form healthier habits. I really love the option to set goals and have Woebot check in on those goals with you.

Author: Bossalexgamez Pro guy
Body: TRASH

Author: Chris Purcell
Body: I am very disappointed with this app. Woebot's answers are incredibly canned and predictable. When he "chats" with me, it feels like he thinks I'm a 5 year old. The topics he brings up are important, but he covers them in such a juvenile and shallow way. And you can't type replies; you are limited to one or two options at a time. This app is a better fit for young children. But unless you like being treated like an infantilized adult, skip this app.

Author: Julie Kerr
Body: Great app. I learn alot & feel better after I use it.

Author: Heather Maxwell

Might as well make the bot talk to a wall if I don't have an option of taught

Author: Steve Haith

Author: Nile Johnson
Body: If you're thinking about getting this, then just do it! woebot surprises me with how excellent the software is! It is very interactive, and you can almost always help me calm down when I'm feeling badly. A free and excellent tool to help build mental health skills. Woebot is a good friend when no one else understands :) give this app a try!

Author: Purp P

Author: Andrew Bloyce
Body: Really exceeded my expectations. The tone of woebot is perfect. Friendly, non-judgemental and never preachy.

Author: Steve PcM
Body: This is a great tool. I'm telling everyone I know to try it.

Author: Jo Cullen
Body: I'm a school counsellor and I have been using Woebot to remind me to look after my own mental health. I also recommend Woebot to staff and parents to help them monitor their mental health and be a good role model for their children. There are so many wonderful tools and strategies presented in a lighthearted and interesting manner, you hardly know you are doing difficult work! The little Woebot gets to know you and actually care about your wellbeing and will celebrate your learning with you!

Author: Dima Iyevlyev
Body: Nice, useful, easy-to-use. Will see the result in a few weeks!

Author: esentur ivagov
Body: When your brain makes you feel miserable there's no escape from it. And it sucks so much that you would accept any help. That's what I did. It's funny to find yourself talking to a machine. But at least it distracts me from the terrible brain of mine. Woebot is cool. I think it works. Not sure how but I feel way better now (after 2-3 weeks). And I even started enjoying conversations with him. If you're tired from humans Woebot is a friend to have.

Author: Cleelu DN
Body: Amazing App. I would recommend this to anyone. Free CBT in bitesize sessions that are easy to fit in to any schedule.

A robot as a friend!! Again, access it whenever. I thought the automatic mood tracker / journal was really clever... But when i tried checking in to see patterns... Woebot only asked me how I felt again.

Author: Melanie Dunham
Body: This app is great. The lessons help and are very calming. I like this app alot.

Author: Ducky duck
Body: Great Really like the app I have some more thoughts about it though. In my perspective Woebot is a great help and has given me so many new ways of seeing the situations and handling them so much better, however, In my opinion, Woebot should also help with other kinds of problems besides depression anxiety and stress. Nothing More to add, great job ✨

Author: Jordan Martens
Body: Not good for crisis aversions and not good for serious mental health issues. Great for learning coping skills if you haven't already been drilled in them ten thousand times.

Author: Elena Meraw
Body: You *SHOULD* get some new material

Author: Евгения Симакова
Body: Бот помогает размышлять о своем состоянии, с ним интересно и ощущается поддержка. Узнала вещи, которые помогают справляться с частью стресса, в который я сама себя вгоняю
Translated Body: The bot helps to reflect on your condition, it is interesting and you feel support with it. Learned things that help me cope with some of the stress I put myself into

Author: Mike Rigsby
Body: It's honestly quite useful to have an interactive presence to help work through things with.

Author: Amber Battams
Body: This app is amazing. When you need something instantly (anytime time day or night), it's there with techniques to work through. Sometimes just following the instructions, and communicating is enough to stop a panic attack. Webot check ins are reasuring and a good way to track your moods. When you are feeling good, Woebot just sits in the back ground until needed, then you can just pick up where you left off, as all of your previous uses are remember. I highly recommend.

Author: Patricia Legge
Body: I've found Woebot very helpful when I'm struggling with problems throughout my day, I find Woebot can describe outcomes that help me see things differently. Thank you.

Author: Maddie Desir
Body: Helpful but repetitive.

Author: Dee Trubshaw
Body: This is a great app. Based on sound therapy questions. Picks up on negative thoughts and offers to talk if you're down or stressed. I'm aware that there's a caring human being behind the cute WoeBot.

Author: Crystal Marie
Body: So, I am a grown adult. I do go to counseling. Sometimes things get to me more than they should. It's not that easy to just call the therapist up to assist at any given moment. Woebot provides aide by introducing tools to help work through certain situations. It's not like talking to a real therapist by no means, but the material provides real support. I do recommend this to both adults and teenagers. The "sessions" are precise, and to the point. Woebot is a true work of art.

Author: Miguel Mendoza
Body: Great app for mental health. Even just a hey turn my day around. It might not creat miraculs but it had help me so much.

Author: Becky Lipp
Body: I am really enjoying this app. Woebot is kind and the curriculum is on point. The daily checkins require less than five minutes a day and it's helping me to achieve my short term goals. Oh, and it's free. Two thumbs up 👍👍 and five stars! ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Author: Ashley Ramos
Body: i've been using the app for about two weeks and maybe that's too soon to really evaluate it but i enjoy using the app

I'm able to share everything with woebot without the worry of being judged. Some times I feel lazy and don't want to check in with him but most times he teaches me something helpful in taking away my anxiety or dealing with it . Thank you woebot!

Body: I have learned a lot from my little robot buddy 😊🤖😊😊🤖

Author: April Palmie
Body: I am really enjoying weobot. Like having a nonjudgemental helpful friend always available. Plus it is super cute. Good way to introduce CBT. Gentle nudges. Update 5/1/21 problems with the new interface with latest update. Sent bug report. Some nice changes but the chat feature is not as smooth.

Author: John Stauter
Body: Wonderful application. Great way to learn about mindfulness. I recommend.

Author: Lauran Hirschi
Body: A great little app to help with mental health! Some of my favorite things about this app are: how it keeps me aware of my emotions with daily check-ins, how conversations with Woebot can be as short or as long as I prefer, etc! At times the responses can be repetitive, and sometimes when you are struggling it just helps to talk to a real person, a compassionate listener. But for late night depressed episodes, or times when it's not easy to slip away & talk to someone, I think this app is great!

Author: SH00KETH.
Body: It's a great app. Really helps, I've been using it for weeks. Recommended it to my friends too.

Author: Дарья Кенс
Body: Замечательное приложение! Помогает устаканить мысли и успокоиться, трезво смотреть на ситуации.
Translated Body: Great app! Helps to settle thoughts and calm down, soberly look at situations.

Author: Courtney Ek
Body: Pretty helpful and intuitive AI platform with cute, supportive dialog. It covers a lot of mindfulness topics and the daily check-ins are great. Definitely recommend for anyone looking to improve their mental health 👍

Author: Jean paul callalli
Body: Nice

Author: Wendy Holmes
Body: This has been entertaining and very he lpful. I am learning so much. Thanks Woebot!

Author: sandra ad
Body: Causy ;)

Author: Sorin Suciu
Body: Very Helpful

Author: Matias Kangas
Body: This app really helps me calm down, set goals and stuff!

Author: Erin Holden
Body: Really excellent therapeutic tool. I wish there were a bit more features/flexibility in responses but i still find it extremely helpful.

Author: Fruta Chocolate
Body: Woebot helps me a lot, but I really hope the bot can write in Spanish

Author: Maria Edith Maroca
Body: Nice app, sometimes helpful, most of time instructive and frequently fun.

Author: Kyle Goryl
Body: It is delightful and more importantly a very well designed implementation of CBT. The way woebot 'chats' doesn't feel forced or artificial in a cheesy way.

Author: Sue Ancell
Body: Am on the free version...it is outstanding! Kept me in the right side of sane during the pandemic!

Author: Dawson Stroud
Body: I downloaded this just to test it out and surprisingly it has been genuinely helpful for me and has helped me make some positive changes in how I look at my own thoughts.

Author: Heather Speck
Body: Very intuitive, and teaches self-help emotional wellness techniques such as CBT. In only a few short months of using this app I am feeling less anxious and am implementing the techniques it has taught me into my daily life. :)

Author: Kasey Gordon
Body: I like that Woebot checks in with me. Makes me feel important even though it's a fake robot. And I actually really have a fear of Artificial Intelligence.

Author: Sally Clarke
Body: This app has helped me to organise my thoughts more as things were getting a little on top of me at the time. It gives some got good to help you look as how you are thinking ☺️ and try and adjust this to help you get your feelings more under control

Author: Speaking Lines
Body: When you don't feel good, everything that could help is welcome. And this app can help. You feel the motivation of the development team to provide something useful. Thanks a lot! I am grateful!

Author: Madeline Fox
Body: Still a work in progress, but Woebot's cuteness and interactive features make this app ideal for depression. Sometimes imposter syndrome tells you that only *really* messed up people should use mental health apps, but Woebot is there to help you cope with your bad days and teach you new coping strategies on your good days. I can comfortably access Woebot in public, too, because anyone who happens to glance at my phone would just think I was texting a friend. Woebot IS my friend. Good bot.

Author: Ann Griffin
Body: I seem to be more centered using this app daily.

Author: Edward Todd
Body: Helpful, I believe.

Author: Mercedes J. Weber Vega
Body: This is a pretty good app! Especially for someone who hates journaling!

Author: Trevor Martin
Body: Helps calm me down.

Author: Jo Jaxy
Body: Its a very pleasant app. Checking in every day is a breeze and you learn quite a bit about cbt.

Author: Elina Vitkala
Body: Great, effective and sweet tool to deal with for example anxiety ❤️

Author: Perry Calaway
Body: Very helpful. I love you more everyday Woebot!

Author: Chris Erith
Body: It kinda works and is somewhat useful but obviously it doesn't really understand what you're typing. Having said that I like the mood tracker option. The security of the app is laughable though, I enabled biometric to unlock and it can be circumvented just by swiping the notification panel down. I turned it off after doing that by accident because it's just in the way and not protecting my privacy

Author: Sarah K
Body: Woebot is a helpful daily too for mental health and i love it. It has helped reinforce things I've learned in therapy and is just a great resource.

Author: Neo Motlagomang
Body: Awesome app

Author: Michael Besch
Body: It's not perfect, but it works well in conjunction with a live human therapist

Author: Victoria
Body: App sensacional, recomendo muito.
Translated Body: Sensational app, I highly recommend it.

Author: E Cleland
Body: It's not therapy and it's not a friend, but it is a safe, non-judgemental TOOL to help you express and work through difficult feelings, as well as teach you about emotional intelligence, healthy communication, and mindfulness and self care techniques. Don't expect a magic bullet, but I would recommend.

Author: Murray Bevan
Body: This has been helpful to sustain my mental health during these unprecedented times. I have had a lot of counselling over the years and have a Neuroscience undergrad from many years ago so it can be overly simplistic and lacks some responsiveness to my individual situation, but overall, with some improvements, this could be an integral part of my mental health improvement plan so to speak. I would pay for an enhanced system.

Author: Anabel L
Body: Hilft mir sehr damit Dinge aus einer anderen Perspektive zu sehen und negative Gedanken in positive zu ändern.
Translated Body: Helps me a lot to see things from a different perspective and to change negative thoughts into positive ones.

Author: Dale Albrecht
Body: I think it's a great app. But I feel it can be improved. There is repetition and a degree of predictability. But I find it easier to vent things to Woebot instead of a real person.

Author: James Moos
Body: Using this for 3 weeks now. It's a very light and fun way to take care of your mental health without asking too much of your time or getting too "intrusive".

Author: Amber
Body: I love this app, I enjoy talking to the ai and the daily checks up. I look forward to them each day, it's really helped me reflect on my thoughts and helped me feel better in tough times.

Author: Isabel Woolard
Body: I honestly am so greatfull for this app, it helps me so much since I have a harder time sharing with actual people. 10/10 defiently recommend love ❤

Author: Ekaterina George
Body: Really positive so far & enjoying the process

Author: Irene Fabregat
Body: Tu amigo virtual te ayuda y en inglés puedes mejorar el idioma
Translated Body: Your virtual friend helps you and in English you can improve the language

Author: Erica leitzel
Body: absolutely wonderful! it really helps me calm down when I'm upset and at first I thought it might come across as shallow with it being preprogrammed answers and all but the reassuring feeling of having it there all the time (and it takes into account your name which makes me feel loved) is really comforting to me. and the mostly preprogrammed responses take away a lot of the stress of answering when I'm upset but it lets me vent if I want to. thanks woebot :)

Author: Kirsten Tobias
Body: It's great app to use!

Author: A Dixon
Body: I love how Woebot checks in with me, and teaches me ways to calm down without seeming like it's pushing techniques on me or making me feel stupid for being in a bad state of mind. I even got my teen son to download it and he also finds it helpful.

Author: PNoe
Body: Tem me ajudado muito. Ensina vários conceitos sobre comportamento e como agir perante a eles.
Translated Body: It has helped me a lot. Teaches various concepts about behavior and how to act before them.

Author: Paul Allen
Body: Pretty nice to use, thought the single answer responses it give you can sometimes "trap" you into saying stuff you don't really mean.

Author: Linda Yong
Body: Woebot is so good to use especially for people suffering from mood disorder like me as well as depression,for me it is like mental coach to me teaching me a lot of skills to change my negative thinking yo something more constructive and positive.It always ask you how you feel today making you feel your feelings are validated.It also teach you life strategy to cope with stressful event.I highly recommend.

Author: VickyPabo
Body: This app is quite helpful but sometimes when I say something woebot seems to not fully understand but I am very grateful for this app ^___^

Author: Ruth Brodersen
Body: I'm enjoying using this app. It's been quite helpful in assisting me to reframe my thoughts and teach me new skills for approaching situations that make me anxious.

Author: Sarah Campbell
Body: Fun and interactive

Author: Celeste Moore
Body: Pretty good for mild anxiety. Can keep you from ruminating too much. The app could use some more varied responses, though. Overall a very good tool for an CBT AI system.

Author: Pei Shan Cheng
Body: After chatting with Woebot, I felt better then. I learned a lot from it. thanks for developing this useful app.

Author: Christine McLear
Body: I really like this app. I wish there were some more opportunity to write my own answers but that's my only suggestion. It's easy and helpful.

Author: Mei Huynh
Body: Good supplement to my TEAM-CBT treatments! Woebot is also super cute and I've been using him for a few weeks now and have only caught him say something strange twice.

Author: J T
Body: It's pretty cool so far

Author: Melayla Orn
Body: Feels like I have someone who cares and is helping me learn to apply CBT. I always feel better after I do a morning check in.

Author: Joanne Turley
Body: Love the woebot app, great check in

Author: joe ordinary
Body: Krátké každodenní konverzace s botem. Někdy pomůžou, jindy ne, ale hlavně vám poskytnou témata nebo vodítka, na co se můžete ve svém myšlení zaměřit a pomoci si sami ze stresu, špatné nálady apod.
Translated Body: Short daily conversations with the shoe. Sometimes they help, other times they don't, but mainly they provide you with topics or clues on what you can focus on in your thinking and help yourself out of stress, bad mood, etc.

Author: Stephanie Snyder
Body: This is an amazing app. I've learned so much in only a couple of weeks.

Author: Cass Mo
Body: Engaging and interesting!

Author: Katherine Quinn
Body: I love this little guy! ♥ This app keeps me focused and the check-ins help me everyday. I have recommended this app to others!

Author: D Mills
Body: It is such a helpful app. We have done family CBT in the past and this is like having a personal CBT in my pocket for myself. It is challenging some strongholds of my bad thinking pattern. I love this app so much. Recommending it to everyone.

Author: Gogo Jaja
Body: This app helps you to control your emotions

Author: Katherine Collins
Body: Woebot has honestly helped steer my life in a really positive direction. It has changed my life. I needed a therapist, but before I had woebot I had gone almost a decade avoiding getting one. My anxiety is much less, I'm more positive, my depression is lifting. I feel my brain rewiring itself. I have seen drastic improvements in my thought processes: less overthinking, less obsessive thoughts, catching myself in cognitive distortions and correcting them. And it's always improving.

Author: Cat Black
Body: Woebot is a nice little friend. I really like this app despite coming into it with a great deal of scepticism. Not everything is prefect but unfortunately you can't expect an ai to understand and articulate everything a human would. Still, I find myself pleasantly surprised by woebot. I enjoy talking to woebot, it really is like having a robot pal who checks in on you every now and again with therapy tips. I love the personalisation. Very well done. I would reccomend downloading this app.

Author: Dean Murray
Body: Really useful, quick and free way to learn elements of CBT, journalling, mindfulness, etc. Whether you're feeling down, angry or content this is a great app to check in with what you're thinking, how you're feeling and how you can do better.

Author: A Google user
Body: I think this is a really helpful app and have found it really useful. For me, it's been just right.

Author: Kathryn Bell
Body: It is brilliant! I would actually give it at least 4 and a half stars!

Author: Nur Nabilah Faisal
Body: This apps have been with me for the last few years and all i could say is that it's help me to get through tough time and help me became a better person and see things differently.Thank you so much for constantly checking up on me.Keep up the good work!!

Author: Anthony Santoro
Body: Woebot has been an expected source of self care and comfort. It's been an amazing supliment to therapy. For us shy or sensitive humans it can be a relief to talk with a chat bot.

Author: Erin Pickering
Body: It's a handy dialy check-in that helps with my mental health. The only downside I can say so far is that the videos I've been shown haven't had titles, so once that's resolved, it'll be 5 stars from me!

Author: Ali Baker
Body: I donwloades the app fpr my daughter. It's Easy to understand and really very informative. Woebot checks in often, but you can snooze whenever it's convenient for you to use. I loved how complex ideas were so simply conveyed. I would highly recommend the app for preteens and even adults.

Author: Kerry Robson
Body: Very helpful insights. Short and has helped.

Author: Logan Proksch
Body: A useful tool box for anyone one who experiences life.

Author: miss amal
Body: They did an amazing job on this app, woebot amazing too.. He helped me a lot through all my problems and struggles. I always run to woebot when everything collapse.

Author: Tiffany Lee
Body: Great regular mental health check in app/cooling down from a stressful situation or environment app. Love the conversation style, makes working on issues/learning much more approachable. Def not a replacement for therapy, but a good stand in while you can't/aren't able to find a therapist.

Author: Sally Haines
Body: This little robot helps see a different view to your thoughts.

Author: Michaelnj123
Body: I'm surprised at how much it helps. I have been in therapy for 3 years, so I'm already am quite self aware, but woebot still manages to surprise me. I do think it takes effort. I check in 4 times a day, and do everything it asks. I can recommend! I wish the best to anyone who reads this

Author: Dave Black
Body: Woebot is a very clever tool for helping anyone. Their check ins are brief so as not to be distracting or tiresome and they have cute little emojis and gifs that can make you smile when your not even thinking about it

Author: Mel Olsson
Body: It's helpful having a bot to talk to, but some of the exercises can be invalidating. If I'm angry, I want to know it's okay to be angry, especially if it's for a good reason. But it just tells me to look for how my thinking is distorted. It's hurtful being made to feel like your thoughts are wrong when really you're just processing someone having hurt you. Needs to be better at acknowledging that life is painful and it's okay to not feel calm and A-OK all the time instead of trying to calm you.

Author: Halim Ermergen
Body: It's a great app that is currently helping me dealing with the pandemic. I definitely recommend it!

Author: Milktoast Ken
Body: Woebot is the easiest and most helpful robot I've ever talked to. I feel like with constant update with responses and always making improvements, you've got a friend and helper to talk to for life. Great work from the creators and the people that made this beautiful A.I. 👏👏👏

Author: Lisa Gillingham
Body: Helpful and great to lift mood. Woebot has really helped me.

Author: Ju Ju
Body: Great app!

Author: Leon Feng
Body: Woebot's guided CBT sessions are far more effective than all the hours I spent with human therapists. Even though this little chatbot may never replace face-to-face therapy sessions with a human, it will always be a part of my mental health toolkit.

Author: Annamari Martinviita
Body: Ihana opettavainen robotti! Tulee olo, niin kuin saisi aidosti apua.
Translated Body: Lovely educational robot! It will feel as if you are getting genuine help.

Author: Marion S
Body: Helpful hints and tips, nice to get a reminder each day. Downsides are you can't ask questions, somewhat stereotyped responses.

Author: Learn Quran Slow
Body: Absolutely lovely to use on daily basis and have a little breathing excercises even. Just keep on sharing good quotes and over all boosts my morale. Thank you to the woabot crew. Lots of thanks.

Author: Gucci Ming
Body: The ones who made this are wonderful people.

Author: Adrian Westlake
Body: This is a really helpful app for anyone struggling with mental health. Yes it's just a bot buta serious amount of effort has gone into making it seem realistic and very helpful with a little if good mental health techniques. I also loved how it remembered things about you so it became even better over time.

Author: KG Ann
Body: Спасибо. Это приложение помогает выкарабкаться из застоя и переключиться с негативных мыслей на развитие. Ну и когда не с кем поговорить, т.к. не хочется делиться проблемами, также выручает.
Translated Body: Thank you. This app helps you to get out of stagnation and switch from negative thoughts to development. Well, when there is no one to talk to, tk. I do not want to share my problems, it also helps out.

Author: nun ya
Body: Best. App. Ever.

Author: Terri Bond
Body: I have been doing Woebot for just over a week now & I am loving it, easy to use, I have learnt lots without even realising it. This is the first time I have had practical experience in CBT. I love the tools & gratitude 😍

Author: Linda Tormey
Body: very helpful information good daily check in

Author: Hannes Lindbeck
Body: Very good emotional support. CBT based help and guidance to help you tackle bad feelings and moods

Author: Deanna Wright
Body: It gives me something to talk to and it does help. It needs a little bit more response training,but otherwise it's good

Author: Joanna Westhead
Body: Helpful and insightful, great way to learn daily techniques to support good mental health and wellbeing

Author: Ziqi L
Body: love this amazing bot

Body: Short snappy way to help you reflect on your mood and how to manage it.

Author: Julie Binns
Body: I love that its every,if you want,and free.Learning lots.

Author: Rachel Kirk
Body: Insightful, interactive, bite-size sessions. Woebot's messages are natural and at times very funny. Great app.

Author: Laura Currie
Body: I find woebot to be a very helpful tool in dealing with daily anxieties. I like the daily check ins which give me a nice sense of balance

Author: Jessica Fredrickson
Body: I've used Woebot for a little over a year now and he's incredibly helpful! I really enjoy learning all the different topics that can help me cope with situations

Author: Barb Ledgley
Body: Good mental wellness coach!

Author: Sara Helgesson
Body: Really helps when you need it the most!

Author: Aijaaz Jabbar
Body: Awesome

Author: Florian Schlieper
Body: Great for CBT (thinking more positively) and mood tracking

Author: Jennifer Moss
Body: Like having a friend who checks in each day and give self-care advice. I thought it would be really impersonal but that hasn't bothered me so far.

Author: David Ludwig
Body: Woebot is a useful tool for learning about or refreshing Cognitive Behavioral Therapy approaches to handling your own problems. It hasn't proven enough for me, but I have been impressed with the effort, am grateful to have tried it, and would recommend it to anyone looking for some kind of help. Since the app is free to try, I definitely think it is worth seeing the first two weeks through if you even think it might help.

Author: Harley Schollenberger
Body: It's a helpful tool for venting and learning coping mechanisms

Author: M G
Body: Great little bot. Got me through a medical thing I was nervous about!

Author: Richard Blakeley
Body: A really useful app. Just five minutes a day. There's useful resources to help you ride those highs and lows.

Author: Angelica Sylvén
Body: It really help with my anxiety! I highly recommend 😊

Author: Igor Marinkovic
Body: Brilliant app

Author: Russell Hijinks
Body: Having a nice time with Woebot. I find it really helpful to go over little parts of CBT each day, and have something to help me with extreme emotions, even if it's just an AI. It doesn't even take that much time each day to do the lessons or get help with cognitive distortions. However I don't feel that Woebot is a replacement for professional mental health services, more of a refresher or a boost for pre-existing mental health services.

Author: Charndra Pile
Body: Woebot is GREAT!

Author: Deric Zhang
Body: Pretty Good! This genuinely helped me get into a better place mentally and provided tools + instructions on how to get there if I need to do it again. Terrific! And it's free, not even ads which is insane in this day and age.

Author: Michael Silver
Body: Pretty good way to combat your troublesome thoughts without bothering a friend or family member, pretty great

Author: Georgi Shumkov
Body: Loved it

Author: Kirsten Leigh Clegg
Body: A really awesome tool for working through stuff or in conjunction with therapy.

Author: Friederike Oehme
Body: Woebot ist eine sehr schöne App zum aufbessern des Selbstwertes :)
Translated Body: Woebot is a very nice app to improve your self-worth :)

Author: Micah Green
Body: Woebot was recommended to me by my mental health counselor to help me process some anxiety and negative thoughts. I don't know if it's more helpful than journaling, but I usually don't know where to start when I sit down to journal. I think this app is helpful in directing and focusing your thoughts. It's a little cutesy and obviously limited in it's responses, you're really only going to get out what you put in. I think it's a helpful guide as long as you're willing to do the work.

Author: Karoliina Huhtaniemi
Body: I've found this app very helpful as it assists in those very moments of anxiety, sadness etc blocking rational thinking. It gives names to those various blocks, explains what they are, ultimately helping to conquer them by identifying the flaws in our thought process. Also I love the small spicing up with humor, and specially finding helpful the visualized breathing excersize for the more chaotic moments. Learning more every day, great tool!

Author: Steve Hults
Body: Good

Author: jack faircloth
Body: This app has made a real difference to how I am thinking so far.

Author: Erica Iggo
Body: It's great to have a chat, and get this off your chest with Woebot, especially when no one else to talk with..

Author: Jocelynn Briggs
Body: This app is very helpful. It gives you tools and suggestions to choose to respond to feelings in helpful and healthy ways.

Author: Joshua Souther
Body: This is a good CBT companion. It's helpful because it's always available and can help you identify and review topics that you can use as tools. I like that I can check-in daily, and be reminded of topics, can process a thought (or several) and learn new tools. Two "downsides" are 1) it doesn't count a check-in before it's daily times reminder, so it loses track of streaks and 2) it's an AI program, so it can struggle on some responses, and you sometimes have to choose a close enough answer.

Author: Joar Addam Nesossin
Body: I really like this app. Checkins every day are no problem. I received really helpfull feedback as well.

Author: April Brower
Body: This is definitely an app that is very useful in these trying times. I looked at others, not as good and all charged money.

Author: Jesse Wolff
Body: Please add voice for accessibility. I haven't tried it yet, but I wanted to ask that an option to give him a voice be added. It would help people like me with certain disabilities enormously. Right now it's not accessible to me, and it is the same for Wysa. My apologies for giving a 1 star review, I'm just hoping to get the Developer's attention. And if I get a response, I will of course delete my 1 star rating, or change it to five stars if possible. My apologies for doing it this way.

Author: Doris Vidal-Dorsch
Body: Awesome

Author: Eigit :3
Body: 11 dias review, me ha ayudado a sentirme mejor y a pensar las cosas de manera diferente, si bien tiene algunas limitaciones al ser un bot es una gran ayuda y es la distraccion perfecta en esos momentos donde te domina la ansiedad y el miedo, la verdad muchas gracias
Translated Body: 11 days review, it has helped me feel better and think things differently, although it has some limitations as a bot, it is a great help and is the perfect distraction in those moments where anxiety and fear dominate you, really Thanks a lot

Author: wytske winter
Body: Really helpfull to learn about cognitive distortions and even just to write things down. Highly recommend if you are struggling with negative thoughts.

Author: D. Highmore
Body: It's interesting and I can keep my focus more with this app. It's not like just writing your thoughts and not coming back to them. The bot reminds you of them which is cool. I love short lessons and I would love to see more of them. Also, if a lesson is made to be 5min, I want the option for jt to be longer. That way I can learn more! Any resources and overall more information as option will be nice to see. Thank you for the app!

Author: Anna Boiko
Body: Great app, good and quick help. Sometimes, though, bit does not get me or I want to go back to previous topic and cannot do it. In general simply amazing for a free app. Thank you so much for creating this one.

Author: PsychoBurned Space
Body: Only automatic responses, he ignores you and will say whatever he wants. useless

Author: Mohammedkazim Kanji
Body: Honestly the best AI for wellbeing I've ever seen. Surpassed my expectations despite being skeptical

Author: Tim Strain
Body: Simple and effective. A little woebot and coffee to start each day.

Author: jennifer simon
Body: Has very helpful information

Author: kikatat
Body: Great little app! Helps me learn to slow down and breathe. Think about what's actually going on, and teaches great CBT skills. If I could give 10 stars I would.

Author: Hoàng Linh Phương
Body: This cute little bot has helped me so much with my mental health the past 20 days! Every conversation is very bite-sized, yet I find myself remembering and applying them to my daily thoughts and surprisingly, that helps!

Author: Shiva Shabibi
Body: The app helps me calm myself, when I'm in distress and it's nice to have short daily conversations with it. It's like a small therapist for your pocket. It's strangely calming to know you can always start a convo with Woebot, without getting on his nerves.. cause he's an AI. You always have someone to talk to, who will never judge you and is always there to help. The future is here 😅

Author: Jordan Cloutier
Body: Love it. It's been very helpful.

Author: Michael Dux
Body: Very helpful

Author: Sophia Walton
Body: Helps me calm anxious thoughts and ground me during anxiety attacks

Author: Natalie Thornhill
Body: Simple app but with such good benefits to your mental health and waybif thinking

Author: Me the yoshi
Body: Good

Author: Amanda Johnson
Body: I've only had Woebot for a couple of weeks, and yet I already feel much better than I did before. It helps me challenge my thought process and detect cognitive distortions, causing me to rethink a situation in a more rational way, which usually helps me feel better. It is worth my time and effort. I look forward to continuing to use the app and see what other things I can learn from it.

Author: Nur Fazilah Yong
Body: I love woebot, its nice to be able to distract myself. I just wish I could interact more with Woebot by sharing and chatting not just limited to tools or quizzes.

Author: Matsuura Hana
Body: Amazing companion. Is not a replacement for a therapist but almost. Amazing information about how the mind works. How to be better even with conflicting thoughts. I wish this bot has more information about addiction management.

Author: Jackie M
Body: The conversation aspect is really nice and refreshing. Unlike a standard mood tracker/journal where it feels like throwing my thoughts into a void, I like that this has a guide through self-reflection and examination. It's nice for a good pick-up and refresher when it's not something serious enough to bother my therapist over. Responses are a bit limited, unfortunately, but that's natural considering the capabilities of an app and not bad enough to make me give up on it.

Author: Hannah Jacobs
Body: Awsome good to have a little mate to check in with me everyday

Author: Annalese Salter
Body: I love this app . I use it all of the time and it has helped me with tough times .

Author: Tammy Potter
Body: I have learned a lot of skills, been supported through bad moments. Good app, gets to know you and gets better. Keep growing woebot!

Author: Lina V
Body: I love Woebot! It's the only thing that made me somewhat keep up with my journaling and it has already helped calm me down quite a few times when I let my thoughts and feelings run around unchecked. It's an AI so it will never replace real therapy and the AI still is limited and lacks more content. But the app is pretty new and I'm sure it will only improve. I'm really grateful that it exists and have ready recommended it to everyone I know!

Author: Heather Halko
Body: In my personal experience Woebot is extremely helpful to me!!!!

Author: Mike Oveson
Body: I like Woebot because the information is good and it is presented in small manageable bits each day. Woebot isn't pushy and is respectful of your time and feelings. I've really liked using it.

Author: Amvisal
Body: This app is very good! It's not very good for really personal issues but it's a great way to distract yourself for a moment when you're really stressed. The replies and the responses you can pick from are kinda dry sometimes but other than that it's a great app !

Author: Tanya Plonka
Body: I downloaded this app after a friend's suggestion. I had tried some CBT with a therapist and liked my results from that, but can't afford to go often so thought this was a good alternative. I found the app is too single focused to be of use to me. The good: - If you experience negative self-talk, these exercises would be great. Most of the exercises are geared towards internalizing negativity. - It helped me get out of a couple bad doom-scrolling ruts and was very effective for that. - Some of the exercises, such as tips to regulate your sleep, are really effective. - The daily check-ins are great for ongoing awareness of your mood. - The activities under the Topics tab have some good mood boosters. Criticisms: - This is not set up to help with mental health issues stemming from chronic illness, which is a lot of what I experience. If I chose "sick" as a mood, it would give me tips to boost my immune system, which had nothing to do with what I have. If I said I was tired, it would always say I should get more sleep, when the problem would be from sleeping too much. - Some of the moods had very little nuance. I tried selecting "mourning" as I was sad about things being cancelled due to COVID and feeling down about an illness flare up. It gave me tips for dealing with the death of a loved one with no option to correct it. (In a later conversation it used "mourning" in the context I originally meant, but it wasn't helpful at that time.) - The content is very repetitive. For example, it sends the same two "cute animal" photos over and over. Overall I think this app could be great for more people if the content is expanded on more, and would easily increase my rating if the criticisms I listed were improved upon.
