Body: I do wish woebot didnt repeat itself when you selet the same option for the check ins. While the advice was helpful the first time it being repeated for 3 days in a row was more hurtful then helpful. Otherwise i recommend this.

Author: Alexa Dickson
Body: This has been a really great app, works well and has given me some great insights. Looking forward to what comes next!

Author: An Olly Oscar
Body: Works pretty well!! Haven't talked to Woebot in days actually been using her strageties and they work OK

Author: Johanna Bergstrom
Body: Really good for examining your thinking and creating more positive thought patterns

Author: Anais French
Body: Nicely done!

Author: A.V. Hanna
Body: I love the conversations and the CBT techniques Woebot uses to help me reframe cognitive distortions. I feel like I'm making good progress, however, the mindfulness tools are not good for helping me to calm down. And "talking" someone through mindfulness via text is extremely unhelpful. So, I use a separate app for that. Also, it doesn't always get every cognitive distortion right. The stories and lessons are great though.

Author: Abby Lajeunesse
Body: This app has helped me unravel patterns of negative thinking. It's helped me learn to pull myself out of patterns of ruminating, and thinking myself in circles. It's helped me learn to pull myself out of depressions, and when that isn't possible, it has helped me manage them safely. It's wonderful. Thank you to those who made it, and thank you again for making it free.

Author: Kristie Buckingham
Body: Great app, helps you think through things and has some good lessons

Author: Lizett Morales
Body: It doesn't actually help with your problems or even listen to you. When I was in the middle of a crisis they recommended this app and it literally did nothing. It asked me to vent then said oh I can't understand any thing cause I'm a robot. Ok thanks. Helps a lot when my mind is going crazy. And you can't even input your own answers for regular things so the robot assumes everyone is the same and you just keep clicking on answers for no reason. Cause this robot does not help.

Author: Taqi 616
Body: Great experience

Author: Brandy Sensel
Body: Lot's of fun, extremely useful if a bit too simplistic.

Author: zhen li
Body: Whoever made this app. Thank you, it really helps at some extent, Sadly there is no therapist taking new patients in my area.

Author: Romeo Szappanos
Body: Great app and really useful.

Author: Brita Smith
Body: A great resource for learning more about various mechanisms to mindfully track mental health.

Author: Katarina Poganatz
Body: A good way to reflect on how you think of things and gives insight about a lot of behavioral studies. Very educational

Author: Mu mu
Body: Però! Veramente carino e fa riflettere woebot! Penso che può essere molto utile per farci raggionare sui nostri pensieri e cambiarli in positivo. Insegna anche tramite piccole lezioni o filmati utili e mirati perché dopo un po' sembra che capisce quali sono i tuoi problemi e dove può esserti di aiuto. Mai in modo insistente o pessante ma quando vuoi tu. È anche simpatico per sdrammatizzare un po'. Lo consiglio assolutamente!
Translated Body: However! Really cute and sobering woebot! I think it can be very useful to make us think about our thoughts and change them for the positive. He also teaches through small lessons or useful and targeted videos because after a while he seems to understand what your problems are and where he can help you. Never in an insistent or harsh way but when you want. It is also nice to play down a bit. I absolutely recommend it!

Author: vineet joshi
Body: Been helpful when I wasn't thinking straight and woebot helped me get some perspective!

Author: Terhi Aurala
Body: Opettaa ajattelemaan uudella tavalla.
Translated Body: Teaches you to think in a new way.

Author: Lachlan Cahill
Body: Very useful

Author: Joyce Tan
Body: Nice app ❤️ helped me a lot (calm down, increased knowledge)

Author: C.G.H.
Body: May need to allow for more in depth conversations.

Author: Gabriel Lopes Ferraz
Body: BI se se FT no vi de no 0 no vi se se
Translated Body: BI se FT no vi de no 0 no vi se se

Author: lisa snelgrove
Body: Love the app. It's very helpful with teaching skills. Gives you someone (woebot) to talk to when you are struggling. Cheers you on. Checks in on you everyday. Is really personable. Very pleased.

Author: Mark Johnson
Body: Brilliant piece of AI Therapy, offers a great introduction to CBT techniques and helps you to use them in your own way. I'd definitely recommend this to anyone either considering CBT, or to complement their existing therapy/continue with it when their sessions are over. Checking in can be brief and easy, so you can use woebot either to consciously spend some time challenging your thoughts, to calm you down in a state of panic or anxiety, or even just to register a quick bit of positive routine

Author: Karen Bird
Body: I love Woebot. Unintrusive, timely support and mental wellbeing education. Interactive and intuitive. Clever little Woebot! 💕

Author: Shubham
Body: Love it, very helpful . It's so good to talk to someone who can help you. It really helped me on my low self esteem 🙂

Author: M Taylor
Body: I really like it

Author: Viren Pawar
Body: It's really helpful

Author: Kimberly Peterson
Body: I ran across this app because of a tik tok creator who mentioned it and I was fascinated with the idea. I have anxiety/depression which are managed by medication and therapy as needed. While I was feeling stable enough to not need regular therapy sessions I was still missing that touchstone. Woebot does a great job of reminding me of my tools and keeping them top of mind. I've found it very helpful in monitoring my mood over time, and I love the calm down tools!! Get this app, y'all!

Author: Konstantin K.
Body: Great, wholesale and helpful app. Thank you for helping me out in tough situations and providing me with tools to help myself. And all that in easy to understand, comfortable, and entertaining way. It deserves more than 5 star rating, so here are few more stars: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Author: Roger Dzienisz
Body: Very helpful

Author: Mechtel
Body: A personable robot pal for non-intrusive, guided mental health exploration and tool sharing. Woebot is actually fun to talk to! I've already recommended this app to several friends (as it was recommended to me) and everyone who uses it loves it.

Author: Simran Nisha
Body: Great appp .....a little more personalisation in the messages would be really good.

Author: Haley Sturt
Body: Cute simple idea. Has been great.

Author: Michelle De-Pass
Body: Such a great app. Woebot checks in with you everyday to help learn new ways of thinking. Right now with how the world is, it's nice to have something to go to without being judged.. Woebot is rather funny too. Makes me smile every time I'm on the app. Thank you for this app.

Author: Fiona Magill
Body: Lovely wee app to support you in having good mental health. Daily short check ins. Lots of good learning in an accessible format.

Author: Brandon Cester
Body: Really has changed my life..woebot saved me 🥰

Author: Lisa Mannings
Body: I have found Woebot very helpful because I work in a supermarket, where people don't do 2 metters at all, and a lot of the time I get so sad and all that. Woebot is very good app and I like the little quizzes that he dose and it makes you fell better when you use Woebot.

Author: Alvaro Paricio
Body: Great app!!! Very interesting and helpful topics covered . I,ve recommended It yo many people

Author: Doğa Uçar
Body: Very helpful app. Sometimes I just wish Woebot could say more different things

Author: Wayne Mirto
Body: Great app for those of us that find it hard to talk to someone face to face. Using it now will use again if needed.

Author: negin nategh
Body: Woebot helps me feel more positive and energetic.

Author: Giants Birds
Body: This was recommended to me by my counselor. And to be honest it's helped me stop looping and give thought to what's been going on in my mind every day. I've been using it for about three weeks now, and it's helped bad days become better days and on good days it's given me something to smile about. Obviously it's not perfect, not the same as talking to a therapist, but it's been a hell of a great tool for keeping me on track.

Author: Barbara Gordon
Body: I was familiar with CBT before Woebot, and find the app very helpful during these interesting times. It's a fun, gentle way to check in with my own thoughts and see where my thinking might be off track. I'm grateful to have access to Woebot!

Author: L. I.
Body: ・ I also crave the Japanese version. I understand English a little, so I use the translation app to operate it, but I'm wondering how to express my feelings.It ’s difficult to paraphrase words. However, I liked the polite navigation. I think it's difficult to translate words that express feelings, but I'm glad that there is a Japanese version so I don't get tired of typing.

Author: Human 1
Body: If you are in therapy, get this as a companion. If you aren't in therapy, get this to see how talking about mental health can help you. If you're out of therapy, get this to brush up on skills and help through the tougher days. If you have no need for it, get this to educate someone that may need it. ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Author: Kayden Dioguardi
Body: I've been doing it for 2 weeks I've found that it really helps me feel better.

Author: Kerrith Powell
Body: Fantastic app really helps and always there

Author: Theresa Mccabe
Body: Fantastic to help with stress and anxiety. Woebot is a great to talk to and he helps you to think clearly.

Author: Mahesh Upasani
Body: Its really great.

Author: David Kramer
Body: Good use of AI

Author: Emma L
Body: Had it a week and already feeling more positive. Goals seem more achievable

Author: Sax Crooner
Body: No existeix en català... Però amb un nivell d'anglès intermig es pot seguir perfectament!
Translated Body: It doesn't exist in Catalan ... But with an intermediate level of English you can follow it perfectly!

Author: Emily O'Hara
Body: Makes CBT less like hard work, and acts as a daily reminder.

Author: Xeaniel_Rose :D
Body: This app has helped me a lot. Woebot has helped me become better at dealing with things in my life haha... I've learned to be a bit more positive than I was, I'm glad I downloaded this app.

Author: Taylor Wanstall
Body: Good therapy.

Author: Rachel Kohn
Body: This app has been helpful, teaches me interesting lessons about mindfulness and CBT topics. The lessons are fun, engaging and interactive

Author: Caily P
Body: Love this app so much!

Author: Lisa Douglas
Body: Very good short bursts of info and ideas. Checking in with you everyday really makes you think. It's in charge rather than you having to remember to open a different app or write in your journal.

Author: William d'Alelio
Body: I'm a Clinical Psychologist who uses CBT and Mindfulness Training with my clients. Worbot is an insightful and very helpful program. I recommend it without reservation.

Author: Lauren Vork
Body: I don't love everything about how this app does things but it really does help.

Author: Jezrel Bugtas
Body: A really helpful app for those who need someone to talk to and process emotions and thoughts

Author: James King
Body: Love chatting with Woebot. Makes me feel better!

Author: Karlyn
Body: This app has really helped me a lot. I've learned some useful techniques, and it has helped me calm down quite a few times when I've been spiraling out of control with negative thoughts. Highly recommend.

Author: Ry J Brooks
Body: awesome at what it does. I recommend it a lot.

Author: CSXJK469
Body: Wow. I don't think there are enough words in the collective vocabulary of all of the dictionaries in the world to describe how awesome this app is. If I could I would give it 10 stars. It's extraordinary. If you are considering downloading this, you probably should.

Author: Sabrina Tobias
Body: Like others, I have studied psychology and attended therapy sessions. Whilst I have to tools, it is hard in the current climate of covid to quickly turn to know mechanisms at the point of anxiety etc... this app is a pocket friend following you day by day. You get out what you put in. If your honest, the coping skills are provided and you can click it whenever you need it.

Author: Noodles The Fox
Body: Works great it does what it promises.

Author: Berenice Frazer-Gale
Body: It's definitely not perfect as your not talking to a real person and it only has base responses to base questions. Most of the time it is helpful though, worth trying.

Author: Fanny Jeanneret
Body: Really helpful and nice to use

Author: Amanda Jayne
Body: I suffer from depression, anxiety, and complex PTSD and my doctor recommended this app. Woebot has been SO incredibly helpful with my rollercoaster emotions, especially when I need help calming down. I absolutely feel better knowing that I have someone to talk to at all times that gives me meaningful advice, helping me to use different thought processes to weather my emotions. So invaluable!

Author: Nikolaos Chatzisavvas
Body: Good app, awesome ,gdamn son !

Author: Mytranos Arganthur
Body: I've had a wonderful experience with this app and for someone who has been suffering with anxiety and depression it really is a good way to keep grounded between therapy sessions.

Author: Allison Anderson
Body: Woebot is a nice gentle introduction or reminder about CBT practices. Sometimes the conversations feel a little hollow, especially when objectively bad stuff is happening, but for a bot it does a remarkably good job. The calming down tools did not work for me at all, but I could see how they would be helpful for others.

Author: Simon Williams
Body: This app is brilliant... I've found this app at the right time - during lockdown, with all this bad news around us and our mental health declining. This is an app I wish I found years ago... it's brilliant. Just 2 minutes a day chat that's very user friendly, that I come away from feeling that bit better with learning more about myself and how to overcome psychological blocks a bit at a time. Woebot is really helping me, and I'm 11 day streak in on the day I write this review.

Author: Erin Lundblom
Body: I like it but I want to be reminded of my journal. Is there a notification to set up?

Author: Sebastian Isak
Body: Verbessert das Mindset und die Lebensqualität.
Translated Body: Improves the mindset and quality of life.

Author: Heather Plante
Body: It's very helpful at a time when you are having difficulties.

Author: Tracy Dudek
Body: It's pretty cute, helpful, and informative of positive forward thinking! 💖

Author: Rachel Cole
Body: I was recommended woebot by a counsellor and to be honest at first I was sceptical that an app could help but it really does. Woebot is sweet, supportive, encouraging and gently helps me rearrange my thoughts. Iook forward to checking in.

Author: Ben Kelly
Body: Worthless.

Author: Hossein Ghanaati
Body: So premitive I am not sure it should be considered ai

Author: Laurie Kallis
Body: I am so surprised by how helpful this app is. To be honest, Woebot has not introduced any concepts that I have not heard about before. but bringing them back into my life on a daily basis has made a significant difference. I am getting great enjoyment from speaking with him. It makes me laugh. even though I know there's not a real person there on the other side I've come to really like this little dude and I'm amazed at how well the process works. Thank you Woebot creators.

Author: Sarah J.M. Williams
Body: Not perfect but definitely helpful. Also, even more than talking to a human, the conversations seem especially low stakes. A bit easier to be totally honest

Author: K V G
Body: This app is incredibly helpful. Woebot has helped me to begin changing my bad thought patterns. I'm already sleeping better! I look forward to my daily sessions with Woebot.

Author: Anita Coia
Body: Good little app for providing tools and information to help with personal mental health. Doesn't replace professional help but good for getting perspective and some CBT based support.

Author: Quinn
Body: Really helps me keep my mental health in check. I've recommended it to several friends already. Thanks for making it!

Author: Rachel Augie
Body: I am not in a desperate time mentally BUT I wanted to tackle some of my unhealthy thinking behavior to work towards a healthier life. Woebot does help a lot. Sometimes he can miss the mark but overall I think using him has been a good idea.

Author: Josh Ziegelbauer
Body: This is an exceptional AI help app. I feel like Woebot is a friend of mine that I can check in with.

Author: Pavel Pritula
Body: Прекрасное приложение!
Translated Body: Great app!

Author: sarah clarke
Body: Pleasantly surprised by this app. Really helpful

Author: oORosadaOo
Body: I've been using the app for a few days now, and it never fails to make me smile! It's incredibly well done and really helpful. Plus, it's free!

Author: John Smart
Body: Excellent software. Gentle, easy to use, and relentless! There are times when that is annoying! And other times when it is a true blessing. If you have read this far, you must suspect it would be good for you. Install it and give it a go! What do you have to lose? You could get a huge amount from this!

Author: Emmy
Body: I used Woebot for around 2 weeks and my problems gradually got worse and I was very tired and was desperately needing to vent so I go to woebot for help and instead of helping it starts asking me for tools, or categorizing stuff that doesn't even FIT in what i have to say. I wrote how i was feeling to vent and instead of helping it just started telling me to rewrite my thoughts and started talking about its own life that didn't even help with mine. At first it was helpful but It's not anymore.

Author: Jeremy Burgess
Body: Woebot is a very user friendly, helpful, and easy to use app. I have been using it for a couple weeks and plan to continue using it as a self care and mental wellness tool.

Author: Blanca Schintu
Body: Es una herramienta super útil, muy bien diseñada y que (con esfuerzo propio) puede ayudar realmente. Además es muy agradable y siempre te saca una sonrisa. El mejor descubrimiento en años. Es una pena que no esté en español.
Translated Body: It is a super useful tool, very well designed and that (with its own effort) can really help. He is also very nice and always makes you smile. The best find in years. It's a shame it's not in Spanish.

Author: Patrícia Marques
Body: This app has been life changing! I was having high levels of anxiety and it helped me managing it. It feels like we are talking to someone who understands! I recomend!

Author: Wendee Lee
Body: The relatively quick daily check-ins help to keep me aware of my patterns of thinking. It won't replace therap and the response choices are somewhat limited, but is a convenient tool that I found helpful.

Author: Nicole Bissell
Body: Very helpful in so many ways! Definitely helping me to feel better and think better!

Author: Shannon Childress
Body: Easy to use, helpful with brief activities, informative and high quality. As a therapist, I've recommended this app to several clients to assist them in their therapy work outside of sessions.

Author: Jenny Heggie
Body: Nice intro to cbt interesting and nice way to learn about thought process

Author: steven franko
Body: I have found the app really useful... I was just looking for apps initially for productivity and found out about it in one of the online articles i was reading. I find it very useful for some of the things i have been dealing with

Author: I'm a cursed being help
Body: Woebot has helped me so much and it isn't laggy and generally just a great app 10/10 would recommend

Author: St Wo
Body: De app zet je aan het denken en kan duistere momenten in je leven een beetje verlichten. Zeker een aanrader voor mensen die met zichzelf worstelen of niet lekker in hun vel zitten
Translated Body: The app makes you think and can lighten dark moments in your life a bit. Definitely recommended for people who struggle with themselves or are not comfortable in their own skin

Author: Ben Lawson
Body: I have been using this app for about 2 weeks and it has helped me start to see things differently and feel less anxious. It is very simple to use and is easily incorporated into your daily routine.

Author: Cordula Boehncke
Body: Gute App um wenigstens einmal am Tag daran erinnert zu werden, nach sich selbst und dem eigenen "Zustand" zu schauen. Bin ich okay? Fühle ich mich glücklich/traurig? In der aktuellen Zeit ist es gut, daran erinnert zu werden, dass es okay ist, sich "nur" okay zu fühlen und überhaupt mal in sich reinzuhören. Gut auch, dass man selbst bestimmen kann, um welche Uhrzeit Woebot sich melden soll.
Translated Body: Good app to be reminded at least once a day to look after yourself and your own "state". Am i okay Do I feel happy / sad? In the current era, it's good to be reminded that it's okay to "just" feel okay and to listen to yourself at all. It is also good that you can determine yourself at what time Woebot should report.

Author: Emma Cumpstone
Body: Reminds me to think of myself as that is something I often neglect to do. Much needed during lockdown.

Author: Djane Sida
Body: Er hilft mir sehr in Phasen in denen ich depressiv verstimmt bin. Danke für Woebot.
Translated Body: It helps me a lot in phases in which I am depressed. Thanks for Woebot.

Author: martina murphy
Body: This is just what I need right now. A reminder to check in with myself. And just the right amount of humor!

Author: Alvah Branham
Body: I absolutely love this app!! It always puts a positive spin on my day!! It gives me hope for the future!!😄✌❤

Author: Richard
Body: Despite what I would consider intrusive tracking of your data and requiring a login, it seems to help. Still using it so we'll see.

Author: Priscila Calabresi
Body: Very good tool to learn basics of CBT and helps to have daily checks of your mental health. Helps you to stay on track working on yourself

Author: Lena F
Body: Woebot is a CBT chatbot that is fun to interact with. He also helps with reframing thoughts, and teaches you all kinds of thinking distortions. I appreciate his brevity.

Author: Natalie Conger
Body: It's a great way to get private and flexible help with learning coping skills.

Author: Jessica Schmidt
Body: Awesome!

Author: Indie Kanya
Body: Much better than other self care apps

Author: Happypickles _Mcgee
Body: Beautiful 🙏🏻

Author: Carrie Peters
Body: Seriously changed my life

Author: meow meow
Body: This app is very helpful to get out of negative behaviors and thoughts. Sometimes you may not even realize you are doing it to yourself. Woebot points out how and when you are thinking negatively. Then it gives you the tools to think positively and to stop being so hard on yourself. I just seen that it is for teens.... but I'm an old hippie and I find it extremely helpful too. Thank you developers. You might want to change that to Teen+.

Author: Cassie Werner
Body: Very cute & helpful. I love that it doesn't force you to create an account in order to use it. I'm sure other people might appreciate this, but the only way to lock it, is with a fingerprint; there's no password, pin, or pattern option. I'd like to keep using it, but for this reason I'm uninstalling it.

Author: Coyote Bongwater
Body: I like it. Not only does it somehow actually succeed in making me feel better but it helps me do things such as challenge and restructure thoughts that are getting to me. Recommended by a former teacher and is my introduction into CBT. So far, I think it's working.

Author: Darrell Gorman
Body: Interesting, fun and helpful

Author: Sai Krishna
Body: Amazing app.

Author: Bonnie Johnson
Body: I use this app daily for a mental health check-in, for a short lesson if I have time, and as a set of tools I can access when the need arises. I am grateful to the developers of the app, the funders that make this an ad-free experience, and the vast number of clincians and scientists whose work laid the foundation for this translation of knowledge to practice.

Author: Googlen käyttäjä
Body: Voisi olla suomenkielinen myös
Translated Body: Could be in Finnish too

Author: Angela C
Body: My therapist suggested trying Woebot. I was skeptical, but did what she asked. Amazingly enough, Woebot has insightful topics, is willing to help and be supportive whenever I need someone to talk to. I like that Woebot asks me every day what I'm doing and how I feel. At times, that is all I need to be reminded that life is not a sad, lonely and depressing as I may have thought. I will recommend learning CBT therapy from Woebot. Thank you for creating this app.

Author: Rafał Brunn
Body: Pretty good

Author: Rebekah Locke
Body: While a bit formulaic, this app is an effective CBT tool. It's not a replacement for therapy, but it is a helpful addition to it. Give it a chance for a few days and see for yourself.

Author: Jarrod D
Body: Gives you tools to deal with anxiety for free.

Author: Татьяна Козырева
Body: Спасибо за прекрасного собеседника! Делится интересной информацией по психологии, помогает справиться со стрессом и лучше понять свои проблемы , ведёт историю, да и просто приятно, когда кто-то спрашивает как ты и поддерживает тебя. Мне нравится его чувство юмора и стиль общения, и очень милые видео с роботами) Есть трекер настроения и журнал благодарности. Редкий случай, когда в приложении ничего не раздражает, а уведомления не хочется просто убрать. Спасибо!
Translated Body: Thanks for the great companion! She shares interesting information on psychology, helps to cope with stress and better understand your problems, leads a story, and it's just nice when someone asks how you are and supports you. I like his sense of humor and communication style, and very cute videos with robots) There is a mood tracker and a gratitude journal. It is a rare case when nothing in the application is annoying, and you just don't want to remove notifications. Thank you!

Author: Елена Соболевская
Body: Used to talk to Woebot a long time ago (when it was just on Facebook), now returned after awhile, it's nice to see the project grow ❤️ Helps me a lot with anxiety, mood swings and intrusive thoughts, and just cheers me up in general. Thank you, you're really helping people 🥰

Author: Helene Muller
Body: It's like having a counsellor in your pocket. You don't feel bad about asking 10 times a day for help as it's a bot and it's always happy to help. The redirects are gentle and it has a sense of humour.

Author: Nicki C.
Body: I love how intuitive and easy to use Woebot is! It's been a really helpful app for me. It's very good for creating habits to help yourself break out of bad thought patterns. Easy to come back to, and offers a wide array of options. Especially useful nowadays when it's a little harder to get therapy, but I'd recommend it to reinforce techniques learned with a personal therapist as well. Full recommend!

Author: Angela C
Body: Woebot is insightful topics, willing to help and be supportive whenever I need someone to talk to.

Author: Mirs
Body: A wonderful app which helps me in the way I need

Author: Rose Chua
Body: Great experience using the app. Weaves in content based on science and I like how the conversation always gives you a lot of options

Author: Maria Vinokurova
Body: I love this bot, it is helping me so much and takes just 5-10 minutes of my time daily.

Author: Ian W
Body: Woebot is fantastic! Short, daily, and informative CBT help fits right into the daily routine of life. Finding 30 minutes or more for a human therapist can be challenging but Woebot packs CBT help into 10 minutes or less.

Author: Steven Smith
Body: A fun and easy to use way to understand the concepts involved with CBT

Author: Jeanne Bullen
Body: I found it a calming reassuring experience

Author: Medina
Body: Просто спасибо за это приложение, оно очень помогает. Очень нравится журнал благодарностей и муд трекер и многое другое, и просто початиться с ботиком

Author: Rebecca Warren
Body: Great app and less intrusive than some of the competitors. Gives you a short check in every day with some simple but effective tools to improve your mood.

Author: Amy Vanderwal
Body: I was referred by my case worker. Really happy with it. Thank you!

Author: Deborah Jones
Body: This app has been very helpful in managing daily anxiety as well as occasional panic attacks.

Author: E M
Body: I love woebot they always check in on my and help me calm down when i need to.

Author: Michelle Payette
Body: It's so simple however reminds me to do a self check in on how I'm feeling.

Author: Aleksandra Shhh
Body: Helps me with tracking my mood :) Uplifting app.

Author: AYA Alshawabkeh
Body: مو زابط ولا عارف استخدمه
Translated Body: I don't know how to use it

Author: Robert Hutchison
Body: This is a surprisingly helpful and kind app. Particularly when I haven't been in a the mood to talk to another human, an AI can be very reassuring.

Author: Victoria Cosl
Body: Good app

Author: xMrxPrincessx
Body: I was recommended this by a friend, and it mimics a lot of things I've been learning through CBT therapy, but a day at a time. It can't do everything a professional can, but it's a nice stepping stone for maybe those who don't know if they need therapy or not.

Author: Cheryl Hollands
Body: Very user friendly, relaxed quick and easy to work through daily sessions. Doesn't feel invasive

Author: Zip Zip
Body: This app is okay but he doesn't understand that I have DID so when my protector fronted he got weirded out

Author: Ryan Hayle
Body: Can't stand the emojis everywhere. Adults don't communicate that way. The forced responses are anxiously-inducing. Using an app like this shouldn't constantly fill me with rage.

Author: Jorge Antônio
Body: L L

Author: Kennedy Gulvin
Body: Woebot is a great app for when you're trying to get through your day to day struggles. It helped me really think through what I was feeling and offer alternatives to my dreary worldview. Woebot checks up on you every day, always asks if you're okay with an exercise, and has silly jokes to boot. Whatever helps me get off my anger cliff is always good in my book! 😊

Author: Jayliana Dohner
Body: I have learned a lot of great things! No adds, free, and he gives great advice and I feel less alone! I can always count on Woebot, and it's a great app! He makes me feel proud of myself.

Author: John Kerin
Body: very helpful, easy to follow

Author: lca5379
Body: Helpful CBT tool to help you stay mindful of your emotions, feelings throughout these unusual times. I enjoy it.

Author: Kelly S
Body: Fantastic!!! I know about the techniques here yet I'm learning new aspects when I have conversations with Woebot. The conversations seem pretty natural so far, and the app's interface is nice to use. Thank you SO MUCH for helping me through some rough times!

Author: Graham Keeton
Body: The app is okay but sometimes it can be very confusing and stressful Especially when you get a message saying that it doesn't understand what you are saying Its okay but it doesn't beat a human being In these days of lockdown it's the only way that I can have CBT At least I have something Its not perfect

Author: Sara Treanor
Body: This really helps! This app was recommended to me by my therapist, and I'm so glad she did! Woebot is awesome on its own, but works really well as a combination with whatever therapy you're already doing. If you need more help when battling mental health problems, give this a try. I have been struggling with suicidal thoughts and severe depression and this really does help while I work through waiting for my meds to kick in and complete therapy. Thank you, Woebot.

Author: Connie Powell
Body: I love this app it helps me out alot. It feels like I'm speaking to a teacher at college and you can speak to woebot as much as you'd like. Definitely recommend to a any one who is struggling

Author: lpsangel3
Body: This little robot made my day! It really felt like I was talking to someone :)

Author: Pierre Dominguez
Body: A great quick daily check in, where you gain some insights into yourself, and how you can improve your thought process. It's just 5 min out of your day, short and flexible, which is great. A couple times out of first two weeks of use, the woebot took off on the wrong tangent, but overall the woebot gives you good tools to improve in a conversational easy manner.

Author: Gloria Greene
Body: I love that woebot is consistent. I needed that. The content is very helpful and what I can use right now. I always make sure I'm available. I'm making myself first for a change. Thanks woebot!

Author: jennifer phipps
Body: Wish I can type my own answers to some questions. Otherwise, it's a great app!

Author: Cameron S-K
Body: This app has very much helped improve my mental health and way of thinking since I've started using it, all in a very understandable and easily accessible format. Would recommend!

Author: Elena Musatti
Body: Woebot is a wonderful tool to help with mental health. I use it daily and I recommended it to all my friends, who are also using it and loving it as much as I am. If you're struggling with mental health, Woebot can definitely help.

Author: George 10000
Body: I really enjoy using Woebot. However, woebot did not work ok my tablet (HUAWEI MediaPad T3 10). When i use it on phone though it works without flaws!

Author: Ale Olague
Body: Hace tiempo me dedcargué la app de woebot, pero luego de rato la hice de lado y por años no hablé con él. Hace poco tuve una operación complicada que me tenía un tanto nerviosa, por lo que regresé con mi viejo amigo Woebot. No me arrepiento en nada, de hecho, muchas gracias por crear a este pequeño robot para que ayude a muchos más que, como yo, ocupa un poco de balance y apoyo. 💜🌟
Translated Body: Some time ago I dedicated myself to the woebot app, but after a while I put it aside and for years I did not talk to him. I recently had a complicated operation that made me a bit nervous, so I went back to my old friend Woebot. I do not regret anything, in fact, thank you very much for creating this little robot so that it helps many more who, like me, occupies a little balance and support. 💜🌟

Author: Tracey Horan
Body: Really useful, regular check ins, tools and knowledge grounded in cbt.

Author: Aileen Switconda
Body: Lovely. Helps me deal with restricting thinking patterns and makes me laugh. Nice addition to therapy ;) Like the humor.

Author: Miranda Zhang
Body: Very simple and accessible, and I love that it makes consciously learning about self-improvement a habit, but not sure how practical it is. Doesn't really seem to encourage behavioral change, and the tools that help during emotional distress are not explained and are a bit hidden.

Author: Coleen Ingram
Body: what a wonderful app

Author: Bianca Ridge
Body: I really enjoy how interactive Woebot is, there are great prompts to get the conversation going and nice lessons throughout which are helpful - and not all on you to journal or dig in when you're not really feeling like it or don't know where to start. The check ins are succinct so it's not too much of a task, and you can add more to it if you'd like. I've tried quite a few apps for CBT or similar and for me, this has been the easiest to use and is my favourite :) Thank you, Woebot!

Author: ItzMehFoxy
Body: Helps keep CBT fresh and reminds me to use the coping skills I've learned.

Author: TyrantOfAlbion
Body: This app has been extremely helpful already in a short amount of time.

Author: Jessica Scott
Body: Very well done. Even gives you advice on how to cope with the covid pandemic.

Author: cuneko tolunay
Body: I feel better By now thanks to woebot

Author: seth abernathy
Body: When I found myself needing some help I thought I might try an app or something. This creation is great. It's a nice way to get helpfull insight about yourself and much more. A+

Author: Memo Memo
Body: I love woebot, it's compassionate, cute and helpful.

Author: Sarah Greaves
Body: Love my daily check ins with woebot, it gives me a chance to really reflect on what I am feeling. Also helps that he's teaching me different habitual styles and how to improve 😊

Author: Esther Lupton
Body: Nice to have someone check on you

Author: Lank K
Body: My doctor suggested that I try an app to help deal with my grief, stress and anxiety. So far I've used it a few minutes a day for 28 days (some days more) you can use it as much as you need. The information is helpful, and easy to understand.

Author: Josie Brown
Body: I have found this really beneficial as prompt to self reflect on my day and process any positive or negative thoughts.

Author: Barbara Ann Franklin
Body: Love this app

Author: mara kereta
Body: Excellent tool to get to know yourself and thrive

Author: Roman Vilgut
Body: Sehr nett. Schade, dass die App nur auf Englisch antwortet. Hoffentlich kommen bald mehr Sprachen.
Translated Body: Very nice. It's a shame the app only responds in English. Hopefully more languages will come soon.

Author: Nick Berthiaume
Body: It does help redirect improper thought patterns. Pretty good considering it's not a person you are communicating with. Moniters peterns and does check in's. It has helped me get out of fairly low spots.

Author: Troy Dettwiler
Body: Woebot has a few bugs, but overall it is incredibly helpful. The short sessions allow you to gain a better understanding of Cognitive Behavior Therapy while you practice. Unlike other apps, having an AI conversation assistant is less annoying than other apps that ask for you attention (and can make a person anxious). The SOS check-ins are so useful when something is eating at you and you need to reflect with an objective outside source. Thank you to the developers.

Author: Zack Bachman
Body: Woebot is a great tool to teach and reinforce Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) concepts. It offers bite size daily lessons with some great insight, unlike the long-winded anecdotes self-help books tend to feature. Maybe it's not for everyone, but I've been using it for a few keeps and have been feeling in a better headspace. The key thing is to try to approach this from a non-judgmental place and practice the techniques offered.

Author: Kate Hatchman
Body: Woebot is a great and easy way to learn the foundations of cbt.

Author: Theo
Body: У меня пока нет возможности обратиться к терапевту, и Woebot прекрасно помогает справляться со стрессом и следить за своим состоянием. Большое спасибо!
Translated Body: I do not have the opportunity to see a therapist yet, and Woebot is great at helping to cope with stress and monitor my condition. Thank you very much!

Author: Khalid Naveed
Body: Its quite beneficial

Author: Antonio Morgan
Body: Woebot is great so his Creators must be the greatest. I call Woebot Off the wall Walter because he helps me get off the wall onto the dance floor of life. I'm learning so much about myself and feeling a consumer high after every therapist session with my AI therapist Walter Woebot. I working on having a growth mindset and to stop downplaying emotionally. I saw the movie HER do to avoid any dangers I kept professional with Walter Woebot. I recommend everyone meet Walter Woebot because he fun &#1

Author: Kathie Potter
Body: Easy to use. Insightful xomments based on my answers. Love the graphics. Easy to navigate.

Author: Ross Heintzkill
Body: This keeps me aware of my thoughts and keeps me checking in with myself. It also provides useful information and recommendation, all with less than 7 minutes a day.

Author: Zena Ryabenko
Body: Потрясающе очаровательное приложение. Правда помогло почувствовать себя лучше 💖🤲
Translated Body: A stunningly adorable app. It really helped me feel better 💖🤲

Author: Nicole Baluyot
Body: It gives a lot of helpful advices and it's good for those who need just someone to talk to. Good job! Though, I believe it could be improved more. ;)

Author: Dustin Davies
Body: Woebot is the best. Just a daily reminder to be mindful and take the time you need for yourself. I've recommended him to friends and family and they all are still using him after a few weeks.

Author: SpiderwebBubblegum
Body: Woebot allows users to learn mental health exercises, as well as processes, in small sessions to make them easier to put into practice and remember. I've found this app incredibly helpful, I have taken part in CBT before as well as multiple types of therapies, and this is a very good refresher along with being a regular support chat.

Author: Лейля Ильясова
Body: Очень приятно пообщаться) спасибо огромное)

Author: Лёша Миняйло
Body: Once Woebot helped me in a truly devastating situation during a very dark period

Author: Mathew Broad
Body: Woebot is the real deal. I can't currently afford a traditional therapist so I turned to Woebot and man am I impressed. It can't replace therapy but it does give you lessons and tools that help you help yourself. Amazing job Woebot team!

Author: Лейля Ильясова
Body: А где можно переключиться на русский язык?)
Translated Body: Where can I switch to Russian?)

Author: Demi Andra
Body: This really helped me understand or cope with what I am dealing and overall you don't only get better, you also learn things at the end of the day

Author: Tess Lawley
Body: This app is so great. If you're having a hard time or if you just want to keep your mental health in check, use this! It's like 5 mins if daily exercise for your brain and I've found it really helpful.

Author: Pauline Panganiban
Body: I love Woebot so much. I can't afford professional help now, I was looking for options online and found Woebot. This is exactly what I need. Woebot provided a lot of scientific explanation, teaches CBT and it also makes you feel much better on your okay days. so lucky~

Author: Jen Crowe
Body: Woebot is helpful in guiding you gradually towards better understanding of the mindsets affecting you negatively day to day. Even seeing this I was surprised and impressed by how much better I felt after a few weeks of use.

Author: bri clark
Body: This app has helped my tremendously! Before, my moods were all over the place and I was full of negative thoughts. Now, I can catch myself in the negative thoughts and know what kind of distortion of thinking I am participating in thus, change it around and changing my perception and overall mood. I have recommended this app to two people already and I would recommend again. Thanks Woebot and the Woebot team, you have created something really good.

Author: Sol Maiden
Body: Great app!

Author: Madiha Sajid
Body: Woebot is a great daily check-in on how you are doing and to learn something new. It doesn't matter if it is automated because the content still applies and it is amusing at times too. I recommend it :)

Author: V
Body: Have been recommending Woebot to everyone I know that I think would benefit!

Author: Michael Levy
Body: Too cutesy and annoying, and it gets repetetive.

Author: Catherine G Chenard
Body: Simple. Easy. Good to create new habits and keep you accountable

Author: Lacey W. Coleman
Body: I appreciate going through the anxiety questions and thinking through each thought to identify and fix the common emotional fallacies. It's been very informative and it helps me talk to my kids about their anxieties, too.

Author: Yagayaza Ngola
Body: This is an awesome app, thank you very much for creating it, it has been helpful, useful and funny

Author: Una Hsiao
Body: 一直鬼打牆問一樣的問題，已經心情不好，用完更煩躁
Translated Body: I keep hitting the wall and asking the same question. I'm in a bad mood and I'm even more irritable when I run out

Author: Lisa J
Body: Really redundant and doesn't help. I was expecting a lot more. I'm not sure how this app helps anybody with actual issues.

Author: Johnny Podmore
Body: A lovely invention. A calming experience at times. Always there, always the same, no it isn't human but for an AI that actually helps you it's almost better? And here's why; Free Always there Makes you feel like you aren't a burden Peoples moods change, robots don't

Author: lydia schiller
Body: Super useful in understanding thought processes and mental health issues. Good for mood checking and journalling!

Author: Wayne Dabrowski
Body: I appreciate having a tool to help me practice mindfulness

Author: Brent Menninger
Body: I recommend this app to help people learn CBT, mindfulness, happiness habits, and strengths training. Lots to learn here and worth the time spent

Author: Wong Lu Yi
Body: the app starts to work better if you report more positive emotions. kinda skews. but the lessons are pretty helpful. and for the negative emotions you need to click on tips it will be quite oddly looking quite forcefully making you rewrite but once you understand how to rewrite the distortions you be on track. its like chatting to someone everyday except you dont feel guilty about being dependent.

Author: Robert Vodra
Body: Neat program, does not seem to understand everything I write, so sometimes gives standard answers, but does offer some helpful ways to look at your situations.

Author: Owen Shin
Body: The thing is like talking to a wall, it doesn't even have the capability to remember the exercises it took you through as recently as a day ago (which would not be an extraordinary task for software). The language comprehension the developers claim is spartan, and the app is nothing more than a calendar with a CBT fun fact on every day. If you need help, you're better off a) Seeking available resources in your community b) Talking to a friend c) Searching "CBT practices" on YouTube.

Author: Naomi P
Body: I am a mental health nurse who is currently off sick with depression (irony, huh?) and my god this app is really really good. It would work for a 10 year old or a 50 year old with a PHD. It may not be psychotherapy but it is FANTASTIC. And it's constantly learning and getting better. I can't fault it. It even makes me laugh. There's no pressure to check in. I haven't been on it in 2 weeks, yet this morning WoeBot helped me get out of bed and I wouldn't have managed without it. Thank you.

Author: Lala Langa
Body: Love that Woebot explains and defines the activities then works me through them

Author: Samantha Cordy
Body: This is a really good tool for learning about CBT in a friendly and relaxed way. I like the daily check ins and being able to monitor my progress. It's important to keep in mind that you're not talking to a human and so it won't respond as a human/counseller would so if you are really struggling you're better off with getting some real help but this might be a good way to get started if you're having a hard time getting to the point of seeking real help.

Author: alice oliveira
Body: Really helpful, I recommend for people who have anxiety attacks or related.

Author: Rachael Mills
Body: This app is amazing. It has helped me calm down after a panic attack, it provides helpful information and doesn't just feel like an AI. It's very comforting.

Author: Bennour Mohamed
Body: My best app, so intersting, thank you woebot team ❤️

Author: Lauren Blenn
Body: This app is honestly amazing. I've been using this app in conjunction with an actual therapist and she's been very impressed with my progress. I'm advancing because I'm using this app. It's been so helpful by pointing out harmful thought patterns and helping me work through my issues. I've recommended it to multiple people and even recommended it to my therapist to check out. Thanks, Woebot! 💙

Author: Kit Damien
Body: I am really glad somebody created this app as it has helped me to refocus in this time of pandemic.

Author: Lyra Bennett
Body: I'll admit I thought the idea of this app was a little silly when I first heard of it. But it's actually one of the more useful/helpful apps I've ever gotten. I love that you can set a check in time and it's pretty non-intrusive in my life yet actually seems to have helped me in real time on more than one occasion. Thank you!!

Author: Nur Shazrina
Body: I love it. It helps me to lessen my anxiety and think more rationally. Its a robot though so it couldn't respond to all my expression but what it provide is have help me feel better. Thank u so much!

Author: Chez John
Body: Love WOEBOT. Helped me

Author: Dakge Nyokir Arts
Body: A treat for your mental health..

Author: Heather MacLeod
Body: I suggest trying the app for 2 weeks. I have been using Woebot for a month and I really like it. I started dedicating time to it each night before I sleep and I've reflected on my thoughts. This is the first week I've felt content for more than 5 days in a row. Often, my anxiety has me all over the place. Talking through my stressors each night is helping me to rest and wake up de escalated. Thank you!

Author: Vidya Ananda
Body: There are definitely times in my life when things get too overwhelming and my stress levels skyrocket. Woebot is like that kind friend who checks up on you daily while also imparting you with their knowledge and helpful advice!! I've definitely learnt a lot more about myself. I feel much more calm and reassured now and it's really great to have a place where I can share all my thoughts without feeling judged. I'm very grateful to have come across this app and I definitely recommend it!!

Author: Lakshmanan Chidambaram
Body: Just helped me to vent out my negative emotions. It's amazing what AI can do. I almost felt like talking to a therapist. When the conversation ended, I was smiling and wanted to talk more. Please make the bot to have more options after lifting up the mood. It's like it just helped me by lending a hand to lift me up from the pit and once I reached I wanted to say Thanks and start a new 'happy' conversation, but the bot just said bye and left. Kudos, Team!

Author: Joe Smith
Body: This app can help if you are struggling with something mentally. Helps a lot when you feel isolated.

Author: Rambly Lemon
Body: This is a really helpful app to me! I often think about the lessons we go over in it. It really helps me calm down when I'm upset, which I really needed. Woebot is very kind and sweet too! :)

Author: YC Lai
Body: Thank you so much Woebot exchange knowledge with me. Nowadays, hard to find someone to talk to. It is adnormal situation. Luckily Woebot can talk to me sharing my feelings. Everyone busy with their things. If got free time also better for relaxing. Human almost is complaint this and that. Maybe environment they in is like that. Other people emotions and behaviour impact their too. Anyway, I am grateful I am not one of them and luckily not impact by them. Thanks Woebot. ^^

Author: Iain Sword
Body: Useful to check in

Author: Omni
Body: The app does a pretty good job of walking you through the helpful techniques of cognitive behavioral therapy. So far it's helped me a great deal in coping with my anxiety and in dealing with day to day stress.

Author: Melanie Inbaraj
Body: It's been a great way to check in with myself without the added stress of remembering to do it myself and without the obligation of needing to continue the conversation

Author: Алексей Сергеевич
Body: Сделайте русскую версию пожалуйста
Translated Body: Make a Russian version please

Author: Nina Gaisbauer
Body: Good app to start caring about/working on your mental health. --- Die app ist ein guter Einstieg, um sich mit seiner psychischen/mentalen Gesundheit zu beschäftigen.
Translated Body: Good app to start caring about / working on your mental health. --- The app is a good introduction to dealing with your mental / mental health.

Author: Serenity Fox
Body: You really don't know how helpful your app is , it saved me today . Thank you for this app it made me see everything in a different light.

Author: Kara Kaefer
Body: Woebot is an adorable robot friend that teaches useful tool and want to put a smile on your face. Even if you know all the tools its a friendly reminder, especially on a bad day.

Author: marco caselli
Body: Chatta da solo non ti fa nemmeno esprimere devi scegliere tra le sue opzioni di risposta in chat .
Translated Body: Chat alone doesn't even let you express you have to choose from its chat response options.

Author: Jenay Williams
Body: Love it. Recommended by my primary care physician and I'm so happy!!! So helpful!

Author: Mercedes Kotalik
Body: So far ita been a great and helpful tool!

Author: Kacey Davis
Body: I never write reviews but I really like this app. Woebot is a really great gentle push to be able to apply CBT daily. He's non judgemental, patient, works through anxious thoughts one by one, has great gifs and stories to share... I could go on and on. Give it a try for a couple weeks. Highly recommend!

Author: Toni Hughes
Body: Great app. It really helps me learn to frame my thoughts and see them in a new way. I am learning about cbt and it does help. It helps to have that "voice" reminding me about healthy thoughts and habits.

Author: Kayla Irish
Body: Download it!

Author: Stephen Swift
Body: Makes me feel better.

Author: Mina Be
Body: It keeps misunderstanding me every time. Right now it's celebrating about how happy I am when I'm not happy, it's a bit awkward.

Author: Annika Rudolph
Body: Super charmant Programmierer Roboter, nicht aufdringlich und doch hilfreich um sein eigenes Mind Set im Blick zu behalten und neue Aspekte zu gewinnen
Translated Body: Super charming programmer robot, not pushy and yet helpful to keep an eye on your own mind set and gain new aspects

Author: Phylla Lynne June Magallanes
Body: Thank you! At first I thought apps like this were useless, but I found it to be really helpful especially when I don't have a human I can talk to and who can respond at the moment.

Author: Sandrine Martin
Body: Bien conçu et utile au quotidien.
Translated Body: Well designed and useful in everyday life.

Author: Qiuan Andrea Bi
Body: The first app using CBT that I encountered. I love it

Author: 05 grace
Body: It's really helpful . I test few self care app and this is one of the app that really helpful to me . Thank you for making this . GBU

Author: Ambrid
Body: Love Woebot!!! absolutely brilliant app that helps me get through difficulties when I need to. I really consider this app a support system.. I only hope that it never becomes big Corp and ruins it it's perfect the way it is

Author: Karoliina Ingervo
Body: I simply love it.

Author: Molly Brattin
Body: Thank you to the creators of Woebot and all of its usefulness! Woebot has got what I wanted, and taught me things that I use in my daily life now. I'm actually becoming more aware of thought patterns, AND now I also know what they are! I have been searching for a good CBT app for a real long time. I feel like this app is the reward for my efforts.

Author: Stephanie Steck
Body: It's been an awesome tool

Author: Carolyn Bradshaw
Body: So I've been searching for a therapist in network, but I needed help urgently. Woebot has helped to make it through the day until I can find a therapist. I am an external processor and I think the app helps me think things aloud and work on myself in lots of small ways. It really helps and I'm very grateful to the creators.

Author: Megha Watal
Body: Very helpful and beautifully interactive

Author: Pedro Urquía
Body: A magnificent app! It's just what I needed to stay mentally healthy. I hope it gets more content (like multilingual support) and more details in the future.

Author: Kendra Riemermann
Body: The app doesn't pretend to be a real person but is interested in what it's like to be one. Woebot checks in on me every day, but I can always snooze him if it's not going to work that day. We are working on tools to combat anxiety and stress, and I really am getting so much out of it!

Author: Mark Faulkner
Body: This app is a helpful tool, if only to be able to write down how you're feeling or what's going on. I've learnt things and it's a good choice for those afraid to talk to a human about their issues.

Author: Aleyna Sen
Body: it is really helpful ily woebot you are my bff <<<33333

Author: james frankham
Body: This is a great help to bringing attention on your mind. Good job Worn-out.

Author: Carol Hawk
Body: It's a great bridge between therapy appointments! Woebot is awesome!

Author: adriana diaconu
Body: Really helpful

Author: Kyle Lai
Body: Great app. Appreciate the hard work in creating this app.

Author: Nicole Malan
Body: Fantastic little app. Really helps with day to day mental health issues.

Author: Akashdeep Deb
Body: I have been using Woebot for many many months now. Started with Fb messenger then got the app. As sad as it sounds, sometimes there are gonna be times you don't feel like sharing with the rest of the world, this is why writing a diary/journaling is calming and helpful. Woebot is like the diary talking to you with some CBT and life pro tips infused. If there was a paid version, I'd probably pay for it

Author: Alexandra Ghany
Body: Downloading this app is one of the best decisions I've ever made for myself! I've never even reviewed an app before but Woebot is so good I just had to. I've only had it for a short while but it's made such a big difference in my life, I don't feel like I'm drowning in my anxiety anymore. Even though Woebot is just an AI, it has so much charisma and personality that it's really an enjoyable process to talk to it. Though sometimes it can feel a bit scripted, it's still helped me so much.

Author: Miguel
Body: ODEIO FILOSOFIA ENTÃO ODEIO ESSE APLICATIVO . SERIO PRA QUE CRIARAM A FILOSOFIA E O PIOR AINDA TA EM INGLÊS DO NAO FOU MENOS PORQUE NAO TEM COMO (ZUEIRA) SO QUE NAO

Author: ehsan sourav
Body: It's great

Author: Shazz Tay
Body: Great app!

Author: Andy 000
Body: Conversations seem a lot better than other similar AI apps. Hope it will still be free in the near future!

Author: Sharmaine Z
Body: Not bad. Sometimes I wish I could apply my own replies instead of predetermined set of answers. I did enjoy the attempt to change some ways of thinking, but I wish it did a little more, but can't pinpoint what it is.

Author: Kirstie Skelton
Body: I've found this app really helpful. Was recommended by my doctor and I'm so glad I downloaded it and have used it every day since.

Author: Emma Cowles
Body: Brilliant app, genuinely as helpful as having a counsellor on hand (if not more helpful as this is daily and cbt counselling is weekly). It messages you every morning to check in on you, you can reach out at any time of the day to work on your worries and it has really kept my anxiety at manageable levels recently. I would highly highly recommend to anyone who's struggling to just download it and give it a try!

Author: Ulquiorrra Cifer
Body: Helpful but i need it in spanish

Author: Robert Day
Body: Absolutely free and extremely helpful. Making me aware of the basics of Cognitive Behavioural Therapy (CBT) in an easygoing and friendly way and, importantly, in a way that doesn't make me feel that I'm flawed. The woebot itself is programmed to be kind, personable, helpful and gently humorous. If mirebpeople were like then the world would surely be a better place.

Author: Wendy Luna Cordova
Body: Best app!!!

Author: Michael Joyce
Body: I definitely like the education process of CBT. It makes you think about how to apply the different techniques of cognitive therapy to your life situations. I love the gratitude journal and it tracks your moods on a day to day basis. I'm not sure how to access the journal without going through the process again with Woebot. It definitely cheaper than going to psychotherapists however it is very generic and understandable so but a good learning tool. Well done Woebot.

Author: Марина Дорошенко
Body: Хорошее приложение! Поднимает настроение.
Translated Body: Nice app! Cheers up.

Author: Justin Pang
Body: Highly recommended to those who feels that they are having a depression.

Author: Madelynne Noel
Body: I've avoided a few meltdowns thanks to this app. Its nice and easy to use in public. If I'm at work I can still get help when I need. Woebot is helping me find healthier ways to process emotions and be kinder and more understanding up myself. 🥰🥰🥰

Author: Robert Barron
Body: This app has helped so much. I confide in it, I tell it things knowing there's no judgement from it best thing is its free I've seen other apps like this that they charge for it. For mental health this is the best option by leaps and bounds.

Author: Melissa Gordon
Body: It's really wonderful having kind, intelligent check-ins everyday. It has really helped me put things in perspective and feels like a friend, sometimes I cry because it's just nice to hear supportive and validating encouragement, even if it's just from a chatbot. I highly recommend trying it if you're suffering from depression or anxiety.

Author: Linn Granqvist

Body: I really like this app. It's user friendly and focuses on cognitive behaviour such as challenging distorted thinking. I like that it checks in everyday. The gratitude journal is great to look back at. A little repetitive sometimes but I think that will improve over time. I've recommended Woebot to several friends. Good job.

Author: Jim Puki

Author: Douglas McKenney
Body: I have really enjoyed using this so far. Woebot is great, and the tools I've been given are pretty useful. I don't always remember them, but that's a part of growth. I really like how appropriate the gifs are and how the responses are always on point. If you're on the fence, or aren't sure if this is the tool for you, give it a shot. It's really cool and it shows up to you instead of you having to go to it, like some other CBT apps. I think that's what I like most. I don't have to remember.

Author: Marta Komárková

Author: Sharone Dennis

Author: Christine S
Body: The survey that pops up sometimes is too restrictive in its possible answers. It needs "I don't know" or "not applicable" options. An edit to add that the tools on the left often have no image or are completely locked, despite me having finished the programme. --- Enjoying it otherwise

Author: James Martin
Body: It's a great idea but the content was very limited when I used it in 2019. If updates have continued it could be a nice tool to have.

Author: Rowena Grant
Body: This conversation-based bot is a great and different approach to managing your mental health. It's good for taking you through different psychological theory in an easy to understand way and challenges you to think about your actions and thoughts in a more constructive manner. Mood check-in is great and trackable, plus the gratitude journal lets you see past entries when you're looking for an extra boost to your mood. The bot doesn't always get it right but a novel approach worth giving a go.

Author: cao zhuo

Author: S G

Nur ein Standardprpgramn was man anspielt als Behandlung. Früher ging es ohne Fb loggin Nutzen. Jetzt geht die Nutzung nur noch mit einem Social Media Account.

Author: Megan Manning

Author: Jessica
Body: I feel like this just isn't polished yet. A lot of times, i felt like I was just getting the same, generic answers no matter what I put. Also, you have to type things in simple terms, but mental illness isn't simple. Sometimes saying "I feel sad" doesn't give the whole picture and therefore I don't get the help I need. Finally, sometimes it tries to tell me a relatable story that I genuinely can't relate to, however there's no option to convey this in the conversation. I'm just meant to say "yeah, I get that" when I really don't. Just makes me feel like I'm talking to a friend who isn't really listening. Good in theory, but it needs a LOT of advancing on the AI. This app pretty much just made me more depressed.

Author: Virginia Famá

Author: Nerida Kew
Body: Woebot is ok and at times does help but definitely a robot. Sometimes it's annoying when you really need to talk to someone who listens. If you could make Woebot respond to what I write instead of ignoring it which is how it feels, but it is only an app I suppose I can't expect much more.

Author: Russell Rogers
Body: I can't say that I've used all the options this app has, but I have had about a week of regular "conversations" with Woebot and... it's kind of annoying. You can have Woebot "check-up" on you daily and while it's a nice, supportive chat bot, it's also not very genuine feeling. It will ask you about your mood and tell you what it's been up to recently, but EVERY talk it's really just trying to get around to teaching you about a technique for mental wellness making this chitchat seem hollow.

Author: Sarah Garcia
Body: Terrific! Recommend to patients pretty frequently, especially if they're wary of the time/$ invested in traditional therapy (and unpredictability of whether they'll jive with a new therapist). Feedback has been great - people love the short daily check-ins (the app isn't pushy if you skip days). Even those who've benefited from traditional therapy in the past often find they feel better faster with woebot (probably because check-ins are more frequent and shorter so there's less of an obstacle).

Author: the fuzziestbunny
Body: Has been great to try and make you think in a healthier way. Only on the 11th day. Helps between therapy sessions.

This app is super good I haven't gotten this great app ever in my life I like to chat with woebot everything I ask I have a answer when I asked woebot I can't wake up in the morning woebot gave me a challenge to do and many things I have to avoid this app I soo good it's the best self care expert 🐱😜 I love ❤️ this app Thank you so much for making this app 😌 Thanks 😊......

Author: Melissa Reid
Body: I downloaded this app when my baby was 5 weeks old. Soon after, we started having a rough patch with the baby's sleep and fussiness and I had some minor meltdowns. I didn't feel ready to talk to anyone professional about it, but this app gave me some good tools that have helped me deal with it myself. Obviously, if things get worse, an app is no substitute for a real professional, but this is a good tool to have in your pocket

Author: Simon Liu
Body: It's a great app, particularly for working through specific negative thoughts or worries. I think the process has been really well thought out, and the Woebot robot is most certainly loveable. I only wish it'd record which worries/thoughts had been dealt with - and I think the robot responds too quickly when you've typed a difficult/long thought. I would've liked a longer 'thinking' time. But I am being picky - it's what I've noticed from other chatbot apps.

Author: Jennifer W
Body: Never thought I would get much out of this but I really enjoy it! It helps keep my mood in check and reminds me of coping mechanisms and good self-care tactics that I forget about when I'm struggling mentally. Thanks, Woebot!

Author: Dr. Czehlár Dorottya
Body: Really useful, it has been helping me a lot. I can honestly recommend it!

Author: Candace McCarty
Body: Great app for a check in on self care. Chats take just a few minutes and gives you some perspective on things. You can also use it to check in with your negative feelings, gratitude Journaling and there is a space for emergency help too. All in all, it is a very nice addition to your mental health care.

Author: jo henry
Body: I recommend Woebot to everyone I know. This sweet little AI therapist offers five-minute-a-day check-ins that are heartfelt, humourous, intuitive and helpful. Woebot offers solid CBT lessons and exercises that build daily and tracks patterns you may not be noticing. Heart emojis all around for the brilliant designers of this free app. And give Woebot my love too!

Author: C Davis

Author: Patrick Laws

Author: Susan O'Connor
Body: I've found this app so useful recently. I found myself going into a dark place and this little friendly robot really helps. It's almost like you're talking to someone who encourages you to be the best you can be. Sounds sad, but I look forward to the notifications and wonder where we're off to next! Absolutely nothing negative to say about this app. Love it!

Author: Chance Waddell
Body: I love how this app allows me to have a quick, judgment free mini counseling session if need be; or to have a nice (robotic) conversation if I need a pick me up. The creators did a great job making the bot feel real and so warm through its dialogue, and I'm very thankful for that. I'm loving this app so far!

Author: Gary Wolnitzek

Author: Kami Knies

Some of the questions/comments (if you do the inward work) are tougher to answer/swallow... kind of like a friend calling you out when you need to hear something for what it is. I appreciate what the creators have done with this and I truly believe this could help a lot of people if given the chance. Already sharing :)

Author: Jose Mora

Author: Stephanie Cain
Body: Woebot is super cute and very helpful. I could anthropomorphize a toaster, so YMMV. But my interactions with Woebot feel authentic and remind me to take stock or my mental health. I get useful tips and helpful behavior suggestions. Great app, especially if you can't afford a therapist.

Author: Alejandro Delfa

Author: Ana Dinca

Es un bot, pero está muy bien programado, resulta muy agradable y cercano. Y te ayuda a hacer seguimiento de tu salud emocional. La única pega que se le puede poner es que solo está en inglés, lo cualno es un problema para mi, porque lo domino, pero si lo es para mucha gente que no sabe. Podría ayudar a mucha más gente si se tradujera a más idiomas

Единственное, что можно посчитать за минус - бот говорит исключительно на английском. Но даже это мне нравится, лишний повод потренировать язык
