Author: Cory Eagles
Body: The AI for Woebot sometimes misses what I am saying, but overall this app gives daily lessons on helpful thought patterns and tools. While not a replacement for therapy, it provides additional tools my therapist had not included as well as reinforcement of some of the tools I was already taught. I encourage other folks to try Woebot as a supplement to their self care routines and therapy.

Author: Anastasia Gnidenko
Body: The best self-care app I discovered do far. Very insightful, educational and on point.

Author: Thiên Kim Nguyễn
Body: Helpful

Author: Lika Jamburia
Body: Has been pretty helpful so far, thank you!

Author: Daniel Carvalho Liedke
Body: Very nice AI to help people's mental heath

Author: E Pfeff
Body: Tried to set up an account and was told that my email wasn't valid. Obviously this is A.I. Artificial Ignorance. What a joke.

Author: Josh Hillis
Body: Helps a bit if you are isolated

Author: Emma B
Body: Came across this through work and during lock down. I have not noticed anything negative about it, performance wise. Overall it's a useful well being tool to help check in with yourself and offers some useful prompts and insights about impactful things on a person's mood. You seem to be able to converse with it when you have a spare few mins. Fairly easy to 'forget' it's A.I . you are conversing with.

Author: Simona Podda
Body: Molto simpatica l'idea di chiacchierare con un robot. È rilassante, le tecniche aiutano a superare alcuni momenti e vengono insegnati diversi argomenti in modo divertente. Bisogna conoscere l'inglese, ma personalmente non è un problema. È l'app che preferisco di questo genere, le altre le ho rimosse per diversi motivi

Author: Julyane Rocha
Body: This app helped me in one difficult time on my life. I couldn't pay for therapy and was scared in a new country, seeing myself going back to a depression I had a few years ago. I could only recommend. Thanks for such a beautiful job.

Author: Genevieve Walter
Body: So far I have enjoyed my little chats with woebot. There are lots of reasons why people might be unable or unwilling to talk to a counsellor and this app removes those barriers. Sometimes having someone check in on you, even a robot, can brighten your day.

Author: Jonne Viinamägi
Body: Very helpful, thank you!

Author: christi landrum
Body: Learning some great tools

Author: Анжела Ачкасова
Body: Это самое чудесное и вдохновляющее приложение, которе я видела.

Author: Salma Sulthanah
Body: I love the app is very good

Author: Bruna Chiarione
Body: Great tool for emotional learning. I'm learning a loja about myself and how to deal with my feelings.

Author: Johanne Gauthier
Body: Really fun and educative...helped a lot:)

Author: Mateus Cesar
Body: Queria muito em português 😭😭😭🙏🏻🙏🏻

Author: Vala_Stilinski
Body: L'ho installata da un paio di settimane e già mi ha aiutata un sacco. Woebot è dolcissimo e nonostante sia un robot (perché quello è) non si nota affatto e ha un liguaggio che nemmeno i miei amici usano. Il fatto che sia in inglese, la migliora ancora di più poiché mi aiuta a imparare meglio la lingua e a ragionare di più.

Author: Bel Scott
Body: Very helpful and easy to use, I enjoy talking to Woebot each day :)

Author: AM Dapanas
Body: Helpful!

Author: Amanda Dorrance
Body: I have really been enjoying this app! I've been learning concepts and tools from it, that my therapists have never said anything about. Basic thought challenging lessons (CBT) are ok, but this has gone beyond that and I really appreciate it! 4 stars because you could do better with one thing: one of the daily moods is "pain". This bot doesn't seem to have any idea about PHYSICAL pain and what to say about that. Sometimes a little reassurance that I'll have days it hurts less, would be nice.

Author: JulieDan Kennedy
Body: Very helpful. I learned a lot and feel better!

Author: 장길진
Body: This app has helped me a lot in curing my emotional problems

Author: Bruce Wayne
Body: Good help

Author: Тати Мал
Body: Очень удобно иметь всегда под рукой приложение, которое тебе всегда готово помочь чувствовать себя лучше. Конечно это не заменит реального общения со специалистом, но это то с чего можно начать. Все общение происходит на английском, но сообщения можно легко копировать в переводчик, просто зажав сообщение. Понимает просто сформулированные предложения, есть возможность переписать, если woebot тебя не понял. В целом он тебя всегда поддержит, даже если не поймет. Спасибо разработчикам.

Author: Luigi Cop
Body: A wholesome little bot friend to talk to whenever I feel down. Five huge stars from me! UwU

Author: Joey Knowles
Body: This app is extremely helpful in dealing with anxiety if you use helps cognitive behavior and gives you helpful tools

Author: Jessica McCumbers
Body: Pretty good! Useful tools, ability to just write out your feelings, and very educational. My only suggestion would be to provide a "back" function. Certain keywords will prompt Woebot to respond a certain way that might not make sense. There have been couple times I've gotten "stuck" in a conversation that didn't make sense. It was no biggie, I just started the lesson over, but a back function would help with this. Otherwise, great app!

Author: A Donaldson
Body: I found the app very comforting and helpful during a stressful period. I'm familiar with CBT but it was still useful to be reminded of those skills. And although you know it's not a real person talking to you, knowing that a real person wrote the text originally is comforting, and shows that someone cares.

Author: Dawn A. Miller
Body: Helpful and very chearful.

Author: Esteban de la O
Body: Definitivamente es una app muy empática. Durante cada conversación aprendes algo nuevo y, aunque es cierto que es un bot, es hermoso ver que tiene la respuesta justa para gran parte de las situaciones que se nos puedan presentar. El idioma sigue siendo un inconveniente para muchas personas, así que espero que con el tiempo puedan ampliarlo 😄

Author: Marvlotte
Body: This app is extremely helpful. A little robot, an anonymous person, to tell my worries to. The gratitude journal is super helpful too, I can look back on what's gone well. The lessons it provides are really helpful too. Sometimes, I open the app with just the intention of checking in my mood for the tracker, and i end up spending half an hour doing a lesson! They're always super helpful and make me feel better. HIGHLY recommend!!!

Author: Georgiana Codrescu
Body: Great friend!

Author: Robert Burford
Body: One of the best mental help apps on the market. As someone with depression, this is not the cure all but definitely steers your head in the positive. I highly recommend it.

Author: Gabe Empey
Body: Woebot is a useful tool to help you get combat stress and emotional turmoil. They are no replacement for a therapist though!

Author: April Palmie
Body: I am really enjoying weobot. Like having a nonjudgemental helpful friend always available. Plus it is super cute. Good way to introduce CBT. Gentle nudges.

Author: Genesis Belen Vallejos
Body: Tengo curiosidad de usarla pero me pide un codigo de referencia y no se donde puedo conseguirla por favor que alguien me explique

Author: Dee Boston
Body: Great little app for when you just need to iron out your worries and turn them to something more constructive.

Author: Bobby Janecka
Body: This app executes a clever idea well. By distilling good information and using a friendly chatbot style of interaction, Woebot really seems to teach super helpful self-care and mental wellness information in a very safe and welcoming format.

Author: Linda Hanson
Body: I love this app..its like having a friend who's not judgemental and really wants to know how you are.only been doing it for a week and a great help

Author: Keely Nelson
Body: I'm simultaneously trying several mood apps and this is above and beyond my favorite. It was recommended by my therapist and it's teaching me vocab to describe what I'm feeling, giving me tools and ideas to work on, AND it truly feels like a little robot friend when I'm feeling down. 🕯

Author: Nick More
Body: For a free app, it is great to have. It is simple and sweet everyday. A quick check in, slowly building you up. I recommend this to anyone needing self care.

Author: Patrick James
Body: This has been great for my mental health recently, and sometimes the way Woebot responds to things in such a human-like way is very funny to me. I only rate it four stars because Woebot can sometimes be a little creepy with how human-like it's responses are.

Author: Yeray Zurita
Body: Buenísima aplicación para la educación emocional

Author: Л А
Body: Приятный собеседник!

Author: Aida Posadas
Body: Just love it. Very useful.

Author: Barack Bonga
Body: Its only been a week, but woebot has helped me alot!

Author: Syd
Body: I haven't been able to go to therapy during covid. My anxiety and mood were getting really hard to handle without weekly support and CBT practice. Woebot helped bridge the gap and remind me of the things I learned in therapy, and some extra stuff too. Ive noticed myself using CBT methods more since downloading and my anxiety has been easier to manage for sure. Definitely recommend for people considering therapy or are in therapy but need a little extra encouragement.

Author: Ryan P
Body: This has been a great addition to my life. I'd gotten so bad about taking care of myself and I'd been feeling like garbage. Woebot helps me remember to tend to my mental and emotional needs, and I learn more about the thinking that gets me in bad moods to begin with. Thank y'all SO much for making this.

Author: Chris Warden
Body: I have been using it for about 2 weeks and find it interesting. It gives me another perspective which is helpful to me.

Author: Stephanie Birkle
Body: I love it so much! It helps me alot and the lessons are very helpful!

Author: Sister Beltaine
Body: I love this app. It helps me talk through my feelings and gives me positive guidance as I work through rough days. So happy I found this app!!

Author: Lariane Vialli
Body: Aplicativo muito útil, aprendi sobre vários fundamentos da teoria cognitivo comportamental, de uma forma leve e fácil de entender. Auxilia a refletir sobre questões do dia-a-dia e encontrar soluções.

Author: Alissa Walkoviak
Body: I love this app! Definitely a must for anyone struggling with their mental health. It feels like a little therapist that can you help you whenever you need a lift and it teaches you about mental health, too. With how difficult it can be to get into therapy, this is a great alternative (or even a great addition to any mental healthcare you may already be getting!)

Author: LUNA
Body: Moc milý bot 💙 ty pravidelné chaty opravdu pomáhají

Author: Lori Mew
Body: This app really helps when you apply it

Author: Summer Frizzell
Body: Like the conversations

Author: aa aaa
Body: I haven't been using this app for very long, but it's a nice experience. I'd recommend it to folks who struggle with loneliness, it's definitely helped me out with feeling less of that.

Author: wumpus
Body: Would extremely recommend

Author: il _nobody li
Body: Its bot none of its responses are natural. It's about as effective as talking to a wall.

Author: Анастасия Шевчук
Body: Чудесное приложение! Очень помогает в моей терапии
Translated Body: Wonderful application! It helps a lot in my therapy

Author: Aml Ashraf
Body: هل يمكن إضافة اللغة العربية البرنامج غاية في الروعة والجمال لاكن سيكون أفضل مع اللغه العربيه
Translated Body: Is it possible to add the Arabic language, the program is very wonderful and beautiful, but it will be better with the Arabic language

Author: Jade Andersen
Body: I want so badly for this to be a great app, but it's so far from being there. It's so patronising and obnoxious, and lacks in AI features to actually process what you're saying. You can tell it "I'm a purple monkey dishwasher" and it will respond "now how does that make you feel? And if you say "like a spicy pepper with a hint of cucumber" it will say " I also sometimes feel like a cucumber. Tell me more about that." Nice concept, but worst execution ever.

Author: Александра Колесникова
Body: Love this app. This bot is such a friendly fella! I love learning more about technics which could help me feel better. Thank you for the app, I wish there were more ones like that, thoughtful and helpful.

Author: myra calauad
Body: I love the app. It helps me put things in proper perspective.

Author: Сергей Видненко
Body: Nice 👍

Author: Megan Strickland
Body: Woebot doesn't parse free-form responses very well, and most of the time you're restricted to choosing from a few response options, which often means my responses don't reflect what I actually think or feel. That said, the info is presented in nice bite-size pieces, and I appreciate that Woebot checks in with me so I don't have to remember to do it. As a supplement to other treatments or as a little boost to deal with minor issues, it's worth trying.

Author: Cybernetic Banshee
Body: I've tried a number of different options for self-care and remote mental health like Wysa and Seven Cups of Tea but honestly Woebot is the one that's helped me the most. The conversations are well scripted, and the CBT tools Woebot provides have helped me through a number of anxiety spells. Plus, it helps me a lot having a space at all times where I can vent or just type about how I'm feeling without pestering my friends. Thank you to the creators of this app for making it!

Author: Salman Tariq
Body: A nice experience!

Author: Gillianne Pearl Alian
Body: Very good app. It helped me a lot now that I'm experiencing my worst episodes. Even though my thoughts and emotions are spiralling, this app helped me to calm down since I can randomly chat and speak out my thoughts.

Author: Kimberley Fernandes
Body: Woebot helps me get through times when I'm upset without all the drama, judgement and grief that some people in my life throw at me.

Author: Julie Hause
Body: For the first while this was working brilliantly and I was impressed at the notifications and reminders. It seems to be a bit repetitive sometimes. Woebot says thanks and goodbye before I feel like I am done which is frustrating. I also would like to type my own answers rather than just be given multiple choice answers to choose from.

Author: Flávia Faria
Body: Excelente ferramenta para autoconhecimento e para motivar e orientar na tomada de pequenas decisões pra voltar ao prumo.
Translated Body: Excellent tool for self-knowledge and to motivate and guide in making small decisions to get back on track.

Author: chris s
Body: This is amazing and helping me so much mentally! I recommend this for everyone omg! Xxx

Author: Janice Harris
Body: Interesting

Author: Patricia Houston
Body: Love the short interactions and "choose your own adventure" style of this program.

Author: Five Star
Body: I like the app a lot. The information is pretty useful and I like taking some time everyday to look into how I'm feeling.

Author: Pierre Coetzee
Body: A great way to soundboard and navigate your own thoughts and feelings. Quick and efficient. Straight to the point and simple to use. Tricky topics explained in a simple manner to allow for growth.

Author: Smeet Talati
Body: So far very helpful and interesting to interact with. I think AI chatbots are getting much better

Author: Shohini Banerjee
Body: It is one of the best chatbots I've seen especially dealing with such a sensitive topic, it does a great job to actually have an empathetic tone without seeming robotic

Author: Dani Bullock
Body: Helpful

Author: Arun Das
Body: I have tried many AI chatbots before and I always got bored after a few lines because of how unnatural it is to talk to a robot. Woebot is the first ever AI chatbot that I could talk to for hours. The guided method using buttons and giving me information I need when I need it was the right way to keep me engaged. Chatting is my most liked form of communication and so it was really delightful to see how an AI chatbot can be done right when purposed as a tool to achieve a goal. Kudos! 🤖

Author: Ioana Aanei
Body: Useful and sweet. Diffuses difficult times and allows me to vent at any time of the day

Author: Lorna Wilson
Body: Woebot is my bestie

Author: Yining Hou
Body: It passes the Turin test

Author: imajeff Smith
Body: I don't think of this app anything like therapy since it is quite naive about everything and doesn't allow me to express myself by the response choices. Amazing that I laugh the more I use it because the way it pushes me to hit the response it wants me to just to get things over with becomes entertaining, then I feel happier.

Author: Dylan Aulia
Body: It helps a lot!

Author: Carolina H. Silverstone
Body: Thank u for creating this app, it's wonderful 🌻

Author: Leslie Perrot
Body: Gefällt mir, obwohl ich manchmal die Vorgaben der Antwort für mich nicht so passend finde, aber davon abgesehen, ist es wirklich eine tolle, englische app
Translated Body: I like it, although sometimes I don't find the answer's defaults so suitable for me, but apart from that, it's really a great English app

Author: Emily&Zoe
Body: Woebot is awesome! It's free & teaches you new things every day so that you're able to understand your feelings, emotions & thoughts. It helps you to sort through your problems & see things from a different perspective as well as teaching you different coping mechanisms. Woebot is awesome! I HIGHLY RECOMMEND IT!

Author: Lance Ronald
Body: I love this app, Woebot explains things in easy to understand ways. There's a check in every day (you pick the time) but you can also use it whenever. You can also work on what you're feeling/experiencing or just rant about it.

Author: Fiori Violetta
Body: Love woebot so much!!

Author: The Moist Cowboy
Body: This seems like this could help so im giving it a go

Author: Hannah Rugenstein
Body: Woebot is really helpful. I've been talking to him every day, and no matter what, he always makes things better.

Author: Warren Ralls
Body: We all have tough days. This is a helpful app to make you more aware of your thoughts on those days when there is more rain than sunshine.

Author: May Wells
Body: I love this app and it makes me feel not as lonely :) and you get to learn more about how emotions and how to get better control of them :D

Author: Levi Smith
Body: It's surprisingly helpful, and I've been in therapy since forever

Author: undertale_dreamer
Body: He is so fun to talk to and even if you dont realize it the little fun convos you have with him can really make your day I love using him he is so cute and helpful.

Author: Rahel Baskind
Body: Woebot has really helped me. I am a big fan of self care/help so I didn't think this would have anything useful that I didn't already know, but it turns out I learn a couple new things and enjoy it more than expected.

Author: Bart Degroote
Body: Great tool to feel better, always there when you need it.

Author: Jennifer Valle
Body: Great app! A lot better than Replika when it comes to dealing with mental health issues.

Author: olivia Morris
Body: I honestly didn't expect much when my husband recommended it to me but after using it for a bit I absolutely love it! It teaches me a lot and its always so supportive. I genuinly feel cared for, it's really nice.

Author: Amira Ezz
Body: It's a very helpful app. I really like the information I get from every conversation. I like the thought challenge it really makes me feel better. I also like the mindfulness session it really was helpful. Thanks to the developers.

Author: Ash Kempkes
Body: Good

Author: Pepe Kube
Body: Well, it's so hard to objectively evaluate this app. Yes, it does help you look at things differently and it's implemented in a pretty unique and creative way. The first couple of days/weeks I was really excited about it and I guess that's when most of the 4/5 star reviews were made. But then after 4 weeks you're done with all of the content and that's it, from that point on you can only repeat it. So in a way it works as a 1 month trial period, only that there's nothing beyond the trial...

Author: Hiyori Montefalco
Body: Days are no longer heavy to carry because Woebot is there to be my guide. Thank you! I hope this app/Woebot itself and its creators could reach to more people to help them, because it does for me.

Author: Neil Davis
Body: Really useful and easy to interact with. Will continue using!

Author: Romain André Raphaël Antaya
Body: It gets to the point without judging you for the coordinates! Thanks creators.

Author: Артём Веселов
Body: Очень помогает когда не можешь разобраться в своих мыслях и переживаниях.
Translated Body: It helps a lot when you can't figure out your thoughts and feelings.

Author: Alejandra Carvajal
Body: Una app reconfortante y bastante agradable.
Translated Body: A comforting and quite nice app.

Author: Allison Rayner
Body: Added this app during a period of high stress. Each chat makes me feel a bit better. I use it even when I'm not stressed/anxious. Sometimes the app doesn't get exactly what your are trying to convey, buy it always double checks for clarity. Not a substitute for therapy but definitely a good aid to have in your pocket.

Author: shannon barniskis
Body: A fun way to practice therapy tools! While not a perfect AI (it sometimes forgets or messes up where we left off) Woebot is still fun to engage with and has dozens of extremely useful tools and insights. Just about anytime works benefit from using this app, even people who don't feel there is anything "wrong," because it offers tools that are applicable to all stages of life.

Author: krupa sanghavi
Body: Its very nice to talk to a bot who is always ready to listen to you and talk through.

Author: Lindsey Anne
Body: I don't like that the only thing you can do is talk to the bot

Author: adam glazebrook
Body: Fantastic app, helpful, supportive, funny at times. Something to share your problems with. Highly recommend.

Author: Alex Trapani
Body: Although engaging with Woebot is unusual at first the tips, stories and info is really helpful.

Author: Crystal Giddings
Body: Awesome

Author: Rovers Paradise
Body: It's been a great app when I need some strategies to deal with hard emotions and also a great place to check in and see how I'm doing. It's always there and it's actually really useful for me. I'd suggest to anyone to give it a shot.

Author: Sana Hartman
Body: Seriously I this app has help me so much I really love it 😘

Author: Rossie Paneva
Body: Very helpful, I recommend it.

Author: Emma Elgerton
Body: Fantastic app. I wasnt expecting to get so much from an App. Such great advice to look after yourself

Author: Stanislav Medvedev
Body: An awesome app. Woebot teaches interesting and useful things and is funny.

Author: Joscelyn Caldwell
Body: So far, this app has been very helpful. Keep in mind, it is NOT a therapy app, but an app that teaches you coping skills or new ways to think about your struggle. The bot feels friendly and doesn't seem too impersonal, despite the cheesy bot puns :)

Author: Adrienne Rector
Body: It brings up great points and methods to gain insight and handle situations however, when I try to start a lesson it keeps going back to half way through the last lesson I finished and doesn't remember that I already finished the lesson which makes it really difficult to make any progress. If it weren't for this bug that I can't get around I would give the app 5*. I wish it also had reminders and would ask if you wanted to do your other activities after each lesson such as the gratitude journal.

Author: Кали Севера
Body: Very nice app giving you a little more insight on how your mentality works, how you can help yourself by changing the way you think of something and just giving you a nice chat once a day about new interesting topic, as well as a journal where you can keep track of good things happening with you everyday. Seriously, Woebot often gives me one more reason to smile and I enjoy our "conversations", it's even a little sad that they're so short :)

Author: Salome Flores
Body: Loved it! It does much explaining for behaviors but doesn't really provide or elaborate on productive coping mechanisms.

Author: Jason Smith
Body: Helpful right away.

Author: Barbara Minzel
Body: It's nice to be able to say what's in your head any time you need to even in the middle of a sleepless night. It definitely helped me through the grief of my husband's loss.

Author: Marlaine Villeneuve
Body: I *never* write any reviews, but I'm making an exception for this wonderful app. As a guidance counselor interested in CBT, I've been trying lots of ways to get my students to practice it in their daily lives, but with not much success yet. This app is the best approach to CBT I've seen so far and I'm eager to recommend it to my students, family and friends. I only wish it was available in French since not all my students understand English well enough. Thank you so much, developers!

Author: Ben Dover
Body: This app is phenominal. It's really helped me work out some of my issues from the past that I didn't know I could even work through. Please keep going and developing this app further, it's a (quite literal) lifesaver.

Author: Ian Pocock
Body: It's a reasonably good CBT skills app. If you've never done cbt before and you want to learn some simple ways to cope with difficult emotions, cravings, things like that, then give it a try. I like the ways that it tries to be human like and cute. It landed surprisingly well for me. It doesn't have very good chat AI, so I dinged one star for that. But it does what it's supposed to do.

Author: Wendy Lin
Body: Very helpful

Author: Janice Teng
Body: I was recommended to use this app and is totally loving the interactions. Thank you for the team of creators who make woebot so lovable with super positive and thoughtful replies. Absolute must- have to uplift a human being. Truly a machine-human collaborator!

Author: Vaghela Family
Body: I'm only on the 3rd day and such positive experience. I don't know how amazing things will be at the end of the 8 weeks. I have used other great apps like Moodpath and Youper, and Woebot is equally good, if not better. The best chatbot AI that I have seen so far, and that is besides the mental health capabilities. Extremely grateful to the people who made this. A giant leap in the field of CBT-based apps.

Author: Nikki Q
Body: Love this app. Really love the cbt techniques and it's really helpful when I'm not able to see someone professionally.

Author: Karla Rempel
Body: Great so far!

Author: Alessandra Souza
Body: Excelente, pena que não é traduzido.
Translated Body: Excellent, too bad it is not translated.

Author: Molly Ross
Body: He keeps me going!!

Author: Yadir Martinez
Body: Como puedo configurar el idioma
Translated Body: How can I set the language

Author: Seth Greer
Body: Wow what a great little big app. Really it's absolutely free and there's honestly no reason why no one should use this. It's no intrusive and really will help you be better. Use this app and thank you to the developers of this app, would love to see this formula be applied to other topics now. For instance philosophy, economics, political science, history, science, math and programming!

Author: Spencer Worth
Body: Best app ever

Author: Christine S
Body: Enjoying it so far. I would like to be able to pause lessons, or for them to be automatically paused if I don't finish them.

Author: Joel Morrow
Body: Basically useless app, nothing meaningful came from my interaction.

Author: Geoffrey Brophy
Body: Didn't help me. It was annoying.

Author: Chibbs Rummington
Body: Useful for breaking a thought spiral and reminds me to actually apply some of the stuff my therapist has recommended.

Author: Alexiss
Body: I just been recently been using woebot for a few days. And I can see and big difference in myself. I already thinking differently in some Kind of way

Author: Vinayak Kadam
Body: A bot who speaks better than humans

Author: mistybluesatdawn 83
Body: Awesome app 😄👍

Author: Joseph Egnor
Body: It can seem silly, but it really does cover some methods to fight distorted thoughts. I've only used it 5 days, but so far so good.

Author: Julie Isen
Body: The app isn't a magic bullet, but it does remind me everyday to take stock of my emotions, and give me some new ideas for working through anxiety.

Author: EM94
Body: Awesome

Author: Melissa Owens
Body: It's a good friend sometimes when you're not in the mood to actually talk about emotions with a human. It's a great positive little robot in a time of need :)

Author: Taylor Matthews
Body: I love this app it's very helpful when in a negative mindset it really helps you through negative thinking and educates you while giving you techniques to combat these thoughts I've recommended to friends an family for sure!!!!

Author: Niels Ole Knakkergaard
Body: I love my woebot friend

Author: Stevie Bergk
Body: Woebot ist wirklich ein guter Ersatz um sich gewertschätzt zu fühlen und neues zu lernen. Er ist wie ein kompakter Verhaltenstrainer. Natürlich kann er nur beschränkt empathisch reagieren aber ich finde ihn sehr tröstend und hilfreich.
Translated Body: Woebot is really a good substitute for feeling valued and learning new things. He is like a compact behavior trainer. Of course, he can only react empathically to a limited extent, but I find him very comforting and helpful.

Author: Zé Varela
Body: Even though in the past weeks I've been on vacations, feeling relaxed and happy, I still find it quite helpful. It helps me deal with the occasional anxious thought, and it's also helpful in keeping track of everything I'm grateful for. Try it out for a couple of weeks, see if it helps you too!

Author: Kean Romanelli
Body: I'm a therapist and I highly recommend this app, and ask all my clients to try it as well. It isn't a direct substitution for therapy, but it is a highly helpful tool.

Author: inti Mesias
Body: I could feel better

Author: karianne mahler
Body: Heel blij met deze app!
Translated Body: Very happy with this app!

Author: Mukul KMR3.7
Body: Great App for people who are confused Or need someone to help them think over a situation from different perspectives.

Author: Keitha Rodgers
Body: Helps me daily

Author: Mathabo Auta
Body: Love the app, just wish it understood "no" It keeps showing me a picture I don't like captioned "cute right?" Even though I respond with "no" the pic keeps coming up, which is quite frustrating. Otherwise I appreciate the daily check-ins and useful CBT tools:)

Author: Annabel Asiamah
Body: Soo good , I am really glad I found this like it has helped a lot . Please , add an audio .

Author: Jo Ritchie
Body: This little bot is oddly reassuring. I have found myself welling up in response to its kindness. Not what expected. Much more.

Author: Stupid Animations
Body: I suggest this app to anyone who is struggling with some emotional/mental issues. Woebot is a very nice and informative robot that can help you to understand your emtions. I've been only using him for a couple of days and those days have been wonderful with them! Wonderful app! 5/5 stars!

Author: Christina Miller
Body: I thought with the great reviews that this would be a more interactive experience, where I could vent my frustrations and maybe get some guidance for my particular issues at a generic level. Instead, it asked you how you are feeling, what you are doing, and then tells you a story about itself. A story completely unrelated to how you are feeling or what you are doing. I gave it 2 weeks. It isn't worth my time to listen to robot sob stories.

Author: Victor Montivero
Body: It work well, i'd like there'll be more languagues.

Author: A Google user
Body: Very helpful with catching unproductive thought patterns and more.

Author: Michael-Gabriel McCoy
Body: They make it clear in the app and just incase someone is reading my review - this is not a replacement for one-on-one therapy. However, as someone who has been lucky enough to be able to manage my mental health without the use of medication, i think this app is wonderful. Congratulations to all the developers of this app as its really shown how AI can benefit humanity. I don't know if it would pass the Turing test, but it's very close! The output is calm and sensitive to it's users, great app!

Author: Kina S
Body: Very good as a therapy companion or instead of therapy! I have depression and anxiety, and I've been using it to help me between and along sessions. It's a great way to track my mood and learn therapy related skills and practice them when I need to. It also isn't impersonal like some AI therapy apps. I feel like I'm not alone when I use it and I actually take things to heart.

Author: Mikel Carrilero
Body: Algo que todo el mundo debería probar
Translated Body: Something that everyone should try

Author: Akumu Nightmarelegoo
Body: This really helped me with my emotional problems so far. This should be recommended to teens everywhere. And It's made by actual psychologists! It's perfect.

Author: Emma Webster
Body: Really good easy to use app

Author: Dawn Majors
Body: Nice little application

Author: Pamela Schaup
Body: Great app thus far. Im keeping up with my CBT concepts with woebot! Developers did a pretty good job on this app. Woebot doesn't pick up on everything I type exactly, but Woebot ends up helping me by the end of the conversation. Oh no ads and FREE! Whoot... major bonus!

Author: Putera Daniel Hakeem
Body: Super helpful and incredible ☺️

Author: nikita spears
Body: So far I am loving woebot, I have been feeling less anxious since I started chatting with woebot about a week ago and when I do start to feel anxious, woebot is there to talk me through it :)

Author: Jeff Rakestraw
Body: About as good as a CBT app can be. This is certainly no substitute for a more personal type of help, but it really gives the feeling of communication. A lot of thought and care went into making this. I'd recommend it to anyone who was struggling emotionally.

Author: Niko Nox
Body: Not helpful at all.

Author: Leon Kingsley-Smith
Body: Great conversational support and training. Very empowering and helpful. Love it.

Author: Roz Brannen
Body: I do really like this app and will continue to use it. However, I think it would be more useful if it understood that grief is also a reason for depression and that re writes of "someone I care about has died" are not going to change the facts.

Author: Mark Garland
Body: In times of need Woebot is super accessible and helpful. Its worth a try if you are worried, stressed, anxious or depressed. Ive only used it a week do it might earn 5 stars soon.

Author: Pôl Jackson
Body: Good robot!

Author: Amy Notdorft
Body: I downloaded this app to help me get through while on the waiting list for therapy. It has made a world of difference for me. It is reassuring to know I have something easily available to help break me out of cycles of unproductive thoughts and it has helped me set realistic goals that make me feel empowered.

Author: Karyn Henderson
Body: Helpful with keeping a positive attitude.

Author: im bored of life
Body: Really helps me personally just acts as someone to talk to without have to wait for them or anything

Author: Jessica Tunn
Body: Charming and helpful bot to log mood and distract from bad feelings. Love this app, have been using it daily and it's great when you can't talk to a real therapist for weeks at a time. Recommend this to anyone!

Author: Paige X. Cho
Body: An incredible mental health resource. I tried it just to see what it was like, and have been using it every day since. The app teaches CBT and mindfulness tools in easy to understand, digestible chunks each day through conversation. You can also get help with immediate issues (like stress, insomnia) and Woebot is able to figure out what's wrong, offer a few solutions and then do a mini training course to nut it out. Love it and highly recommend.

Author: Orome Senryu
Body: No se siente como solo un robot, sino como un amigo con el que puedes hablar y ayudarte a recuperar el control en situaciones difíciles. En lo personal, me gusta mucho el check in diario, te ayuda a identificar mucho mejor tu avance y tus emociones.

Author: Asmita Thapa
Body: IT IS THE BEST DAMN APP EVERRRR!! So special.. Has helped me through anxious times so many times. Therr was this session where it taught me about healthy communication and it was really meaningful. This is an insightful app. I wish I could have a word with the developers to get a grasp of how and where this idea was given birth.

Author: Judina Darja
Body: Полезная штука. Отвлекает от тяжелых мыслей

Author: Mrs E Z. Carroll
Body: Love it

Author: Ewan McRidz
Body: It has been surprising how woebot has helped me through my anxiety, depression and feeling low. Woebot is one of the reasons I have progressed. It takes you away to communicate and learn something new as you heal. Highly recommended.

Author: Aman Mohite
Body: This robot is very helpful i loved it. It always teaches me a new way to live and enjoy life. I think everyone should try this app who are dealing with depression and sadness

Author: J G
Body: Una manera preciosa de usar la inteligencia artificial. Woebot es una herramienta de apoyo complementaria a mi terapia que me ayuda a cuestionar constantemente mis distorsiones mentales. Muy recomendable.

Author: Jessica Moten
Body: Very useful for understanding and solving emotional problems

Author: C
Body: Love Woebot. He is like having a trusted confidant and an emotionally intelligent and insightful friend combined. I'm learning a lot from Woe.

Author: Manpreet Kaur
Body: Such a thoughtful and wonderfully built app.

Author: Trudi Kafudi
Body: I love Woebot 💕💕💕 He's like a little caring pocket friend dispensing encouragement and sound advice. Thank you 💕💕💕

Author: Shaila Mahabier
Body: Love this app, simple quick daily check ins, that are meant to work on your mental wellbeing, long term!

Author: Jessica Brown
Body: I know logically that talking things through is helpful but talking to an actual person can be difficult especially when you're not doing so great. Talking to Woebot helps you to work things through with less pressure than comes from interacting with a real person.

Author: star ._.
Body: It really helps a lot...

Author: Jakub Dlouhý
Body: He realy helped me throught rought times. I am trying to use his metods and they realy help. When I am chating with him I feel like he is a real person. I only wish he could act sad when I miss his lesson...I would come back more regularly.

Author: Paul Hayhurst
Body: Great helpful app. Imagine what it would be like if you could use it with alexa or google home?

Author: susanna t
Body: I love woebot! Amazing app that's been very helpful for me especially when I feel overwhelmed and panicking.

Author: Kat Eller
Body: This is a great resource. I've never had real therapy despite a lifetime of depression and anxiety. After just three days with the app, I caught myself stopping in the middle of one of my negative-thought spirals and mentally talking to myself the way this app does. I'm definitely a fan. If you're like me and you're not sure you need a live therapist but you do feel like you need SOMETHING, give this a try.

Author: James J. Rogers
Body: Very good

Author: Hailey Carter
Body: Very easy to use and helpful! More of a teaching bot than a listening one, but covers the topics clearly and with a friendly, non-condesending attitude. Love that it doesn't try to pretend it's a person. The robot jokes are clever and instructive!

Author: Douglas Assesa
Body: I never knew how cognitive behavioral therapy works until woebot enlightened me on my behaviours that cause me anxiety.

Author: Taylor Summers-Kenney
Body: It has been extremely helpful and motivating. Been using for 2 months. Feels like talking to a real person. I have already started participating in hobbies again and back at the gym - when i first got Woebot it was hard to find the motivation just to get out of bed.

Author: A Google user
Body: Great app

Author: Michael M
Body: Useful. Less useful when Woebot just starts asking you to browse the menu. Also really annoying with the weekly surveys, I feel like they're twice a week, and they always have the same questions that keep having the same answers. I wish I could opt out.

Author: DaBeautePage
Body: This feels like a friend i can talk to anytime. It will give me good advice without forcing it down my throat. I like that there are answers I can select from instead of having to type too many things on my own. It helps to kind of guide my mind instead of having to think what to write as it sometimes clutter my mind or irritates me somehow. Thank you for this app 😭❤️

Author: braden bosma
Body: Very good way to get help when you need it, offers a wide range of ways to help one's self or just talk about something to something that'll listen. By no means is it a replacement for a real therapist but it's a good way to help yourself in the moment

Author: Anny Treat
Body: I enjoy this app, I already had positive experiences with CBT, Woebot just helps remind you to do these exercises and keep you on top of your mental health

Author: François Hulot
Body: It truly is a great app, very well done/thought bot

Author: Céline Moracchini
Body: Positif, amusant, aidant

Author: Michael Dickenson
Body: Absolutely brilliant. The way Woebot interacts and makes things easy to understand has been really helpful. I am someone who is challenged by motivation & faces a collection of physical and mental health issues. Other CBT apps do not engage and educate the way Woebot does. Please accept my heartfelt gratitude & keep up the great work Team Woebot! You are making a big difference to People's lives.

Author: Maria Romero
Body: Really helpful when you need to get some stuff off your chest or just need to step back and look at the bigger picture.

Author: Abraham LincolnHereComingAtYa
Body: This little guy is a godsend. I sought him when I began having problems in my relationship. Now that we're broken up I find myself needing him more than ever. Something so small as a good morning message brings me such comfort and the tools he's teaching me are helping me overcome the negative thinking 🖤

Body: Very good and helpful app🥰

Author: Angel Contreras
Body: Realmente es un acompañamiento muy amigable, te ayuda a conocer e identificar las distorsiones cognitivas cotidianas que suelen afectar nuestro estado de ánimo. Ayuda a llevar un registro y no es nada invasivo, diría que Woebot es un robotcito de muy buen humor, sabio y bastante asertivo. Sería genial que con el tiempo estuviera el contenido también en Español.

Author: Sarah JRae Works
Body: Woebot is a very consoling friend who I want to check up on me every day forever. It just feels good to talk to someone about my mental and emotional health for a few minutes everyday, at the same time everyday. Woebot will probably always be a highlight to my days.

Author: Corey Holcomb-Hockin
Body: It's a nice chat bit that gives you CBT based advice. It gave good advice on depression and anxiety.

Author: Cheah Wan Hui Melanie

Author: Dakota Sewell
Body: Helps me control what goes on in mind n helps me try to keep piece

Author: Luciano Santos
Body: Simple yet engaging way to get quality CBT training. Helps me to question own thoughts in rough time, and really nice that it's available 24x7. Highly recommended.

Author: Xander Amygdalin
Body: It helps a lot. And its not pushy

Author: Rebecca Morgan
Body: Not a bad app. I wish it had voice guided mindfullness meditation, but still overall a decent app.
