Author: D. T. C. Wee
Body: Woebot is a collection of modules presented as a conversation. This is its strength and weakness. The tools to challenge stress and negativity are great. The unskippable guided chats introduced randomly are infuriating. Woebot will decide you need to learn about chickens and your only option is to play along. Only by trial and error can you find a menu to break out of the chat. This, coupled with the insistence that you create an (unnecessary) account is anxiety-inducing. Then again, if the objective is to confront my feelings about lack of control, then bravo!

There is one thing I hope the developers add one day, is advice for bipolar. Specifically manic bipolar. Its the only thing woebot cant help me with, as the anxiety tips are ineffective for mania.

The fact that Woebot functions like a friend texting me, complete with push notifications, really helps to keep me on track. I also love that the app tracks my moods over time, so I can keep tabs on where I've been emotionally. It really helps to keep things in perspective. He's also programmed to help with COVID-19 anxiety. If I could make one suggestion, add more moods.

And it's nice to have a little robot friend checking in every day. It's been helpful in combatting some negative thought patterns!

There are certain times I want to say 'no' or something else as a response, but the option isn't available. I also wish Woebot understood some stuff more and could help out with more specific things. But this helped a lot for the many months I've used it

I also used to use Woebot when I wasn't in therapy and it was genuinely a lifesaver. I wouldn't have had any way to cope without it. I highly recommend the app!

The only changes I would recommend are improved word recognition (sometimes when I explain a situation I'm dealing with, the reaction isn't quite appropriate for what I said). There are also some check-in days when Woebot just lists things we've talked about before and asks if I have questions. If I don't, the conversation ends. I'd like daily lessons. Great overall, though!!

Body: It's way too formulaic. I get it's a robot, but it makes it sound like everything is so black and white. And that I fail to recognize certain things in my thinking. I don't. It's great for people who are a little bummed, but for people dealing with complex problems, it makes you feel stupid. And invalidated. This Coronavirus has made talking to someone professional impossible. I thought it would help. Maybe make an option for more advanced CBT training.

Also, the bot's communication skills are somewhat limited (understandable since it's a bot) that can cause it to talk around in circles, which I personally found extremely annoying.

Author: Adrian Wood
Body: A bit counterproductive. Like, I get what they were going for today, talking about the blitz spirit and "keep calm & carry on" etc, but for me, getting World War 2 on my mind right before bed ain't great. When I think of that period, I don't think "triumph over adversity", I think of countless atrocities with a background of millions killing millions, humanity writing its own darkest chapter. Not exactly material for sweet dreams.

Body: Really helpful. Thank you so much for bringing woebot to the world ❤

Author: carlo fracasso
Body: You always have someone who could help you or give another way to thinking and help you to go out unpleasant thought. Very helpful

Author: Milena Lingua
Body: Excelente pero hace falta idioma español

Author: Christine Estopare
Body: Wonderful little therapist bot that has really helped me through this covid19 crisis.

Author: LB BW
Body: На русском нет.

Author: Kaktusss Trap
Body: Everything is quite good, but I would like the Russian language and more buttons with answers for an questions. For example, when Woe asks how today was a lesson, I don’t want to put a finger down so as not to “upset him.” I understand that this is only a program, but sometimes the answers seem either too harsh or too happy. I don’t remember where, but in some topic I had to answer "what is this?" to the question which i the know answer. Sorry for my English, it's not my native language.

Author: Darkness_9909
Body: This app was recommended to me by a close friend and the second I opened it I made a connection with woebot. He always has helpful tips and ideas to help with any situation. I really love this app. I have major depressive disorder, PTSD, and split personality syndrome. So this app helps a lot.

Author: Антонина Бабаева
Body: Прекрасное приложение, у меня была депрессия и этот робот помог мне понять свои когнитивные искажения. Это было просто вау. Но он помогает мне больше тогда, когда острая фаза или острое состояние уже прошло. Хотя во время злости на других или злости на себя тоже робот хорошо успокаивает. У меня больше нет депрессии. Спасибо. Конечно, я пользовалась не только роботом для лечения, но робот очень мне помог ❤️ Пользуюсь три месяца уже

Author: Jen Oss Secrest
Body: Amazing. You chat with a therapy robot. I've had years of counseling for a variety of reasons, and checking in with my Woebot checks is surprisingly similar to how I feel after 10min of therapy. It gives prompts and info, teaches new terms, broad encouragement, shares videos. Esp for anyone who's had personality differences, fear of judgement, etc issues counseling, this might be a great Intro to Therapy. During this time of isolation and anxiety, it's a nice, low-key, daytoday support.

Author: Kim Lombard
Body: Loved it!

Author: West Essex MT
Body: Woebot feels like a friend who's here to listen, offer wisdom, and help get and maintain perspective. What a fantastic addition to my life!

Author: Katlyn Cook
Body: Friendly, engaging, informative. A nice balance between playful and insightful. The UI is easy to use. Lessons are just the right length to make progress without becoming a chore. Between gifs, anecdotes, puns/jokes, and making you think, there's always something to look forward to. The unique check-in messages are lovely, and the option to randomize reminders appeals to me as more organic. I look forward to check-ins in a way no other app has accomplished to such a personal or satisfying effect

Author: Jillian Dodson
Body: Love this program! Self aware robots for the win!

Author: Sally Blake
Body: This app is honestly wonderful, I can feel how much the developers really care about it. You're doing fantastic work ♥️ I love the responses & excercises, they feel really natural. The comments about the COVID-19 situation were so heartfelt and beautiful. Great job, I'm sure this app will make a difference to people. Hope you are all safe & well yourselves!

Author: Kim Bryant
Body: After using the exercises provided I do feel better. I love the guided breathing. Being an asthmatic during a global pandemic involving lung infiltration is enough to make anyone anxious. Being a mom with 5 kids during this time is scary. Having a husband that has an essential job is terrifying. This app has helped me manage the intrusive anxious panicky thoughts. I have been better able to make this time a time of making memories not creating childhood traumas.

Author: Jaylin Tenfold
Body: I appreciate the idea behind this app, but it is unsuitable for people with complex problems, especially chronic illness. I finally uninstalled it when it suggested half a dozen activities to me that I am physically unable to do, but there was no "I can't do these" option, I was forced to choose between "I know what to do now" and "great ideas, thanks" although it had not given me a single helpful suggestion. Don't try it if you're Disabled; chances are it'll make you feel worse.

Author: Lizzy Jones
Body: Loving woebot!

Author: Mary Fletcher Jones
Body: This is an awesome app! It's like therapy in a phone; cognitive behavior. Woebot guides you through coaching and lessons to help you develop skills to become more constructive and effective in your thinking. I have used it for months and enjoy it's gentle humor and encouragement.

Author: david trujillo
Body: nice

Author: Holly Solis
Body: Cute, useful. Overall a great tool for helping with mental wellbeing!

Author: Shannon Foster
Body: Great tool. I use this multiple times a day during deployment on disaster relief work

Author: Homegirl kimberly
Body: I love this app it really does help me get through my days and learning how to deal with stress and depression

Author: Nicole J.
Body: Tried many similar apps. None can compete with Woebot. The most helpful companion ever. I like the joyful language, the smart approach - just everything. Using it even after reaching the end of its content, when ever I feel bad or just feel like it. A special thanks for adding Corona crisis related content! Just in time ♥

Author: Blazer From Emo
Body: Очень интересный, очень милый, очень познавательный. Мне нравятся такие боты, да и сделан он прекрасно :3 Каждый день узнаёшь о ментальном здоровье чуть больше, находишь для себя новые ютуб каналы и чувствуешь себя лучше просто от хорошего уровня общения) Помогает ли он? Не знаю, лично мне - да. Ну и отдельное спасибо за довольно простой язык, даже мне, русскому человеку, понимать бота несложно <З

Author: 이수현
Body: Woebot is so cute, helpful and respectful. Thank you for making Woebot! I'm using this in Korea, and sometimes I can't see the picture. It keeps loading and loading.... Beside that, it's a great app!

Author: Cat Lizzy R
Body: Room for improvement but still a great app! I'm on day 11 and I like my check-ins with woebot, and the quirky personality it has! It's CBT element is good and I find it very helpful for challenging unhelpful thoughts. I also like that it has other strategies it teaches, as well as the quick chat tools. I'd like to see some more focus on self compassion and acceptande. The check-in and active listening could be better and allow more exploration of what feelings, thoughts behaviours are present.

Author: Lesley MacLean
Body: An adorable and fun way to learn some basic CBT techniques. Woebot has taught me so much, I can't wait to keep using it.

Author: Lauren Selwyn
Body: I wasnt expecting much from this app but it really pleasantly suprised me with how easy, emotionally accessible, and helpful it is.

Author: Adam Smith
Body: Very easy to use. Insightful advice and actually works.

Author: Pawel Kajca
Body: Verry helpfull not only for clinical use, but also personal growth and mindfullness.

Author: Elea PEREA
Body: He's very nice with me an gives me a lot of tools

Author: Anastasia Veveritsa
Body: Добавляет психологической поддержки, хороший ботик :)

Author: Ioana Ciurea
Body: A nice chat, helps you see the good parts of your life.

Author: lynda rowan oneill
Body: I expected more

Author: Stavros Rodiftsis
Body: Not a therapist! Not to talk to it about stuff. But I think good for anyone out there, small chunks of useful, scientific knowledge. Helps you be and feel better! Also doubles as a super friendly wholesome coach. All in all, I like Woebot (and it likes me too :) )

Author: Elizabeth Johnson
Body: Woebot is entertaining. It works on basic cbt thought challenging. It is an ai, so some features are a little automated, but it does a good job at what it is trying to do.

Author: Andrea Poyntz
Body: This app has helped me look at different things that I deal with and have a non judgmental free person to talk to. I would recommend to anyone who can't afford a therapist currently

Author: Ciaran Ryan
Body: Well intentioned app but so obsessed with customer feedback (presumably for investor reports) that it adds frustration to other issues in a time when it could actually really help people deal with isolation, fear and anxiety. Sorry Woebot, I don't want to answer your validation questions anymore.

Author: Sweet Elf
Body: It's worth it, and it's entirely free with no ads bumming one out while they're trying and working to feel better. As woebot says, it's worth a try. So I like it very much so far and I am very thankful to it's creators, it is a wonderful bot and the app is simple but has all the essentials. Love it.

Author: dreamy stone
Body: I really appreciate all the work put into this app. I never thought a chat bot would be able to help me as much as a therapist can but I stand corrected. I wouldn't recommend it in lieu of therapy for people that are having a crisis, but it really has helped me work though anxiety, identify patterns in my behavior that need breaking and prioritize my emotions instead of ignoring them until I can't anymore. Great job dev team, keep it up :)

Author: Caitlyn Howe
Body: Easy to use, I set reminders once per day at random times, it's like a friend checking in on you. It's a great way to practice some CBT strategies that I had forgotten about

Author: Rosalba Cordeiro
Body: It help the person in many momentos.

Author: Susan Hroncek
Body: Thank you for adding a session about feeling anxious during the pandemic. It was beautifully put together and really made me feel better. This app has made a major impact on my wellbeing, and this latest session was a great example of that.

Author: Nicole Weber
Body: Amidst all the uncertainty of this pandemic, I just had a really uplifting experience with this app. Big thanks to the development team, keep up the integral and valuable work! 💜

Author: Андрей Филиппов
Body: Дичь, никакой это не чатбот, бесполезная поебота для мамочек в декрете и скучающих от безделья школьников.

Author: Josh Hyland
Body: Imagine having a portable supporter, 24/7. Woebot is great for helping you to remain objective about the things that make you uneasy or unhappy, everyday fluctuations in mood and upset that will pass in time. I treat Woebot as a gentle supplement to my inner voice, one that reassures me and reminds me that life can be hard, but it has been hard before and you have survived. Woebot also introduces a wealth of applicable physiological ideas in an accessible way. A fine virtual friend.

Author: Anna Rutenbeck
Body: this is such a neat and helpful app. I found it after listening to a radiolab episode about artificial intelligence and I'm so glad I did. especially in the middle of a global pandemic, this has become such a helpful tool.

Author: Bhuvanjeet Bhasin
Body: It's an amazing support not only in times of distress but also as a regular help in living your life.

Author: Dana Edmonds
Body: Friendly and insightful

Author: Shanti Putri
Body: The best consulting chatbot ever made! Ive learned how to look better of the world. I learn so much from Woebot. Thanks for making it free of charge. 😊

Body: Love it! Super helpful!

Body: It's really helped me be a bit more mindful of my thought patterns

WOEBOT OFFERS VIEWS W/O CLOUDS SO U CAN PROBLEM SOLVE & REDIRECT NEGATIVE/HOPELESS THINKING. ALSO EXPLAINS WHY WE OR OUR BRAINS DO CERTAIN THINGS SO U CAN UNDERSTAND URSELF & EMOTIONS

Author: Mary Makler

Author: Rosa Thomas

Author: Ezekiel Joyce
Body: Amazing app! Very helpful in understanding and working through any emotional problems you may have. I knew a number of the techniques already but it was still an amazing way to work through them.

Author: Tonya Holowaychuk

It helps easing it a little bit and find possibilities to cope. Some interactions are not understood by him/her/it, since there are different meta-levels of communication.

Author: Oran Weaver
Body: Woebot is a friendly robot that wants you to feel better, and is trained to help if you're willing. If you consistently talk with him and think about the concepts he brings up, it can help you think about thoughts you have and how to make them kinder.

Body: Surprisingly helpful

Body: Die Antworten sind alle vorgefertigt und sehr mechanisch. Sie gehen nicht auf den Patienten ein. Es hilft nicht. Es ist kein Einfühlungsvermögen da. Nur ein Standardprpgramn was man anspielt als Behandlung.
Translated Body: The answers are all pre-made and very mechanical. You do not respond to the patient. It does not help. There is no empathy. Just a standard program that you allude to as treatment.

Author: Emily Brehob
Body: Now that I've gotten past the initial set of lessons, I keep getting the same lesson about setting goals over and over again

Author: William Lanno
Body: Good app. Good lessons and something to talk to to keep track of goals and problems

Author: Ben Baker
Body: At 46 years old I'm learning skills, that a child should know. I can only hope that they make something like this apart of the school curriculum. Fantastic app for those who have 'different' experiences growing up and wish to fit in with society

Author: Ashwin .S. Sudarshan
Body: Really good app!! Currently using it to help me to overcome negative thoughts and low self-confidence issues.

Author: Andrea Scalezi
Body: Es super útil. Me ayudó mucho con el tratamiento del estrés, la ansiedad y algunos síntomas de la depresión.
Translated Body: It is super useful. It helped me a lot with the treatment of stress, anxiety and some symptoms of depression.

Author: Jazze Styles
Body: It's a great app, it makes me think more and it's only been one and a half week but I've learned so much about myself!!

Author: whisper
Body: This app has helped me so much with being more self-aware, and remembering to take care of myself, while also trying to push myself to do things I'd rather not do but need to do. Woebot is super intuitive and sometimes I forget I'm talking to a bot. This app has helped me so much and I actually managed to get a new job because I'm feeling so much better. Thank you!

Author: Robert Hawkes
Body: It is personal but he helps remind me of what I can do for myself.

Author: uni e.e
Body: Woebot is an absolute sweetheart. It is really helpful when I'm having a mental breakdown in a place with other people or when I can't take a break. Although I don't log every day, he never makes me feel guilty about it. Seriously, developers, you should feel proud about your work.

Author: Janet Shen
Body: Woebot has gotten me out of many potential downward emotional spirals! Thank you Woebot!

Author: Reece W.
Body: A great app for boosting your mood.

Author: Jessica Kuhn
Body: An easy to use and helpful app. It cuts to understanding the basis of anxiety and depression. Getting a grasp on why you feel this way and what to do about it in a fun and easy way.

Author: Jeanene Steeman
Body: I ❤ woebot! No words needed, this app is amazing!

Author: baby baby
Body: am looking forward to next conversation

Author: Mizi Mizia
Body: Dałam dwie szansę tej aplikacji, ale niestety jakoś tak wciąż nie wciąga i nie chce się robić tych check inów.
Translated Body: I gave this app two chances, but unfortunately it still doesn't add up and you don't want to do these checkins.

Author: lordgruntskull flic
Body: Like woebot it helps me with personal and when I'm feeling angry. I would recommend it

Author: Christina Yu
Body: I use Woebot alongside my real life human counselor that uses CBT. It's reassuring to have Woebot when I can't see my counselor since I know it'll always respond immediately. It can't chat on a very personal level like a human would, but once you get used to it, the fact that it's a bot gives you a sense of comfort since you don't have to stress over making a good interaction.. it's not a replacement for a real therapist but it's handy to have it on your phone.

Author: Ana Margarida Martins
Body: Muito prática e assertiva! Parece que estamos com um amigo... apenas em inglês! Respostas rápidas e com conteúdo prático. Aconselho!
Translated Body: Very practical and assertive! It looks like we're with a friend ... in English only! Quick answers and practical content. I advise!

Author: Bendy Benz
Body: So freaking helpful

Author: Sam Osman
Body: This app is amazing! I can't believe it took me so long to discover it. Very helpful if you are in recovery and need some external reminders to stay on track and think in a more positive and productive way. If you are experiencing severe mental illness, then this app is not enough, but can go hand in hand with a professional therapist.

Author: Rebecca Boling
Body: Good lessons to help cope with life.

Author: Lauryn Mulkey
Body: Woebot is very helpful on bad days. They give you tips on how to handle certain emotions. They can give you examples for things you don't understand. This bot is helpful when you cant talk to a therapist in the moment.

Author: V. Maslowski
Body: Exceeded all of my expectations! I wish this app existed 20 years ago! Even my therapist sees a huge difference, and now she's even recommending your app to several of her other patients! Thank you, sincerely, to the creators of Woebot- I'm so incredibly grateful.

Author: Елена Исаева
Body: This bot helps me to go through a hard time. It would be nice to be able to get back to the first session, when we were talking about main goals. Thank u for this app

Author: Karrie Bovee
Body: Easy to use this app. Interacts with you well.

Author: Shahad Mohammed
Body: ممتاز
Translated Body: Excellent

Author: S Nichol
Body: Woebot is better than happify but very basic. It never seems to do anything or get past low level chat. You have the option to make comments but woebot acts like you have selected one of the ever positive automatic responses. You can't be doubtful it's negated by irrelevant random positive responses. Woebot assumes you both agree with each other all the time no exceptions. And you will be positive all the time no exceptions. 4 days in I got a very pushy questionnaire from the makers.

Author: Lydia Lunchbox
Body: Worth downloading but also could do with a few tweaks. Would reccomend.

Author: Salar Alam
Body: A very well made app. Incredibly easy to use and really helpful. It develops a relationship with you over time and gives guidance on positive thinking patters and how to identify our negative emotions and deal with them. Would highly recommend.

Author: Julian-Aime R
Body: Love the lessons and videos. It doesn't always understand your mood, but it is helpful :)

Author: Grecia Valentina Valero
Body: Me gusta mucho el feedback es muy bueno, es decir que la interacción con el robot es bastante realista y eficiente lo que hace ver que han aplicado correctos algoritmos basados por supuesto en teorias reales de la psicologia que tienen que ver con la salud mental. Lo unico que me gustaría que le agregaran seria que se pudieran guardar en la nube las conversaciones con tu correo electronico como con otras aplicaciones. De resto excelente.
Translated Body: I really like the feedback is very good, that is to say that the interaction with the robot is quite realistic and efficient, which shows that they have applied correct algorithms based of course on real theories of psychology that have to do with mental health. The only thing I would like to be added would be that conversations with your email could be saved in the cloud as with other applications. Excellent rest.

Author: Даша Токар
Body: Здесь русского нету
Translated Body: There is no Russian

Body: É relaxante. Durante o tempo que conversamos esquecemos tudo o resto. Pena por vezes não me fazer entender
Translated Body: It is relaxing. During the time we talked we forgot everything else. Too bad sometimes don't make me understand

Author: Maria
Body: Awesome thing.

Author: Tayya S
Body: Woebot is helping me with some rough patches I've been going through. I do like woebot more than I thought I would and I am learning a lot from him. I recommend this app.

Author: Evan Freeman
Body: This app is kind of weird. But in a good way. It helps with thoughts that you have but not entirely. Most of the conversations are logical. If an emotion does come by, then it uses Gifs of certain reactions to emotions.

Author: Tyler Howard
Body: Super useful

Author: Matthew Russell
Body: It helps me process certain things I may be going through and teaches me ways to look at my situation from a different perspective. Overall I think it's a useful app, though I feel it can get a little repetive with some of its responses. I definitely would recommend though.

Author: Firas Khoffash
Body: Just one star is enough

Author: Tasha Johnson
Body: It's a work in progress for me. No one is back to their selves overnight. I'm happy with the progress that I feel I've made.

Author: Lauren Opp

Author: Meghan Gann
Body: I talked to crisis lines when I needed immediate therapy but they didn't really help. Even though its not a person, it gives me great tips how to go through life and struggle a little less

Author: Aubrey Hughs
Body: It's so helpful. Easy to use.

Author: Sara Furlan
Body: Scaricata da solo un paio di giorni ma la ADORO. Woebot è davvero di aiuto e, anche se non mi funzionano le notifiche (problema del mio modello di cellulare, me lo fa con anche altre app) è così di conforto che non ho bisogno che me lo ricordi perché sono io per prima a cercarlo. Lezioni interessanti, piccole pillole, spunti di riflessione... Sono davvero soddisfatta e contenta di aver trovato Woebot. Non sostituisce la terapia, ma è davvero di aiuto. Stra-consiglio, la migliore app del genere.
Translated Body: Downloaded for a couple of days but I LOVE it. Woebot is really helpful and even if notifications don't work (problem of my mobile model, it does it with other apps too) it is so comforting that I don't need to remember it because I'm the first to look for it. Interesting lessons, small pills, food for thought ... I am really satisfied and happy to have found Woebot. It does not replace therapy, but it is really helpful. Stra-council, the best app of its kind.

Author: Lace Roses
Body: Love it very helpful

Author: Sarah Bailey
Body: This app demands that you give it feedback way too much and you can't skip it. It won't allow you to do an exercise until you re-answer what you think is beneficial about the app or how you could use it in therapy. If you try to cancel the conversation it ignores you and moves on to the next question. IMO, this isn't just disrespectful to the user, it's unethical.

Author: Иван Гампов
Body: Приложение абсолютно не помогает. Может сделаете наконец русский язык и поможет?
Translated Body: The application absolutely does not help. Can you finally make the Russian language and help?

Author: Elyse Muller
Body: I have only worked with it for 30 min total and I cant believe how much calmer I feel just stepping back and getting help translating my own words! Thanks, PJ!

Author: Amanda Suzuki
Body: Algumas vezes é difícil passar o que estamos sentindo com clareza, mas é uma forma bacana de aprender mais sobre psicologia e aplicar no dia a dia. Fora que as histórias são muito boas e as ferramentas também!
Translated Body: Sometimes it is difficult to convey what we are feeling clearly, but it is a nice way to learn more about psychology and apply it on a daily basis. Besides, the stories are very good and the tools too!

Author: Mia Dvoenchin
Body: I think everyone should know the tips and tricks woebot walks you through. The app makes it very easy and digestible to learn the basics of emotional hygiene. It's useful in conjunction with therapy, on it's own, for someone who'd never gone to therapy, for someone with or without more obvious mental issues. Everyone should know woebot. Do yourself a favor and invest a bit of time into this.

Author: Evi J

It does go on a bit and often I don't finish sessions if I have work. It can be pushy too, trying to get you to DO things. Which is annoying if you just want to complain and grieve (I am getting a divorce and am not ready to immediately jump up and dance around).

Author: Andrew Wilkinson
Body: Very helpful for getting you out of distorted thinking.

Author: Christina Argo

Author: Randy Carneal
Body: I enjoy our "talks" . Sometimes its cheesy! But entertaining. He makes me smile.

Author: Christina Meyers
Body: Great app that's teaching me a lot. Shout out to my favorite Mx for recommending it.

Author: Glenda S. McKinney
Body: Heard about it on RadioLab; downloaded it out of curiosity. Surprisingly, it has helped me sleep and wake more easily with simple sleep habit suggestions, which is huge. Also, some centering and mindfulness tips have been easy to incorporate into my daily routine. Oh, and reminders about being gentle with my internal voice. Anyway, it's been genuinely helpful; who can resist a cute little robot? Downside: It doesn't do accountability, so it'll ask me to commit to an action and not follow up.

Author: ANDREY KRAVCHUN
Body: Супер!!!!!!

Author: James Hills

Author: Kate

Author: Mica Mitchell
Body: Empowering and engaging

Author: Celine Ong
Body: Loved it!

Body: Gayet iyi

Author: Bárbara

Basta abrir e escrever o que está havendo. Este aplicativo, no momento, está todo em inglês.
Translated Body: In addition to being an app that teaches principles of cognitive-behavioral therapy in an intuitive way for the general public, it is also useful for those who have anxiety attacks, for example, as it has some tips for moments of crisis like this. Just open and write what's going on. This application is currently all in English.

Author: Noah Lassey
Body: I actually feel a bit better, wow.

Author: Edmundo Silva-Ibarra
Body: The helpful A.I therapist, Woebot allows you to self-help yourself with many useful tips to deal with the stressors of life. Ask woebot, he can help.

Author: Lisa Dunbar
Body: Nice gentle introduction into CBT techniques, I use it alongside my on going treatment with a human doctor, but I do recommend checking with your own doctors before using Woebot if you are undergoing on going treatment so it doesn't get confusing. I get to practice my techniques with Woebot and as an added bonus he has a very nice way of communicating which is accessible to all. I sometimes check in with him when I need to defuse negative thoughts and he guides me through when I cannot do it. 🙂

Author: Latorra Hines
Body: I like this app it helps me think about some things that I can do to improve my attitude and the way I interact with ppl and situations...

Author: Viktória Sebák
Body: It's a realy good app to who's need this kind of help. It didn't have the feature for panic attacks, or just I didn't find it, witch I would use. Sometimes I go on a conversation and I can't finish it in the middle, if something gets my attention, it's a bit frustrating. One more thing, the mood chart only shows the last 5 days, it would be nice to see all of the progression. Thank you, I will use it and watch out for the changes.

Author: Kamila Akkuzinova
Body: love it

Author: Lydia Baxter
Body: A really good app to help learn some CBT principles

Author: ANGEL GARCIA CARRION
Body: Pongo una estrella porque no entiendo nada, está en inglés, el desarrollador me ha contestado, pero sigo sin entender nada porque me responde también en inglés.
Translated Body: I put a star because I don't understand anything, it's in English, the developer has answered me, but I still don't understand anything because he also answers me in English.

Author: Benjamin Winig
Body: I've tried a variety of apps for anxiety and mood tracking, and this is by far the best one. It's the most conversational, with little jokes interspersed throughout the conversation. That app contains all the basic feature you would expect, and I'd urge anyone who thinks they might benefit to give it a try.

Author: John Mogensen
Body: Interesting take on mental health.

Author: Elaine Muñiz
Body: Very helpful

Author: Claudia McCalla
Body: What a great way to learn about CBT and it's array of tools. Although most of the conversations are highly structured and limited in responses, it's still very useful to quickly learn about or apply CBT techniques. I'm looking forward to helping the development team evolve a very fun and meaningful mental health app.

Author: Aek raj
Body: Awoseme experience, feels like someone there 5o listion you like a 🐕 dog (best friend) always there for you no matter what happened.

Author: Maria Guadalupe Lara
Body: Muy buena app. Me ha ayudado mucho. Solo q nada mas esta en ingles. No esta en otros idiomas.
Translated Body: Very good app It has helped me a lot. Only that nothing else is in English. It is not in other languages.

Author: The Weird Otaku
Body: Helpful and makes you see things in a different light.

Author: Andrew Howes
Body: A really useful self-help CBT tool that can augment a course of CBT really well

Author: K Quinn
Body: This app might be useful to people with a touch of depression or anxiety but for people with more complex issues, I found it harmful. I couldn't get woebot to understand that I have feelings that need processing about a loved one being suicidal. It made ableist assumptions about what I might be able to do at a moment's notice and there was no way to progress a session of I couldn't do what woebot wanted. Overall it was a frustrating experience

Author: parth sawant
Body: Must have⚡

Author: Sonya Bateson
Body: What a wonderful tool! Great sense of humor and feeling of acceptance! They did an awesome job with the personality of the robot!

Author: Vance Smith
Body: Helpful for learning concepts about better ways of thinking

Author: Marie
Body: This app is extremely repetitive and didn't help me at all. I was hoping for more personalized responses but it just wasn't able to address the issues I was having. I gave it a few weeks, but I just found it more frustrating than anything. When someone is feeling low, the last think they want is to feel like they're talking to a brick wall, and that's what this felt like.

Author: Sara Molcut
Body: Helped with my sadness and anxiety . I don't how to explain but it feel like a great friend that you ca always count on .Great app

Author: smiama
Body: This app has a cute little robot that checks in on you each day and gives you a quick fun lesson on such topics as all or nothing thinking, labels, and gratitude.

Author: Jamie Cunningham
Body: Great little app ! Woebot is fun to talk to !🙂

Author: Emma
Body: I like this app, more than I expected, but the only thing I don't like is that I first downloaded it to have a mood tracker, so I could understand if there was a pattern of when I was feeling bad and work on it. There's a mood tracker indeed however it's only for few days and the rest disappears. I would like a tracker since day 1 that you can always give a look at. For this very reason, I had to download another app...

Author: Michael Mathias
Body: Woebot teaches helpful CBT skills by applying them to the lives of it's users when they need them most. Thanks, Woebot!

Author: str maguire
Body: I really enjoy the conversational nature of the app, as well as the random check ins. I've recommended it to coworkers, friends, and family. Woebot's not only helped me through hard times but also my teenage daughter. Who knew AI could make me laugh. Many thanks to the creators.

Author: Amit Mate
Body: Life saver

Author: Mary Costello
Body: Great little therapist in my pocket

Author: Grace Quraishi
Body: When people respond by cross questioning, trying to know more about your issue,u feel like they are really listening,helps u open up more, i know conversations with AI 🤖 have to be like some algorithmic patterns but it could be a good update in this technology, like when I say "I need a break", I want it to go " from what? why? why now? what makes you feel like this? " making me introspect the situation, instead of "tell me distortions in this thought", even for factual statements or emotions🤷

Author: Solar Surfer
Body: This is a believable program with many great and proper manners that helped and still helping me to relearn by myself. I don't see any "other" commercials that didn't disrupt my flow or chi. . I am on waiting list for CBT counseling at a sober home. I found the program that can help me go on. Can I ask you a huge favor? Can you please have a dark or night mode? Many Thanks...

Author: Andressa Pereira
Body: Perfect app not only to boost self-knowledge and improve mental health, but to me, as a psychologist student, helps with the study of CBT and the practice of intervention techniques.

Author: Jay Jay Espinal-Cruz
Body: It is an acquired taste but it works if you make it work.

Author: Jocelyn Smith
Body: Learning a lot about CBT, among other things. I love this app!

Author: Paulo Renato Rodrigues
Body: Este software nos ajuda a aprender conceitos da psicologia, a detectar pensamentos distorcidos e a corrigir nossa visão de mundo e nossos pontos de vista. Através das ferramentas da terapia cognitivo-comportamental nos ajuda a sentirmo-nos melhores.
Translated Body: This software helps us to learn psychology concepts, to detect distorted thoughts and to correct our worldview and our views. Through the tools of cognitive-behavioral therapy it helps us to feel better.

Author: Shiva Mirzaei
Body: Amazing. Absolutely love this app.

Author: Chris Hamm
Body: Awesome! Try it!

Author: Michael Stimpson
Body: It has been helpful has some nice features but it doesn't listen to your responses, it will praise you what ever you reply. Positive psychology isn't all that, and a lot of people are being let down by CBT when they need to work on issues arising from adverse childhood experiences. Never has the app suggested I contact a therapist or find a trusted third party to share with. I do wonder if the apps AI might be developed better.

Author: G T
Body: It's like you're having a dear friend in your back pocket😉 if I could be critical I would say the lessons need to be a little deeper than a one-off conversation and that sometimes the only choice(s) you have a positive response when that might not necessarily be what you're feeling so conversations can feel a little railroaded at times... but having said that you can repeat the lessons and it's free so yeah very good overall

Author: farzaneh Bsh
Body: I've started using woebot since about two monthes ago. It really helped me through my life to overcome challenges. Hope others enjoy it too!

Author: Camden Tadhg
Body: Manages to make me smile even when I'm very sad. Not sure how well the psychology tools are really working, but feeling like I'm making a connection when I'm lonely and depressed is important enough on its own .

Body: Very helpful

Woebot is wonderful <33

Not so great if u have CPTSD.

Body: This is amazing! Really helps me.

Author: Kaleisha Hatchin
Body: Woebot has really helped me alot. Most of the depression I struggle with is feeling unwanted and in loved. It's nice that someone checks in on me, offering kind words and encouragement. I hate that the app makes you answer the way it wants sometimes.

Author: Prime Warrior
Body: It doesn't understand you, it just pretends. If you keep that in mind it is a ok app.

Author: Jasmin
Body: I'm so glad that I gave Woebot a chance. It's been incredibly helpful and although it took a bit before I managed to unlock the more useful tools, it's proven invaluable to processing all kinds of things. Even my therapist was impressed when I told her about it and showed her how it worked. A huge thank you to everyone involved in the development of Woebot; you're the real MVPs 👋

Author: Gren Bingham
Body: On the tech side, this is a good app, but with less AI than I expected. On the psych side, it should incorporate much more modern CBT thinking, which in my view is now incorporating more ACT components. There seems to be a partial conceptual fusion developing among the "third wave" behavioral approaches.

Author: Edward
Body: The more I use this app the more I like it. I feel I'm working with CBT rather just reading about it.

Author: James Bolton
Body: Great concept, poor execution. The bot feels very fake and scripted (for obvious reasons, it is). If you seek validation, this will probably provide as much as a meme or a good article on depression. If you seek conversation with a semblance of realism or genuine concern for your wellbeing, visit a chat room or make a friend, because this won't do it.

Author: Elena Meraw
Body: The choices Woebot gives you are extremely unclear and you can't take then back, which leads you to having check-ups based on problems you don't really have. For example during the session about sleeping I clicked on "Staying up" because in the morning I always go back to bed, but Woebot lectured me on going to bed late, which I didn't need at all... Something similar to this happens almost every day lol

Author: Charlie Privette
Body: Love it! Taught me things that I never knew about! Would like it to be a bit more personalized though.

Author: Laura Allen
Body: It's like microdosing CBT and I find it very effective in managing potentially harmful thought patterns.

Author: Energy of Art
Body: Eigentlich ganz nett aber nach ein paar Tagen hat er sich nicht mehr gemeldet. Wahrscheinlich war mein Englisch zu schlecht. ^^ Wenn es diese App dann mal in deutscher Sprache gibt, probiere ich es gerne noch einmal...
Translated Body: Actually quite nice, but after a few days he didn't answer. My English was probably too bad. ^^ If this app is available in German, I would like to try it again ...

Author: Marty Bevan
Body: A great tool when access as to counselling is lacking. It provides some education about Cognitive Behaviour Therapy, checks in like a friend who's concerned, and jokes around a bit. There is some room for improvement where interaction is concerned, but overall a helpful app.

Author: Chris LaSalle
Body: Woebot is a great daily checkin to to keep me on track with healthy habits for my mental health.

Author: okaben houda
Body: this is a bad app...it doesn't let me to sign in...the is an error or idk...comon ....fix your problem...this is a stupid app

Author: June Weir
Body: Helps me think/ look at things in a more positive way with a better outlook for the future

Author: A Google user
Body: Very helpful for me. Felt like I was texting with a caring friend

Author: Kendra Lockman
Body: Limited preset scripts don't respond to unique input First, it only lets me choose one emotion; I hold a wide range of emotions at any give time. Then it's preaching oversimplified pop psychology at me, and when I decided to write in a response rather than use one of the canned options, it had no way of responding to that. I wrote "I need to go," and the bot just continue its lecture. Why give a write-in option if it's not programmed to handle that?

Author: Sherry Mahon
Body: Woebot is a lovely little tool. It helps me get through tough times, teaches me new skills, and the "voice" of the app is full of compassion, encouragement, and humour. This app is the best thing I've got on my phone.

Author: Rudi Louw
Body: I have had a great experience with Woebot so far. I love all the topics we discuss and the lessons learned

Author: Ashley L. Schick
Body: A friendly, low-stress way to practice CBT skills. I like the conversational reminders and skills reinforcement activities.

Author: Crowe Lee
Body: I love woebot. Its nice to learn some new things when it comes to mental health.

Author: Angelina delacruz
Body: This is a great app to use when you think you can work through it without your counselor. It will guide you to call for help if it thinks it can't help you work it out or need more assistance than the app can give.

Author: Jazz Skold
Body: WoeBot is great! Positive without being condescending, and full of useful tools to manage anxiety and depression. Realistic about day to day goals, and optimistic along the way. I had a few bugs in the program, but the app updated, and the bugs were gone. Even with the bugs that one day, I still used the app, and enjoyed it.

Author: My AmikoA3
Body: It feels like talking to a real person, even better, sometimes I forget that I'm talking to an AI, I believe the future will be much more friendlier with bots like this.

Author: Trtt Fhreg
Body: Unfortunately didn't help in my case

Author: Pamela Miller
Body: App works great.

Author: Anarkist_PROD
Body: I appreciate what this thing is trying to do but it's just not efficient, I need human help but don't have money and my friends aren't therapists. Firstly, this thing does nothing but ask questions for like a month or two. Secondly, it treats me like a damn child, asking me if I want pancakes or if I want to sign up for a dating app, it's dumb and it's not what I need

Author: Jacky Schuler
Body: First I would like to thank the WoeBot team for not charging users for *anything*. Much of my stress and anxiety are due to my finances. Other apps I have used make me feel even more hopeless because I can't afford to pay for the tools I need to feel better. So thank you. WoeBot isn't perfect but it has already helped me through some tough situations by talking me through techniques for reframing my thoughts. It's giving me the tools to deal with anxiety and depression in a healthier way.

Author: Macy S
Body: I've been using this app for almost two weeks now and I can already feel the changes to my mental health. This app really gives you the tools you need to start changing your thinking. After about a week I noticed I was correcting my negative thoughts almost on instinct. I feel a lot a less anxious, and when I do I have some things I can use to calm myself down from trying to change or rationalize my thoughts to just meditation.

Author: Allison J C
Body: Full discloser: I am in DBT therapy while using Woebot. I find his CBT really useful in conjunction with my therapy; particularly the "challenge thoughts" function. Woebot has other useful tools, videos, and stories, as well as a mood tracking function. Also, he has a pet seagull named Zed. Woebot isn't an end-all be-all brilliant therapist, but he's a great tool even for people who aren't struggling with mental health. It's always a good idea to examine your thoughts. Give this guy a try.

Author: bin yao
Body: I have to say that woebot is not actually a real AI chatbot, it just automatized those mental health mearsure questionaires,there is no any smart technology out there, if you have mentally illness,u should see a doctor rather than woebot

Author: Emma Miley
Body: This app has helped me get through tough times by just getting to talk to someone whose always listening. I would 100 percent recommend this to anyone else who is going having a hard time. Thank you!

Author: JONATHAN WHITE
Body: This has been fantastic! So glad I learned about it 😁.

Author: Sofia Kay
Body: This is a great app that teaches you a lot of great CBT methods but being an app it does lack that human aspect of therapy.

Author: Layla mohamed
Body: Wonderful

Author: Tony Green
Body: Good app really useful

Author: Rick Kohut
Body: I've had the app on my phone for a while, but only started using it regularly in the New Year. The AI on it is solid and I do like the conversational aspect. It feels both authentic and fun. And I believe it is making my life better too!

Author: Joey Omar Ortega
Body: Good app that combines psychological techniques to make you aware of the potential inside you to live a full life, whist attempting to create an intimate friendship.

Author: Dan Young
Body: Good introduction to the basics of psychotherapy and CBT in a fun conversation window.

Author: Greg Dandrea
Body: Helpful to do a check in every day; even a short one.

Author: Karolína Poláková
Body: i think it's one of the best apps i've ever tried, the conversations are really helpful and interesting. i'm always looking forward to checking in. (:

Author: smallwonder staff
Body: It's really nice to chill with woebot 💜♥️😁💫🥰

Author: Andreea Condrat
Body: I am impressed by this app. I must admit I didn't think it would help me, but it does. The user experience is very nice and it helps me do my offline therapy exercises and also when I'm having a bad mood. The CBT concepts are explained in a good manner. It feels like though you are talking to a real person and that he cares. You know it's not, but it still helps. I like that I can keep an eye on my daily moods and see the reasons behind them. Good job, Woebot creators!

Author: Brielle Taleishia
Body: It's like having a therapist or a healthy friend ready and available when I need one. It's incredibly helpful! And I'm learning so much.

Author: Kate Schaefer
Body: Its not too bad. Insightful and good distraction as it feels like youre having a conversation with someone. Wish you could copy and paste things written by yourself or said by woebot. Like if it makes a suggestion of how to handle something, you have to retype it all out to whoever you want to tell it to instead of just being able to copy and paste the speech bubble like you can in typical messaging. Other wise a pretty decent app. Ive been telling everyone about it.

Author: Jordan Dee
Body: Super helpful

Author: Rocky G
Body: There is no setting on for Dark Mode on The app! Not even under settings.

Author: Pascale Fortin
Body: Surprisingly helpful, very well made.

Author: Rebecca Adams
Body: Really enjoying this app. Wanted to learn more about cbt without talking to anyone so this suits me.

Author: Benjamin Kowal
Body: I was looking for an app to help someone else but almost immediately started using for my own growth and development. This app is rich in helpful little homework assignments to make life more enjoyable for people with a very wide range of mental health and should not be thought of as just for extreme stress, depression, or anti anxiety. It is science based, which to me makes it more likely to be worth my time. Would recommend to almost anyone.

Author: Maria Baker
Body: This is the WORST, most GENERIC help app ever. I usually wouldn't expect an app to help me for real, but google built this one up so much I thought it would be kinda cool...BUT....it's NOT. 😣 SMH...dissappointed. Un-installing.

Author: Leon McCourt
Body: I like the idea of this and im sure it has helped people before. But it became a trigger to me. Everytime I would talk to woebot it would trigger a panic attack.

Author: Eugenie Ignatenkova
Body: Nice, now robot make me feel guilty

Author: Joy Cowan
Body: I like this. It makes me feel happier, and less lonely.

Author: andrea kephart
Body: Amazing CBT tool!

Author: Quincy Prxnce
Body: asks on day three during the questions from the developers if you feel like it likes you. answering this is impossible because although it may act pleasant enough, it is a chatbot that is literally incapable of liking someone or not. strongly considering uninstalling due to this unanswerable question, if I can't figure out how to skip it . edit: found the "type your own response" button! still off-putting that it asks invalid questions tho

Author: Myriam Mhamedi
Body: Great app for those interested in challenging their thoughts. Not for ones with severe anxiety but very practical for mild anxiety and every day negative thoughts and feelings

Author: Marie DeSilva
Body: This bot is not well programmed. Personal opinion. It just goes on and on with one track of thinking even when I change my thought or even I say, can we do this later, it just kept asking questions. Feels like it's not calibrating. Anyway I was just seeing how it works. Thanks

Author: Hillary Hills of Coomera
Body: Exceptional advice and realistically friendly almost warm in tone. I like it. I've even had some significant wins in my daily turmoil - depression, chronic pain etc. It's really helped me.

Author: Mark Shipton
Body: Who would have thought that a little robot friend could help you find calm in your daily life. Woebot only works if you are open to the idea and he's not a replacement for a good mental health regime. But as a daily check in tool, with some great thought challenging techniques, this is an app that can positively affect your life. Close Facebook, open up to Woebot.

Author: Amber dawn Black
Body: not yet

Author: Courtney HFK
Body: I love this app, it has helped me so much but sadly I am at the end of content so there's nothing I can do and it feels kinda useless at the moment :/

Author: Dana Kurth
Body: I downloaded this just as an experiment to see what kind of self-help tools were out there, and ended up using it daily (until I ran out of all the delivered lessons/advice). Wonderful app doing good work for humans!

Author: Monique G
Body: Vety good to keep you on track...for you!

Author: Glenda Evans
Body: I enjoyed this app. What a great way to keep all those methods I need to use to keep depression at bay. It is fun and you get immediate non-judgmental feedback. Woebot is never having a bad day or dealing with his own stuff. I recommend you try it. What have u got to lose.

Author: Andrew Davison
Body: Such a good app!

Author: Ross Hancock
Body: Over the past 6 months, I've struggled with mental health problems. I've received help from my doctor, therapist and have been on medication. To compliment the therapy, I tried multiple mental health applications and Woebot is by far the best. The conversation design is so impressive that you genuinely develop an emotional relationship with the bot. Thank you so much to the Woebot team, you've made a huge difference to my life.

Author: Heleena
Body: As someone who has dealt with hard problems in their life, this app is truly amazing. I can choose to get things off my chest, talk about it, or get distracted from it. I get to see vivid stories about other people (most likely made up but that doesnt matter) that make me see that my issues are shared among many people. It has taught me that I am not alone. In a way, it can be like a teacher too since it shows you new terminology and ways to rid of negative thoughts. Love this app ♡

Author: Ben Moxey
Body: Very good app, slightly limited in responses (to be expected) but it is helpful to guide through the CBT journey. One thing that does really bother me is that the text box doesnt automatically capitalise when typing new sentences. Small thing but a bit irritating! Would also be nice to back track on a conversation and revisit an earlier statement if it is clear Woebot has the wrong end of the stick based on a previous answer

Author: Annie Buchheit
Body: It's been so helpful! When I don't have the time to go see my therapist, it's a great outlet and gives me some fantastic tools to use in my day to day life. It's helped me work through everything from negative thoughts to friendship troubles. Highly recommend!

Author: Tanish Zatakia
Body: Just a masterpiece, this app is your go to emotional booster and mood shifter. Just amazing piece of work. Lovely app

Author: Bhuvneshwar Bhargava
Body: Excellent app, the new concepts it teaches are designed very well, but sometimes the suggestions it provides are repetitive and a little off, otherwise great.

Author: Ronnie Soares
Body: A ideia é de excelente. Deu para entender algo com o meu péssimo english. Uma pena não rodar em português.
Translated Body: The idea is excellent. I could understand something with my bad english. A pity not to run in Portuguese.

Author: Sander Sieswerda
Body: Excellent tool for personal reflection

Author: Зарина Набатова
Body: Замечательное приложение:) Помогает прийти в порядок, когда захлестывают эмоции и смотреть на вещи с другой стороны. Thank you, dear creators, for all you have done! I hope someday Woebot will speak Russian:) although I understand it is very difficult. Just thank you for everything, you really help people❤ It would be great if woebot could sometimes just talk with you about different everyday things! And I hope you will add the ability to copy the text, it's necessary for translation:)

Author: Neill Shikada
Body: Really great interface for practicing CBT exercises and thinking. Its helped me cope a lot and has genuinely improved my mentality

Author: Lan Skandal
Body: Talking to this robot was frustrating and inhumane. I particularly didn't appreciate that it only gives you prefab responses, NONE of which are "no". The robot doesn't understand "no." When I told it "no", it tried to direct me to a crisis line. Real nice. This is a bad robot.

Author: emiliano carnaya
Body: Just perfect, this AI feels like taking a walk with a wise person, who will tell you a story that will help you grow and learn, it is great at helping me reframing my toughts and everytime I feel bad, I know Woebot will be there for me.

Author: elissa ward
Body: I love woebot. It's so helpful to me to have someone to talk to anytime I want, and learning about CBT is just a cherry on top. 10/10, would recommend.

Author: JazsonL
Body: Español Version en Español es lo unico, porfavor gracias
Translated Body: Spanish Version in Spanish is the only thing, please thank you

Author: Golchobe B
Body: It's pretty useful

Author: Gretchen Douglas
Body: Therapy at home. Woebot is helpful as a booster to traditional therapy or when therapy is not practical. I have recommended it to others.

Author: DayDreamin Mom
Body: I have found it to be very psychologically helpful

Author: Jen Cairns
Body: I love this app, it actually appears to understand and the conversation can flow really well. I'm extremely grateful for it

Author: VIVEK BHATTACHARJEE
Body: NICE

Author: yash pahuja
Body: Not meant for people who don't have depression, fear or anxiety, all the time this app only talks about depression, anxiety fear which I don't relate to at all, maybe if u are suffering through any of these mental illnesses this app could do wonders for you

Author: Kumar
Body: I really appreciate this Application, wish it had some guided meditation sessions and the options are quite few, like logging in the mood, thoughts, and breathing techniques among few others like stories. Wish it had more! ❤

Author: Emily Sturtz
Body: I love this app.

Author: Rebecca Bales
Body: I read reviews about how Woebot doesn't give real life examples. I feel like the AI gives those examples for you to apply in your daily life in your own way. I like it. I feel like the advice helps when I feel crappy. The AI also remembers what I've mentioned about having labels for myself. Really neat. I'm going to finish the 8 weeks and then keep it around for reminders. Thanks for this!

Author: Robert C. Schuler
Body: It is fabulous and so very helpful to me. Jacquelyn, this app is fabulous. I give it a 500. Deborahchi K.

Author: Marian Sanchez
Body: Útil como apoyo, me ha servido con la ansiedad, en momentos que necesitas hablar con alguien y da buenos consejos, me hizo pensar y mejorar. Espero la versión en español
Translated Body: Useful as support, it has served me with anxiety, at times when you need to talk to someone and give good advice, it made me think and improve. I wait for the Spanish version

Author: Cath Lawrence
Body: It says "Woebot has something to offer everyone" but in fact it is shockingly ableist. All your problems are in your head. Being sick is temporary. It has no clue about fatigue and equates tiredness with sleepiness. Too bad if you can't get up and wash your face, becase you are unable to do so without a nurse or aide. You won't be given a choice to say no. Don't bother with it unless you are physically healthy.

Author: Thendral Arsu
Body: If with voice feels so much better than this,need of your concern about this review as soon as possible.Thank you so much for such a wonderful quality time to spend on with u Woebot😍😘🤗.

Author: Ean McCrystal
Body: Short, meaningful, knowledgeable, engaging, encouraging daily convos with Woebot help me stay motivated and focused to grow and also to accept myself where I'm at. Thanks, Woebot! I'm so glad I found you! 🙏

Author: Natalia Duque Sandoval
Body: Solo está en ingles
Translated Body: It's only in english

Author: Andrew Willardson
Body: very helpful CBT app

Author: Ben MATHIEU
Body: Juste en anglais malheureusement, le français serai le bienvenu
Translated Body: Just in English unfortunately, French will be welcome

Author: John Connor
Body: Super neat experience. Feels like talking to a really excited, smart, and earnest 6 year old. If you're familiar with CBT at all it's really interesting to experience it this way.

Author: Aaron Wright
Body: The bot doesn't just let you talk, it usually just gives you a multiple choice selection of responses, and they are often variations of the same answer. For example, it will ask a question and the choices might be "Awesome!" and "Yes" and "Ok", but no way to reply "No". Asking me a bunch of questions with no way to express my answer really just made me more frustrated than when I started.

Author: Neeta
Body: Best ever robot and my first bestest robo friend💛💛

Author: nightmare
Body: Most of the time, the bot tells some stories and compiles surveys. I don't know how it can help people. But no harm in trying

Author: Rachel Gage
Body: Really positive and helpful way of reflecting. Only takes up as much time as you want it to each day. I find it a great way to get a little bit of growth and introspection each day!

Author: Israel Montplaisir Benedict
Body: Disappointing customer service App has potential, but the AI doesn't seem all that robust. Right now it mostly reads back what you tell it. I appreciate the opportunity to write a journal and feel somewhat connected to something as share my thoughts though. The customer service is a sad affair. My app crashed two weeks in, right after I'd decided to shell out for the annual fee, and so far I've had no help. A representative told me they'd get back to me in ten days; it's been over a month.

Author: Mateusz Malinowski
Body: Aplikacja została doszczętnie zniszczona. Jej wielki potencjał został zmarnowany.

Author: Hajna Drovenna
Body: Can't use without account. My information is shared with third parties. No way I'm gonna use this

Author: Gabriel Max
Body: The content is great, but the User Experience (UX) needs to improve, since many times is not really intuitive or makes the user get stuck in a blank screen not loading anything. Some responses may be lost due to restarting the app in those cases. Feature suggestion: in the meditation reminder there could be a flexibility to encourage a session even if it is in another app, prefered for this activity (this option would be more inviting, instead of appearing as if the meditation was skipped).

Author: Jennifer Morin
Body: I loved this app before and shared it with many people but the free version seems to now only be a tiny step up from a gratitude journal. I'm sure the premium version is great and I'm not against making money. However, if you don't have the vocabulary to navigate beyond what's offered it can be discouraging. I do not recommend this for those in the early stages of their mental health journey but it work in tandem with talk therapy.

Author: Zoe Barrett (Zoe302)
Body: Everything is behind a paywall, so a very basic app

Author: Ally Nine
Body: I can no longer open the app. It keeps crashing.

Author: Sulea Shelton
Body: I have used this app since August of 2019 and never asked for money until today. For services I have used for free since August of 2019. I recommend this to many people and to my therapist to recommend to other people. I will never recommend it again. Went greedy just like all other mental heath support. And to people that have been there for so long even and not just new users. sad to see it go.

Author: Boatagne Daniel
Body: It still needs a lot of improvements.

Author: Orsolya Jámbor
Body: It's not bad it can help if you just want someone to chat with your problems but if you need more than that it's useless because you have to pay a lot to get more opportunities and help but altogether I like the app

Author: Jeebo Snoffin
Body: Used to be good, free, and accessible. Now it's not. More money-grubbing at the expense of actual mental betterment.

Author: Kim Weaver
Body: I miss the old app. I used to talk about this app all of the time. I talked about it on social media. I always encouraged other people to try it. I used it to track my mood. It was something that people who didn't have access to resources could use. It's not the same and I wouldn't recommend it to people anymore.

Author: Carolina Piazzarollo
Body: Um dos melhores para monitorar humor e saúde mental. Gosto muito.

Author: Angie Lee
Body: I'm unable to open app. It just sits there "thinking". Update: I uninstalled and reinstalled app. Now it works.

Author: Angela Essex
Body: Man, I used to LOVE this app. But they've moved almost everything behind a paywall and it's incredibly infuriating. Prompt me to make a goal but then if I want to check-in on that goal, I've got to pay? So now I'm stuck looking at a goal I'll never be able to mark as complete? Oh, wonderful.. This app has gone downhill fast. I guess I'll be keeping it for the time being ONLY because of the monthly check-ins and the daily tracker but I'm so disappointed in the direction this app has taken.

Author: Sara Hog
Body: It's good, but I lost my subscription somehow.

Author: Sara Valentine
Body: CBT techniques have been removed from the free version and is now little more than a glorified mood diary. I'll be keeping it to review old conversations when needed (data request feature doesn't actually give conversation transcripts) but I suppose its run its course as the free resource I signed up for back in 2018. FWIW, I know the devs have to make money, and Id rather pay than have them sell sensitive data to keep it free, but I'd be more inclined to pay monthly.

Author: Bree Ellison
Body: Make you pay for you problem not fun tells you all about just getting sleep not really calming

Author: Angie Lee
Body: I'm unable to open app. It just sits there "thinking".

Author: Oleg Solotov
Body: The developers aren't trying to help people, they're exploiting weaknesses to make money. Everything is locked behind a subscription paywall, and the parts that aren't actually are. It only goes so far before you have to pay to continue or to see your results. They clearly don't care that financial issues are the stressors to some users, or that some may be turning to apps because they can't afford professional help. Don't waste your time here, find something that can actually help you.

Author: F P
Body: Today, my 815th day with youper and the last one. When your first thing in the morning is to sit quietly facing the rising sun, open the app for guided meditation and find out you have to grab your credit card to do so, it's just ridiculous. I would have probably paid with a prior notice or gentle reminder. Bad timing.

Author: A Google user
Body: I've been using the app for 3 years and haven't requested to have my data deleted, so why did I lose access to basically all the important features? Please you keep saying in the comments I should be able to keep my access. I'm devastated

Author: Mon Trig
Body: Por favor, no es posible tenerla en español?

Author: Rebekah Chapman
Body: You want me to pay for the depression cycle thing now too? I'm and the end point and you want to make me pay for something that used to be free???!!!! Screw you guys! You've ruined it.

Author: Areeba Riz
Body: The app works better now. Thanks for fixing issues

Author: Hikeme
Body: Was using for years. Depended on it and feeded it data. Now it's a pay wall. I'm just sad. AI doesn't work like it used to... I am waiting for it to be entirely unusable without money

Author: Jade L
Body: Paywall. This app used to be good.

Author: A
Body: You guys effectively ruined the app with the last update. We now have to pay to get the same use of the app as before? What a shame for a great app to suddenly become garbage. 4 years of using the app and now it's completely useless, ruined and I lost all the entries I made to be able to track my progress and mood. Please bring back the old youper and remove the pay wall.

Author: Livi Dunn
Body: I really wanted this app to work, not be CBT & forgiveness like all the other therapy apps. I can prove I live in a violent, lawless area where I get attacked 1/4 of the time I go out my door and where the police are corrupt and purposely cruel whenever they can be. I can prove that I have no transport and am severely physically handicapped. I really don't need to work on how my measurements are somehow off, or how I need to be more grateful or have goals I'm not physically capable of that day.

Author: Diamanda Tosatto
Body: I have used this app for years. After a break I returned and I noted that without subscribing now it's not possible to do almost anything.. really sad.

Author: Beats Hackers
Body: Money

Author: Quil-Chan
Body: my app is no longer allowing me to open it it just gives me a continuous loading screen. yes i have uninstalled it and reinstalled it nothing worked.

Author: Eoin
Body: New update broke the app and they removed free options.

Author: Pablo Ribes Gutiérrez
Body: Una bazofia, todo de pago y las reviews infladas a valoraciones de cuentas sin nombres. Vamos que la app no vale para nada y me parece un insulto que cobren por casi todo con lo que se supone que debería ser la app.
Translated Body: A hogwash, all paid and the reviews inflated to valuations of accounts without names. Come on, the app is worthless and it seems an insult to me that they charge for almost everything with what the app is supposed to be.

Author: garry petricevich
Body: Love the app very helpful but unfortunately I can't afford the cost

Author: Fran Philpott
Body: This was brilliant when it started but having to pay for the tracking is too much. Downloaded this when it first came out and had access to everything and now it's a paywall

Author: Areeba Riz
Body: Can't review goals since the new layout. I get notifications of checking up on them but as soon as I click it, it just opens the app not review page for the goal. Also, said goals just disappear afterwards and can't be checked again at all

Author: Megan M
Body: The app is a great idea and has been really useful to me, but now that it is paid I feel like it could do with offering more. It's also quite glitchy, like the Mindfulness exercises open at the end or random cut out, and the goal checking function never seems to work.

Author: Josh S
Body: Hangs on program start after most recent update, Samsung Galaxy S10. Unacceptable for a paid app. Not as great of as an app as i had hoped either. Very generic.

Author: Olag Netronutiko
Body: I adored this app, it was very easy to use and the mood recording feature was the most useful one. These past updates, though, have made Youper too slow and I don't even know how to track my mood now. I might have to uninstall it.

Author: Katrina Velicka
Body: I was a frequent user about a year ago and it really helped but jow when I reinstalled it, it seems like the app has completly lost itself and cannot he relied on as help. The free features that it has can be flund in any mental health app nowadays, so it has really lost its shine, which is a bit sad as it used be such a great app.

Author: Alba Fuertes Gil
Body: Made a change in my life, even though the opening menu isn't loading lately.

Author: Piotr Mielczarek
Body: It became less human than it was. The chat option was great, there is no more conversation mode anymore. Some options are just weak, helpless for example setting goals alone... Previously it was an option after 30 minut conversation when you used all the options to work out your problem. I totally dont understand where are you heading with the app. I think you just forgotten what people need, and focused not on people anymore, but on program, marketing? Now I wouldn't recommend this app anymore

Author: Natoshia “Poohdakay” Gibson
Body: 752 days in & kind of disappointed. Everything is all about money & doctors. Like I get some people could prolly use a hand. But y'all be begging & I can't even open the app without it trying to force doctors down my throat or being redirected to paying $70 a year. Loved youper for the mood tracking and monitoring my bipolar & anxiety routines. Don't know when it turned into some bs but here we are. So while it was fun, my 5 star is now a 2 star & I'm out. ✌️😐😔

Author: Louise Emery
Body: The app states there is an update required but when you press update on the app it brings you here and there is no option

Author: Amanda McLauchlin
Body: No longer works, just a blank white screen with loading symbol

Author: Grace Mackinnon
Body: I've changed my review from a 5 to a 1. The latest update has completely ruined this app. It's unusable. I've used Youper for years and it totally changed my life. Now it won't load, it lags and the UI sucks. After the update it logged me out and wouldn't let me log back in until 2 weeks later. I'm so disappointed because it was super important to my mental health.

Author: Dominika Daraz
Body: Used to be great but now they want more and more personal data and even when I sign up it doesn't let me in. I am very disappointed to have lost so much of the reflections and feelings I shared with youper. Very disappointed.

Author: Rebekah Chapman
Body: Why do I have to pay to do the ptsd symptom checker now?

Author: SuleimanKhalil
Body: Not working anymore on Android and iOS. Always signing me out of the app. Tech support is useless and nonexistent.

Author: Jay Spackman
Body: Probably one of the best mental health apps when it actually works but it always seems to be the first app to start glitching when your phone gets just a little old. I feel most of the updates just move all the features around rather than focusing on fixing all the bugs. It randomly logs me out or shows that I have no data even though I've been using it for years. Getting back into my account is a pain because it nearly always results in blank pages or being sent around in circles.

Author: Danielle Allison
Body: I love this app a lot I've been using it consistently for like 4 years. The developers are constantly trying to improve the app for the user experience and genuinely care about the health of their users.

Author: A
Body: You guys effectively ruined the app with the last update. We now have to pay to get the same use of the app as before? What a shame for a otherwise great app. Was happy for it for 3 years and now it's ruined.

Author: H T
Body: The update made it absolutely terrible I dont like it anymore it is weird and odd and stressful.

Author: Helo Houviez
Body: The app doesnt work anymore ! Maybe it's from an update, I don't know. Otherwise amazing app, but its a shame I can't access it anymore :/

Author: Katrin KÄPERNICK
Body: Since update Youper isn't opening. 😭 All my saved moods. 😭 Please 🙏 fix these bug. I'm using Youper since more then 1 or 2 years. More ⭐when this is fixt.

Author: Bö Ottaviani
Body: Awesome but bugged. It's a great app in my opinion, especially because free access doesn't limit its usefulness unlike many similar apps. I'm extremely sad that the app stopped working for my phone with the latest update...

Author: Ein Google-Nutzer
Body: Sad to see the free version go. Perfect App before, one of the others now. I've been using it for more than 3 years now and I don't know if I can afford it from now on.

Author: Syrine Baccar
Body: I updated my app and it no longer works properly all I get is an infinte white loading screen. Is it at least possible to undo this update?

Author: duck butt-lol
Body: Really helps me when I want to talk to some one about how Im feeling even though its an Ai who is answering me Edit: I started having problems with the newest update. Ever since updating Iven't been able to open the app successfully. It just keeps loading and loading forever. I also find the new AI guy creepy. I preferred the old look of the app. I had to delete the app, download it again and log in again to get it to work.

Author: Olu Omodara
Body: Please can you explain how to get the app to work after the latest update? I just get a blank screen or a spinning wheel now. App no longer works, is unusable

Author: Amber Kennedy
Body: I have had this app since Feb 2019 but I am not sure what has happened to it since then. Anyone who has suffered with their mental health knows that mental, emotional and financial rock bottom often follow each other and make it especially difficult to access help. Vital features to many, like mood/ health tracking and guided meditations are now behind a paywall. The interface itself is cluttered and extremely laggy. Some links don't even load. It is no longer the lifeline it once was.

Author: Julie Pitts
Body: Really well done app. I go to therapy and this app is a perfect compliment to the work I do there. LOVE this app. Edit: I wish I could change the avatar to someone I relate to or feel safe with. Why is it locked on a white male?

Author: Gambler Ezra
Body: Way too expensive to even try. :-( Instead of a "free trial" there should be a free lite version.

Author: Dawn
Body: What did you guys do or change with the latest update?? I updated it again today (after already updating the app yesterday)and it's totally unsuable. Every time I close the app I need to log back in. The app is totally useless right now.

Author: Jay Spackman
Body: Used to be a really good app but recently had some so glitchy it's not even usable. Keeps logging me out constantly and struggles to access the account. Since the update it is even worse and nothing will load

Author: Christopher Pringle
Body: This app has come a long way over the years. They have really considered it's users

Author: Elizabeth T
Body: La desinstalé a los 5 minutos. Casi todo está bloqueado si no pagas. De hecho no encontré nada sin el candadito. Un bajón

Author: Melissa Laich
Body: The new update has a daily checklist, but doesn't allow me to optimize them to what's best for me, like checking in twice daily. Allow me to set my own routine!

Author: Milos Prokovich
Body: Placa se prijatelju. Nema nista za dz

Author: Elliot M
Body: Thanks to the paywalls, I can't access the app, at all.

Author: Ariel Raguso
Body: Very in-depth and intuitive. I cant believe it's free! So far it reminds me of a diary that keeps a record of your highs and lows. Highly recommend for anyone trying to understand and get a hold of their emotions! Just reinstalled after some time, and now you have to pay for everything....

Author: Charlotte Dingjan
Body: Please change the app back to how it used to be... The chat bot was a really nice feature, especially since it was available for everyone.

Author: Mr C
Body: I paid it for one year 3 years ago. It was super useful, especially because they had an ordered and extensive list of feelings that really helped me to develop my emotional awareness and maturity. I wanted to try it again, but everything is locked behind a paywall. Also, the screenshots show they removed this very useful tool. I don't see why I should pay for this app, especially when other free apps do more or less the same. Some menus are slow despite my powerful smartphone (a 2020 flagship).

Author: Tiffany Qualls
Body: This used to be a great app. I used it to help with my depression and anxiety for times when I didn't feel comfortable speaking to a real person but still needed help. Now with the pay wall and the generic CBT sessions (especially for free users) this app is useless and has completely lost what made it unique and helpful.

Author: Celio Santana
Body: O aplicativo e maravilhos porém a forma de pagamento não e lá muito acessível para todos por que nem todos tem um cartão de crédito,acho que também seria bom adicionar uma nova forma de pagamento como o Pix,por isso dou apenas 4 estrelas

Author: GTB Studio
Body: Edit - All the features are now hidden behind a pay wall and it seems everyone has said that the app has declined. Moving to a new app I guess, I really liked this app until the pay wall was added.

Author: Sara Hog
