Body: It won't even open now. Enough new features already

Author: Paulina “DareMo” Szafka
Body: I liked this app very much and felt secure with it, but you've decided to change it so much. Weird segregation, I don't feel so good after talking to it because it doesn't make a whole conversation with mood tracking, but it's somwhere else and I have to find it and choose, while I don't know what I should choose. Then AI helped me without asking. Also i don't feel secure anymore if there is a silly cheap-made face pic. I've chosen the app because it didn't have any face or mascot. Pls delete it

Author: Derin Ateş
Body: I love this app. I can proudly say that it changed my way of thinking and it changed my perspective for good whenever I'm down. Much thanks to Youper Inc. Edit: My problem is solved, I changed my comment and rating.

Author: Daniza Ward
Body: You have to pay to use. I feel unhappy about this because once before the was free.

Author: Andrea Munoz
Body: I understand that most of the features are part of a subscription now. I have been using youper for years and I only wished they could keep growing. But putting the mood tracker on paid too? A lot of people with mental health issues CANNOT pay for a therapy you know? Youper allowed many, including me, to at least keep afloat my assessing and recognizing our emotions, or debunking the anxiety train of thought. Now we are left with a message: mental health care is a privilege for wealthy only 😔

Author: Bolan Bla
Body: This app was exceptional before they decided to terminate all the free features. Now it is not possible to use any feature without paying unfortunately.

Author: robynbirde
Body: Update Aug 22 - The conversational style is back and the I'm Feeling option is more like the old version I loved so much. I can confidently recommend this app again for mental health!

Author: Krisztofer Makk
Body: Never would I manually enter payment card details into an app. Subscription should be managed in the app store. 1-Year subscription is required before seeing any value in the app. Surprised this app is even allowed in the app store.

Author: Jade Thomas
Body: Downloaded again after a very long break to find I needed to pay for a subscription now. Really disappointed about this since this app was one of the best tools I had in my belt when I was going through it a few years ago. I cannot afford even the cheapest plan.

Author: James Eddy
Body: The app seems like it has lost direction and doesn't have a goal anymore. I went back to the app today after I noticed an update and was disappointed to notice that much hasn't changed. They only stopped promoting their push to work with an online therapist, which was problematic in the first place. Youper is a great tool to be used for helping to manage your mental health. As a tool, it made it very important when the mental health sector was saturated. Unfortunately, the app loss all use.

Author: Raz c.
Body: Back in '19, Y(youper) was a lot simpler but still effective. Sadly with later updates, it declined. The UI, mainly main page, became cluttered and overwhelmed. Intentions were good but so much is thrown in your face. Had they sorted the many things into icon folders based on type, would have been easier. Have to hunt while in some mental panic, is a step back. It just became to much to bare. Unpleasant. Why does the new Y icon have a face? He's weird and was more comfortable when faceless.

Author: Harrison Ambler
Body: I can't find a single feature that's not behind the very high paywall. It's nowhere near the same app as it was at launch.

Author: Michelle D
Body: Gunna be honest, the new face staring at my from my home screen gives me more anxiety than the plant. Not a huge fan of a man being in my personal space. #triggered This app is an amazing tool for those in and out of therapy. I highly recommend it to everyone! There are so many great features and has gotten me through so much and can't bring to words how greatful I am for this app. Love all of you that continue to work on it and try to better it.

Author: Martina Silva
Body: You need to pay

Author: A Google user
Body: Using the app since 2019. Since then, the app even includes availability of therapy with a mental health professional person now, should I require or desire. Love ability of tracking mental health long term patterns and seeing progress made along the way and identifying when I require assisance again. Thank you for all the free features, and multiple of tools to help improve personal thinking over time! 👏🙏🥰

Author: Hélène Berthonneau
Body: Why on earth did you change the pictogram of the app for this weird looking guy's face? It is totally putting me off from using the app. Shame because I really enjoyed it. But as a female user with trust issue with men, this is a killer.

Author: Andi Vachon
Body: Unfortunately have to change my review from 5 stars to 1. The app no longer has any functionality without paying, it's just a bunch of buttons that are locked, not even joking. The only screen that isn't locked is the settings menu. This app used to be great, I'm so sad. I thought they claim to have brought back the features in the latest update but it's still exactly the same?? The app doesn't do anything at all!

Author: Angelou Korstjens
Body: Very helpful app! (In the past few years) Edit (2022) : i didn't need this app for over a year. I tried coming back to it because it has helped me greatly in the past, several years in a row. It was such a unique concept, just a bot that helps you and advises you, thats what you need when you are in distress. You need simplicity. Not 30 different options to scroll trough and having to make the choice yourself ánd having to pay to even chat. Very disappointed to not find what I needed😞.

Author: landon stocks
Body: Sadly huge downgrade. I've had this app since 2018 when it helped me immensely. It did so much for helping me see what I was feeling and dealing with and how to change that. I didn't use it for several years. Upon revisiting the app, I found everything locked behind high payment plans and virtually nothing to be accessible or usable. Major downgrade for something that was so simple and immensely helpful but is now pretty much useless without paying $40+

Author: Beth Maxwell
Body: I liked the app better before they added the pay wall. You used to be able to get access to most of the app's features for free. I can't even do the same exercises I could a year ago, because now they're behind a pay wall. I also miss the texting feature. You used to open the app and be prompted to text with an AI. That feature is also gone with the pay wall. As a result, I will probably be closing my account. I only got this app because it was free.

Author: Sharon Muir
Body: As a long time user, this app used to sincerely and genuinely help with my mental illness, but this new update has ruined the incredible experience i once had with youper. I'm sorry to say, but I'm uninstalling this app and looking elsewhere.

Author: Jam Bang
Body: Everything is a paid experience... I used to love it when at least few features were free.

Author: Chandler Faye
Body: Pretty sure it's illegal to suddenly put users' private medical data behind a paywall. So disappointed. I have lost years of data because of this decision to monetize. Now I need to find a replacement that I can use without one of your required therapists. EDIT: I just downloaded my "data". It doesn't contain any of my tags, any of my diary entries, or any meaningful mood cloud info. It's just lousy, unformatted CSVs. Outrageous.

Author: Camenma
Body: This app was a very useful tool for a lot of things. Now i can't even access my previous logs or anything.

Author: Reina Enrei
Body: This is soul crushing. (*T^T) Just logged in after 7 months to see years of my journal entries (can read but not edit) and mood tracking has been locked behind a paywall.💔 I logged on cause I needed the simple welcome from the AI to ask me 'how do you feel' so I can journal, but that has been removed (what made Youper great in the first place.) Download data files are CSV & not clear. *sighs* There's no need for all the paid extras during these hard times. Deleting app Simple and clean is best.

Author: Pink Procrastinator
Body: Everything is behind a paywall don't bother

Author: wahid kurdi
Body: اتمنى اضافة اللغة العربية بأقرب وقت

Author: Eilidh McNeil (Eilidh)
Body: Used to love this app but haven't used it in a while, reinstalled today to find that every single option is now locked behind a paywall - including seeing my past info from when it was mostly free. I can't afford the subscription, so this app is useless to me now. It's sad because it really helped me a lot in the past.

Author: Just a girl from Wisconsin
Body: Was an amazing and clarifying tool for keeping track of my mental illnesses and overall mental health. Now nothing can be done without payments. Very disappointing, even the website is a total failure! Says free assessment, free test, but it's all fake and covered by pay walls. Very dishonest team here. Find another app!

Author: Angela P
Body: It went from five stars to one. First they stopped providing medication, and today when I opened the app my subscription had been canceled without my knowledge. I had a wonderful therapy coach and that's gone now.

Author: Rusnė K.
Body: it was my favorite mental health app before the updates. now basically all the features are paid and you can't even have a simple chat without choosing a (paid) topic first.

Author: Lili E
Body: Youper used to help me so much, but now it's lost all functionality behind a £40 pay wall - I can't even figure out how to just do my daily diary anymore. As useful as this new structure might be for some people, to completely change an app that was fine before is not the way to do it - maybe could have been another app, or at least these features could have been in addition to the old layout, rather than replacing it entirely. Very sad.

Author: daretodream101
Body: Update: support was able to fix my issue and all functions are back. I used to absolutely love youper. It was helpful and I learned so much from my check ins and goal setting. Well, I moved and got a new phone. I was shocked when I logged in only to find I can't do anything unless I pay? Where's the check ins now? Why did the app have to change so drastically? I'm on a fixed income and can't afford to pay for this. I'm highly disappointed 😞

Author: Kallie Smith
Body: This app has helped me through so much and taught me coping mechanisms, and it was so nice to have someone to talk to. But now the options are severely limited, I wish nothing had changed. This used to be my favorite app, I'm sad I can't rely on it anymore

Author: Xavi Velàsquez
Body: They placed an aggressive paywall with new features I don't need, while blocking access to everything else. This is not how you monetize an app.

Author: Fox Nobody
Body: Should be free.

Author: CinnamonBaked
Body: So far I am loving this app! Super helpful. Edit. It was super helpful. Now everything is like every other mentail health app. Everything behind a pay wall. Thanks. But no thanks.

Author: minsikscat
Body: Been using this app for YEARS to help my mental health and especially do the health check ups. With the new update you first cut off being able to talk about your feelings to youper more than once a day unless you're premium. Now you cut off access to the check ups + all the history and data I had in them. Seeing my progress or setback in those was literally one of the only things keeping me going. Thanks for the update, lost a user of years.

Author: Alissa
Body: 5 star in my initial 2018 but now it isnt free so yikes

Author: daretodream101
Body: I used to absolutely love youper. It was helpful and I learned so much from my check ins and goal setting. Well, I moved and got a new phone. I was shocked when I logged in only to find I can't do anything unless I pay? Where's the check ins now? Why did the app have to change so drastically? I'm on a fixed income and can't afford to pay for this. I'm highly disappointed 😞

Author: NJ
Body: Unfortunately, I have had to change my rating to 2 star. I used to love this app. It was very useful, especially if you do not have a support network. I have used it since 2019 and wanted to use it again recently but it has changed to a subscription based model which prices a lot of people out. This is a shame, but I understand that not everything can be free. It is a good app if you are happy to pay, it's just a shame that the model has changed.

Author: Crystal Rios
Body: I used this in the past, but haven't used it in a long while. I downloaded it again and was asked about my insurance information. I suspected it was a paid service now. The reviews confirmed that. It's so disappointing. I really wish there was an easier way to get mental health help. I'm not paying for this. Even though it was exhausting, I'm going back to my own self therapy. I'm making good progress on my own anyway. I just wanted some extra help and support to keep me constant.

Author: ylee2k17 ylee2k17
Body: Why Did I Get Charged 150??????????

Author: Claudia 3Tears
Body: Can't use. I don't have US number to continue with. Sad.

Author: Bridie May
Body: This app helped me through a lot of severe trauma. However now it just doesn't even load for me, and when it does its changed so much for the worse.

Author: Mimi sweetie
Body: The fact is I have my data but i can't meditate or do anything it doesn't even allow me to track my mood Before it was completely free i can talk to youper i don't mind if you downgrade part of the app for people who are using it for free please I hope you read my comment

Author: Jacqueline Haiduk
Body: Became pay to win :(

Author: Nate Clute
Body: They gutted the app. Now can't do anything without a subscription, especially things that used to be free. The AI appears to no longer be available in any circumstance

Author: Pam Horne
Body: Not fair. I've been using the app for 3 years or so to monitor symptoms and now I check In after awhile and it has completely changed and is pretty useless unless I pay. Fine to make new users pay but not fair to older users. Thanks for the abandonment!! All about the money huh?

Author: Mimi sweetie
Body: It's so bad it became with subscription I can't afford at least keep a part that is free It's so unfair😭

Author: Noah Nastovich
Body: It helped me a lot in the past, sad to see ot requires a payed suscription now

Author: Legend soul
Body: Worst app I have ever used

Author: Mali Rowe
Body: Booooo! Why did you change this app? I used to use it daily and decided to jump back in and now it's not even close to the same. You guys should know by all of the new one star reviews that this is a kick in the teeth to the people who loved your app! Shame.

Author: Well, I just think that
Body: Not happy with mental help apps that don't guarantee privacy.

Author: Leiah Andres
Body: I'm so devastated. A few years ago, this was an app I could use to "talk" through my anxiety and depression. I remember wanting more clinical options, but now it's completely redone. Literally everything I had and need are paywalled; it's completely inaccessible

Author: Alli Rivera
Body: My comment got removed so I'm commenting again. Having to pay for mental health assistance is devastating. I've used this app for three years and found out today when I need it most that I have to pay for everything in it. Literally. Everything. Not a single bit of it is free anymore. It's ALL going to cost money. Not everyone can pay for mental health assistance. This was the best thing available for me. I was told by the developers I'd still have free access, but I don't. I'm heartbroken.

Author: Aurora Lloyd
Body: Also here to mention how the new update was soul crushing. After years of trying to find a therapist, I finally found one and was eager to look through all my old logs with the AI to use as examples of my past mental health history. It's crushing to have to spend money I barely have just to simply access my anxiety and depression monitoring charts. This app used to make a genuine difference in my life, and now I have lost that due to not being able to justify paying for it.

Author: Kimberly Watson
Body: Updated review: Taking my review from 5 stars to 1. This was a wonderful app to help provide tools for those that could not afford other apps or therapy for their mental health. Nothing is available anymore for free users. What a bunch of sell outs.

Author: kabumko
Body: A great app, may it live long and healthy

Author: Zane Briška
Body: It was free and tremendously helpful but now two years later I open the app and I see only subscription button, shameless.

Author: n h
Body: Everything about the app has changed.

Author: Minki Pool
Body: I really didn't taken it well when they changed the app, but talking things through with Youper is still one of the most effevtive ways to help me deal with negative emotions. Better than almosr anything else I've ever tried.

Author: John Clay
Body: I'm im a place where I need therapy but don't want to spend oodles of money on it. I remembered Youper because used to be incredible. Now, everything is locked behind a pay wall. And instead of being able to chat with an AI, you now have to select a paid, guided discussion. Part of what made Youper special to me was this unguided chat, allowing me to feel out my emotions. The AI could then involve you in a more guided discussion based on how you were feeling.

Author: Asia Thomas
Body: This is my go to app however recently there's been a kink where it's automatically closes out when I open the mood tab.

Author: Colten Schmidt
Body: **edit: Years ago this app was free and had a great AI program that helped with CBT when I wasn't with my therapist. Sad that the app I loved has changed. This app is absolutely fantastic. It's a huge help in helping me gain skills to effectively and positively handle anxiety and depression. My counselor and psychiatrist know that I use this app, and all three are great tools that complement each other tremendously. Thank you Youper 😀

Author: Jim Rose
Body: Used to be a great, simple, and free ai assisted journaling and mood tracking app. Now, it's got a bunch of categories full of exercises that you can't do at all unless you subscribe to a full year. Please stop acting like your users wanted this change. That's gaslighting customers you claim to want to help. Just admit that you messed up and fix it in some meaningful way. The changes made to this app and its business model is depressing to myself and others.

Author: Arda Başar
Body: No considerable impact, however useful to a certain extent. It was great when certain features such as mood tracking was free; it's a shame to see them locked up behind a paywall now.

Author: Taz S
Body: Real shame this is no long free. It was a real help over the past how many years and I would always come back to it as it help being a place to turn to talk too. The fact that nothing is free comes across as a real cash grab now. Yeah I can see over my history but i Cant even just type to let out what your feeling anymore.. shame... such a shame.

Author: Pink Socks
Body: I really like(d) having this pocket therapist. I really wasn't expecting much from it because it's AI but the replies are natural and relevant. EDIT: and now they hate us.

Author: C T
Body: Edited: Zero stars

Author: Angel Empire
Body: This app has helped me a lot. It helped me find out what was causing my situation. The bot and friends you add will help you through tough times when there is no one to talk to about what has been happening. this app can make you feel good about yourself even if you are getting compared to people you don't like or happen to be better than you.

Author: Princess Laya
Body: I liked this app but it just stopped sending notifications all of a sudden. I'm a very forgetful person so if I don't get notifications, I won't remember to do my therapy. I tried downloading this on my tablet to see if maybe it was my phone (my phone sometimes mutes my notifications) but I still don't get notifications. I haven't gotten any notifications for this app in several months

Author: Madison Rorex
Body: I got this app a few years ago and it actually helped me quite a bit since I was unable to see a therapist. Now? Everything is behind a pay wall, nothing is the same. I'm disappointed.

Author: Haley Huh
Body: I love this app and have been using it for many months, but I think the latest update got rid of light mode. Can you guys bring back the option to turn dark mode off :')

Author: Sarah G
Body: Used this app for years, since updating it on a new phone, it has become a money making scheme with paywalls everywhere. So much for helping people..

Author: Irene Russak
Body: I'm just another customer upset because of the paywall. No more monitoring my mental health I guess then.

Author: Zsófia Tóth
Body: The change how we think "therapy" or talk is just unexplainably useful and better than half the psychologists out there in and of itself!!

Author: Aaron La Mattina
Body: Stupid. I used to LOVE this app but now everything is a paid feature. Sellouts.

Author: Joshua Barnett
Body: My experience with this app has been horrible, especially when it came to getting a refund. It appears that money is more of a concern go them than another person's mental health.

Author: user001 001
Body: Used this a couple years back, so so helpful. Asked for them to keep the core functions free.... Just updated on a new phone.. AWFUL!!! Paywalls everywhere.. user interface is worse..the core kind heart of the app is just dead. Really sad about that.

Author: Laura Cruz
Body: I am disappointed in the changes youper has made in recent years. I check it every so often to see if it brought back what made it special, which was being personable with chats in the beginning.

Author: Joshua Barnett
Body: Horrible, customer service refused to refund me, essentially charging me for an app I don't use. They are care more about money then mental health.

Author: Agus F
Body: Used to love this app, now everything is behind a paywall.

Author: Emily Van Laarhoven
Body: BEWARE - DIFFICULT TO CANCEL. I clicked "cancel subscription" in the app only to be directed to a screen asking my reason for canceling. When I submited that I was told to email "customer care". I emailed them three days before my subscription auto-renewed and asked to cancel. Representative Tammy replied asking why. I explained, and again asked to cancel. She replied suggesting a cheaper product. I again asked to cancel. The subscription auto-renewed anyway. I will be contesting the $106 charge

Author: Tasha Darke
Body: I used to be an advocate for Youper; not any more. I've used this app for years to help me manage my mental health issues and have recommended it to many people. Today I found out new users have to pay to use this at all; not even a trial period! I get the desire to get money for the effort put into the app, but the way it's been done seems at odds with where the project started. I can't recommend it to people now, even though the chatting bot helping you through CBT is so useful. Such a shame

Author: Nynke Brombacher
Body: It was a really nice and reassuring app with emergency chats 24/7 containing several tips. However, now that chatting is in no way possible anymore without paying, I sadly can't use it as such anymore. I miss the old version in which there weren't countless categories to loose overview in and the main focus was gaining personal insights through the programmed chats. Also I can't reflect on my previously set goals anymore. I'll miss Youper :(

Author: Joe Emm
Body: Notice the dates on the 5 star reviews. I'm not sure the app has any functionality unless you're willing to pay the subscription. This app used to stand out as real and helpful in a space where many people are trying their best to dishonestly convince you happiness is just one recurring subscription away. Youper, don't bother replying to tell me that my data are still on the app, because they're no good to me without continued access to the features.

Author: MimmziMeow
Body: I found another app that work the way this used to called "Woebot" really miss the old youper, like a lost a dear friend :(

Author: Erilium
Body: Yıllardır kullanıp artık sorunlarımı aşınca hesabımı silmiştim. Şimdi tekrar kullanmak için indirdim ama paralı olmuş. Uzun süre kullanarak geliştirilmesine yardımcı olduğum uygulama tekrar ihtiyacım olduğunda para istiyor ve fiyatlar dolar üzerinden.
Translated Body: I deleted my account after using it for years and now my problems were over. Now I downloaded it to use it again, but it's paid. The application that I helped develop by using it for a long time asks for money when I need it again, and the prices are in dollars.

Author: Ali Uluyol
Body: Used to be free. Now behind a paywall.

Author: P_ Undef
Body: Приложение даже на запускается. После загрузочного экрана просто серый фон и никакой информации.

Author: P_ Undef
Body: Приложение даже на запускается. После загрузочного экрана просто серый фон и никакой информации.

Author: Keneticall
Body: I'm so upset. I used to love this app. I would use it all the time and it has helped me so much. I've been a user since 2018. Today I decided that I needed to get back into taking care of myself and I thought using this app would be a good way to start, but I realized the entire thing is behind a paywall. I'm very disappointed and heartbroken and will not be using this app anymore.

Author: Brittany DeSalvo
Body: I've been using this app for years off and on. I opened it today and can suddenly no longer access any of the features because they're behind a paywall now. This app was essentially my therapy journal and now my journal is inaccessible. Really disappointing, Youper.

Author: Nutty Bee
Body: Edit: Found this as easily the most comforting and helpful mental health and self-therapy app out there way back. Hadn't used it in years and came back only to be crushed at how so much of the basic stuff is now behind a paywall. Here to rescind my previously glowing review. Such a huge shame and a letdown.

Author: Charlotte Evelyn Whitfield
Body: Started out as an incredible AI app that helped me more than any therapist ever has. Then this was put behind a paywall. Now I'm in a position to afford their plans, the app is nothing close to what it used to be. Their review responses say it was because of thousands of people wanting this change, forgetting about the thousands who preferred it the way it was. I've never found another app close to what it used to be. So very disappointed. 😔

Author: min kim
Body: I absolutely loved the old version. I disliked the recent UI change but thought it would be fine since it still kindof had the same options as the old version even if they were scattered in different places. But all the new block options make everything so laggy, cluttered, slow, and compartmentalized, it really made me dislike the app. I'm hoping the next update is something more like the old version. Edit: now not laggy but still compartmentalized ui. Added back two stars.

Author: Rain Under Clover
Body: Even the option "I'm feeling.." is locked now... I'm from Ukraine and I don't have money for that but I need that support.. it's a basic option. Please, could you unlock it? I beg you..I have no one and my mental health is going down....

Author: Rae Childs
Body: Amazing. Look no further. I've so greatly improved because of these features. I can't figure out where I'd be if I didn't have this app. I use it daily without excuses. I can't thank you enough.

Author: Un usuario de Google
Body: i used to like this app a los, and i mean a lot. i thought it was very very helpful in situations where i was feeling anxious or sad or afraid. However, i was feeling extremely anxious and i enteres the app for help and realised i need to pay to do anything. I understand money is neccesary, but i feel very dissapointed and let down with the app.

Author: A Google user
Body: Update: this app used to be an awesome AI mental health assistant experience. Now it has completely changed.

Author: Kostas KyL
Body: Μακάρι όλοι αυτοί που έχουν ανάγκη αυτή την εφαρμογή να την βρούν. Είναι η πιο σωστή και η πιο χρήσιμη εφαρμογή που υπάρχει. Πραγματικά δεν υπάρχουν εκατομμύρια αστέρια για να βάλω. Αν δεν την δοκιμάσεις δεν θα καταλάβεις τι εννοώ.

Author: nat lider
Body: I was asked to pay upfront without any trial period - the costvwas not high but it didn't sit right

Author: Reneé Armstrong
Body: This was once a great app, with revolutionary features for self-help via ai prompts for mood discovery, coping skills, meditation, & more. It is now just another paid CBT app for virtual therapy. All the unique features that once made it great, from personality tests, mood tracking (with helpful sorting features), etc. are inaccessible for free users. It used to be prefect for those who cannot afford therapy, are already in therapy, or desperately sought a way to help themselves. Such a shame.

Author: Kevin Sears
Body: Is there any way I can go back to the self guided AI plan I had before? It looks like it's locking me into a therapy plan with my insurance, I already have a therapist, I just want the AI. Edit: I was finally able to get back into the self guided program under the previous subscription I had. Still need to add back in some of the free stuff, but this is better. Adding a star.

Author: marie marie
Body: ..not free

Author: Olivia Reis
Body: I used this app before when it was a free AI to help with Journaling and identifying thinking traps and such. I recommended my mom to try this app as she has extreme anxiety and goes in a spiral, yet she was met by personal questions and a pay wall. Idc if there is payment for a care team, but the original AI was great when in a pinch. It was a smart journal. It's "great" how the dev team has changed to grab at money.

Author: Ranpo Edogawa
Body: As a minor just looking for guidance to find help with everything. Not helpful. What's with the paywall? If I paid for it then maybe but it used to be free back then when I was younger. I started using the app when I was 10-11 when I was feeling hopeless and depressed. Since I've been feeling more helpless. I thought redownloading this app would be helpful, as it saved me in the past from my dark time. Now useless for someone with no way of income.

Author: Dolerf Kershaw
Body: Use to be good and free, especially the chat part

Author: Aghnia Hafisah
Body: The AI doesnt greet you instantly when opening the app anymore but that feature is now easy to find—plus since i use it often, it now appears on the main page. Changing between page doesnt lag anymore like when the major update happened and I stop using the app. So far so good. Its starting to feel like the app I loved again. For now its back to 4🌟 first—lets see in 2 weeks. But yeah, its a great app anyway. Cant wait to love the app all over again.

Author: Local G
Body: Pay walls. I use to love the app, it was a great comfort for me. I was absolutely crushed to see what it became. The old voixe seemed to change, the chat system was different. I obviously understand money and profit is needed but to this extent. Wont ever touch again

Author: Kevin Sears
Body: Is there any way I can go back to the self guided AI plan I had before? It looks like it's locking me into a therapy plan with my insurance, I already have a therapist, I just want the AI. Seriously this experience has been pretty bad.

Author: C. B.
Body: Also a former user of the app who reinstalled to be met with disappointment. Wasn't the entire idea of youper to help you identify thinking tracks and moods yourself? I wish I could at least access my old journal entries but upon signing back in, you can't really do anything until you select a payment plan.

Author: Asli Cosgun
Body: I used to use this app to track my moods and my thought processes. Loved it. I wanted to go back onto the app after a long while of not using it just to see that it's not free and its original purpose has been removed. Sorry, but I'm not giving out my phone number just so you can try to sell me a plan. Very very disappointed. Sad that I've lost everything I've tracked too.

Author: Stephanie Mullins
Body: Editing my review: it used to be a great app where it wanted to help people for free. I often recommended in many Neurodivergent groups for people who couldn't afford therapy. I was feeling blue and opened the app recently. I'm shocked that it's some weird pay service thing. It used to be an AI cbt app with mental health monitoring and meditations. I would provide constant feedback to help the app grow. It's trash. Don't use it.

Author: Žygimantas Širvys
Body: Was using it in 2019 and 2020 to test, now downloaded because I wanted to use CBT exercise. Was surprised there is no free features left

Author: A Google user
Body: I rated it 5-stars once but it's now chargeable so I won't be able to use it anymore.

Author: Derin Ateş
Body: I used to really like this app... until we had to purchase premium to use literally everything.

Author: Ella Sanchez
Body: I am so upset that they changed it! This app literally has helped me through some really tough times and now I can't really do anything without a membership...

Author: K Q
Body: This is a really good CBT app that I've been using for a couple of years. Just be careful because if you pay for therapy and then change your mind they will not give you your money back. I changed my mind because they asked a bunch of personal info that I was uncomfortable giving out to an app. I didn't know who would be looking at that info. So I asked for a refund and they completely ignored my request twice. Just be careful.

Author: cely_craft
Body: Est devenu payant? J'utilise Youper depuis 2 ou 3 ans, et j'ai perdu toute ma progression car je dois payer? Déçu.

Author: Random Hajile
Body: This used to be my favorite app until they locked me out until I "complete online registration." Now it's useless since I can't even log in anymore. Stupid greedy company.

Author: BadlandsAllicat
Body: I'm so disappointed I now have to pay for this app. I wanted to have a good moment and look at how far I've come by looking through my YEARS of tracking and now it is all gone because I can't afford to pay.

Author: Siân M
Body: Used the app when it first came out and deleted it when I found I didn't need it anymore. Meaning it worked brilliantly!! Downloaded it again today and wowza has it changed for the worse. Bit uncomfortable giving my phone number to recieve a plan I don't even want. The old version didn't require that. All I hoped was to be able to use the app to rationalise my thoughts and track my mood. Very disappointed :((( will have to find a replacement now

Author: Jamie Jacopelle
Body: Same as everyone else, disappointed by changes. I hadn't used the app in a year, almost exactly a year. Every January and February my depression gets bad, and I wanted to track my moods again like I had been for a few years. Now you can't do anything except subscribe to talk to a therapist and everything is paid. I have a therapist already, I was just trying to continue mood tracking. I'm so disappointed. Now I have to find a new app to use.

Author: Allison Stickel
Body: I used to use this app all the time. The AI "I'm feeling..." Chat was a great way for me to journal how I felt and take the next appropriate steps to feel better. However now it is a money-grabbing paywall. They obviously don't care about helping people anymore, they just want profit. Which, I would be willing to pay up to $10 one time just to have that AI chat feature again. But it looks like they would rather be like every other therapy subscription that preys on the depressed and anxious.

Author: Wolf Money
Body: I am also a member of "I used to love this app, but now..." I can't even login now without having to answer a thousand personal questions that apparently will be used to help you find a counselor/therapist for a weekly fee. I don't need a counselor or therapist, I need an app to help me in between my appointments with my already-established Healthcare team. Huge disappointment to have seen this app shifted in the way that it has. It was really helpful the way that it was. Boo.

Author: kamilla omarova
Body: changed from 4 to 1. terrible update. i genuinely liked your app before

Author: Jasper Zukaziki
Body: Changed from a 5 to 1 star review. I loved this app so much for so long. I had the app to track my mental health and take with the AI all of the last 5 years and really needed it today. I loved this app so much before. Could have just as easy made a separate app for the paid therapy and kept this one for the free tracker on its own, right? Maybe a cheap subscription for the AI and tracker for a few bucks.

Author: Joy Chang
Body: Three years ago, this really helps me get though a hard time. However, now I'm super frustrated when I cannot fall asleep and trying to get some voice leading me to meditate but found that this app ask me to answer lots of question before accessing to any function and I still don't get the solution to my problem. Truly upset. It seems everything changed. I appreciate what you guys are doing right now but this is not the youper what I was expecting.

Author: Fearie Star
Body: Changed my review from 4 stars to 2. I just opened the app after a year to look through my past chats with the AI and saw that EVERY SINGLE THING was paywalled! I wasn't expecting that! I wish Youper would have communicated this change to users, because that's really important after using the app for free for 3 years. I understand that they need to make money, but I wish there were more supscription options. Especially for people who don't want a therapist and just want the AI.

Author: Sarah Simon
Body: good idea. glad to have found this app. its well done ans growing as I see. thank you. New entry: I am very disapointed. After all this time, every Meditation is locked unless you pay. Not even the once I used every day are available. I have been using Youper for years now.

Author: Lee
Body: Free version gone?

Author: C Thom
Body: I get what they're doing with the new changes, but I really liked how the app used to be. I'll be getting rid of it because it doesn't work for me personally, but I hope others get more out of it.

Author: The Lorax
Body: I really liked it!

Author: Prokriti Basu
Body: Disappointed that they have gotten rid of the AI. The previous version of Youper was incredibly useful to me and I could have used that form of it again now. Disappointed that just communicating with the AI is no longer an option. Devastating.

Author: Kevin Michaelis
Body: After having a mental health crisis and ending up in the ER I decided I really needed to track my mood. I remember this app and I'm extremely hurt to see it now asked for money (I'm a broke college student) and human interaction. I will miss this app

Author: Nyan Cat
Body: app got ruined go next

Author: dorichoi choi
Body: what the hell is this, i always used this app, it was really good and suddenly absolutely every feature requires subscription (which is expensive af btw) I'm uninstalling right now i understand you need income to keep the app going, but this much? it's plain ridiculous

Author: Ash White
Body: I'm so upset. I went to get access to this app again and get back on track and now I can't use the main functions without a subscription? You guys are the absolute worst for taking advantage of people with mental illnesses. No one wants your generic apology sitting on a paywall.

Author: Rebecca Stoebe
Body: Like others I used this app for a long time and loved it. Now everything is subscription based. If they had even 1/10 of the features that used to be free still available for free (symptom tracking, ai conversation/diary, mood tracking, meditation, etc) this would be a 5/5 app. But everything is behind a paywall, which sucks. I already have some of the things offered here (ie a therapist), so to pay for everything in a bundle as the only option is a bummer.

Author: Jackson Kulinski
Body: I used to use this app to map my mood and track triggers and it genuinely helped. The app now has no free options and has moved completely behind a paywall. It is devastating and was done with no warning. The $36 a month is too high to ask for an AI service. I am fairly certain no one asked for this.

Author: Aleksandra Boykova
Body: 2019: Использую приложение уже около года и очень им довольна. Помогает сесть, выдохнуть и переосмыслить своё состояние, находить связи между внешним и внутренним, а также отследить настроение и уровень тревоги и др. Очень советую) Апдейт: Увы, не смогла даже посмотреть приложение без соглашения на ежемесячный план подписки. Плюс сильно переключились чисто на аудиторию США. Печально

Author: Aleksandra Boykova
Body: 2019: Использую приложение уже около года и очень им довольна. Помогает сесть, выдохнуть и переосмыслить своё состояние, находить связи между внешним и внутренним, а также отследить настроение и уровень тревоги и др. Очень советую) Апдейт: Увы, не смогла даже посмотреть приложение без соглашения на ежемесячный план подписки. Плюс сильно переключились чисто на аудиторию США. Печально

Author: Elena Cazacu
Body: This app had helped me tremendously just for the simple feature where I could write down my feelings. A feature now costing $85. Seeing that I can't use any of the features anymore was very disheartening and has affected my mental health in a very bad way. I guess the ones that are not privileged don't deserve help. Not a single human response to new comments. Only bots. Maybe you don't care about people's well-being as much as you advertise it, sadly. All we ever wanted was discreet help.

Author: Paula N
Body: I used to like a lot this app, it was very practical and helpful. I just realised I can't do anything at all anymore without paying. I completely understand you need monetary support to keep this service, but I can't find even one thing I can still do without subscribing. I wished that at least the emotions tracking was still free. I can't even see the factors/tags for each emotion, nor the monitoring of anxiety etc I had from before the update. It also works quite slow. I'll have to delete it:(

Author: Adam O'Neill
Body: Used to be 5* now 1* as they have moved to a subscription model. All my data and information from the past is now inaccessible. Pity.

Author: Jamie Waldock
Body: I used to LOVE this app. The mood tracker with triggers and the AI therapist prompts were AMAZING. They have since updated to require a subscription and a human therapist assigned to you. Not what I was looking for. Huge bummer.

Author: Jessika Osborne
Body: I used this app a few years ago during a tough patch and it really helped. I really loved seeing the progress or backwards slips. I wanted to use it again, but it has totally changed. I am so disappointed. The old version was so easy, but the fees and the therapy really doesn't suit well with me.

Author: Timothy Kimmel
Body: Used to be free to use the bot. Now you can't even do that without paying. Disappointing.

Author: MistyJadeYT
Body: I absolutely loved this app before they decided to put all of their features behind a paywall. I might have supported if they ONLY charged for the therapy service, but they decided to charge for all of their features we used to get for free. The response people are getting basically says they are choosing not to sell users information....excuse me what? There are other ways to make money to keep running that do not include paywalls OR sells users info. Uninstalling.

Author: Shelly Evans
Body: What on earth has happened to this app 😔 used to be my go to mental health app and now it's absolutely useless... uninstalled but where do I go now??? Thanks for nothing 🙃

Author: A Google user
Body: I said in 2018 that "it really helps you gain perspective, and I've been able to feel better about myself - even on days when I'm not the most cheerful." A lot has changed since then because Youper's business model has changed, so now the time I spent with it and any data I had is now behind a paywall. I deleted the app in disgust. I have no doubt in my mind that it's still a very helpful app, but as someone returning to it in this state when I needed it the most... I'm honestly disappointed.

Author: Melissa Sutherland
Body: Downloaded this app to try it out, and it makes you put in your phone number which I found a bit sketchy. It also "needs" access to all of your Google information. I didn't even finish setting up a profile before my phone started getting bombarded with spam phone calls. I have had to block 10 different phone numbers in less than 24 hours. Definitely not worth it.

Author: Paweł Kowalski
Body: The app no longer does what it's supposed to do. Rather than emotion tracking tool, it is online therapy.

Author: Victor B
Body: Youper has changed a lot. It once was a great app for tracking emotions but even that is a paid feature now. I am afraid I won't be downloading it again unless they bring the old app back

Author: Xin Yi
Body: Good for mood tracking if you're using the free version. Would like the app to keep a conversation that hasn't been completed on hold so I can continue it later, as sometimes I'll accidentally exit the app mid-typing but the app auto ended the conversation, leaving me without closure.

Author: Adri
Body: So tem em inglês 🙄

Author: A Google user
Body: Just wanted to see my old logs, from a few years ago, but you have to leave the app and go to a website to even sign in now. Wack:/

Author: Weronika Duś
Body: Can't log in without phone number, and there's only US prefix. How to log in if I don't live in US? I used to have this app before, when it didn't require phone number, and it was helpful, but now I can't use it.

Author: Taylor Doner
Body: Absolutely devastated. The AI of this app was incredibly helpful in mood tracking, gratitude, and thought insight. I knew about the update and how it completely changed the app. I resisted it and continued using the old version long ago. I forgot today and accidentally updated all my apps. This AI was perfect, especially if you like reflecting and not necessarily want to speak with a real person. I would sign up for a subscription just for the AI feature.

Author: Lizeanne St Pierre
Body: I wish that I could rate this zero stars. I hate the new changes. And no, it's not because 'I can't handle change' as was the response to another similar comment. this app helped my teen who was not open to live talk therapy but was willing to use an app. Now I can't access the app part but have to input a lot of personal information only to get to 'talk to a therapist' or 'get medication'. there are live people where I live who can do this if we want to access it. Bring back the app only portion please - I'll pay for it. but not this.

Author: Brittany BrittAny
Body: This app literally changed my life in 2018/2019. I'm so sad to see how much they have changed. :( Re installed to see how I could continue to improve my life and will be uninstalling right away. Please give us the AI back!!

Author: Anne Sharifah
Body: This rating is for the previous version where you just talked to a chat AI and document your mood daily - the version without therapists or anything paid

Author: gattiina
Body: i relied on this app for two years, uninstalled it for storage a while back, and just redownloaded it, only to find the entire app had changed. i dont want to talk to real people, i want the AI back

Author: Tora Jernberg
Body: The app had ever since 2019 helped me through many tuff times, it was easy, quick, great and felt like the AI was intelligent at what it did, and i loved how personal it was. But now? It's a mess, no more AI chatting, and you have to pay for your mental illness! Why did they so suddenly make a huge update? I thought finally, an app that doesn't depend money on the users mental health, guess I was wrong. It was nice while it lasted, but I'm really disappointed.

Author: Fan Plan
Body: I used to have this app a few years ago and it helped me greatly when I was having problems. But now you have to pay for it and I just can't afford it at all. I'm a teenager that barely has time to work and am generally stressed out by school and my social life. This used to be my outlet and the AI was helpful for helping me de stress. Now when I see this all I feel is ugh.

Author: Áine Rickard
Body: Used to be free, so disappointed

Author: Angela Pacelli
Body: After reading some articles, I was incredibly disappointed to see that this app has become one that involves payment and talking to an actual person, rather than being free and talking to AI when I had downloaded and launched it. If I wanted to talk to an actual person and have to pay for service, I would use something like BetterHelp (which I don't trust with a ten-foot pole due to some of stuff behind the scenes) or 7cups. You've lost a potential user.

Author: Piia Ahokas
Body: The what? While changing phone, this app has lost all my user data and put up a paywall.

Author: Doody Tco
Body: Where is youper? Why do I have to talk with real people and pay for it? Why is nothing free anymore?! This is quite disappointing

Author: Steevee Pirshafiey
Body: I used to really rely on this app...it's completely changed. Bummer they don't have a plan for the AI service only. Uninstalling. Try My Possible Self app. It's a lot like what Youper used to be.

Author: Gabi Gallagher
Body: No free version useable. Pretty much forces you to get premium. They need to at least offer a free trial if that's the case... Disappointed

Author: Michal Kasprzak
Body: There's a bug in account creation which prevents me from entering my phone number correctly (country code is always +1). I cannot proceed from there, which makes the app unusable

Author: Steevee Pirshafiey
Body: I used to really rely on this app...it's completely changed. Bummer they don't have a plan for the AI service only. Uninstalling.

Author: Marta Łusiarczyk
Body: I used this app for a long time and now i cant because you have to pay for everything

Author: Probably Riivo
Body: Literally unusable without paid subscription. Don't know why it's even listed as a free app since it's not anymore.

Author: Constant Creations
Body: This used to be a wonderful app that helped me so much. I am coming back to it seeing a money hungry monster. I hate what this app has become like I see many others have. It's not about helping anyone anymore. The free AI was all we needed that offered tools for us to get better. Now it requires all of this set up and subscription?? Ridiculous I have now changed my 5 star to a 1.

Author: A Google user
Body: It helped me quite a lot when I was having my crisis and battles, but now that it has a subscription, I no longer can use it. Whoever wants to subscribe to it, they can do it, it's quite a nice app that helps you keep track of your moods, but I will be uninstalling it.

Author: Lore Ly
Body: Wdym talking to a robot isn't free anymore?? Dafak???

Author: Riley Conlon
Body: Kinda annoying they don't have a basic level subscription for the AI and mood tracking. It's too expensive for a basic level self help app

Author: Weronika Duś
Body: Can't log in without phone number, and there's only US prefix. How to log in if I don't live in US? I used to have this app before, when it didn't require phone number, and it was helpful, but now I can't use it.

Author: Ash Watkins
Body: Sadly, I've had to edit this review. I once gave the app 5 stars. I loved what Youper was, as it was so helpful to me. Now it's no longer a free AI mental health app, it's a paid telehealth app all about profit. I can't access anything on it anymore, not even simple mood tracking or 2-minute meditations. It destroyed everything that made it so innovative. Now it's just another money-driven trash app. So disappointed. Really, overwhelmingly disappointed. Shame on you.

Author: Just a girl from Wisconsin
Body: Was an amazing and clarifying tool for keeping track of my mental illnesses and overall mental health. Now nothing can be done without payments. Very disappointing, I will have to find a new app that cares more about it's users than it's profits.

Author: Ciara Ben
Body: I used to love this app. It helped me through so many hard times. But now it is completely changed. I miss having the AI to talk to, and I never wanted to talk to an actual person. That was the whole point of this app. Now you have to give personal information. I want the AI to come back.

Author: Christopher Lane
Body: Used to be good. All features require a subscription now.

Author: Jonathan Townsend
Body: This is my favorite therapy chatbot, and I'm happy to see they've finally monitized it so it can keep getting maintained and developed. But having to pay a minimum of $45 to unlock everything or pay nothing to get nothing is kind of silly, there should at least be something available for free. And maybe something available between the free and ultimate tier. (Similar to what competitors do.) Maybe I'm just not the target audience anymore. Ah well!

Author: Codrin Dragusanu
Body: I gave it one star, because unless you have a phone number which starts with +1 you can't use it.

Author: Justyna Filar
Body: A good app, it helped calm down many times. I particularly liked the mindfulness exercises. The mood tracking feature is very clear. The full version is pricey, yes. But I used the app for a very long time and because it helped me, I paid for a yearly subscription (in February). Cancelled recently as I cannot afford the next payment. The subscription status says it expires in Feb 2022, yet premium stuff is locked for me. Not using it anymore anyway, but I should be able to until Feb, I guess?

Author: Anna Niedbala
Body: Good idea poorly executed. I think this app has a lot of valuable features in theory. But they don't really hold up in practice. I've often found myself more upset after interacting with the bot than I was when I started because the conversation options are inflexible and there's no way to break out of the chat if it's 'misunderstood' what I wrote. For example, I recently logged that I was feeling upset because I couldn't sleep and it kept telling me to be more specific about what my goal was.

Author: Dominik Brault
Body: L'application est géniale, ou plutôt, elle l'était. Jusqu'à ce qu'elle devienne payante. 7.44$/mois.. J'ai bcp aimé ses fonctions d'auto-évaluation, les "check-in" quotidiens avec les conseils que youper donne. Cest une très belle app. (En anglais seulement.)

Author: Lottie Day
Body: Used the app for years and loved it, now you have to pay just to have an account. Mental health support is increasingly difficult to find and impossibly expensive for many people, and to have it reserved for those who can afford it is totally counterproductive. Will be uninstalling 👎

Author: Akshay T
Body: Its too much expensive

Author: Grace Gadston
Body: I loved this app but I took a break after the birth of my little girl and now I'm feeling the need to start journaling again.... Where has the Youper chat bot gone? This was the most useful, helpful and genuinely soothing feature. Right now the app just feels like Insight Timer, but worse.

Author: simon kruger
Body: Suddenly locking everyrhing behind a paywall was an unfortunate design change. Bit disappointed, as prior to this you could still get value from the app as a free service, with the paid option being an additional benefit. Removing all free functionality on a mental health app seems a bit exploitative :(

Author: Chicken Nugget
Body: I did appreciate this app before it updated to where you have to pay, before it was helpful now its confusing. I can't even get into my account without paying the subscription thing. I think a couple adds would be fine, our info gets sold anyways. I know they need to get paid but a feel they could have done it differently. Not everyone can afford to pay for help or access to it, but almost everyone needs it. This was a accessible and free way to get it and now it's been taken away

Author: Sameer
Body: used to be a very good app, now it is asking for mandatory phone number and also there are bugs.

Author: Hess Rombaut
Body: I have youper for many years and today i only get lots of problems whats wrong

Author: Grace Gadston
Body: I love this app but took a break after the birth of my little girl and now I'm feeling the need to start journaling again. But where has the Youper chat bot gone? This was the most useful, helpful and genuinely soothing feature.

Author: Cryptid
Body: This app used to be the only thing keeping me sane and now I can't even use it the app is pretty much usless now so I will be deleting it

Author: Blue Wizard
Body: I wish they had the AI and assessments were still available for free. I feel like getting people in and then pulling the rug out from under them with fees is a really shady business practice, especially where mental health is concerned. Most of the app's formerly free functionality can be replaced with a journal and looking up assessment forms yourself.

Author: Tövisi Otto
Body: I have been using this for more than 2 years now, and it has helped a lot to accept my feelings and to discover who I am.

Author: Brittney Sosa
Body: Really disappointed in the changes made in this app. So much of it used to be free and the AI chat + health monitoring were incredibly useful to me during moments of intense anxiety. Now, they've completely sold out. Who is paying $9/month for a service that used to be free?? I have a therapist already, why is youper trying to be BetterHelp when it was unique and helpful pre-update? I've uninstalled the app and moved on to WoeBot.

Author: Michelle
Body: Was the most amazing app I have ever downloaded! NOW it's a money making app, like all the others:(

Author: Rita Elise Martinez
Body: **2021 update** ⭐/5 This app used to be free and simple. I can no longer afford to use it. Youper's AI chat feature was extremely helpful to me in the past, but there's no way I can pay 45$/week for access.. I am grateful that it let's me see my old journal entries though. **original 2018 review** ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐/5 This app is amazing. It uses similar therapy techniques to what I've learned through my own therpay experience.

Author: Jena Kaske
Body: Nice way to capatalize on mental illness and self therapy. I was using this app to track my moods and mental illness, and now you need a premium membership to do anything, paying about $10 per month. This could be someone's 13th reason why, poor people have a high suicide rate, but at least you're getting paid.

Author: Baily Hannon
Body: Downloaded. I need to create an account but it will not load after I click "sign up using your Google account". I only want to sign up using my Google account. All the other sign up options work.. Tried for the last 2 days. I can't do anything or see what's available..

Author: First budgie
Body: Another stupid app that doesn't say anything about fees until after you sign up. This is just a stupid scam to get your info don't bother !

Author: Aneta Nowakowska
Body: It would be great if not for the price....But it's pretty clear developers are more interested in money than anything else. Read other people opinions. They even removed free functionalities to force free version users to pay for it. It's a shame..

Author: Kiki Mowery
Body: So disappointed that I can't access my old mood tracking data without paying now

Author: Swiftest Odin30
Body: Can't even access the account I already have because the app is behind a paywall... I used to use this app for years and now I can't even access it because of a money drain smh what a shame cost prohibitive bahooy nobody cares about people's well-being anymore so many memories down the drain

Author: Aneta Nowakowska
Body: It would be great if not for the price....

Author: Google User
Body: Fantastic app for mental and emotional self care. Essential to actively monitor my mental health. Using it regularly 2.5 yrs now and app is always getting better. Its a wellness toolbox that created massive changes in my life, also saved me several disasters and got me safely out of several emergency events. Cannot recommend it more.

Author: Alice Coco
Body: To be honest, I like better before the huge update. The dialogue with youper part was really fun, like talking to a nonjudgmental person... before the developers somehow decided to take that out. Now I barely use it anymore.. A shame though, I used to love this app.

Author: Megan Connolly
Body: This app is so useful, it helps me so much

Author: Aidan Smith
Body: Although I've been a user for years, I hadn't opened this app for the past few weeks and was shocked to discover today that everything is behind a paywall, most notably the mood monitoring quizzes/health tracking. Having a simple mood journal in one place like Youper was amazing, and it's a huge disappointment to see it become a subscription feature. I understand the team needs to be profitable to keep doing this, and I respect the hustle, but they could have left us a few crumbs lol.

Author: jay g
Body: I wanted to go back to this app since I'm struggling and it had helped so much but it's not free anymore and I don't have the money money pay for this AND my therapy and meds. Such a shame too.

Author: Antony Gaming
Body: Well this app became useless

Author: Alexis Dugo
Body: Used to be such a good self help app 😞

Author: Marino Sabijan
Body: What did you do with the app? It was better before

Author: Mary Wang
Body: Everything is paid for

Author: Amanda Rose
Body: Glitched when I attempted to create an account and now, even after uninstalling and reinstalling, I am unable to login.

Author: Giada Salvan
Body: What the hell happened with this app?! It used to be so welcoming and user-friendly, but now... online therapy and medication whatever? Like... long time ago I installed this app to track my mood and help me understand my emotions. If I wanted an app for therapy I would've downloaded something else! I'm sorry but I just can't get around the app anymore and don't know what to do with it. Uninstalling 👋🏻

Author: Sh dhar
Body: if anyone is looking for alternative as this app is bit costly download RiseUp -AI based Therapy for Anxiety and Depression

Author: Gen Glon
Body: The free version doesn't really let you do anything. Need to pay to actually use the app

Author: Kitty
Body: теперь здесь абсолютно ВСЁ платно. хотя нет, бесплатный стандарный опросник на депрессию 😐 ну нет никакого смысла продолжать им пользоваться. просто ВСЕ платно, офигеть
Translated Body: now absolutely EVERYTHING is paid here. although no, the free standard depression questionnaire 😐 well, there is no point in continuing to use it. just EVERYTHING is paid, go nuts

Author: Kitty
Body: теперь здесь абсолютно ВСЁ платно. хотя нет, бесплатный стандарный опросник на депрессию 😐 ну нет никакого смысла продолжать им пользоваться. просто ВСЕ платно, офигеть

Author: Derek Brewster
Body: I used to use this app all the time to track my moods and emotions, but now no features are available without the paid subscription. Very disappointing RE: The generic response I expected. The cost is the slightest of problems. It seems like the whole app has been redesigned 'to make money' not to help people. This app had many unique free helpful features such as the interactive AI and mood tracking and now it seems like it is just trying to emulate Better Help. If you really read the other reviews, you'll see that many users have been finding it difficult to navigate the app as well. There are many ways for apps to generate revenue besides selling users' information. I get that the app is a business, but don't disguise greed as altruism.

Author: Derek Brewster
Body: I used to use this app all the time to track my moods and emotions, but now no features are available without the paid subscription. Very disappointing

Author: Jelena Nikolic
Body: This is so not fair, why can you use it only if you are from USA? When I check that I do not live in USA I can not proceede

Author: Adam King
Body: (edit) The developer responds saying that the money goes to the production team, but there's better ways to monetize. they also didn't respond to other criticisms I gave, only that. If you're not looking for backlash, don't fully monetize something you released for free. You tested it on the poor so that when it was proven "good" you could sell it to the better off. Mental healthcare is already expensive. I'm not going to pay for something that didn't know how to stop when it was ahead.

Author: Nicole Ventura
Body: I finally made sense of the new UI design & was beginning to enjoy the app again, however, since adding the new subscription plans, Youper has taken an even bigger nosedive. Even at a reduced price, $4.95/wk for a professional to prescribe you medication, the app is overpriced. It used to be $44/yr for their AI chat (before they even updated the UI, which was confusing at first for many). Now, it's $9/wk for access to those same features.

Author: Miss Nightmare
Body: I was using this for more than a few years now. Though last year i had to delete this app because somehow after the update i couldn't use it unless i paid for it. No free version. Then after half a year i tried again and up until now it was okay. Aaand now I had to delete the app again because i can't access stuff unless i change my subscription which is only available to people living in US. I'm not from US. Sad that i won't be able to use the app..

Author: Kitty
Body: теперь здесь абсолютно ВСЁ платно. хотя нет, бесплатный стандарный опросник на депрессию 😐 ну нет никакого смысла продолжать им пользоваться. просто ВСЕ платно, офигеть
Translated Body: now absolutely EVERYTHING is paid here. although no, the free standard depression questionnaire 😐 well, there is no point in continuing to use it. just EVERYTHING is paid, go nuts

Author: Lily Crimsoncandy
Body: This app used to be my lifeline. Something simple to help me reflect on what affects my mood and mental state. It would help me notice patterns and I myself would be able to navigate out of my slumps. BUT NOW, it has become confusing, frustrating, and no longer helpful for free. I wish I could rate it 0 stars. And I wish the app had anything useful to offer for free, like it did before. And hey I wouldn't mind paying for a subscription, if the prices weren't $45-$55 per WEEK. Very disappointing.

Author: Anja Müller
Body: Die App wurde leider durch die Monetarisierung weitestgehendst zerstört. Der hervorragende KI Chatbot existiert noch, aber leider gut versteckt. Meine frühere Bewertung hier war 5 Sterne und eine uneingeschränkte Empfehlung. So wie die App jetzt strukturiert ist, kann ich nur sagen dass ich hoffe, dass eine App vergleichbar mit der ursprünglichen Version wieder auf den Markt kommt.
Translated Body: Unfortunately, the app was largely destroyed by monetization. The excellent AI chatbot still exists, but unfortunately well hidden. My previous rating here was 5 stars and an unreserved recommendation. The way the app is structured now, I can only say that I hope that an app similar to the original version will come back on the market.

Author: Sam Glines
Body: Horrible!! This app used to be such a useful tool that allowed you to become familiar with the gauge of your emotions and to work yourself through your thoughts! I can only hope someone with a brain can recreate what this app used to be. (I'd pay a flat fee to use that!) I came back and reinstalled it excited to use it again - what a slap in the face! Nothing like the original - huge paywalls. The only thing good about it is how easy it is to delete your account.

Author: Adam King
Body: Awful Proof that Altruism is Dead This app saved my mental health at one point. Then it slowly became more and more impersonal, cutting out simplicity, before finally shoving a paywall between mental health and the poor who need it. Will never, ever use this app again. Was going to recommend it to a friend in need but because she's broke, as one often is in a crisis, she can't use it. Disgusting. Developers should be ashamed.

Author: TheKennyWorld
Body: I don't recommend anyone to take drugs via an app.

Author: Cynthia
Body: Originally 5 stars and much appreciated, I haven't used it for a while. After 3 emails in less than an hour pushing drugs, I installed the app to delete my account and was immediately greeted by more drug offers. The spam is outrageous, and the drug pushing is infinitely worse. I thought the whole point of this app was to help YOU manage things. With all the drug adverts, anyone who opens this app might be convinced they need medication immediately. Sad that a good app has turned to trash.

Author: Jane Watson-Brown
Body: I'm so disappointed. I used Youper for free a few years ago when I was going through a very difficult time. I've had a tough week, remembered Youper and now I have to pay. Could there be a graded approach to what you offer? I don't live in the US, so some of the things Youper provides may not apply to me.

Author: Timmothias Johnsanos
Body: Youper was a very nice 👌👌 tool, but I'm not the type of person who can commit time every day to use it. It has changed a lot in the past 3 years, and I ended up only using it to take the health surveys once in a while.

Author: Kelly Garcia
Body: I used to love this app, but ever since it's changed format, it's near-impossible to navigate. I used to go on it to process negative feelings, but now it doesn't give you options to help manage them any more, it just offers to set you up with one of their therapists. I live in the EU & have access to cheaper therapy in-person, this option being pushed in my face all the time is annoying. It's a shame because this app has really helped me a lot in the past.

Author: Charis Jordan
Body: This app used to be great just to track your mood and help you out when you're having a bad day but, ever since it became a mental health service for therapy and meds, it just went downhill from there. In fact, Youper's original charm was that it wasn't a mental health service but a SELF-HELP app. Also having to pay for nearly everything is ridiculous for people, like me, who have little to no money to spend on services like this...

Author: Angela P
Body: I got the paid version so I can get some affordable help. So far I've only spoken to the ai but it's been very helpful! I recommend giving it a try.

Author: Екатерина Михайлова
Body: Можно, пожалуйста, сделать русский язык? Иначе я не смогу и удалю приложение (
Translated Body: Can I please make it Russian? Otherwise, I will not be able to and will delete the application (

Author: Екатерина Михайлова
Body: Можно, пожалуйста, сделать русский язык? Иначе я не смогу и удалю приложение (

Author: Catherine Vojta
Body: Fake reviews! I just received an email and clicked "Get started for $19" just to see what type of company this is. Whenever I clicked it, it lead me to this app where I noticed a review supposedly from me, WITH today's date on it, that I DID NOT write. It read "very interesting, nice app. I love it."

Author: Tabea Sara
Body: It used to be amazing and it helped me a lot. Now it's completely unusable, you can't even track your mood without paying a lot of money which unfortunately I can't afford.

Author: Chad Ford
Body: It is a great tool 🔧😀.

Author: 57367/3 33x1\6/2
Body: Used this app for 2-3 years and sad to say that it has gone an utter capitalistic trash. It used to be so helpful and easy to navigate (which is great for people with mental health issues as it lessens the overwhelm), but now it turned it a completely different things from what it was. 10 new tabs appeared all offering therapy and medication services - none of those are even available in my region, yet the tabs won't disappear. No new updates on the former free AI therapy chat.All for profit now

Author: Rob Sinclair
Body: Old review: 5 stars - Fantastic app for monitoring your mental health over time and understanding what behaviours make you feel good and not so good! New review: 1 star - Useless. Everything is behind a paywall! Even Basic PHQ-9 Depression Results. This app used to be the only one I needed to monitor my clinical depression... Now, it's impossibly expensive, and not something I can afford on my low income. It's apparent that mental health and wellbeing support is reserved for the wealthiest.

Author: Monserrat Achigar
Body: Excelente. Muy útil y completa, aunque se ha vuelto un poco menos intuitiva.
Translated Body: Excellent. Very useful and comprehensive, although it has become a little less intuitive.

Author: Orion GF
Body: Fake reviews! I just received an email and clicked "Get started for $19" just to see what type of company this is. Whenever I clicked it, it lead me to this app where I noticed a review supposedly from me, WITH today's date on it, that I DID NOT right. It read "very interesting, nice app. I love it."

Author: brentleycourtney
Body: Information should be provided up front if providers aren't available in your area.

Author: Sara Valentine
Body: Previous issues have been fixed, load times are significantly improved. Only problem I have right now is a very persistent update notification that takes me to the Play Store with no available updates.

Author: B Lawrence
Body: So good to have a daily check in.

Author: Sadie Carter
Body: Most of this stuff used to be free, I just wanted to listen to some of the guided meditations, but now I can't because you got greedy. I'm disappointed.

Author: Mathew Veerasammy
Body: Nothing is free content.

Author: Lucas Sencabaugh
Body: As of February 5th this app is unusable. Pixel XL 2. It was great prior. Update sept 5th : The app was a good mood tracker before but now it no longer does that and still has performance issues.

Author: pauline dit
Body: It helped me a lot just talking to youper. Sometimes it was like talking to a friend or writing a journal. Now i have to choose an option, which is already hard enough at some points. However, I feel like every option I choose ends up with meditation or setting goals. Added 2 Stars since there is improvement and the App has helped me a lot the last years

Author: Silver Weston
Body: This app used to have some free content but now they are disgusting money grabbers. Change it to what it used to be, no one asked for a giant pay wall. Can't even use the ai features. Wysa is better than this BS.

Author: Leonor Oliveira
Body: demasiadas funcionalidades pagas, deveria ter mais avaliações disponíveis para fazer acompanhamento do progresso de outros problemas
Translated Body: too many paid features, should have more assessments available to track the progress of other issues

Author: Paoulo (Paoulo)
Body: It does give slightly improved mood and learning but is not highly responsive to individual answers with much nuance.

Author: Le Shaay
Body: Not at all what it used to be. This was my favorite app. I am heartbroken💔

Author: Doctor Derpage
Body: I'm not really a doctor.

Author: Lola Wang
Body: Please bring back old format where youper would greet me as soon as I opened the app. It was very comforting and reassuring and my number one reason for using this app. I get that the app is always evolving but you don't need to fix what isn't broken.

Author: Random Hajile
Body: It's helped me for over 3 years to observe and improve my mental health. I'm able to go back to any time and review my thoughts and feelings to better educate myself about how to improve. I honestly don't know what i'd do without Youper at this point.

Author: Elise Adrian
Body: I was going to renew my subscription cause I'm hitting a rough spot and this app had helped me tremendously in the past. Sadly the price has gone up so much, that I can't afford it. The layout is now completely different and just too complicated for me, when I really enjoyed how easy it used to be and how much relief I could get from a quick chat. Too bad :/

Author: J T
Body: Downloaded it again after a long while and everything that was free is behind a paywall now... I get putting up a paywall for all the new things but if it was once free it should stay free especially the anxiety, depression tests as it was before

Author: A Google user
Body: It was free for me earlier now I can't see my account. I was one of the user at start.

Author: Catherine Symphonie
Body: Great app. Very helpful But...Actually I liked previous versions much more. And now this app became worse, more meditations but more useless stuff. Also it became paid and they removed almost all free features. Subscription is hugely expensive. I can't afford it. I'll wait a bit and if nothing changes I'll have to remove it. I'm very disappointed

Author: Bianca Suddaby
Body: I've used youper on and off of a few years, whenever I felt I wasn't coping very well and it really helped me. But when I downloaded it again today, because I'm struggling again, it was a completely different app. I saw replies to the comments saying that this new version is what people asked for, but couldn't you have just made a second app instead of completely changing youper? I really liked the simplicity of the original and the easy of use is what made me feel like there wasn't any pressure

Author: Alexandra Dronova
Body: barely working, takes ages to load – definitely not a phone's problem, it runs heavy soft. medication ad page as a first in health tab instead of symptoms is extremely annoying. used to love it, now keep using only because I don't want to loose 3 years worth of data.

Author: Dana Sky
Body: I used to use this app daily when it was free now its not free anymore & it's really expensive yesterday I had a panic attack because I couldn't use the app and today also I feel bad I think I will look into other mental health app then this one that's too bad

Author: Reece Dial
Body: App won't load even after clean install.

Author: Kathy Zhang
Body: This was a good app. You opened it, it started chatting with you to take down your mood. Use notifications to check in on your goals. Then they updated it to clutter up the screen and require you to make additional decisions and clicks before using it. And then they started to sell an additional service (it's already a paid app) that takes over the notification system! You can't opt out of not receiving advertisements, so I had to block all notifications. And now it just plain won't open at all.

Author: A Google user
Body: I have been using this app since 2019 and it was a geat tool to use for one's mental health needs, it really helped with my anxiety and panic attacks (5 out of 5 stars). Every since it got a big new update and format, I can't even get the app to load or even login (1 out of 5 stars). I will be uninstalling this app since it continues to not open for my phone (Samsung Galaxy A32 5G). Very unfortunate since the app was so good until they came out with version 10.

Author: Jessi Bee
Body: The new layout is terrible and not helpful at all. Youper doesn't start chatting once you open the app, instead you have to scroll through dozens of options.
