What I loved about Youper was that it was so easy to use, just like talking to a real assistant and supportive without pressure. But now, it took me days to find the usual mood tracking feature. Please change it back - at least the chat at startup. Keep the new categories easily accessible on a separate tab, but give the chat its own tab.

Author: Dawn
Body: *Update*: latest update made the app literally unusable. Can't open the app, not even after restarting my phone. This is an app development issue, not a phone issue. App isn't as good as it used to be. Used to feel like you were talking to a counsellor - now it's just an entirely unhelpful obvious computer. The death of a loved one section merely skims the surface and doesn't help with grief. The app used to help me digest my thoughts by acting as a person, not an obvious AI that is now

Author: Greg Felice
Body: A case study in how to ruin an app.

Author: Emily the strange
Body: Used to be 5 stars

Author: Jennifer Babb
Body: 3 years later edit!! From 5 stars to 3 stars *** I uninstalled because they started push advertising medication and therapy. I can't handle ads on the best mental health app I've ever used *** For anyone who benefits from CBT and DBT, this app is a must-have. The tracking for moods, symptoms, and changes is the best I've seen so far. The support team is fantastic. Highly recommend 👍

Author: Paulina Sadelska
Body: To use it effectively, you must pay 150 $ per year! I don't have access to my data from 2,5 years! I can't use it now, thanks Youper

Author: Hunter Robb
Body: After over 1000 days using this app I'm uninstalling. What was once a great, lightweight mood tracking app has become bogged down and rather difficult to navigate and use. If they've decided to go in the direction of providing mental health assistance through the app, that's all well and good, but the fact that they pedal it so hard is a complete turn off (I've been receiving emails and notifications nearly daily about their new services). This change marks the fall of a once great app.

Author: Cristian Murari
Body: I don't like the new layout, i prefered it when youper greeted you and I love how accessible and well explained the personality DNA was. I'mma search for an alternative. I'll give it 2 starts because you still get a lot for free.

Author: Jello K
Body: I have been using this app for more than 2 years, and it's helped me cope with my feelings a lot. It used to have a sort of MBTI test? But it seems in the recent update it was removed (?) I'm not sure but I can't find it. I'd like to ask if it's possible to add it back again? It was nice

Author: Ling Xin Yong
Body: I downloaded the app because it seemingly has good review but after downloading there seem to be limited feature for my country. However the premium has set it and I was already charged by the time I canceled. It was for a year of sgd120 over dollars! They said they could refund it but 2 weeks later there is still nothing, emailed the customer service twice but no response. Be very cautious with this app, the way they take your money is like they cannot wait to rip you off.

Author: Robyn Youngberg
Body: Unfortunately I tried to use the app again. And while not bad I just couldn't get behind the new interface. I thinknits just me and the app does have a lot on it... I just cant get into the setup. I have ADHD and FASD. So I preferred the original set up becisevit was super easy to get into and this one requires more from me to get what I need from it. Not for me but not horrible either. ♡

Author: CİHAN KAYA
Body: Herşeyi ingilizce ingilizcen yoksa indirme benim gibi
Translated Body: Do not download everything in English if you do not have English like me

Author: Gerard Nicholls
Body: Not a single feature available without paying for the subscription. Bye.

Author: V
Body: Theres a huge pay wall for most of the info so if you dont have a lot of money this is not the app for you

Author: Macey Mitchell
Body: Traumatic to say the least. ive used youper as my go to help for two years since im not able to afford quality or consistent therapy and today my app updated and everything is gone. every past entry deleted. the last two years of my mental health journey erased. vanished as if there was nothing. this experience has traumatized me from trusting anykind of mental health app to be there a stable. thanks for ruining a good thing

Author: Aghnia Hafisah
Body: Why did the developers change all the layouts? :( The AI that greets you right after you open the app was so good for checking in—Youper can tell us about other facilities on other tabs like how the tab usually change after a check-in. Or at least have the Check-In on a separate tab, not just a button among SO many options? The UX is worse tbh... The load time when switching tabs is also so slow now. Seeing how many recent bad reviews from long-time users are, I guess I'm not alone

Author: Gabbie Timmers
Body: Used to have this app to log my emotions and get a better understanding of my mental state. Upon redownloading the app I see it has been reduced to a cash grab. A total pity.

Author: Tövisi Otto
Body: I have been using this for more than a year now, and it has helped a lot to accept my feelings. However the new update (9.x) kinda broke the jurnaling feature and the ui is laggy so I went back to 8.06

Author: Carlee Peterson
Body: So sad to see it went paid.... I used to use Youper a great deal. I was depressed and was frankly desperate. It's free chat sessions, despite being all automated, really helped me to reframe my thought processes While it did have its limits, I found this app valuable. I got to a good spot and uninstalled it, grateful for its help. Now, in a dark stretch again, I went to re-download it only to find it has gone paid. And I get that. But it was a beacon for those who can't afford therapy.

Author: Ayla Snow
Body: This app was an amazing tool that kept me sane through some horrible bouts of depression, anxiety, paranoia, panic attacks, and other miserable situations. Talking to Youper (an "AI") was the closest thing to regular psychotherapy I've ever experienced. For those of you that miss when that was the primary function of this app, I have a suggestion. Search online for an apk (installable app file) of this app at version 8.06. That is right before they massively overhauled it. ✌

Author: Mario Medina
Body: When it will be available in Spanish?

Author: Karen Mitchell
Body: This app used to be an awesome free mental health check where I could keep track of my emotions etc. Now it's been updated and more and more features added, which just made it confusing. Plus now you have to pay a subscription cost, which is high. I have since deleted the app.

Author: mudslide crisis
Body: Generally a very good app! I used to track my emotions here all the time. Since the huge overhaul though I'm having a hard time with it. It just doesn't feel as personal and caring as before. It's often too draining to think about what I want to "talk" to Youper about before entering the conversation. Now, in order to actually talk to Youper, I have to choose a topic, a solution, an emotion even before I know much about it and in which case Youper used to help me figure that out.

Author: Xin Yi
Body: (issue has been responded)

Author: 廖子庭
Body: 真的為我的心靈帶來不一樣的覺察，非常的棒！
Translated Body: It really brings a different awareness to my mind, it's great!

Author: veronika
Body: мне очень нравилось это приложение. пользовалась им с 2019. это было одно из немногих, хороших бесплатных приложений. но после последнего обновления весь прогресс пропал. также теперь за все нужно платить. как студент, я не могу оплатить полный пакет. к сожалению, придется прощаться с youper.
Translated Body: I really liked this app. have been using it since 2019. it was one of the few good free apps. but after the last update all progress is gone. also now you have to pay for everything. as a student, I cannot pay for the full package. unfortunately have to say goodbye to youper.

Author: veronika m.
Body: мне очень нравилось это приложение. пользовалась им с 2019. это было одно из немногих, хороших бесплатных приложений. но после последнего обновления весь прогресс пропал. также теперь за все нужно платить. как студент, я не могу оплатить полный пакет. к сожалению, придется прощаться с youper.

Author: Invalid Argument
Body: Big pharma entry funnel. Don't waste your time.

Author: Zsuzsmoux
Body: This app used to be super helpful for me to track my mental health journey. Now, with the latest updates, I can't see my progress in the monitoring section anymore without paying. Putting features that were completely free before behind a paywall is a really shady tactic. I also had loads of notes on how I was feeling on particular days and all of those are gone now too. I'm so disappointed.

Author: Emelie S.
Body: I used to really enjoy this app and use it a lot, but unfortunately it seems to have moved on from what it used to be. :( Edit: Thank you to the dev team for their response! I actually wouldn't mind paying for Youper, but I think the user experience isn't worth it, unfortunately. I really liked how Youper was before with the easy to use interface and the chat. I actually wrote to the team years ago saying how much I liked the app and that it would be a service I would be willing to pay for!

Author: DaddyMac BigDaddy
Body: Was perfect back when it was usable. Now every is behind a 100 buck a year paywall. Absolutely heartbreaking and has actively damaged my mental health progress.

Author: Nash MacDonald
Body: Prior to the version 10 update, this was the best mental health app on the playstore. Without a paywall, I was able to track my mental health reliably and could activly see results from the app. After the version 10 update, every useful feature has been blocked behind a $109.99 a year paywall. Can't simulate a therapeutic text session, Can't use any of the guided exercises, Can't even use the mental illness monitoring. I didn't want a medication delivery service, I wanted simple discreet help.

Author: Hsin-Yi Chen
Body: 除了人格特質測驗(MIBT) 外的功能都要收費，不知道是bug還是本來就這麼設計，幾年前第一次使用時，大部分功能都是免費的，當時mental assessment功能(和chat bot對話，會引導使用者做正念練習)也是免費的 I'm not sure if it is intended but all features (except personality test) are locked and require additional payment(full access). I still remember this app used to be free for most of its features.
Translated Body: Except for the personality test (MIBT), all functions are charged. I don’t know if it’s a bug or it’s originally designed as such. When I first used it a few years ago, most of the functions were free. , Will guide users to do mindfulness exercises) is also free I'm not sure if it is intended but all features (except personality test) are locked and require additional payment(full access). I still remember this app used to be free for most of its features.

Author: Monique van de Beek
Body: This app literally helped me so many times through rough times but since the update in seems like everything changed. I recommended it to my partner but he didn't even get the same functionalities as I have (both free version). I was so happy with this app but now it just seems like another commercial health app. Such a shame to see something so special go.

Author: Emelie S.
Body: I used to really enjoy this app and use it a lot, but unfortunately it seems to have moved on from what it used to be. :(

Author: David McAleese
Body: Used to love this app. It felt like it was checking in and I felt like I was able to sort out my feelings. I really miss the way it checked in. Now I just get brought to an add screen. Sold out to the point of not even being the same app.

Author: Lunette Emelie
Body: it has now paywalls everywhere. i do not recommend

Author: Makaela M
Body: Update: i am so disappointed in this app but have been using it for three years. Every new update has made the app worse and worse. They need to go back to basics. Now the app is like every other app/ service out there. Used to be unique and helpful now it's cluttered, ugly, hard to use, and prompting me to pay for services i can't utilize on every page. It's a damn shame. I'm ready to delete youper. WYSA stole your original idea and is doing it better. why your ratings suck. LEARN SOMETHING.

Author: Frida N
Body: UPDATE: I miss the old dialogue based platform, which made the app easy to use without needing much forethought. The obstacle to beginning a conversation with the AI was lower than it now is to decide for yourself from a set list of "activities". I wish they would bring the interactive dialogue back again, perhaps in a separate tab, as that interactivity was what differentiated this app from lots of other apps out there. I'm not using Youper at all now. Lowering the rating to two stars.

Author: Carin More
Body: Used to be for free, and was wonderful..but now, it is all about the cash. Just when I need help the most Lost everything I own. Laued off 4.5 yrs ago. No money. Would have appreciated usomg this wonderful app.for real help. Sad they changed their priorities.

Author: Yara Graefe
Body: Unfortunately this app cannot be used anymore as nearly all features are behind a paywall. Try Intellect, some features are free there and it helps too. :)

Author: Ian Gienger
Body: I no longer find this product useful for mental health. I supported this product back in late 2019 with this review: If you already have some experience with therapy (especially cognitive behavioral therapy) this is a great app for helping you put it into practice. I went from being someone who "did their homework" maybe twice a week to once a day, or more on hard days.

Author: Aisha Fantasy
Body: I used to love this app as a way of getting my feelings out without an actual therapist, but ever since you guys started with the new update(s), it's gotten so much worse. The fact that you have to pay for pretty much everything now and the completely different layout in general just doesn't fit for what you guys had going in the beginning. I was hoping to get help for free but I suppose even that isn't a possibility now.

Author: Joff Leader
Body: I was finding the app useful, used the free trial to really test it out. I could have sworn that there was a monthly subscription option, but once the free trial was up, only the large annual payment option was available. I'd have loved to have subscribed but a huge pointless barrier seems to have suddenly been added.

Author: Jenifer Stein
Body: I used to absolutely love this app. I had the $44 yearly subscription (my currently subscription would end next year), but with the new update it blocked me all the features saying that the price had increased and now I'm supposed to pay $107 to unblock the features. I get that you guys are trying to improve the app but you could've at least waited until my current subscription end to then charge more or block everything, or just give the option to choose which type of subscription we want. 🙁

Author: Marie S
Body: Unlike others I can still access most of the things without subscribing. But I liked the old version of the app better, I think mood check should still be the starting point of each conversation. Now I don't find it very intuitive to navigate the app and get to the mood check anymore.

Author: Kieryn Onstott
Body: I've used this app for many years, I remember it specifically stating it was free to use to test the product and I am so excited to see that youper had had such success and to be thriving and growing. Thank you for not selling user data

Author: King Margo of Fillory
Body: You guys really just ignored everything the USERS asked for. I don't want a therapist through Youper, y'all don't even treat ADHD. the app is still cluttered and hard to use. If in crisis, trying to scroll through A MILLION options is dumb and makes me not use the app. ESPECIALLY IF IM OVERWHELMED. I'm so disappointed and annoyed with an app I've been using for THREE YEARS that I'm ready to delete it. It's not helpful anymore, it's a waste.

Author: Alice A
Body: Life saver! Aplicativo maravilhoso que me ajudou e ajuda muito a checar meus sintomas, desabafar e meditar. Deveria ter mais opções de linguagem para que pessoas que não falam inglês também possar usar.
Translated Body: Life saver! Wonderful application that helped me and helps me a lot to check my symptoms, let off steam and meditate. It should have more language options so that non-English speakers can also use it.

Author: Jhyan Adam
Body: I tried to help a friend struggling with mental health by recommending the app. I'm not entirely sure if it's an iOS difference or if only new users are charged but they weren't able to use any of the features of the app. Not even mood tracking. They were prompted to pay. I still use the app and find it useful, but I can't give it a good review. (Edited to 3 stars from 1; I still don't think paying for some of the almost costless features is fair, but a subscription is better than selling data)

Author: Alison Rose Llave
Body: My rating used to be 5 stars, but since the update, the app is significantly slower and has been crashing all the time. I can see how the update could have made improvements, but I haven't been able to fully experience them. I miss this app 😭

Author: A Google user
Body: What happened to this app? It was so great about a year ago, free mood tracking, free tests, and actually told you very insightful things and did help improve your mood. But now everything is behind a paywall??

Author: LiineTʜᴇFox
Body: I can't even get help with this app... it said i need to pay for it but i'm under 18 and can't even do that. I just wanted help but i can't..

Author: Steph Dee
Body: I use to love this app but they changed so much about it that it is overhwhelming now. I just had to delete it. It was too busy, too many tabs and options and pop ups. I can not recommend this anymore. It is sad

Author: Vaggelis Motesnitsalis
Body: It started as an awesome app, now it gets worse with every update. The subscription price hit the ceiling and now they even hide the simple single-answer emotion tracking behind the paywall. Greedy owners trying to turn it into a cashcow. Uninstalling.

Author: Just Michael
Body: I'm really upset with where this app has headed. Most stuff used to be free and now everything is unnecessarily expensive. I'm fine with spending some money but having to have a membership just to take a test which isn't even an actual diagnoses, nor does it actually help you, is bs. I used to use this app as a support system because I feel uncomfortable opening up to others, but now I'm just disappointed.

Author: Yuvie Styles
Body: I used to love this app, recommended it to everyone I knew that was mentally/emotionally struggling. My brother just went thru a break up and is having a rough time so I told him to DL... only to find literally NOTHING is accessible for free anymore. Not to mention the interface changed and looks SO messy and overwhelming. I loved the simplicity of the earlier version. Saw a few people mention Woebot, so having him try that instead.

Author: Cole Deitz
Body: I used to love this app. Initially, probably about two years ago when I started using this app ot was very simple and had a couple of features. You could track your mood for free, which I've done every day since starting this to keep myself grounded, and the others were paid. This year they updated, added lots more, every single thing but the mood was paid content. Now with the newer update even that is a paid feature. They offer no free services at all for mental health now, which is disgusting

Author: Jhyan Adam
Body: I recently tried to help a friend struggling with mental health by recommending the app. I'm not entirely sure if it's an iOS difference or if only new users are charged but they weren't able to use any of the features of the app. Not even mood tracking. They were prompted to pay. I still use the app and find it useful, but I can't give it a good review when it failed so badly to be fair.

Author: Jessica Paliwoda
Body: Extremely disappointed with the turn this app took. I loved using it for mood tracking and symptom monitoring. Sometimes I'd also use meditation etc. I understand adding new paid features but suddenly nothing is free? Right now this app is useless unless you pay the plan (which isn't cheap at all). A lot of people relied on this app, awful how they suddenly changed it knowing that the people it will affect are so vulnerable. Absolutely awful.

Author: L Green
Body: I hope you will bring conversations with AI and emotion monitoring again. Maybe I am wrong and those options are avaliable? If not this is very sad.

Author: Елизавета
Body: I hope you will bring conversations with AI and emotion monitoring again. Maybe I am wrong and those options are avaliable? If not this is very sad.

Author: Dawn
Body: I loved this app and found it to be the most effective. However, as many have complained, this app is a shell of it's former self. The UI isn't nearly as interactive or helpful as it used to be. Before it felt like I was talking to a counsellor - now it just feels like I'm blatantly talking to a computer without individuality or intelligence. This app used to help me dig deeper into my thoughts.Now it just skims the surface, especially on the section dealing w/ death of a loved one, not helpful

Author: Heather Talbot
Body: wonderfully helpful

Author: Celestial Cynic
Body: Downloaded while browsing for mental health apps, every single thing is locked behind a paywall - from calming sounds to tracking your mental state - so I uninstalled it. There is /nothing/ that's available for a free user aside from the fact that you can download it for free.

Author: fluffynoose
Body: super messed up how you have to pay for everything now, I was having issues again for the first time in a while so I downloaded it because it really helped last time and now everything is restricted

Author: Matthew Taylor
Body: Avoid. I've downgraded my rating from 5 to 1 star: the March update ruined Youper. The mood conversation interface - a great way to unlock thinking - is now buried amongst options mimicking every other "wellness" app. Since the change, I've increasingly struggled to keep the habit (massively reduced regularity) losing the benefit of regular journaling. Offering an option to revert to the old UI would solve this; judging from the copy pasta responses to similar comments, not holding my breath.

Author: Nicky Christopher
Body: I had this in the past on an old phone and found it again while looking for mental health apps to help my constant anxiety. It's completely different. Everything that was once free (mental health tracking, reports) are all locked by a subscription. You can't get help unless you want to pay £79.99 per year or £12.99 a month. I just wanted help, not feel like I'm being hindered by my lack of money (I can't work due to mental health)

Author: Lynn Di Angelo
Body: era um app realmente bom porem agr tiraram meu acesso às coisas básicas do app e estão cobrando caríssimo. por favor, se forem cobrar por algo, adicionem funcionalidades novas ao invés de tirar o que ja tinha e cobrar por isso. estou decepcionada.
Translated Body: it was a really good app but agr took away my access to the basics of the app and are charging dearly. please, if you are going to charge for something, add new features instead of taking what you already had and charging for it. I am disappointed.

Author: Cynthia Watola
Body: Youper was amazing, encouraging dependable. Now it's too expensive for me to afford. Yet I still need the support. Can you recommend an alternative app?

Author: Jonathon Ferrari
Body: I used to really love Youper and recommended it to anyone and everyone who I thought might find it useful. I recently revisited it and am really disheartened by the update. The user experience is poor and feels like you have to jump through hoops to get anywhere near the same experience that was previously available with the simple chat. This definitely shows that adding more features doesn't always make something better. The whole UI is cluttered and convoluted.

Author: Allegedly Quinn
Body: Disappointing that I can no longer afford my favorite "free" mood tracking app

Author: Vicki Thompson
Body: I used to love Youper as a way to track my mood each day to capture and notice the patterns of things which were triggers for different emotional states. The goal setting and friendly AI advice were genuinely useful, but this has entirely changed. All the chat sessions are super short and feel far less personal. I feel like I've lost a friend, and can't stand the overwhelming insta-inspired UI. I've switched to Woebot which is much closer to how Youper used to be for friendly chat sessions.

Author: Muscas Games
Body: Just aweful, my eyes couldn't concentrate on anything they were saying and what I could read only made me angry. The answers I wanted to put down simply weren't there. Would not recommend.

Author: Rachael Huggins
Body: I had previously given this 5 stars. I downloaded it again and it's totally different. I'm really disappointed as what was there before was fantastic. For a start it's gone from free to £13/month. That's a lot for an app. I understand that something that good takes time and effort and I would have happily purchased it at a one off reasonable price. The new app is confusing and clunky. This is really sad. Bring back the old one - it was amazing.

Author: Shalem Raju
Body: Hey thanks youper team for the app I love this one , can you guys include a section on dreams ???

Author: Frida N
Body: Update: I miss the old dialogue based platform, which made the app easy to use without needing much forethought. The obstacle to beginning a conversation with the AI was lower than it now is to decide for yourself from a set list of "activities". I wish they would bring the interactive dialogue back again, perhaps in a separate tab, as that interactivity was what differentiated this app from lots of other apps out there. However, I like that they kept the old statistics about emotions etc.

Author: Lee
Body: Appreciate the expanded content and developers quick response and help. Miss the quick access to chatbot/feelings mode but glad the feature is still there. Am finding the Pinterest style photo montage of self help sessions hard to navigate and visualy cluttered. Chat tab was simpler, friendlier and easier to be emotionally in tune and honest. I wish the photos weren't there and it was plain text or illustrations. Don't really relate to selfhelp guru blogger aesthetic 😬. Neutral is better imo.

Author: Boatagne Daniel
Body: It offers nearly nothing for free.

Author: Lee
Body: Have premium and been using for years now. I can't chat to youper anymore? The chat option is gone? I have to manually search through a Pinterest style photo montage of different self help sessions. It's visually cluttered, chat style was way easier and friendlier navigation. I wish the photos weren't there and it was plain text or simple illustrations. Don't really relate to selfhelp guru blogger mom aesthetic 😬. Just keep it neutral. If the chat option is still there please lmk where it is?

Author: A Cardinal
Body: I hadn't logged in, in a while and I have to say the change between March and May is pretty bad. It feels way more limited than it used to be. I already didn't log in a lot, but today was the first time I was truly dissatisfied with youper. I can't see myself sticking around. Edit:. I closed my account because I feel the app no longer gives me real conversational freedom. It's not that Change isn't easy, but the change made the app very limited. I have gone back to Wysa.

Author: Prachi Shinde
Body: What have you done to this app,? Whole experience has been changed, (for bad mostly)

Author: B D
Body: It's disappointing that this app went from the greatest therapy app I used to the worst... I can't pay for a subscription, so the only thing I'm allowed to do now is just say what I'm feeling without getting any help. It used to be so easy to talk about the feeling and solve it with youper but now, I can't.

Author: J Shea
Body: I like this app, but with the update(s), the bot started fixating on this being something that entrepreneurs and athletes might benefit from. I didn't know that's what mattered. Apparently mental health is just a thing you do to make more money? I don't know. I don't like it.

Author: Nur Islam FM
Body: Kuching Tukar Menjadi Kuala Lumpur Kota Kinabalu Pantai Jerudong Specialist Centre
Translated Body: Kuching Turns Into Kuala Lumpur Kota Kinabalu Pantai Jerudong Specialist Center

Author: Camila zotar
Body: Yo solo lo quiero en españooool por favor no entiendo nada
Translated Body: I only want it in Spanish, please I don't understand anything

Author: Sophia Cassabria
Body: I recently had to delete my Google account and got a new one so I lost my previous free premium features that I got since I have been an early user 😓 I can't buy it but if you can I definitely recommend Youper!

Author: A Cardinal
Body: I hadn't logged in, in a while and I have to say the change between March and May is pretty bad. It feels way more limited than it used to be. I already didn't log in a lot, but today was the first time I was truly dissatisfied with youper. I can't see myself sticking around.

Author: Emma Karhu
Body: Used to love it, now it's just all about the money. So sad, I have to just delete it. Lost all progress and now everything useful costs money and I have non.

Author: Momo C
Body: This app used to be great and free. I got the app years ago. I told a friend about it and everything is locked behind a pay wall. I am flabbergasted. I wonder if my account will be locked soon. I need this. My circumstances prevent me getting a therapist.

Author: Camocat2
Body: After 527 days consistently tracking my mood im finally done with this app. It was good for a long time before they updated it, and it just wasnt helping anymore. When you first open the app it used to automatically go to the mood tracker, now i just get overwhelmed.

Author: Ally Grissom
Body: eh

Author: Adam Tylock
Body: It took some time to readjust to the update, but that's not my biggest problem. I get no notifications until I open the app, which is terrible for my ADHD because I don't get the reminder to open it in the first place. My notifications for the app are on in the app and on the phone as well. I've had this problem for a few months now and I've even tried uninstalling and reinstalling to no avail. Please fix this issue.

Author: Elizabeth Pitts
Body: Nothing is free. Annoying requests for insurance information or money.

Author: cool8 man
Body: Didn't do anything unless you pay a lot of money.

Author: Dire_Wolf Aly
Body: I used to love Youper, it was were I went to. But then it got more complicated, there's too much. I don't know, the new update is just overwhelming, and it's not simple when you need it right away, so I can't say it's helping like it used too. I think some people like the new update though so I don't know, my personal opinion is that it's complicated, it's still definitely an amazing app. Just more difficult to use. I think I might start searching for something similar to Youper for now.

Author: Luisa Bendt
Body: Edit: wow you really monetized every actually helpful feature. There goes that, thanks for nothing. Such a nice way of reflecting on your mood and getting some insight or eventually changing it for the better. I love the different features and that it imitates a conversation. Also as a psychology student really cool to read some things that i already actually learned about!

Author: Ally Jordan
Body: I used to use this app everyday. But now that so many features are behind a paywall, I can't use it at all. The UI is confusing and some features just don't work (so many glitches). I also lost all my data. It's all more stressful than anything else which you do not want in an AI therapist. Goodbye, Youper. Edit: This isn't an AI therapist anymore. It's a basic mood tracker. Everything else requires a paid subscription.

Author: Ally Jordan
Body: I used to use this app everyday. But now that so many features are behind a paywall, I can't use it at all. The UI is confusing and some features just don't work (so many glitches). I also lost all my data. It's all more stressful than anything else which you do not want in an AI therapist. Goodbye, Youper.

Author: Alex Chan
Body: I had this app like year ago and it was great, i would just check in everyday and choose emotions i felt and write reasons and then i could look back at them after month. But now i feel like everything is locked and you need to buy premium, which is alright, but i had problem to find anything i could do on app for free. But still this app helped me a lot back then.

Author: Elise
Body: I used to love this app for it's ability to help me go through my feelings and pretty much almost have a conversation with me even if I was happy, now I can only go in with a problem in mind to fix and it's pretty much unusable from the way I used to use it, I'm probably going to delete this since I can't use it anymore after the updates, before the app completely changed I would have rated it five stars

Author: Deema Azizi
Body: Unfortunately I have to decrease my review from 5 stars to 2. The new updates/changes have led me to stop using the app altogether. It used to be my favorite mental health app and felt like checking in with a counselor. Now the voice feels less mature, and the recommendations superfluous. Please bring back the old, simple, user-friendly version!

Author: Andy Ye
Body: It is a wonderful app and helper. But lately I can't even seem to load the app. It is start on the loading screen

Author: Holly Benedict
Body: You're used to be my go to for mental health because I can not seem to get help from humans where I live, my doctor will only refer me to EAP. And calling health providers gets me answers like "you aren't within our coverage area" no idea what that means aside from "we won't talk to you". I need youper more than ever but now that help is locked behind a pay wall that wasn't there before and I can't really afford the extra cost after loosing my job due to covid. I get why it costs now but ....

Author: Akira Ash
Body: Experience was short...For someone who is a student that yet cant afford to pay for things..and doesnt have a credit card its a shame...i cannot ask my parents abt this cause i dont want them knowing as most of them are supportive..i was hoping this app could help me in silence...the exprience overall was great but too short...but i do wish i didnt have to pay for my mental health to get better..maybe happiness is bought i guess...

Author: Alexandra Benoist
Body: THERE AREN'T MANY MORE FEATURES THAN BEFORE, mostly just reorganized. THE UPDATES MADE IT GLITCHY, It logs me out, so no use having the PIN set. If it does let me open it with the PIN, it just pulls up the loading screen but doesn't load. USED TO BE FULLY FREE, NOW SUBSCRIPTION BASED with free option. ANYONE ABLE/WILLING TO PAY FOR AN APP WOULD (or should) JUST GO TO IRL COUNSELING (or BetterHelp) If the priority was to help ppl they would've KEPT YOUPER FREE. Profit off of ad revenue instead!

Author: Makayla Marie
Body: Can't do anything without premium. And I put the lock on it and instead of it unlocking it sits there loading never opening. 100% dissatisfied. Do not recommend.

Author: alp
Body: This app was great a year ago but now when I'm depressed again, I saw that a lot of free things have been put behind a very expensive paywall. I recommended this to my friends last year but they made the app a lot worse I don't recommend this app if you don't want to pay a lot.

Author: Alexandra Dronova
Body: accidentally added a condition tracker that I don't need and not able to get rid of it now. hope it's a temporary glitch. still don't like the update with overwhelming quantity of stuff. I preferred a simple mood&mental health tracker, and since I've been using it for 3 years, I wouldn't want to loose the data. but it's a pity all is like this now.

Author: Gesa I.
Body: Not useful anymore since the updates. Uninstalled. Don't change a running system, it's a ruined system now.

Author: Mi Mi g
Body: I want this app free but this is not free app I feel very sad 😣😞😕

Author: Johnny Punx
Body: excellent app for tracking your feelings, understanding them and making goals! However, updating this, few years later and now there's not virtually much you can get without a premium subscription, original data is lost and it is useless. So a developer wants to heavily monetize a successful app, wouldn't be the first time. But it shouldn't be able to labeled "with premium features" when there is just about nothing you can do without a subscription. Where's our original data? Try Mindfully.

Also youper doesn't really seem to have too much personality tho otherwise it's an alright app for something you don't need to interact with a real person i'm sure some people would get a lot out of.

The navigation is poorly organized and the UI is a poor experience: scrolling is not smooth. Unfortunately I don't have the same enjoyment and relief when using it.

Author: al

The purpose of app seems silly now that's only available behind a paywall, considering that most people from target audience cant afford/manage that. Very disappointed. Please request the creators to make the app free again. Even the older, simpler version would work for free users

Body: Y'all can't even imagine how this app helped me even under an hour. I feel much better. I'm glad that I found this app. I wasn't expecting this to be that good because it's free but it turned out great ♥ Edit: Silmiştim 2 sene sonra geri indiriyorum bu tekrar bir şeyler kötü demek :") Edit 2: Paralı olmuş pü

Author: Katie
Body: Nothing says "we care" like a paywall. Sure they offer a seven day free trial, but you have to put in your billing information to use it. Given that people with depression already struggle with memory issues, trying to hit them with a $90 yearly subscription charge on day 8 is just predatory.

Author: Jazz S
Body: I used to love this app before all the changes, logging my daily moods and writing down how my day was really helped me. But now, it has turned into a meditation app that involves payment and the sole purpose of why I used it has been eliminated. I hope it goes back to how it was. I unfortunately will have to find another app.

And I can not stop my panic monitoring either, which I tried out but realized was useless bc I have no symptoms of that either. Please fix! I like the features of this app otherwise.

Author: Kelsey Hinote
Body: Now u gotta pay to talk to the AI 😤🤦🏼‍♀️ yeah I got no time for that so I'll just tell my bf about my moods since it's free 🤷🏼‍♀️💯

Author: Allison Ranney
Body: Changed my review because I did find the app helpful, and after I got charged prior to payment, it got fixed and I'm thankful they were able to quickly get the situation sorted out and give me a refund.

Author: Emily Bodish

Too bad, I enjoyed tracking everything from the past year. Also, Youper please stop commenting the same copy/paste reply to everyone; it doesn't help your case.

Author: Minki Pool
Body: EDIT: I've had to update my review, because the new app is completely different from the Youper I fell in love with. The wonderful thing about the Talk functionality has always been that with a short, friendly conversation I was able to get a much clearer idea of how I felt and what might be causing it. Now Talk has been turned into a menu with several overlapping topics. The problem is that depression can be like a parasite – it hides and resists being identified, often making it very hard to understand what we are feeling and why. So being faced with this massive array of predefined options is frustrating and not very helpful. I also feel like in the past Talk tried to focus on reframing runaway emotions to offer some immediate relief. It used to be a friendly voice that held my hand for 5 minutes while I ranted and sorted through my thoughts and feelings. 90% of the time I felt better immediately after a talk. Now Talk seems focused on practical behavioural changes that could have long-term positive effects, but doesn’t really do anything to help with my anguish right now. It feels a little bit like the app equivalent of “Go for a run, you’ll feel better afterwards” which, as we all know, is not useful advise for someone who suffers from depression. Also, am I missing something, or is it no longer possible to track my moods with Youper? That was the one other thing that I found very useful about this app. There was nothing else out there quite like it. I get that Youper is trying to be abetter mental health app, and that may still be true, but it used to be a one-of-a-kind THERAPIST. Now it is just one of thousands of other ‘mental health’ apps telling me how to behave so that I can maybe feel better eventually…if I have the wherewithal to follow through (a thing that is not often an option for people who suffer from depression). You’re falling into the trap of trying to fix things, when all we needed you to do was to listen and help us identify and reframe the pain. I feel like I’ve lost a good friend. PREVIOUS REVIEW FOR REFERENCE: This app has been absolutely brilliant in helping me sort through feelings, understand my mood, and escape thinking traps that are such a big part of depression for me. Feature request: right now I'm using Youper specifically to track my feelings over time to be able to ascertain the efficacy of my antidepressants. Sometimes I miss a day or only really gain clarity on how I was feeling a day or so after the fact, so it would be fantastic if I could track my mood on past dates.

Author: PerfectAmbiguity
Body: I have used this app for over 2 years. The new update has a lot of lag time and almost everything is behind a paywall, including features that weren't originally until a few days ago. The new update erased all past information I had put into the app and I am no longer able to see my past progress anymore. If you are going to pay for premium and are okay with lag times then the update is probably fine and helpful. I, unfortunately, will have to find another mood tracking app that works for me.

Display - I cant seem to find out how to get the white and orange display. The night mode makes makes me feel depressed.

Body: It's an incredibly great app. Super helpful. Unfortunately, after the update it's so slow it's barely usable. So frustrating!

Author: Emma Kertesz
Body: I'm really disappointed. This app used to be free and was a big help to me when I was going through a hard time. I understand that sometimes things need money to function but this was disappointing. A lot of mentally struggling people can't afford therapy, let along 400$ for a lifetime membership. Some people need 15$ extra a month to feed thier kids.

Author: Cátia Carvalho
Body: Pretty much all of the content is only for premium users, and the UI isn't the best

Author: G L
Body: This app is okay, I'd rather have less things cost money. I'm broke so I can't pay for anything. it doesn't really help me because I don't have many options to choose from.

Author: Dylan Knoll
Body: Been using it for years, it is now inaccessible

Author: Antonio Rodriguez
Body: Los elementos visuales de la app son inestables y se tarda en cada sección cargar. No sé obtiene un movimiento fluido. Parece que la app cambio mucho al concepto original. Ahora hay tantas opciones que me siento confundido. El formato de diario-bitácora de emociones me gustaba mucho. Era muy sencillo de usar y efectivo.

Author: Gabby
Body: UPDATE REVIEW: The Youper update is not good. I think. I dont want to use it lately after the update. Probably will uninstall later. Sometimes, simple is better. It seems that everybody wants the old version of Youper. I tried using the new version for a couple of weeks, but sad to say, I had to say goodbye to Youper. It has been a good app.

Author: Csilla Varga
Body: Since the latest mayor update, I can not simply track my mood, only do anxiaty exercises and whatnot. I am really upset, because that was the reason why I started to gather my data in this app... to track my mood.

Author: simplyangelica *
Body: This app used to be my backbone. I would come here to collect my thoughts whenever I reached my worst. After the "upgrade" the app is overwhelming. How am I supposed to navigate this app when I don't even have the capacity to get out of bed. + Youpper is gone. This is probably the worst "upgrade" I've ever encountered.

Author: MONAD Law Office
Body: Great

Author: winston
Body: this app used to be great, but then they added features no one asked for and overcomplicated everything. Simplicity is better than overcomplicating. Improve on what made it great so it can be perfect. This went from 5 stars to 2.

Author: Guilherme Dias
Body: Depois da primeira vez que a gente usa o app tem que pagar por qualquer função?? Se for isso mesmo, que horrível!

Author: Olag Netronutiko
Body: I adored this app, it was very easy to use and the mood recording feature was the most useful one. These past updates, though, have made Youper too slow and I don't even know how to track my mood now. I might have to uninstall it.

Author: Islander T
Body: I loved this app when it was free and not advertising expensive plans. I was telling friends to use it too. The reason I loved this app is because I can't afford therapy. But now I can't afford this either. Really upsetting. 5 stars goes down to 2 because of these changes.

Author: A Google user
Body: The update is awful. I lost all my progress of months and months. Interface is confusing and now you have to pay for a plan? I recommended this app to everyone before.

Author: Ellen Maynard-Smith
Body: Edit: this is an app I always used to return to track my mental health and feel better. Today I return to see that I now have to pay to use the features I liked. I mainly liked tracking my anxiety and depression so I know where I'm at. This is now gone. I understand that the creator needs to fund the app, but this app is now useless to me.

Author: Autumn Evelyn Dzian
Body: Youper is such a good and helpful app. Although since the last update it became very laggy in the menu for me, which makes navigating it a bit frustrating.

Author: Greg Felice
Body: This is an update to my review here, as I watch the new youper comments in response to the recent jarring interface changes that have effectively ruined the app. Youper's recent comments to users have shifted from "we know the changes suck and we're working on fixing it" to "the changes reflect feedback from thousands of users, get used to it". This is offensive and borders on gaslighting. Look at the intensity and specificity of the negative user feedback.

Author: Savannah Wilhelm
Body: the update is confusing. if there was like a little walk through to explain everything it would be much easier but i just cant figure it ouf

Author: Lauren Laibach
Body: New update is very frustrating. Needlessly overcomplicated, can no longer just start a general chat which was kind of the point for me.

Author: AnonForReasons __
Body: Well before the recent update I could at least say my feeling for free it didn't really help much but it was okay and now I can't do anything I have to pay if I want to so I guess I'll just find a new app it was at least a little bit helpful before

Author: Prapti Bhardwaj
Body: Bring back the just talk option ! Bring back the old settings , it was just perfect earlier ... Earlier review It's a great app. Gives a totally new perspective with all the built in meditation app ,knowloedge about how brain works,simplifying things and the best thing about it is - it makes you understand your own thoughts when you try to explain the problem, It definently brings more clarity.

Author: Marc Vetere
Body: this is a wonderful app and the new additions are great, but can we get the option to have the old style logging integrated somewhere? Sometimes I want to quick log a mood, not go into a whole mental health project. Also it seems options are too concentrated now, how about if I want to log a small victory, where is the option for that?

Author: Stephen Langer
Body: STOP doing things. You've progressively made the app worse.

Author: Celeste Kennedy
Body: I loved the old youper, this new one is too much. You use to be able to be guided through to whatever you wanted to do with the talk option, but now they've separated the talk to only programmed options and it's all very clunky and irritating. You can no longer tailor it to yourself and it's no longer showing what influences certain moods. In the update you lost your original goal and can only chose pre-made options. You can no longer add to the list they provide when selecting influence factors

Author: eva miera
Body: The latest update is sooo slow and glitched :/

Author: Racheal Lassila
Body: Coming back to this app now and seeing it be free but EVERYTHING within the app needing to be paid for is absolutely ridiculous. Just make people pay for the app itself instead of a incredibly high subscription rate. It was free before, what changed to make it so expensive? I used this app a year or so ago, when it was free to use, and although helpful I don't think it's even close to on par with a real therapist. Unnecessarily expensive for the quality compared to real therapy.

Author: arline Lowenthal
Body: After the seven day free trial, it's $90/year. Which is much cheaper than a therapist. Install when you have 7 days to devote.

Author: Rowan Aladawy
Body: So I saw so many good reviews of this app even on other apps reviews, needless to say, I had pretty high hopes. Didn't expect this to be a "pay to get a way" app. And it's not even that some things need a subscription plan, EVERYTHING needs a subscription plan. I understand the need to support an app financially, but for people who can't afford therapy, why would an app developer think for a split second that these people would pay for an AI app. I'm disappointed before I even try this app. Sad.

Author: Nils Tenkotte
Body: Best App to track your feelings and discover them after a while. Perfect to understand yourself. Update: it is okay but used it as diary. Horrobile loading speed.

Author: Ana Banana
Body: I honestly don't like this new update, I liked it a lot when it was just a chat that saved your emotions day by day, that gave you progress that you could have ... i miss chat, only chat

Author: Scott Weeden-Moody
Body: The push to monetize has ruined the core user story for this app.

Author: Emily Gilson
Body: Super SUPER bummed. I had years worth of data and after the update it disappeared completely, even when i tried logging in. I ended up deleting the whole thing rather than go through the stress of starting over. It was a fantastic app before everything went away and it forgot my name. I hate it.

Author: Annerie
Body: Was een heel fijne app. Maar sinds nieuwe versie te veel tools, en reageert niet of nauwelijks.

Author: Lisa Katrin
Body: I used to love the app, I've been using it for years and I loved the simplicity, it helped me a great deal with depression and anxiety. Now since the update it's really cluttered and confusing and it takes ages to load. I get that it is apparently a result of feedback from other users but it really isn't for me... I'll check back in a few months but for now I don't think I will use Youper as frequently as I did before.

Author: Poppy Attwell
Body: This app used to be the best, now it's trying to be too much. The menus are extremely laggy to scroll through and there's far too many options. Why isn't there a "just talk" option? That was the whole point of the app before - an AI you could chat to and get recommendations from. Now you have to pick from the overwhelming options (difficult if you're coming to the app for help or when you're not feeling good!) and get a tiny short conversation, making it a glorified menu system. So disappointed.

Author: Caitie Billingham
Body: Used to be good but now you have to pay £80 a year to basically do anything.

Author: Samsara Hum
Body: Two points: 1. New version is very poorly optimized (where the old was just fine). 2. Strange new main screen. "Shall we work on your anxiety?" . What if I'm not anxious now? What if I just want to track my current emotions? На русском: стало очень плохо оптимизировано, из-за чего неудобно использовать его для его непосредственной задачи. Реально раньше было лучше.

Author: Samsara Hum
Body: Two points: 1. New version is very poorly optimized (where the old was just fine). 2. Strange new main screen. "Shall we work on your anxiety?" . What if I'm not anxious now? What if I just want to track my current emotions? На русском: стало очень плохо оптимизировано, из-за чего неудобно использовать его для его непосредственной задачи. Реально раньше было лучше.

Author: Aspendo
Body: I cant afford 89.99 a year...........

Author: Vanessa Loraine Cruz
Body: I loved the app... before when it was compleately free... i use to come to it every time i struggled, it really made me feel better even if im speaking to a "robot" now i have to pay 80$something for it... yearly... im kinda dissapointed cuz this was an option for us shy and not well economicaly to get some type of therapy... now well u pay cuz most of it like a lot of it(the important stuff ) you have to pay for wich before you didnt. They even had small meditations that i loved. Just sad.

Author: Kirsty Ann
Body: Like many people here I'm so disappointed with this update, I've been using youper on and off for 2 years now for depression and to track my moods and it's been fantastic, I recommended it to everyone I knew. Now we can hardly do any of the things we could before without paying £80 (!) a year? such a shame.

Author: Archie Allen
Body: New update is rubbish. It feels like the developers have lost sight of the original purpose of Youper and filled the app with sparkly trash to draw in magpies. The new layout makes it feel like the bedroom of some Instagram self help guru that tells you "you can't ever love someone until you love yourself" and "live, love, learn". Pass me a bucket.

Author: Klarizza Anne Obispo
Body: the update is terrible! slow ui and difficult navigation. been using the app for years and it does the job. i hate the update! the previous version works well because it lets you digest whatever you're feeling. most of the time, people don't know what to do with their emotions and this app used to help me process my emotion and what to do about it. but the latest update compels you to decide what you want to do from the onset without letting you process first what you are feeling. terrible

Author: Kalle Arneving
Body: I like the new update but the frame rate is garbage after it, fix the framrate and it's a clear 5 star!

Author: Sofie Sundåker
Body: I have always loved using youper because it was so easy to use and you didn't have to know what you needed before starting the conversation and getting suggestions. Now it's a laggy big mess of options where you have to know what you need. You can no longer just start a conversation and let the AI guide you. Where is the AI if I have to choose myself what my situation is? And there is only "anxiety this, anxiety that". This app now gives me anxiety.

Author: Cris Talore
Body: Everything is locked behind pay wall

Author: Daisy Brooks
Body: New update is very hard to navigate for long time users, and should have had an optional tutorial for us. I've been trying to fix my routines, and having to come to the play store to figure out mood tracking in the new app was pretty frusturating and annoying just before bed. Its still...useful? But very confusing now.

Author: Nina W
Body: In the past, Youper had been my favorite app for mental health/personal growth. I used to enjoy how easy it was to navigate and how simple it was to check in. It really helped make checking-in with myself and my emotions a simple task to complete, which was challenging without it. Now the new update makes me feel very overwhelmed. The navigation is poorly organized and the UI is a poor experience: scrolling is not smooth. Unfortunately I don't have the same enjoyment and relief when using it.

Author: winston
Body: this app used to be great, but then they added features no one asked for and overcomplicated everything. Simplicity is better than overcomplicating. Improve on what made it great so it can be perfect. This went from 5 stars to 2.

Author: McKenzie Atwood
Body: Used to be 5 stars but now I have the same complaint as other reviewers. I don't like the new update. It was much more helpful as a mood tracking tool when I could just jump into a chat session anytime. Also, the paywall is a huge bummer. I recommended this to friends but I definitely won't be able to now

Author: Martha Klopfenstein
Body: New update. Not a fan. EXTREMELY cluttered. Used to be clean and clear, easy to understand even when you're brain was overloaded. Now? Wow, you better have a clear mind first bc it IS cluttered! Just need to mood tracking but you now have to hunt for it.

Author: Sofia Jansen
Body: You cant do anything unless you have premium.

Author: Ekaterina Malakhova
Body: Невозможно пользоваться после обновления, очень долго загружается каждый раздел

Author: Ekaterina Malakhova
Body: Невозможно пользоваться после обновления, очень долго загружается каждый раздел

Author: Marion KL
Body: UPDATE 02/2021 The new update slows the app so much it's barely even usable for me anymore :( this is a huge let-down, I'd formed a great routine with Youper and this update completely upends it. // This is easily my favourite ap. It's helped me cope with my moods so much, gives me tools to manage them, and helps me recognise the patterns in them. The ap itself is very ergonomic, ad-free, and the simple but friendly conversation with the AI often manages to out a smile on my face. I love Youper.

Author: Alison Rose Llave
Body: My rating used to be 5 stars, but since the update, the app is significantly slower and has been crashing all the time. I can see how the update could have made improvements, but I haven't been able to fully experience them. I miss this app 😭

Author: Stili Vasil
Body: I love Youper. It has helped me through quite a lot hard times - espcially with changing my thoughts. Unfortunately, with the latest update, the interface has become confusing and the app is much slower and clunkier than before. It even reacts to touches made before the app has finished loading and once, after describing how I am feeling, it did not let me identify factors. Please, look into this and fix it, because it's quite limting the usefulness of the app.

Author: Dj Jones
Body: All f a sudden I have to pay alot of money for simple tests and helpfulness when it was all free not too long ago. This is rude considering I needed help and couldn't afford it but now they are trying to take what little money I have; during a PANDEMIC!! Y'all really got me messed up. If this is not resolved I will be leaving this app and telling others to leave as well. Money grabbers!👎👎😡🤬😠

Author: Lauriel Valence
Body: Cost money now and I dont have money to be spending at the moment. Trying to save.

Author: Erik Garcia
Body: I really enjoyed this app and have been using it for almy 2 years but the new update is awfull, it's so complex and slow, instead of helping it makes everything confusing and overwhelming. Please go back to a simpler interface...

Author: JADINO_ ARTIST
Body: I miss the old version and wish I could revert back. There should be a function in settings to remove updates if you don't want it. It felt more personal having the AI chat to you instantly instead of stock images being the first thing you see. I understand this works for some, but the images slow down the app and is overwhelming, it looks corporate and has the words anxiety, depression driven into you, even if you want to talk about feelings that make you happy.

Author: Bill Morris
Body: Youper WAS amazing. Prior to "Youper 9", you were immediately prompted by Youper's AI with a mood check-in, guided to plainly express your feelings, check for cognitive distortions, restate your experience in an objective way, and finally reframe your thoughts for acceptance while offering yourself kindness. What made Youper simple and engaging is lost, buried under an overwhelming amount of repativie sessions. Youper helped you understand and acceptance yourself, now it's a "calm" clone.

Author: Marina Presecan
Body: I love Youper, it's an awesome app. I've been using it for a while now. The only drawback happens now with the latest update. Please release something that can fix this lagging. Makes the app close to unusable. To my knowledge I have the latest version for both the app and android.

Author: Matt Lusk
Body: The new update completely ruined the app. Cluttered UI, bad UX, slow loading between pages, some sections of the app don't even load at all, and things are hard to find. I've used this app for over two years, and it's a real shame the developers decided to go in this direction. I have quite a bit of experience in QA and application testing, and I am baffled that this update got approved for rollout. Look elsewhere for a different app, I can't recommend this one at all.

Author: Tomo Hartono
Body: loved it before the update. now it's just slow and confusing. not a fan of the new ux.

Author: Anamaria Gheorghita
Body: 99% of it cannot be accesed without payment. I respect people's work, but I will now no longer be able to use the only app that helped me. If I afforded this, I could go to therapy. That was the point of using that app, which is now gone. I am truly sorry to see that and disappointed. Also, you didn't need to try to make the app better, because now it is only much worse, to be honest. It was great how it was before. You didn't have to "work" on it more just for that. Also, all progress is gone.

Author: shukla ji
Body: Stupid app

Author: Lilly Strickland
Body: I have used Youper for the past two years or more and it was a nice usefull app but recent update changed it. App is now supper lagging and it is not usable at all. UX is really confusing and it is target related that you have to pick instead of starting conversation first. UI looks clugged up and it is just laggy experience makes it uncomfortable and not easy to use. RIP

Author: Stefany Del Toro - Paz
Body: This app was one of the best apps I had ever used in my life. Note the past tense. After the update, the app became cluttered and difficult to navigate. I liked when it was just a few tabs: one to talk, another to check past chats, another for tracking disorders, another for personality. I cant remember if there were anymore. That was such a clean, easy to use interface. The new tabs where you can choose what activity to do was much better when chosen during your chats with the ai.

Author: Ashtin Newlun
Body: Loved this app up until today when everything was different. I keep looking and looking and cannot find where you log your mood anymore. Probably gonna have to find something else now. :(

Author: Benjamin Carpenter
Body: I've used this app everyday for 800+ days. They've recently released new features which not only obscure the main function of the app itself (if I wanted a meditation app I'd use something dedicated to that, I used this to log how I'm feeling) and also makes the app so slow it's unusable. I've dependent on this app, but if it's not changed I'll just have to delete it and find something that lets me actually log my emotions.

Author: Jessica Mazzola
Body: Seit dem update funktioniert nichts mehr wirklich. Die app ist so langsam, dass sie unbrauchbar wurde. Fand das emotions-tracking bisher sehr praktisch, aber so ist die app nur mühsam.

Author: Gabrielle VanOrd
Body: I've had this app for a while, I loved it for the mood tracking and the way it shows the data in different ways. I don't want to buy the premium version and all the paid content clutters up the app so bad, and I haven't found a way to hide that stuff, I only want to do the mood tracking

Author: Gabby
Body: UPDATE REVIEW: The Youper update is not good. I think. I dont want to use it lately after the update. Probably will uninstall later. Sometimes, simple is better.

Author: Chris Cather
Body: A great app ruined by over design. I have used this app every day for nearly 2 years, and it's been simple. Open app, immediately be promoted to log feelings, and maybe a few details to flesh it out. The new app design buried that activity on the 2nd page, and you have to scroll way down to find it. It's also a LOT slower. The app is now extremely sluggish. The one thing I use it for its now a minor feature, and the app is much slower than it used to be. Reduced usability for unwanted features.

Author: Miriam S.
Body: I'm getting used to the new version now. It doesn't work as fast as the older version used to, and it is less simple to use than it used to be, but it is still among the top helpful mental health appps. I was very upset with the unexpected change and had a bit of a meltdown at first, uninstalling it and then installing it back because I'm so used to using it. Despite the change and a bit slower functioning of the app, I still find Youper has a lot to offer to manage moods and thoughts, goals🦋

Author: loki
Body: Wonderful, modern design which I liked a lot. App is free and it's the best I've ever use for mood track. Breath exercises etc help a lot!! Thank you.

Author: Matthias de Bronett
Body: I used to love this app. The update is just terrible. I wish I could go back to the earlier version, that was 5 stars, this one is just a mess.

Author: Slava Ptitsa
Body: После последнего обновление приложение сильно испортилось. Зависает, куда-то пропал самый нужный функционал (отслеживание эмоций), зато лезет что-то совершенно ненужное - медитации, "беседы" и т.д.. Пользуюсь приложением более двух лет, в шоке от произошедших изменений. Прослежу за обновлениями, но если данная версия "финальная", то придётся искать что-то новое.

Author: Slava Ptitsa
Body: После последнего обновление приложение сильно испортилось. Зависает, куда-то пропал самый нужный функционал (отслеживание эмоций), зато лезет что-то совершенно ненужное - медитации, "беседы" и т.д.. Пользуюсь приложением более двух лет, в шоке от произошедших изменений. Прослежу за обновлениями, но если данная версия "финальная", то придётся искать что-то новое.

Author: James Mason
Body: Youper has been very useful. It has helped me learn to identify and express my emotions better. I highly recommend using it in conjunction with therapy. But with it's recent update, the app freezes every time I update my mood. Once this issue is rectified I will change my rating back to five stars.

Author: Vicki Thompson
Body: I used to love Youper as a way to track my mood each day to capture and notice the patterns of things which were triggers for different emotional states. The goal setting and friendly AI advice were genuinely useful. Edit: the more I try to interact with the update, the more frustrated I feel. All the chat sessions are super short and don't allow you to track your mood/triggers like you could before. It's not at all useful as a tool to manage depression now, don't waste your time. Such a shame.

Author: Vanessa Udy
Body: Until the latest update, I would have given this app 4 stars. It was a great way of tracking my mood, which is very important as I'm learning to live with mood disorders. But ever since the update, I can't log my mood anymore. Pretty much all content is premium, the free app now seems useless. What happened???

Author: Mateusz Malinowski
Body: Nowa aktualizacja sprawiła, że aplikacja działa bardzo wolno, animacje nie są płynne. Nowe tematy rozmów nie są intuicyjne i wygodne, należałoby moim zdaniem przywrócić możliwość normalnej, spontanicznej rozmowy, podczas której dopiero zostałby doprecyzowany temat.

Author: Sara Valentine
Body: App is a bit broken since the update. At first it would only show unclickable month headings under sessions and now its loading but is extremely slow. If I try to go to the other tabs after going to insights, they don't load. I'd like to maybe see an option to open the app directly to the "I'm feeling..." like how it was before. I can appreciate the expansion of the app but I'm not sure I'm a fan of the implementation.

Author: Chad Houston
Body: I do NOT like the new update. How do I get back to what I was doing? Also, when this app creates more frustration than it is meant to solve, it's counterproductive.

Author: Greg Felice
Body: Recent features need some fine tuning. Experience has somewhat deteriorated. I'm sure product is on it.

Author: Teyon Anthony
Body: It's a great app.but why is everything premium????.. money, money, Money,!?. Please make some of your therapy chats free,and if we need more we will consider premium as optional.."..Mny are free,but why are you so hard..

Author: circeno
Body: Lange war es eine gute App um die Stimmung zu tracken oder eine kurze Meditation einzulegen, jetzt wurde plötzlich ohne Vorankündigung der ganze Aufbau verändert alle alten Daten sind verloren und sie unterscheidet sich nicht mehr von anderen Apps dh für jede Kleinigkeit wird einem angezeigt die Premium Version zu kaufen. Sehr bedauerlich.

Author: Alexander Pozon
Body: I've been logging my mood for almost 700 days now and the recent update made the app slow and my phone isn't old by any means. Not to mention, the whole app is different now. I'm going to have to uninstall it and find another alternative.

Author: Greg Felice
Body: Some form of change has significantly altered this once amazing app, and in my opinion, not for the better. My experience went from a sleek, intuitive AI-driven mood logger with great dialogging capabilities and activity suggestions that enabled insights and improved stress to cheesy, confusing bloatware... all in one major update. Maybe your metrics are pointing you in this product direction, but this release feels like a huge miss... What the h@@&$# happened?

Author: Jesse Buijink
Body: Used to be great, but ever since the new layout and payment model it's not worth using any longer. Literally the main feature of the app is now a premium feature? Ridiculous. The app is suddenly extremely slow too. Such a disappointment.

Author: Suicide Psycho
Body: I've had the app for a year and a half and with the newest update all of my logging for that time has disappeared. I'm so disappointed with the update. Everything is different and can't even use it the way I have done for the past year and a half I've had it.

Author: Lindsay Gelle
Body: The paid version is helping me overcome adversity. I was hesitant to start but Youper has been immediately available for me when I've needed support. It provides a really useful journalling system that is allowing me to observe my progress.

Author: Caitlyn Ruffin
Body: I've been using this for only less than half an hour and I feel a difference. It makes me feel calm and makes my problems easier to deal with, and I'm very excited to get to know the app even more. Edit: I miss the original format of the app where you could select an emotion and discuss it with Youper, even if it was a happy one. I just wanted to share how happy I was about my day, but I can't? This used to double as a journaling app for me and I want that feature back.

Author: Alexandra Dronova
Body: Would love the option to choose waking hours instead of conventional 00:00 reset and/or an option to input mood for previous days. New update is A LOT. I guess it looks nice and more sophisticated, but it was a very sudden change and it made me anxious because I could barely find what I needed (search button helped find "I'm feeling"). overall, this update made the app incredibly slow and nearly impossible to use. had to restart it 5 times.

Author: Camocat2
Body: 8/15/19: i enjoy this app so far 5* 2/10/21: what the hell is this update. Took away the simple mood tracker and replaced it with an overly complicated system. It takes so much longer to load (if it loads at all without me restarting the app) it wouldve been nice to have this new talk feature as an option. Not make that the only way to track your mood

Author: avril shields
Body: Great app, with developers that listen to feedback Since new update - app is much slower, almost too slow to use and you can't just simply log moods anymore :( I used to use this as a diary but cant see how to anymore. Please add it back!

Author: Vicki Thompson
Body: I really loved Youper as a way for tracking my mood each day to capture and notice the patterns of things which were triggers for different emotional states. The goal setting and friendly advice was useful. But I cannot for the life of me find how to continue doing this in the new update, as the regular chatbot seems to have been entirely replaced with exercises? Not what I used this app for, I might need to find an alternate mood tracker if this functionality is no longer available... :(

Author: Miriam S.
Body: Overall good app. I preferred the older version. It was simpler worked better.

Author: whitehead 03
Body: Very helpful for tracking your mood and helping you feel better. It takes you into your thoughts to realize why you're feeling how you do and to help you cope. It is very organized in a helpful way with a simple graph. But, ever since the new update, the app has been very slow, and has locked a majority of the content behind a paywall.

Author: cas w
Body: Some of the tips and things youper says can come off as quite unhelpful for chronically ill folks.. Such as "this won't last forever".. Or when youper asks "What can you do to feel less tired?". Quite literally nothing. And I see the positives in the new tools, but it's so difficult to log my mood now, and it's a tad messy :(

Author: Jade C
Body: ORIGINAL 05/12/2019: Have been using Youper for over a year now and find it useful and helpful when I'm struggling. Sometimes just writing down some things and having a prompt to reframe some thoughts can go a long way and take me away from negative thoughts for a few minutes. Tracking my mental and physical wellbeing can keep me on track. **** UPDATE 10/02/2021: What have you done to the app?! The format is ruined, everything takes super long to update, I can't see my 94+ days streak now....

Author: Marta Kaniuk
Body: I use this application daily for over a year and I was very happy with it - allowed to simply track moods. After a recent update it gained many new options (that are blocked for free user) and I can't find the one that was imporant to me. I'm very confused with new panel and irritated by using it now. Also works extremely slowly.

Author: Lucas Sencabaugh
Body: As of February 5th this app is unusable. Pixel XL 2. It was great prior.

Author: Natalie Krawczyk
Body: Loved it before the update, now it's slow and confusing. It's very confusing how to log a mood, which was why I downloaded the app years ago. Now I have no idea how to log my mood. There's so many other things to do, but where do I log my mood? The app is also very, very slow. What a disappoinment.

Author: Theresa Aten
Body: I had this app 2 years ago. Last year it wasnt on Google Play so I was locked out of my account. I redownloaded bc it helped in the past but every single thing is now locked. The AI helped a lot when it felt like I couldnt confide in friends or family. I'm really sad that everything is locked and the only way to get access is to pay for premium. There isnt anything to let you try out.

Today, I discovered I was charged $48.36 that I never agreed to. Never checked a box, never actively sought a subscription. This smells underhanded and of small-print-taketh-away. I have cancelled the "subscription" and want my money returned to me. For an app purporting to encourage mental health, this tactic undercuts it.

Uninstalled. You guys sold out. Bigtime.

There isn't much you can do for free anymore, and every conversation has a money grab to try to sell more subscriptions. So much for being a therapy app for anyone who is struggIing. I only paid $40 or so for the year but month after month I'm disappointed and regret even paying that.

I was upset to find that it's actually premium. I suggest this app should not be labelled as a free app.

Body: This app has been extremely useful for me to just keep track of my moods and keep a consistent log such that I am able to notice particular patterns in my feelings. It's comforting to know that there's a preserved record outside of my own experience that ratifies my feelings. It's a very useful app for engaging in personal reflection, and has a lot more functionality than I personally use. The main feature I'd like to see improved is how the app presents the data on a weekly summary. At present, the graph it produces does not handle frequent entries very clearly.

Author: Adam Stephens
Body: The app's basic premise, its function and design, seems solid, but a major red flag has me tempted to uninstall it. The algorithm - the bot - made mention of happiness as such being the goal. This is a serious problem. We're dealing with matters of mental health and psychological well-being, thus the goal is health, wholeness; happiness is a symptom, not an end of itself, and not the symptom of psychological health on the whole. If you aim for the wrong target, you won't hit the right one.

Author: Kaden Kai
Body: I like the app overall. I paid for the full version. I like being able to track moods and their causes. But most of the suggested social activities to help me feel better are currently prohibited because of Covid-19. Like "Go out for coffee" or "have a meal with a friend". And every time they are brought up I feel worse / more sad because they are impossible to do. I try to focus on the fact that the situation we are in will change. But I wish those suggestions would be discontinued until then.

I then set up two times to give the app ample opportunity to function, but I haven't received a prompt notification in weeks. Considering uninstalling if this isn't fixable. I'm just using this to track my moods daily, and if it can't even do that, I don't see the point.

Author: Rochelle Flynn
Body: I have been using this app for 2 years (paid version), and recommend it to everyone I know who is feeling depressed, anxious, or overwhelmed. It helps to relax me and refocus my attention away from obsessive or otherwise detrimental thoughts. It also helps me to appreciate the things that make me happy and to better understand myself. It is less expensive than weekly visits with a psychiatrist, but allows me to maintain a mood journal to share with a therapist. Excellent concept and results!

Body: Like many others, I was enjoying the app until being repeatedly asked to pay for a subscription. Continuously ask how I feel, say I can't answer without paying, then end the conversation when I'm unable to pay?? Then on top of that being told that if I truly value myself I would pay for a subscription...People are using this app in search of support. Stop asking after the first "No" & don't try to guilt people who are struggling into paying you! This seems really gross & exploitative. Do better.

Author: Mela SN
Body: At first, this seemed like a promising app. I needed the extended features, so I bought a subscription. However, the app refused to acknowledge what Google Play & PayPal have - that they received the money. Every time I attempt to prompt it to acknowledge my subscription, it tells me "subscription not found". When I tried to contact them for help, they just sent me to the page detailing the path that kept giving me that error. After that, all I've received from them is silence. Despite the app & the staff's shared refusal to work, Google will refuse to give you a refund for this nonexistent service. Don't expect more of a response than stock feel-good phrases, and I definitely don't expect it to actually WORK. If this is the only way to make mental healthcare more accessible, it's worse than the current complete lack of support.

(and as a bipolar I need that) I paid for the premium version, which is relatively cheap compared to others, but you can do what you need to do without it. Great app, definitely would recommend.

I have tried several mood apps already but I guess seeing these little orbs of my own emotions floating around really made me feel occupied and calm. Also it doesn't force me to say anything about my moods, it lets me to just put the mood out there, which is great, since I'm not the kind of person who's always in the mood to explain how I feel.

She recommended this app, and it's good, but I wish you could have more than 5 reminders. My mood is very variable, and it would be helpful to have a reminder every hour from 8 am to midnight.

Author: Kyo Vez
Body: So far this is such a nice app. To get the most of it I'd recommend purchasing premium. I like that it's customizable to your needs. You can add moods and create your own colors. It's visually appealing which is a big deal to me. Bonus it's cute. The food tracking is convenient you can rate from healthy to junk food and leave notes. Simple cute and convenient.
